      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.85em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">3</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 4.233em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_27" style="word-spacing: -0.0014em"
              >2.1 Spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 4.055em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_52" style="word-spacing: -0.0307em"
              >1. Introduction &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 5.8129em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >All the spaces on the Main Map have two characteristics that
              define &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 6.7629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1009em"
              >them: whether they are fortified and whether they are the home
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 7.7129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >space for one or more major or minor powers or are independent.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 6.5528em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_83">T</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.1214em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand and Isabella </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1188em"
              >is a 4-player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 7.5028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >game based on the reigns of Isabella I of Castile and Ferdinand
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 8.4528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0594em"
              >II of Aragon, best known as the Catholic Monarchs. The game’s
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 9.4028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_86" style="word-spacing: 0.1283em"
              >name is taken from their popular motto (“Tanto Monta, Monta
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 10.3529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.0318em"
              >Tanto”) that roughly translates to “As much as the one is worth,
              so &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 11.3029em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0326em"
              >too is the other.” Each player controls one or more major powers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 12.2529em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0203em"
              >that participated in the military, political, and societal
              conflicts in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 13.2029em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0494em"
              >the Mediterranean, Western Europe, and North Africa during the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 14.1529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0077em"
              >reign of the Catholic Monarchs. The players’ roles are: the newly
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 15.1029em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_90" style="word-spacing: -0.0614em"
              >unified Spain, the maritime empire of Portugal, the emerging
              power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 16.0529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >of France, and the Muslim powers of the region who desperately
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 17.0029em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >resisted the advances of the European Christian kingdoms.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 9.0793em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >Fortified Spaces</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_92">:</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_93">A</span
            ><span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_70">forti</span
            ><span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_95">f</span
            ><span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_96">i</span
            ><span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_62" style="word-spacing: -0.0623em"
              >ed </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >space represents a walled city or town. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 10.0293em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0176em"
              >A power must successfully besiege a fortified space to gain
              politi</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0176em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 10.9793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.018em"
              >cal control of that city. Up to four friendly land units may
              remain &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 11.9293em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0211em"
              >within a fortified space to defend that city against an enemy
              siege. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2667em; top: 12.8793em; z-index: 2720"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0459em"
              >Fortified spaces also serve as winter quarters. There are two
              diffe</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_98">r</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_98">- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 13.8293em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >ent types of fortified spaces: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9333em; top: 15.0294em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0198em"
              >Key: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0252em"
              >A </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0198em"
              >key </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0199em"
              >is a fortified space represented by a square. Keys &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 15.9795em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.055em"
              >are the most influential and wealthy spaces; control of a key
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 16.9295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0511em"
              >gives a power victory points (VP). If a player loses all keys for
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 17.8795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.014em"
              >one of their powers, that power surrenders and may not spend
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 18.8295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0582em"
              >CPs on any actions to recruit new units until it recovers at
              least &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 19.7795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.037em"
              >one such space. If Catalonia, the Nasrid Kingdom of Granada,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 20.7295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0539em"
              >or the Beltranejos faction surrenders, see the special rules in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
