            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.8916em; top: 32.136em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• 12</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">dice &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 29.946em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0421em"
              >Unfortified Spaces: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: -0.0737em"
              >An </span
            ><span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_103" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >unfortif ied </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0152em"
              >space represents the cities and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 30.896em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >towns that can be controlled without siege. Forces from two
              powers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 31.846em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >that are at war must fight a field battle if they ever
              simultaneously &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 32.796em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.063em"
              >occupy the same unfortified space. There are two different types
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 33.746em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >of unfortified spaces: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9333em; top: 34.9462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_104" style="word-spacing: 0.0976em"
              >Strategic Spaces: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0828em"
              >A </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_104" style="word-spacing: 0.1251em"
              >strategic space </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >is an unfortified space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 35.8962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0306em"
              >represented by a triangle. These spaces represent locales that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 36.8462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >were critical to control due to their strategic value (such as
              river &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 37.7962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >fords, mountain passes, and road junctions). 1 VP is obtained
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 38.7462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >when a power controls it. Strategic spaces cannot be controlled
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 39.6962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >by military units in an adjacent space; controlling them requires
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 40.6462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the presence of units in the strategic space itself. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 34.53em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_39" style="word-spacing: -0.0137em"
              >2. Game Board &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 37.0278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >The game is played on a map that depicts the areas of the world
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 37.9778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0501em"
              >critical to these powers during the late 15th Century and early
              16th &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 38.9279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.083em"
              >Century. The main playing area, referred to as the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0819em"
              >Main Map </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108">in &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 39.8778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0999em"
              >these rules, includes the Iberian Peninsula, southern France, the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 40.8278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0387em"
              >Italian Peninsula, and North Africa. Cities and towns that played
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 41.7778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >important roles during this period are represented on the Main
              Map &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 42.7278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0462em"
              >as squares, triangles, circles, and eight-pointed stars called </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">spaces</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 43.6778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.007em"
              >A network of lines called </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0187em"
              >connections </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0086em"
              >links these spaces. A space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 44.6278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0808em"
              >connected to another by one of these lines is an </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.081em"
              >adjacent </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">space. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 45.5778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Some of the spaces are also ports (a circular symbol with an
              anchor &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 46.5278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0799em"
              >inside). </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0798em"
              >Ports </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0798em"
              >allow access to a series of areas called Sea Zones &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 47.4778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >(blue regions with bright blue boundaries). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9333em; top: 41.8464em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_110" style="word-spacing: 0.1221em"
              >Simple Space: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0868em"
              >A </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_110" style="word-spacing: 0.1222em"
              >simple space </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_111" style="word-spacing: 0.1239em"
              >is an unfortified space rep</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_111" style="word-spacing: 0.1239em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 42.7964em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0689em"
              >resented by a circle. No victory points are awarded for their
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 43.7464em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0678em"
              >control. These spaces may be controlled by military units in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5998em; top: 44.6964em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >adjacent spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 46.0628em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0629em"
              >Independent Spaces: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0628em"
              >The gray spaces of Tunis (in Africa); Milan, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 47.0128em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0859em"
              >Modena, and others in Italy; Roussillon (in the Pyrenees); Metz
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 47.9628em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0046em"
              >(in France); Ragusa (on the Adriatic Sea); and the Canary Islands
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 48.9128em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.033em"
              >are </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >independent spaces </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >and are not aligned with any of the powers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2667em; top: 49.8628em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >represented in the game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 48.8443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >On the bottom right of the map is the peripheral play area called
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 49.7943em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Exploration Map </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >which includes the regions bordering th</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_41">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106">tlantic &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 50.7443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0171em"
              >and Indian Oceans that were explored and settled by these powers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 51.6943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >during this period. Circular spaces on the Exploration Map are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 52.6443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0463em"
              >called </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >Exploration Map Spaces</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.045em"
              >; they start the game vacant but can &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 53.5943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.014em"
              >come under control of a power that establishes a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.014em"
              >settlement </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >at that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 54.5443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >location. Each Exploration map space is considered to be
              connected &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 55.4943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >to the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >Ocean Zone </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >that it borders. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 56.8607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0411em"
              >The political status of each space is updated throughout play
              using &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 57.8107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >control markers. Detailed information about control markers and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 58.7607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0062em"
              >Main and Exploration Map elements is provided in this section of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 59.7107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >the rulebook. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1938em">
            <span class="stl_113 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_3" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">4</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3442em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0541em"
              >Home Spaces: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.054em"
              >Spaces that are not independent are </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0542em"
              >home spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2942em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0348em"
              >of a specific power, as indicated in the following table of
              powers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.001em"
              >which lists the color of each power’s home spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.6396em; top: 7.4608em">
            <span class="stl_116 stl_17 stl_13">Nasrid &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.3459em; top: 7.4608em">
            <span class="stl_116 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.9374em"
              >North </span
            ><span class="stl_117 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0632em"
              >Portugal </span
            ><span class="stl_118 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.7259em"
              >Beltranejos </span
            ><span class="stl_116 stl_17 stl_13">Spain &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.1369em; top: 8.0439em">
            <span class="stl_116 stl_17 stl_80">African &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 39.6719em; top: 7.4608em">
            <span class="stl_116 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.4365em"
              >France Catalonia Papacy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1146em; top: 7.895em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13">Powers &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5027em; top: 7.895em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13">Color &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1146em; top: 9.0975em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Castile &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5027em; top: 9.0975em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_68">Ochre &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.2158em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_28" style="word-spacing: -0.0007em"
              >2.3 Control Markers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1146em; top: 10.3em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Aragon &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5027em; top: 10.3em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Red &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.7956em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.037em"
              >Control markers are used to denote the political control of a
              space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.7456em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0749em"
              >These control markers are color-coded by the conquering power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.6956em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_122" style="word-spacing: 0.1267em"
              >and also include the flag, banner, or symbol representing that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.6456em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0415em"
              >power during the late 15th and early 16th Centuries. Aragon and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.5956em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0391em"
              >Castile share the same control marker as the foreign policy of
              both &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.5456em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0418em"
              >kingdoms was united in the hands of their monarchs, hence their
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.4956em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: -0.0634em"
              >heraldic shield is their control marker. The Berbers of Tlemcen
              and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.4456em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.011em"
              >Sultanate of Fez share the same control marker as both kingdoms
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.3957em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0127em"
              >form the North African Alliance. Some control markers have dif-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.3457em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0829em"
              >ferent heraldic shields on the two sides representing each of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.2957em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1009em"
              >powers controlled by the same player (in the Spanish case both
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.2457em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0344em"
              >powers use the same shield so the two sides are identical). There
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.1957em; z-index: 2840"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0034em"
              >are three types of control markers as detailed below.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1146em; top: 11.5026em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_80">France &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5027em; top: 11.5026em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_13">Blue &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1146em; top: 12.7051em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_13">Portugal &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5027em; top: 12.7051em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_80">Garnet &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5027em; top: 13.9077em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_125">Turquoise &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5027em; top: 15.1102em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Ivory &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1146em; top: 13.9077em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_13">Beltranejos &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1146em; top: 15.1102em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Principality of Catalonia &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1146em; top: 16.3127em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_13">Nasrids &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5027em; top: 16.3127em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_126" style="word-spacing: 0.0048em"
              >Dark Green &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1146em; top: 17.5153em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0276em"
              >North African Alliance (S. Fez)</span
            ><span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.787em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_27">Green &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1138em; top: 18.7178em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_127">Nort</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_34">h</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_101">A</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_106">frica</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_34">n</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_101">A</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >lliance (Berber)</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.5919em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0043em"
              >Light Green &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1138em; top: 19.9204em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_61">Navarre &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1138em; top: 21.1229em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_13">Papacy &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1138em; top: 22.3254em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Genoa &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5019em; top: 19.9204em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >Dark Gray &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5019em; top: 21.1229em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_13">Purple &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5019em; top: 22.3254em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_80">Pink &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1138em; top: 23.528em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_83">V</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_80">nice &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5019em; top: 23.528em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Orange &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.4828em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_66" style="word-spacing: -0.0028em"
              >Square Marker &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1138em; top: 24.7305em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_126">Florence &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1138em; top: 25.9331em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_13">Naples &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5019em; top: 24.7305em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Light Blue &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.5019em; top: 25.9331em">
            <span class="stl_124 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >Dark Brown &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.369em; top: 24.729em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.08em"
              >Square control markers are used to show control of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.365em; top: 25.679em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_129" style="word-spacing: 0.1221em"
              >keys. These markers are transferred between the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.365em; top: 26.629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.028em"
              >player’s card and the map when a key is captured or &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.365em; top: 27.579em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0461em"
              >lost in order to allow VPs for controlling keys to be
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.365em; top: 28.529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >easily tracked. Note these four rules: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.7053em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_130" style="word-spacing: 0.004em"
              >2.2 Political Control &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.2852em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.056em"
              >The </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: -0.0507em"
              >political control </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0561em"
              >of each space is tracked throughout the game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.2352em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0849em"
              >By default, each space is under the political control of its home
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.1852em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0329em"
              >power. As political control changes, control markers are placed
              on &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.1352em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0409em"
              >top of the space to indicate that the political control has
              changed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.0852em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0695em"
              >to a non-home power. These control markers are color-coded by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.0352em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >power and also include a flag used by that power during the time
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.9852em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >period of the game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 29.7291em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Every</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0529em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0513em"
              >key on the map must contain a square control marker. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 30.6791em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Exceptions: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Independent keys not currently under major power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 31.6291em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0281em"
              >control and keys of minor powers when they are neither allied
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 32.5791em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >to a major power nor captured. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 33.7793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Every</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0229em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.018em"
              >square control marker must be either on the map or on
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 34.7293em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >the appropriate Player Card. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 35.9295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.232em"
              >• Possession</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0529em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0641em"
              >of a key grants VP to the controlling player helping &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5831em; top: 36.8795em; z-index: 3405"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.0053em"
              >them win by Standard Victory or by Domination Victory.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.2723em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_27" style="word-spacing: -0.0014em"
              >Controlled Space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.5185em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_132">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">s</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >pace that is controlled by a major or minor power is a controlled
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.4685em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >space. Controlled spaces for a power include: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 38.0796em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.037em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0319em"
              >a player succeeds in placing all his square control markers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 39.0296em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0045em"
              >on the map he will get an Automatic Victory (22.2). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 39.5855em; z-index: 1111"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Home</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0052em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: 0.0036em"
              >spaces that have not fallen to another power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 40.7026em; z-index: 1152"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Independent</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.0047em"
              >(gray) spaces seized by the power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 41.8196em; z-index: 1193"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Home</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0052em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.0038em"
              >spaces of other powers seized by the power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.3161em; z-index: 3502"
          >
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_134">T</span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_135">r</span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_52" style="word-spacing: -0.0007em"
              >iangular Marker &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8231em; top: 41.5623em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_136" style="word-spacing: 0.1271em"
              >Triangular control markers are used to show the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8247em; top: 42.5123em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0151em"
              >status of strategic spaces (triangular in shape on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8247em; top: 43.4623em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_137" style="word-spacing: 0.1219em"
              >map). These markers are transferred between the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8247em; top: 44.4123em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0229em"
              >pool of such markers and the map when a strategic &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2497em; top: 45.3623em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >space is captured or lost. Note the following three rules:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 42.9367em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1073em"
              >• Home spaces of allied minor powers that have not fallen to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 43.8867em; z-index: 1255"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0099em"
              >another power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.1723em; z-index: 1264"
          >
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_36" style="word-spacing: -0.045em"
              >Control </span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_138">T</span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_18">e</span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_139">rminology &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.4185em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0779em"
              >Friendly: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0945em"
              >The term </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.096em"
              >friendly </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0959em"
              >refers to any game element (space, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.3685em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >unit, stack, formation) that is controlled by the active power or
              an &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 48.3185em; z-index: 1399"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_140" style="word-spacing: 0.0091em"
              >ally of that power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9162em; top: 46.5625em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Strategic</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0811em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0759em"
              >spaces still controlled by their home power should &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5828em; top: 47.5125em; z-index: 3804"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0078em"
              >not contain a marker. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9162em; top: 48.7126em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.2321em"
              >• Add</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0221em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0169em"
              >a triangular marker to a strategic space whenever a non-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5828em; top: 49.6626em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >home power gains control of it. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 49.6018em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_141" style="word-spacing: -0.08em"
              >Enemy: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_142" style="word-spacing: -0.061em"
              >The term </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_141" style="word-spacing: -0.0619em"
              >enemy </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_142" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >refers to any game element that is controlled &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 50.5518em; z-index: 1510"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_143" style="word-spacing: 0.0027em"
              >by a power that is currently in a state of war with the active
              power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9162em; top: 50.8628em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1203em"
              >• Possession of a strategic space grants VP to the controlling
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5828em; top: 51.8128em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0536em"
              >player helping them win by Standard Victory or Domination
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5828em; top: 52.7628em; z-index: 4017"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_145" style="word-spacing: 0.0024em"
              >Victory, but never by Automatic Victory. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.8351em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0351em"
              >Independent: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0525em"
              >The term </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.053em"
              >independent </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0528em"
              >refers to any game element &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.7851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0104em"
              >that is not controlled by a major or minor power. For the
              purposes &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.7351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0321em"
              >of the rules, independents are considered neither friend nor
              enemy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.6851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.011em"
              >except for the special case of the Guanche people of the
              Canaries, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.6351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0371em"
              >who despite being independent have special characteristics
              (21.7). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2497em; top: 54.1292em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_146" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >There is no limit to the number of spaces a power can control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2497em; top: 55.0792em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0071em"
              >with triangular control markers; if a power uses all of its
              markers, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2497em; top: 56.0292em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >improvise with unused markers from other powers. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.9184em">
            <span class="stl_147 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.099em"
              >EXAMPLES: </span
            ><span class="stl_148 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.1039em"
              >Independent units cannot intercept moving forces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 57.8684em">
            <span class="stl_148 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0374em"
              >as only enemy formations may attempt intercepts. Adjacent inde-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 58.8184em">
            <span class="stl_149 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0596em"
              >pendent units do not prevent unoccupied, simple unfortif ied
              spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 59.7684em">
            <span class="stl_148 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: -0.0154em"
              >from being controlled from another adjacent space, an action that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 60.7184em">
            <span class="stl_148 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.004em"
              >is restricted by the presence of adjacent enemy units.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_4" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.85em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">5</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Passes also: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_52" style="word-spacing: -0.0006em"
              >Hexagonal Marker &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 5.5436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Block</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >spring deployment of land units, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.229em; top: 5.5987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1009em"
              >Hexagonal markers are used to show the status of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.225em; top: 6.5487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0407em"
              >fortresses and simple spaces. They are also used to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.225em; top: 7.4987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1019em"
              >indicate Ocean Zones explored by a player on the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.225em; top: 8.4487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.023em"
              >Exploration Map. There is no limit to the number of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.225em; top: 9.3987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0559em"
              >spaces a power can control with hexagonal control &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7497em; top: 10.3487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >markers; if a power uses all of its markers, improvise with
              unused &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7497em; top: 11.2987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >markers from other powers. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 6.7438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1003em"
              >• Prevent interception by an enemy formation that is adjacent
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 7.6938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >across a pass, and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 8.8939em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.2418em"
              >• Inhibit</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0619em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >land units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_151">’</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_152">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >bility to control adjacent spaces and remove &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 9.8439em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >unrest in adjacent spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.2104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Units may retreat or avoid battle over a pass. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.4972em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_68" style="word-spacing: -0.0013em"
              >Seville Inland Port &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.0354em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_28" style="word-spacing: -0.0009em"
              >2.4 Special Elements of the Main Map &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.5358em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0022em"
              >Shared Home Spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.3307em; top: 13.7434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_142">Ther</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_153">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_154">i</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_55">s</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_154">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_155">n</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_154">i</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_142">nlan</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_155">d</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_156">w</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_142">aterwa</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_155">y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_154">c</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_142">onnection &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.3552em; top: 14.6935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0779em"
              >between Seville and Jerez (based on &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.3552em; top: 15.6435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >the fact that the Guadalquivir River is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.3552em; top: 16.5935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >navigable to Seville) which connects &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.3552em; top: 17.5435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_157" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >Seville with the Gulf of Cadiz Sea &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.3552em; top: 18.4935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Zone. Seville is considered to be a port &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.3552em; top: 19.4435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0468em"
              >of that maritime zone as long as you &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.3552em; top: 20.3935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.031em"
              >also control Jerez. See 16.8 for more &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.3552em; top: 21.3435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0422em"
              >details of the special status of Seville. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.5041em; top: 15.782em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0442em"
              >In the kingdoms of Castile and Aragon &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.5001em; top: 16.732em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0065em"
              >there are several spaces that are color- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.5001em; top: 17.682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >coded with two home space colors: one &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.5001em; top: 18.632em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0302em"
              >at the top and one at the bottom. These &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.5001em; top: 19.582em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >spaces serve as home spaces for two &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.5001em; top: 20.532em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0077em"
              >different powers. The space is initially &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.5001em; top: 21.482em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.088em"
              >under control of the power shown on &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 22.432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.069em"
              >the bottom of the space (and that power controls the space if no
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 23.382em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0376em"
              >control marker is present). Thus the split home spaces that are
              yel- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 24.332em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >low on top and turquoise on the bottom are initially controlled
              by &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 25.282em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0371em"
              >the Beltranejos faction, but can serve as a Castilian home spaces
              if &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 26.232em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0969em"
              >the Castilian power later gains political control of that
              location. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 27.182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Zahara and Gibraltar are home spaces split between Castile and
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 28.132em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0919em"
              >Nasrids, which means that if either of these two powers control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 29.082em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0006em"
              >these spaces, they can use the benefits of a home space there.
              The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 30.032em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >same applies to the home spaces in northeastern Spain initially
              held &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 30.982em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_137" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >by the Principality of Catalonia which can later become home
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 31.932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: -0.0537em"
              >spaces for Aragon. Finally, there are spaces with dual
              color-coding &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 32.882em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0356em"
              >in the Kingdom of Naples. These spaces show their home color on
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 33.832em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1001em"
              >the bottom and the independent gray color above. These spaces
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 34.782em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >became independent after the death of Ferrante. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.6306em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >Strait of Gibraltar &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 36.0647em; top: 23.9601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0609em"
              >There are three spaces (Ceuta, Gi- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 36.075em; top: 24.9101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_160" style="word-spacing: -0.0574em"
              >braltar, and Tangier) which are ports &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 36.075em; top: 25.8601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >on either side of the Strait of Gibral- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 36.075em; top: 26.8101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1188em"
              >tar and two Pass connections link &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 36.075em; top: 27.7601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0676em"
              >these spaces. These connections are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 36.075em; top: 28.7101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >treated as standard Pass connections &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 36.075em; top: 29.6601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >with these two exceptions: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.917em; top: 30.8603em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Land</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0819em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0769em"
              >movement is possible across these connections only if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 31.8103em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0301em"
              >the moving power controls or is friendly with either the origin
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 32.7603em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >space or the destination space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.917em; top: 33.9604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_161" style="word-spacing: 0.135em"
              >• The Muslim player can treat both connections as one-way
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 34.9104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0146em"
              >connections (i.e., 1 CP movement cost, possible interception,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 35.8604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.058em"
              >possible spring deployment) if he controls Gibraltar. However,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 36.8104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0471em"
              >in this case these connections are only considered normal con-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 37.7604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0129em"
              >nections for the Muslim movement (including spring deploy-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 38.7104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0623em"
              >ment and interception movements) from Tangier or Ceuta to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 39.6604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >Gibraltar (south-north direction) but not vice versa. See Section
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5835em; top: 40.6104em; z-index: 3466"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0044em"
              >20.1 for more details on Gibraltar. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.0691em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_67" style="word-spacing: -0.0081em"
              >Home Spaces of the Sultanate of Tlemcen (Berber) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.8972em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.008em"
              >Sea Zones &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.1434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.1099em"
              >The Main Map contains nine Sea Zones, plus a tenth zone cor-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.0934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1029em"
              >responding to the Canary Islands which has a direct connection
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.0434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0771em"
              >to the Cape Bojador Sea Zone. The boundaries between the Sea
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.9934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0819em"
              >Zones are shown with a blue line. Only naval leaders and naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.9434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0959em"
              >units may occupy Sea Zones; land units must always end every
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.8934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >action in a space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.9686em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1195em"
              >In North Africa there are eight light green spaces belonging to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.9186em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0303em"
              >the Berbers of the Sultanate of Tlemcen. These spaces enter play
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.8686em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0145em"
              >on Turn 4; before that time they are ignored as if they did not
              ex- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.8186em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0736em"
              >ist. When they do enter play, they are treated as home spaces of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.7686em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0898em"
              >the North African power, except for the Algiers space, which is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 48.7186em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0078em"
              >independent until play of the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0031em"
              >lgiers </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0045em"
              >egency </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0053em"
              >event. This event &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 49.6686em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0079em"
              >changes Algiers into a Berber home space (20.2). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.2599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_164" style="word-spacing: -0.0616em"
              >The Sea Zones of the Tyrrhenian Sea and Central Mediterranean are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.2099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0151em"
              >considered adjacent if you control the Messina space, are allied
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.1599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0169em"
              >the power controlling Messina, or the power controlling it allows
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.1099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0312em"
              >you to pass through. The Alboran Sea Zone is considered adjacent
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.0599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >to the Gulf of Cadiz if you control at least one of the ports in
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.0099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0587em"
              >strait (Tangier, Ceuta, or Gibraltar), are allied with a power
              control- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.9599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.007em"
              >ling one of these ports, or one of those powers allows you to
              pass &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.9099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >through. If the use of one of these passages is denied, movement
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.8599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0462em"
              >between these zones is also prohibited when lending naval units
              or &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.8099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0046em"
              >returning them to a controlled port in winter. If passage is
              granted &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.7599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0038em"
              >at any time during a turn, this player retains access between
              these &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.7099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >zones for the remainder of the entire turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 50.9557em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_165">Pass &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.2019em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_166">A</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_62">c</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_167" style="word-spacing: -0.0603em"
              >onnection shown with a dashed line is a difficult mountain,
              river, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.1519em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.0637em"
              >desert, or strait passage. There are passes of this type
              throughout the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.1019em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0301em"
              >Main Map and in the Canary Islands Box (which should be consid-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.0519em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >ered as an extension of the Main Map for all purposes even though
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.0019em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_168" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >the box is placed near the Exploration Map). Formations of land
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.9519em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >moving over a pass expend two command points (2 CP) instead of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 57.9019em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0034em"
              >the usual cost of 1 CP for moving over a normal connection.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_5" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">6</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.002em"
              >Sea Ports &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.055em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_43" style="word-spacing: -0.0195em"
              >3. Players, Powers, and Rulers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.024em"
              >Most (but not all) of the spaces near the coast act as ports,
              which &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.003em"
              >provide access to one or more Sea Zones. One-zone ports possess
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.4237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0025em"
              >a single anchor symbol. Two-zone ports have two anchors next to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.3737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0679em"
              >them, one anchor within each of the two Sea Zones that may be
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.3237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >accessed from that space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.5528em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >This section defines players, powers, and rulers and gives
              high-level &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.5028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >information about these game concepts. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.2396em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.002em"
              >3.1 Player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.6108em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_172" style="word-spacing: -0.0038em"
              >Special Zones &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.8195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0217em"
              >A player is a human participant in the game. </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_83">T</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >nto Monta </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0278em"
              >is spe- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.7695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1108em"
              >cially designed to be played by four players. Each player has a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.7195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0501em"
              >Player Card (4.0) that tracks his situation with respect to
              allowable &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.6695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0351em"
              >actions, card draws, victory points, and current rulers. Many
              game &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.6195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0441em"
              >functions are conducted one player at a time in the following
              order &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.5695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >(known as Impulse Order): &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.857em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.029em"
              >There are two boxes—the English Garrison on the French Player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.807em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >Card and the Paris space on the map—that may contain military
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.757em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.0324em"
              >units but are not considered valid targets for events. Foreign
              War &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.707em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0419em"
              >cards are also considered to be such special zones that cannot be
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.657em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0427em"
              >targeted by normal events; although as indicated in 20.9, combat
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0025em"
              >and response cards may be used to impact Foreign Wars.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 16.7697em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >1. Muslim &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 17.8867em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >2. Portugal &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 19.0038em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >3. Spain &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.3438em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_28" style="word-spacing: -0.0009em"
              >2.5 Exploration Map Elements &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.9237em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0943em"
              >Ocean Zones: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.1064em"
              >The game’s Exploration Map contains 10 Ocean &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.8737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >Zones. Eight of these zones also contain Exploration Map Spaces
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.8237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1116em"
              >where players may build a commercial settlement. The players’
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.7737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.043em"
              >Naos and the naval squadrons that escort them are the only units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.7237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >that can occupy oceanic zones. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 20.1208em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >4. France &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.4872em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0929em"
              >Some cards refer to a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.093em"
              >Christian </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0928em"
              >player; read this to mean either &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.4372em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Portugal, Spain, or France. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.173em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_174" style="word-spacing: 0.0134em"
              >3.2 Powers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.659em; top: 25.0904em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0014em"
              >Navigation Checks: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >The boundaries be- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.655em; top: 26.0404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_175" style="word-spacing: -0.0607em"
              >tween the Ocean Zones are shown by large &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.655em; top: 26.9904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0321em"
              >blue or red lines. Particularly treacherous &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.655em; top: 27.9404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0212em"
              >passages (such as the crossing of the At- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.655em; top: 28.8904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0401em"
              >lantic or Indian Oceans, or sailing around &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.655em; top: 29.8404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_176" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >the Cape of Good Hope) have arrows &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.655em; top: 30.7904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >across these boundary lines to indicate the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.655em; top: 31.7404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.0798em"
              >danger. Naos (5.2) that cross these lines &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.655em; top: 32.6904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_177" style="word-spacing: -0.0603em"
              >must roll one time on the Navigation Table &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.655em; top: 33.6404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: -0.0323em"
              >for each arrow, with each roll running the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.655em; top: 34.5904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >risk of damaging or sinking the Nao. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.7528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_166">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">p</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0645em"
              >ower is a nation or city-state present in the game. There are
              three &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.7028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0435em"
              >types of powers, each described below. Each player controls
              either &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.6528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.061em"
              >two Major Powers or one Major Power and a Limited Major Power,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.6028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0371em"
              >depending on the player they represent. Players may also control
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.5528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >number of Minor Powers based on their success at activating Minor
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.5028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Powers to join their cause. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.79em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_178" style="word-spacing: 0.0118em"
              >Major Power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.0362em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >There are six Major powers divided among the four players as
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.9862em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">follows: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 35.1863em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Nasrid</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >Kingdom of Granada (Muslim player) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 36.3034em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• North</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.05em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0183em"
              >African Alliance (Muslim player) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 37.4204em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Portugal</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >(Portugal player) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7502em; top: 35.9568em; z-index: 1299"
          >
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_179" style="word-spacing: -0.0684em"
              >Exploration of the </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_180">T</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_181">e</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_179" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >rra Incognita: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >Each time a player attempts to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 36.9068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >move a Nao into an Ocean Zone that they have not yet explored,
              that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 37.8568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_182" style="word-spacing: -0.0038em"
              >player must roll on the Terra Incognita Table to determine
              whether &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 38.8068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.0339em"
              >the zone is successfully explored (which allows the unit to
              enter). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 39.7568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30">Zone</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_183">s</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_183">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_152">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0575em"
              >nd B contain only ocean, and therefore no settlements can
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 40.7068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_184" style="word-spacing: 0.07em"
              >be established there, although they are otherwise subject to
              Terra &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 41.6568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.0499em"
              >Incognita exploration rolls in the normal way (16.1). Each Ocean
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 42.6068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >Zone on the Exploration Map has a box that initially holds one or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 43.5568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >two </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_152" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >1 VP </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >markers (each of the 16 markers indicates the Ocean Zone
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 44.5068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0074em"
              >to which it belongs) that are awarded based on Gain VP results on
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 45.4568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_43" style="word-spacing: 0.04em"
              >the Terra Incognita or Cartography tables. These two awards may
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 46.4068em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.0126em"
              >not be claimed by the same player; they go to the first two
              players &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 47.3568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >who receive such a Cartography result for that zone (16.6).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 38.5375em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Castile</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >(Spain player) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 39.6545em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Aragon</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >(Spain player) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 40.7716em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• France</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >(France player) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.0566em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_185" style="word-spacing: 0.0067em"
              >Limited Major Power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.3029em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Limited Major Powers represent factions in active civil war
              against &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.2528em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0192em"
              >the Spanish player. They play a role fighting Spain and will
              disap</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0192em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.2028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_186" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >pear from the game if they are forced to surrender. The two
              Limited &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.1528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Major Powers are controlled by the players that only have one
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.1028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Major Power each: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 48.303em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Beltranejos</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0047em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >(Portugal player) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 48.7232em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0859em"
              >Restriction: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0868em"
              >On Turns 1 and 2, Portugal is the only power who &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 49.6732em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0491em"
              >may move Naos but he can only establish settlements in the spaces
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 50.6232em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0134em"
              >reserved for Portugal with his color. This restriction goes in
              turns &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 51.5732em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0065em"
              >so that on Turn 1 he may only move Naos and create a settlement
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 52.5232em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0108em"
              >in Ocean Zone 1 and on Turn 2 he may do so up to Ocean Zone 2.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7502em; top: 53.4732em; z-index: 2287"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0072em"
              >If the event, </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: 0.0061em"
              >chool of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">agres</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.0073em"
              >, H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_188" style="word-spacing: 0.029em"
              >enry the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_189">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">v</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ig</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_141">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191" style="word-spacing: 0.0074em"
              >or </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0077em"
              >has been &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 54.4232em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >played, Portugal is not restricted on these turns and may sail up
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 55.3732em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0491em"
              >Ocean Zone 3 and freely establish settlements in any of these
              three &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 56.3232em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0268em"
              >zones. Also, the crossing to the Atlantic Ocean Zones A, B, 7,
              and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 57.2732em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0589em"
              >8 or the crossing to the Indian Ocean Zones 4, 5, and 6 are only
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7502em; top: 58.2232em; z-index: 2552"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0679em"
              >allowed when the mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0498em"
              >verseas </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">V</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191">o</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_192">y</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0685em"
              >ges </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0677em"
              >has been &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 59.1732em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >played; the lines to first enter these Ocean Zones are shown in
              red &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 60.1232em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >to remind players of this restriction. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 49.5032em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Principality</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >of Catalonia (France player) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.7033em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0169em"
              >These limited major powers do not have their own foreign policy
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.6533em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0071em"
              >or diplomatic relations with minor powers, so they cannot declare
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.6033em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1199em"
              >war on anyone, nor can anyone declare war on them. However
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.5533em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0439em"
              >outside the diplomacy section of the rules (9.0), assume any rule
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.5033em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >that applies to a Major Power applies to them as well.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.79em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_193" style="word-spacing: 0.0104em"
              >Minor Powers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.0362em; z-index: 4364"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0233em"
              >The minor powers are: Navarre, Florence, Naples, Genoa, </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">nice, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.9862em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.1012em"
              >and the Papacy. The alliances of these states can change during
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.9362em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >play (21.0). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_6" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.85em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">7</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.233em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_66" style="word-spacing: -0.0029em"
              >3.3 Rulers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.8129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0184em"
              >Each player is represented by their ruler, who is the leader of
              their &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.7629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0411em"
              >most important major power and plays a key role during the game,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.7129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0486em"
              >either a monarch (Castile and Aragon, France, and Portugal), or
              an &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.6629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Emir/Sultan (Nasrid Kingdom of Granada, Sultanate of Fez). Play-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.6129em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.055em"
              >ers also track the current Pope since the Papacy provide benefits
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.5629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >to the power with historical ties to that particular historical
              Pope. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.9293em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0249em"
              >The initial ruler for each player is printed on the left side of
              their &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.8793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1189em"
              >Player Card. The rulers of several major powers change during
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.8293em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.024em"
              >play as a result of Mandatory Event cards (6.1). Subsequent
              rulers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.7793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0309em"
              >enter play when one of these Mandatory Events is resolved. These
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.7293em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0599em"
              >cards are placed over the ruler printed on the Player Card so the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.6793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.076em"
              >new ruler’s attributes are visible to all players. The ruler for
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.6293em; z-index: 786"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0668em"
              >Muslim player changes immediately to </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_196" style="word-spacing: 0.1236em"
              >ultans of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0486em"
              >z, </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_192">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_197">ta</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_197">- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.5793em">
            <span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.0233em"
              >sid </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.023em"
              >ynasty </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.023em"
              >when the Nasrid Kingdom of Granada is conquered &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.5293em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0071em"
              >(22.1); in this one case a ruler changes without being triggered
              by &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.4793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0093em"
              >a Mandatory Event. When a ruler dies or is replaced, and has any
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.4293em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0468em"
              >marker that affects any of his attributes, those markers remain
              in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.3793em; z-index: 1023"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_66" style="word-spacing: 0.0072em"
              >effect on the new ruler. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.5692em">
            <span class="stl_198 stl_08 stl_152" style="word-spacing: -0.0154em"
              >4. Player Cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.6667em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_133">Attributes &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.067em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0548em"
              >The status of each player and their major powers is tracked on a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.017em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0091em"
              >Player Card. Each of the four Player Cards contains the following
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.967em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">sections: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.9129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >All rulers possess two attributes: </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >Administrative Rating </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >and </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">Cha- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.8629em; z-index: 1113"
          >
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_131">risma</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_140" style="word-spacing: 0.009em"
              >, as described below. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 27.1672em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.026em"
              >List of Actions: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.003em"
              >A list of each possible action that this player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 28.1172em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0898em"
              >can undertake during the Action Phase (11.0), including the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5832em; top: 29.0672em; z-index: 2516"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_199" style="word-spacing: -0.0076em"
              >action’s CP cost. The list of possible actions differs by player.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.2293em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0709em"
              >Administrative Rating: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >The administrative (or “admin”) rating of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.1793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.0094em"
              >a ruler evaluates that ruler’s ability to conserve national
              resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.1293em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0683em"
              >so they can be applied in times of need. A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_200">n</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >dmin Rating is always &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.0793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1209em"
              >given in terms of the number of cards that ruler can save from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.0293em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.005em"
              >one turn to the next. Additionally, this attribute can be
              voluntarily &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.9793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0449em"
              >reduced to modify the result of the Headline event roll. For each
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.9293em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_201" style="word-spacing: -0.0609em"
              >point committed, subtract 1 from the ruler’</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_202">s</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_186">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >dmin Rating that turn &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.8793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0471em"
              >and place a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0478em"
              >–1 Admin Rating </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0501em"
              >marker on his ruler card. The Muslim &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.8293em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0062em"
              >ruler </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0059em"
              >Boabdil </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0122em"
              >has a base Admin Rating of 0, however his attribute &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.7793em; z-index: 1660"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0025em"
              >rises to 1 if the Nasrid power currently controls Gibraltar.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 30.2674em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_203" style="word-spacing: 0.1008em"
              >Initial Ruler Card: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_137" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >Attributes of the initial ruler for each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 31.2174em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.003em"
              >player, as described in Section 3.3. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 32.4175em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: -0.0039em"
              >Bonus VP Box: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0259em"
              >This is a holding area for markers that show &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 33.3675em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0296em"
              >the player has been awarded Victory Points for one or more of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 34.3175em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0078em"
              >the results in the Bonus VP list (22.3). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 35.5177em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >Dungeons: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Rival leaders captured in combat are placed here. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 36.7179em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_28" style="word-spacing: 0.0805em"
              >Available Fortress Boxes: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0714em"
              >Holds two </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0.0821em"
              >Fortress </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0717em"
              >markers that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 37.6679em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >can be used to fortify simple (circle) spaces on the map.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.1457em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.059em"
              >Charisma: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0412em"
              >This attribute assesses whether the ruler is exceptional
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.0957em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >in mobilizing resources to support their national initiatives and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.0457em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.064em"
              >military campaigns. Therefore, the number of cards a player is
              dealt &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.9957em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0286em"
              >is highly dependent on their ruler’s Charisma. Section 8.3
              details &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.9457em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_204" style="word-spacing: 0.1275em"
              >the complete rules for receiving cards for each power. Muslim
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.8957em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0091em"
              >and Portuguese players can have their Charisma value reduced by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.8457em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.021em"
              >1, if they have lost control of two home keys of their own (North
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.7957em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >African or Portuguese). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 38.868em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_205" style="word-spacing: -0.0314em"
              >Warehouses: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0461em"
              >Place Resources gained here until you are ready &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 39.818em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >to expend them. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 41.0182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_62" style="word-spacing: 0.0083em"
              >Automatic Victory Track: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0078em"
              >Each player has a track of spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 41.9682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0531em"
              >where his available square control markers are placed. Placing
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 42.9182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >all of them on the map triggers a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_206">n</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >utomatic Victory (22.2) for &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 43.8682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_172" style="word-spacing: -0.0578em"
              >that player. Note, with the exception of the Spanish player, that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 44.8182em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0541em"
              >the rest of the players have the boxes of this type
              differentiated &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 45.7682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >between those corresponding to home keys of the main power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5832em; top: 46.7182em; z-index: 3312"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0574em"
              >that grant the player 2 VPs for each and the rest that grant
              1V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 47.6682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.019em"
              >For these players, it is necessary to control all the home keys
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5832em; top: 48.6182em; z-index: 3408"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: 0.0036em"
              >of these own powers to obtain the automatic victory. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.0833em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_130" style="word-spacing: 0.004em"
              >Additional Functions &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.3295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.047em"
              >Some rulers also act as military leaders (5.1). This additional
              army &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.2795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0017em"
              >leader function is entirely separate from these personages’ role
              as &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 48.2295em; z-index: 2223"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0078em"
              >ruler of a major power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 49.8184em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0311em"
              >Used Home Cards: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.031em"
              >Place each Home card here (face down) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 50.7684em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >after it has been played. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.1348em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0131em"
              >The Player Card also contains customi</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0131em"
              >ed information that differs &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.0848em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0647em"
              >by power, for example, a record of piracy VP for the Muslim
              player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.0348em; z-index: 3638"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_199" style="word-spacing: 0.0032em"
              >and a record of Treaties signed by France for entry into Italy.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_7" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">8</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3442em">
            <span class="stl_208 stl_17 stl_14" style="word-spacing: -0.0177em"
              >FORMATION EXAMPLE: </span
            ><span
              class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_144"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0223em"
              >The leaders from the Beltranejos Pa- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2942em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0076em"
              >checo (command rating of 8) and Archbishop Carrillo (command
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.2442em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_172" style="word-spacing: 0.0573em"
              >rating of 6) are stacked in Toledo with 12 infantry units and two
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.1942em; z-index: 2365"
          >
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_210" style="word-spacing: -0.0582em"
              >cavalry. The Portuguese playe</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_211">r</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_18">w</span
            ><span
              class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_184"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0604em"
              >ho controls his Beltranejos allies, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.1442em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0653em"
              >spends 1 CP to move a formation to </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_212">T</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >lavera. If the formation does &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.0942em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.078em"
              >not include any of the leaders, only four units may be moved. If
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.0442em; z-index: 2531"
          >
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >he includes only a single leade</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_194">r</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.045em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_99">t</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.035em"
              >he number of units moved must &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.9942em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0829em"
              >be equal to or less than the command rating of that leader plus
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.9442em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_201" style="word-spacing: 0.0301em"
              >1 additional cavalry. You would have to move both leaders if you
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.8942em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0.0101em"
              >wanted to move all 14 units from Toledo. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.055em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0232em"
              >5. Military Units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.5528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >There are four types of military units: leaders, Naos, land
              units, and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.5028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.052em"
              >naval units. This section shows an example of each military unit
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.4528em; z-index: 266">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0286em"
              >and explains the importance of any numeric values on the counter.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.4028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0561em"
              >The pieces provided are an absolute limit. No more may be created
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.3529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >for any purpose; the number provided is indicative of the overall
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.3029em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >manpower and financial resources of each power during this
              period. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.2529em; z-index: 488"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_213" style="word-spacing: -0.0596em"
              >Military units use the same color as the home spaces for each
              power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.2607em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0795em"
              >Single-Leader Formations: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0483em"
              >Two home cards (</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_140" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >rown o</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_215">f</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_37">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_152">ragon &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.2107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0792em"
              >and </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_108">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >he </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_162">R</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_162"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0624em"
              >ise of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131">rance</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >) allow single-leader formations to make a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.1607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0511em"
              >special move; several rule sections also allow single-leader
              forma- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.1107em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0581em"
              >tion to remain in a specific space during Winter. The capacity of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.0607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >such a single-leader formation is limited to the Command Rating
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.0107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_90" style="word-spacing: -0.0574em"
              >just one Leader, plus 1 additional unit which must be cavalry.
              Other &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.9607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >leaders may accompany the designated leader but do not contribute
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.9107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >to the maximum formation size in these cases. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.9896em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_11" style="word-spacing: -0.0025em"
              >5.1 Leaders &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.5695em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >The numeric information contained on the leader counter differs
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.5195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0019em"
              >slightly for army and naval leaders. Naval leaders have an anchor
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.4695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >symbol on their counters that distinguishes them from army
              leaders. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.7566em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0075em"
              >Army Leader &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.889em; top: 20.0028em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1056em"
              >Battle Rating: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1058em"
              >The top number on army leaders is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.885em; top: 20.9528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0609em"
              >their battle rating. Higher battle ratings increase the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.885em; top: 21.9029em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >chance of successfully intercepting or avoiding battle,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.885em; top: 22.8529em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >and add extra dice during assault and field battle. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.198em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_36" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Naval Leaders &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.389em; top: 23.4442em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0846em"
              >Battle Rating: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0939em"
              >The top number on naval leaders is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.385em; top: 24.3942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0609em"
              >their battle rating. Higher battle ratings increase the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.385em; top: 25.3442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >chance of successfully intercepting or avoiding battle,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.385em; top: 26.2942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >and add extra dice during naval combat. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 24.2193em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.102em"
              >Command Rating: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1019em"
              >The bottom number (always appearing in a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 25.1693em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.0603em"
              >yellow box) is the leader’s command rating. This number indicates
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 26.1193em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the number of land units the leader can control at one time.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.4066em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_216">Formations &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 27.6606em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_145" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Piracy Rating (only present on a few Naval leaders): </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >The number &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 28.6106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >after the “P” indicates the number of extra dice the leader
              provides &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2501em; top: 29.5606em; z-index: 3465"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.003em"
              >when present in a Sea Zone where the player is initiating piracy.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.6529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0553em"
              >A formation is a group of land units in a single space that
              functions &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.6028em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0718em"
              >as a combined entity for the purposes of movement, field battle,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.5528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0429em"
              >intercept, and assault. One or more army leaders may also be in-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.5028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0639em"
              >cluded in the formation or even move without units. The maximum
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.4528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >number of land units in a formation is dependent on the Command
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.4028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Ratings of any leaders present: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 30.9271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >Remove a naval leader from the map if there are no longer naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 31.8771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0549em"
              >units present in his location. Return him to any home port under
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 32.8271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >friendly control at the start of the next turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.5644em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_182" style="word-spacing: 0.006em"
              >5.2 Naos &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.1569em; top: 34.8973em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80">Leaders &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2226em; top: 35.8473em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.7052em"
              >Present Maximum</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0052em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Formation Size &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.389em; top: 36.1442em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0602em"
              >Naos </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >represent the intrepid crews who set sail with an &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.385em; top: 37.0942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >exploratory spirit to discover new places and establish
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.6461em; top: 37.0562em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_131">none &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.4732em; top: 37.0625em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">4</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.385em; top: 38.0442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >overseas colonies. During this period, they skirted &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.385em; top: 38.9942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.057em"
              >Africa, rounded the Cape of Good Hope, and sailed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.385em; top: 39.9442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.083em"
              >east in search of India while also venturing west in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.4732em; top: 38.2778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0023em"
              >Command Rating of Leader, plus one additional &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 7.4732em; top: 39.2278em; z-index: 1426"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_218">cavalry. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.2676em; top: 38.7464em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18">1</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.474em; top: 40.443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Sum of highest two command ratings, plus one &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.4739em; top: 41.393em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >additional cavalry (</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Exception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Ferdinand and the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.4739em; top: 42.343em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Great Captain may not combine their ratings). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 40.8942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0583em"
              >search of spices and the New World. Exploration, piracy,
              settlement, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 41.8442em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >looting by competitors, and fighting against attacks from the
              native &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 42.7942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >populations were all constants in their lives. Naos are added to
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 43.7442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >Exploration Map with the Construct a Nao action (17.4). A single
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 44.6942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >player may never have more than </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >two </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Naos on the Exploration Map, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 45.6442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >although he may have any number in the Built Naos box. Nao
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 46.5942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0829em"
              >counters have two sides. Place them on their front (</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_66" style="word-spacing: 0.0905em"
              >full strength &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 47.5442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >side) after they are constructed. Both sides have these two
              ratings: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.7965em; top: 40.9116em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">2 or &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5883em; top: 41.8616em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_21">more &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7507em; top: 43.8345em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >Army leaders and siege artillery are never counted when determin-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7507em; top: 44.7845em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0421em"
              >ing the size of a formation. Formations may not include units
              from &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7507em; top: 45.7345em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >two different major powers except in the following cases:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4173em; top: 47.0178em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0631em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >leaders of the Nasrid Kingdom (El Zagal, Muley Hacén &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0839em; top: 47.9678em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.038em"
              >and Boabdil) may command a combination of North African
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0839em; top: 48.9178em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >and Nasrid units. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 48.9106em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.1189em"
              >Crew Rating: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1238em"
              >This number after the “C” is a modifier for any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 49.8606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0748em"
              >other dice roll that a Nao has to make. It is the crew’s ability
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 50.8106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >survive treacherous voyages on the Exploration Map represented
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 51.7606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.0011em"
              >by Navigation and Terra Incognita rolls. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4173em; top: 50.1179em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Ferdinand</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.007em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0019em"
              >or the Great Captain may command a combination &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0839em; top: 51.0679em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0138em"
              >of Aragonese and Castilian units. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4173em; top: 52.2681em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1216em"
              >• Anjou may command a combination of French and Catalan
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0839em; top: 53.2181em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">units. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 53.127em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0121em"
              >Piracy Rating: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >The number after the “P” indicates the number of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 54.0771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >extra dice rolled in piracy attacks on settlements. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4173em; top: 54.4183em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1329em"
              >• Afonso V may command a combination of Beltranejos and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0839em; top: 55.3683em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >Portuguese units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 55.4435em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_36" style="word-spacing: -0.08em"
              >Damage: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >The back of a Nao counter is the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_36" style="word-spacing: -0.0619em"
              >Damaged </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_36" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >(D) side. Naos &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 56.3935em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.0613em"
              >are flipped to this side if they take losses when undergoing
              Naviga</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.0613em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 57.3435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0351em"
              >tion or Terra Incognita rolls or while pirating rival settlements
              or &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 58.2935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0226em"
              >Naos for loot. The cargo capacity of a Nao is one resource if it
              is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 59.2435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >damaged, and two resources if it is not. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7507em; top: 56.7347em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0409em"
              >The counters of leaders who can command units from more than
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7507em; top: 57.6847em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0848em"
              >one power are marked in both colors as a reminder of this trait.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7507em; top: 58.6347em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >All formations may include minor power units that are allied to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7507em; top: 59.5847em; z-index: 2182"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >the major power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_8" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.85em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">9</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8675em; top: 4.4028em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_220" style="word-spacing: 0.1069em"
              >Cavalry: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_129" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >These units facilitate efforts to avoid &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8453em; top: 5.3528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >battle or intercept enemy forces and are important &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8453em; top: 6.3028em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0581em"
              >weapons in field battles. The numerical value of the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8453em; top: 7.2528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_221" style="word-spacing: 0.1264em"
              >piece shows the number of cavalry units repre- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8453em; top: 8.2028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >sented. Cavalry units have a multi-colored horseman &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.233em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_36" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >5.3 Land Units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.8129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0849em"
              >There are three types of land units, all represented with
              circular &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.7629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0844em"
              >pieces: infantry (regular and militia), cavalry, and siege
              artillery &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.7129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >(only for the powers o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_200">f</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >ragon and France). Land unit pieces come &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.6629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >in differen</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_222">t</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >denominations </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >(1, 2, 4, and 6) to facilitate stacking. Not &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.6129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0548em"
              >all denominations are available for every power. Regular and
              Mili- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.5629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >tia units are on the reverse side of the same counter with
              identical &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.5129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.0674em"
              >denominations; Siege Artillery, Cavalry, and Regulars for Minor
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.4629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Powers have different denominations on the front and back.
              Play</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.4129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0232em"
              >ers may free up small denomination units at any time by replacing
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.3629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >several pieces (all of the same type and all in the same space)
              with &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.3129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >a stronger piece of equal total strength. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2505em; top: 9.1528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >symbol and a solid stripe across the bottom of the counter in
              their &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2505em; top: 10.1028em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_139" style="word-spacing: -0.0592em"
              >power’s color. Cavalry units fight like regulars in field
              battles, and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2505em; top: 11.0528em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_223" style="word-spacing: -0.0565em"
              >may decide to charge in those contests. However, they are
              ineffec</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_223" style="word-spacing: -0.0565em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2505em; top: 12.0028em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.0802em"
              >tive during siege operations. The first cavalry unit in a
              leader´s &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2505em; top: 12.9528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: -0.069em"
              >formation does not count against the formation limit. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_224">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_104">p</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: -0.0623em"
              >layer may &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2505em; top: 13.9028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_225" style="word-spacing: -0.041em"
              >choose to dismount a cavalry unit, swapping it for a regular of
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2505em; top: 14.8528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0251em"
              >same power at any time (even just before combat), but this action
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2505em; top: 15.8028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >is irreversible. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.5396em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.002em"
              >5.4 Naval Units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.1195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.069em"
              >There are two types of naval unit: naval squadrons and corsairs.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.0695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0679em"
              >Rectangular pieces are used to represent naval units. Each naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.0195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0522em"
              >unit always represents a single group of naval vessels. There are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.9695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0589em"
              >no denominations of naval units. The numeric value on the counter
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.9195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >shows the number of dice it rolls in naval combat and the number
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.8695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0647em"
              >of enemy hits required to eliminate it. The color around the
              number &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.8195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >shows which power owns the unit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.144em; top: 21.1692em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0022em"
              >The four denominations of Castilian regulars &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.3412em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >If, after freeing up small denomination units wherever possible
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.2912em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >across the board, a power still has an insufficient number of
              small &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.2412em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >denomination units to properly “make change” to satisfy a Combat
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.1912em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >or Event card result, that power loses additional units from the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.1412em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.104em"
              >space where the combat or event is occurring until a number is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.0912em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0629em"
              >reached that can be represented with the available counters. It
              is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.0412em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >not permitted to voluntarily remove units from the map to obtain
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.9912em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0519em"
              >enough units to satisfy the needs of a combat result or an Event.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.9412em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >If through an Event or resource you should receive units and you
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.8912em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >do not have enough units in your force pool, you only receive the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.8412em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >ones you have. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 26.4017em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_227" style="word-spacing: 0.121em"
              >NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1239em"
              >Naval units from Spain always move and fight as a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 27.3517em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >single force so they are depicted with both the colors of Castile
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 28.3017em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0138em"
              >and Aragon on their counters. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.9278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0081em"
              >As shown in the table below, most powers receive naval units but
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.8778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.1048em"
              >in a very limited number. Some of these powers can build both
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.8278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >naval squadrons and corsairs; the type of a unit in play is
              depicted &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.7778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1009em"
              >by which side of the counter is face up. Powers with two-sided
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.7278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0521em"
              >units should carefully consider the unique properties of each of
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.6778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0468em"
              >two types of naval units when deciding which units to construct.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.6278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1129em"
              >Restrictions on naval unit construction are found in 17.3. Units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.5778em; z-index: 4049"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0576em"
              >listed in the final three rows (with the O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_228">ttoman</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_131">-V</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0471em"
              >enetian </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_229">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">ar &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.5278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >annotation) are not available until the play of their associated
              event. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.2076em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0179em"
              >Infantry: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >There are two types of infantry: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 34.4078em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: 0.2399em"
              >• Regular</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0798em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span
              class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_171"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0719em"
              >Infantry (or </span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_171">Regulars</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.081em"
              >): </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >These units represent profes- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 35.3578em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_184" style="word-spacing: -0.0602em"
              >sional soldiers of the royal army. Regulars have a multi-colored
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 36.3078em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.035em"
              >unit symbol and a solid stripe across the bottom of the counter
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 37.2578em; z-index: 1485"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_140" style="word-spacing: 0.009em"
              >in their power’s color. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 38.4579em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18">•</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 9.6823em; top: 38.4579em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.023em"
              >Militia Infantry (or </span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80">Militia</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.012em"
              >): </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0289em"
              >These units rep- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 9.6783em; top: 39.4079em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_227" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >resent non-professional troops often recruited &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 9.6783em; top: 40.3579em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >for a specific military campaign. Militia have a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 9.6783em; top: 41.3079em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0638em"
              >solid black unit symbol. Militia are found on the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.67em; top: 38.7967em">
            <span class="stl_230 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Powers with naval units: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.67em; top: 39.8339em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0551em"
              >North African &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 40.9201em; top: 39.8339em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">7 NS/Corsairs &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 40.9201em; top: 40.9169em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >1 NS/Corsair &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 40.9201em; top: 41.9999em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.0003em"
              >6 NS &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.67em; top: 40.9169em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Nasrids &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.67em; top: 41.9999em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Portugal &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 9.6783em; top: 42.2579em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_220" style="word-spacing: 0.122em"
              >reverse side of regulars. These units, while &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.67em; top: 43.0829em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Beltranejos &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 40.9201em; top: 43.0829em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.0003em"
              >1 NS &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0835em; top: 43.2079em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0929em"
              >cheaper to construct than regulars, may be disbanded in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0835em; top: 44.1579em">
