          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.3749em; top: 21.6366em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Naval</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0129em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_68">Transport &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.9008em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_60" style="word-spacing: -0.0087em"
              >6. Cards and Resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.3279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0768em"
              >This limitation persists even if a resource is expended to extend
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.2779em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0221em"
              >the impulse. All other actions available to the player on the
              Player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.2279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0409em"
              >Card may be performed without limitation. The Home card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_236">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_70">anto &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.1779em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_237">onta</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: -0.0607em"
              >, M</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_238"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0256em"
              >onta </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_236">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0537em"
              >anto </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >is associated with both Castile an</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_239">d</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">ragon, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.1279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >so it is not subject to this restriction. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.3987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >The game play in </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_240">T</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_61">a</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_67" style="word-spacing: -0.0596em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand and Isabella &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.3487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >is driven by a single deck of 130 cards supplemented by a pool of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.2987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.038em"
              >50 naval resource counters and 20 caravan resource counters. This
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.2487em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0708em"
              >section explains each of the different types of cards, and how to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.1987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >manage the addition and removal of cards from the deck.</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.3299em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0351em"
              >It also &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.1487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0422em"
              >describes management of</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.1759em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0421em"
              >resources, which are treated as a special &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.0987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >form of card with limited uses. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.4943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0022em"
              >Once used, Home cards are placed on each player’s card (not into
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.4443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0111em"
              >the discard pile) to show that they are not available until the
              cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.3943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >are dealt again at the start of the next turn. Home Cards can
              never &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.3443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.1079em"
              >be taken from a power’s hand when a random draw is required
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.2943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.1278em"
              >(either by Event card play, diplomatic agreement, or piracy) or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.2443em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1179em"
              >when a specific card is chosen (Event card play). If a power is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.1943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >forced to reveal his hand, he must also show any Home cards that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.1443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0012em"
              >he is holding. As long as he has a Home card in hand, he may not
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.0943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >perform a Pass action. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.8355em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_241" style="word-spacing: -0.0067em"
              >6.1 Card Types &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.4153em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_126" style="word-spacing: -0.0146em"
              >There are six types of cards in the game, as described below.
              With &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.3653em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0251em"
              >the exception of Mandatory Event and No Event cards, every card
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.3153em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0028em"
              >may be played as either an event, or as command points (CP). CP
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.2653em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0232em"
              >may be used to take actions (11.0), or to declare war (9.4). When
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.2153em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >playing a Mandatory Event, the event takes effect first, then the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.1653em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.008em"
              >active power receives 3 CP to spend on actions. If a player uses
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.1153em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >card as an event, he or she follows the instructions printed on
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.0653em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0549em"
              >card. Some cards have alternate sets of instructions separated by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.0153em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0804em"
              >the word “OR” in capital letters. These cards give the player an
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.9653em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0311em"
              >option of playing them different ways. When playing a card with
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.9153em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0102em"
              >multiple sets of instructions, only the conditions and effects in
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.8653em; z-index: 1824"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.0042em"
              >portion of the card chosen by the player apply. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.3817em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_128" style="word-spacing: -0.0047em"
              >Mandatory Event Cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 38.6279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Cards with the name of the card in red and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 39.5779em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_104" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >the word “Mandatory” printed on them &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 40.5279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_242" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >are Mandatory Event cards. Mandatory &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 41.4779em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0081em"
              >Events must be played during the Action &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 42.4279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >Phase of the turn in which they are drawn; &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 43.3779em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1028em"
              >alternatively they can also be played as &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 44.3279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0647em"
              >the main card of the Headline event. When &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.1525em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_60" style="word-spacing: 0.0014em"
              >Home Cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 45.2779em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_243" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >executed, the event is always resolved &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 46.2279em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >first, then the playing power receives 3 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 47.1779em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_244" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >CPs to spend on actions. Mandatory &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 48.1279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >Events may never be held from one turn &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7131em; top: 46.3987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0958em"
              >Each player has three Home cards each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 47.3487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >associated with one or both of the major &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 48.2987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0091em"
              >powers he controls throughout the game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2094em; top: 49.0779em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0318em"
              >to the next. A player may not pass during &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 49.2487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >Spain has all three Home cards available &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.0279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0263em"
              >his impulse in the Action Phase if a Mandatory event card is
              still &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.9779em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0819em"
              >in his hand. Mandatory Events may be removed from play after
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.9279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >they occur or remain in the deck on a turn-by-turn basis, as
              indi- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.8779em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >cated by the text of each card after it is played. Some Mandatory
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.8279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0274em"
              >Events are automatically executed at the end of the Action Phase
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.7779em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0251em"
              >of certain turns if they have not yet been played and these are
              then &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.7279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >removed from the game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 50.1987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0922em"
              >from Turn 1; the other three players re- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 51.1487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_42" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >ceive their third Home card on either Turn &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 52.0987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0462em"
              >2, 3, or 4. The Spanish player will always &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 53.0487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_245" style="word-spacing: 0.1224em"
              >use all three of their Home cards. The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 53.9987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0278em"
              >other players may only play two of their &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 54.9487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >Home cards each turn (</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >Exception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Portu- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 55.8987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.049em"
              >gal if it has signed the Peace of Alcaço- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 56.8487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0147em"
              >vas). When a player other than Spain has &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7497em; top: 57.7987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >three Home cards in his hand and plays the second of them, he
              must &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7497em; top: 58.7487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_199" style="word-spacing: -0.0592em"
              >discard the third one immediately. Home cards can be played in
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7497em; top: 59.6987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Action Phase or as the Headline event. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_10" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4643em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_247">11 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_45" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >Response Cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_18">P</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_250" style="word-spacing: 0.139em"
              >aPal </span
            ><span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_36">B</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_251" style="word-spacing: 0.1157em"
              >ull </span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_216">Card &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.1988em; top: 5.2945em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.036em"
              >The </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_83">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_252">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0459em"
              >l </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0375em"
              >ull </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >card is a Normal Event &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2091em; top: 6.2445em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_129" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >with special properties. If the current &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2091em; top: 7.1945em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >ruler of the Papacy (3.3) is associated with &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2091em; top: 8.1445em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_253" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Portugal, Spain, or France, this </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_254">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_255">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_256">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_255">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_255">l &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2091em; top: 9.0945em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0955em"
              >ull </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0948em"
              >card is given to that player at the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2091em; top: 10.0445em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0316em"
              >start of the turn. This card may never be &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2091em; top: 10.9945em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_257" style="word-spacing: 0.1284em"
              >drawn by another player, nor can the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 34.2091em; top: 11.9445em; z-index: 1798"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >player choose to pass while holding </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_258">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_259">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_260">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_259">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_259">l &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2091em; top: 12.8945em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_261">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_262" style="word-spacing: 0.1275em"
              >ull </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_263" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >in his hand (much like a Home &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 34.2091em; top: 13.8445em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">card). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7131em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0629em"
              >Cards with the name of the card in blue &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >and the word “Response” printed on them &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 7.4237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.092em"
              >are Response cards. Response cards are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 8.3737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0202em"
              >playable as an event in the Action Phase &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 9.3237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_264" style="word-spacing: 0.1261em"
              >during any player’s impulse (including &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 10.2737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0515em"
              >your own). Play of a Response card inter- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 11.2237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_265" style="word-spacing: 0.1112em"
              >rupts a player’s impulse, a battle, or an &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 12.1737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_199" style="word-spacing: 0.0958em"
              >Event card play. Players should allow a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 13.1237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0689em"
              >reasonable amount of time for play of a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 14.0737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_266" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Response card by another player after &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 15.0237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0798em"
              >each action, event, naval combat, or as- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 15.9737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0149em"
              >sault. Response cards can also be played &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.4146em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_201" style="word-spacing: -0.0255em"
              >6.2 e Deck &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7497em; top: 16.9237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.038em"
              >for CP during a player’s impulse if a player does not wish to use
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7497em; top: 17.8737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_267" style="word-spacing: -0.0578em"
              >the card’s special ability to interrupt another player. Response
              Cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7497em; top: 18.8237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0241em"
              >may only be played as events in the Headline Phase in response to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7497em; top: 19.7737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >CPs that another executing event has awarded. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.9945em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0231em"
              >The cards available to each power each turn consist of their Home
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.9445em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0749em"
              >cards and a variable number of cards dealt to that power from a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.8945em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0177em"
              >single deck of shared cards. The deck is reshuffled each turn,
              after &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.8445em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >any new cards for that turn have been added, and before cards are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.7945em; z-index: 2073"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_56" style="word-spacing: 0.0084em"
              >dealt to each power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.0608em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_39" style="word-spacing: 0.0011em"
              >Combat Cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7131em; top: 22.307em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >Cards with the name of the card in black &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 23.257em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >and the word “Combat” printed on them &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 24.207em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >are Combat cards. Combat cards are play- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 25.157em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0532em"
              >able as an event only during a field battle, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 26.107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: -0.0035em"
              >assault, piracy, or naval combat in which &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 27.057em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.083em"
              >the card owner’s units are participating. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 28.007em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >The Combat card is played just before that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 28.957em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0052em"
              >battle is resolved. Combat cards can also &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 29.907em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >be played for C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_53">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_268">d</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_269" style="word-spacing: -0.0609em"
              >uring a player’s impulse &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 30.857em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: -0.0245em"
              >if a player does not wish to use the card’s &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 31.807em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >special ability to be played during combat. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.0816em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_216" style="word-spacing: 0.0033em"
              >Adding Cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.3278em; z-index: 2139"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.0587em"
              >The upper-right hand corner of many cards contains a turn number.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.2778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0015em"
              >None of these cards are used on Turn 1. Instead, add them to play
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.2278em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1em"
              >at the start of the Card Draw Phase of the turn specified on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.1778em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0261em"
              >card. Home cards added on a specific turn are given directly to
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.1278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0609em"
              >appropriate power; all other cards entering play are added to the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.0778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >deck (before new hands are dealt). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.365em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_228" style="word-spacing: -0.0045em"
              >Discard Pile and Cards Out of Play &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.6111em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0531em"
              >After a card is played, it is either removed from the game or
              placed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.5611em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >in a single discard pile shared by all players: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.3442em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_205" style="word-spacing: 0.0047em"
              >No Event Cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.9276em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.0628em"
              >Out of Play: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Cards are removed from the game if they are played as
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.8776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >an event and the text </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.0127em"
              >Remove from deck if played as event </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">appears &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.8276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0211em"
              >on the card or if the text </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0185em"
              >Remove from deck after [some condition] &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.7776em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >appears and that condition has been satisfied. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7084em; top: 34.5904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Cards marked with the phrase “No Event” &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 11.7092em; top: 35.5404em; z-index: 1148"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.108em"
              >in brown must be played for C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.101em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">hese &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 36.4904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0672em"
              >cards all have a base CP value of 6, which &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 37.4404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0211em"
              >is the number of CPs they grant if played &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 38.3904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_270" style="word-spacing: 0.1128em"
              >during the Action Phase. They have a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 39.3404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0195em"
              >higher CP (shown in parentheses) which &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 40.2904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0304em"
              >is used if played in support of a player’s &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 41.2404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Headline event. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.144em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0468em"
              >Discard Pile: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0468em"
              >Cards are always placed in the discard pile if they &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.094em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0769em"
              >lack the text </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: 0.0829em"
              >Remove from deck</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0768em"
              >… Event cards with this text are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.044em; z-index: 2855"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0371em"
              >also placed in the discard pile if they are played for C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.027em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">r</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0372em"
              >ather than &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.994em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.089em"
              >as an event, or if the condition listed after </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: 0.096em"
              >Remove from deck</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: 0.096em"
              >… &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.944em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0339em"
              >is not met. One of the cards in the game (</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_236">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: 0.0463em"
              >anto </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_237">onta</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.0343em"
              >, M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_238">onta &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.894em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_236">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_140">anto</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0091em"
              >) can be exchanged for a card selected from those currently
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.844em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0082em"
              >in the discard pile. There are a few restrictions on these
              retrievals &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.794em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >from the discard pile: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.5942em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >Normal Event Cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 45.9941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Neither</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0399em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_83">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_252">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0449em"
              >l </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_102">ull</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0167em"
              >, T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >he </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_102">lague</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >, nor any Mandatory Event &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 46.9441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >may be retrieved from the discard pile. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.6988em; top: 46.8404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >The name of these cards is black with no &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7091em; top: 47.7904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.066em"
              >highlight. These cards are played as events &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7091em; top: 48.7404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_271" style="word-spacing: -0.0617em"
              >or CPs during the owning player’s impulse &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7091em; top: 49.6904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0032em"
              >in the Action Phase. Normal Event cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7091em; top: 50.6404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >can be played in the Headline event. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 48.1443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0072em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >player may never retrieve a card from the discard pile that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 49.0943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >this same player played earlier in the turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 50.2945em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0239em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0292em"
              >recovered card cannot be played as an event in this turn if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 51.2445em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0221em"
              >it has already been played as an event before in the same turn.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.5316em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_272" style="word-spacing: 0.0006em"
              >Forming the Deck for a Turn &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.7778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >All cards in the discard pile are reincorporated back into the
              deck &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.7278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0156em"
              >during the Card Draw Phase at the start of each turn. These cards
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.6778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0241em"
              >are combined with (a) the cards that were not dealt during the
              pre- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.6278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >vious turn, and (b) the new cards entering play to form the deck
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.5778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >for the upcoming turn. Never include the card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_83">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_252">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.043em"
              >l </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0315em"
              >ull </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0328em"
              >in the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.5278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >deck, instead award it directly to the Christian player that
              currently &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.4778em; z-index: 3763"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0034em"
              >controls the Papacy as an activated minor power ally.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_11" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">12 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_199" style="word-spacing: -0.0052em"
              >Resource Arrival &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.233em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_45" style="word-spacing: 0.001em"
              >6.3 Resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >There are two sources of resources during the game (18.8 for
              details &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >of arrival and how to use them). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.8129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0199em"
              >Resource counters represent the riches obtained through all types
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.7629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0423em"
              >of trade including slavery, spices from the Orient, and wealth
              from &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.7129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >settlements on the Exploration Map. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.8401em; z-index: 1938"
          >
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >1) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: 0.0036em"
              >Resources that players obtain in winter. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 9.0403em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0439em"
              >◊ From settlements. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >Resource Markers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.1079em; top: 10.2462em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0.0954em"
              >Resource </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0848em"
              >markers are divided between &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.104em; top: 11.1962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >caravan and naval resources, as depicted &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.104em; top: 12.1462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.041em"
              >by the picture on the front of each coun- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.104em; top: 13.0962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_199" style="word-spacing: 0.1178em"
              >ter. On the reverse side they show the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.104em; top: 14.0462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0799em"
              >value of the resource, either a replace- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 10.2404em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.044em"
              >◊ From caravans. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 11.4406em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1164em"
              >◊ Through trade in the Mediterranean and North Sea (French
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 12.3906em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >player only). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 13.5908em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0146em"
              >◊ Through the Mesta (Spanish player only). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 14.7909em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >◊ Through control of Ragusa. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7503em; top: 14.9962em; z-index: 443"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0447em"
              >ment unit, Card, V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.029em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.039em"
              >r C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.083em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0391em"
              >t the start of the game, place all naval &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 15.9462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >resource counters in a pile next to the board with the image of
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 16.8962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >ships facing upwards so that the value of each counter is hidden;
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 17.8462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0974em"
              >create a similar pile for the caravan resources. As resources are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 18.7962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0542em"
              >spent during play, set them aside with their values revealed to
              form &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 19.7462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >a discard pile of resources expended that turn (except those
              marked &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 20.6962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0537em"
              >with VP). These counters are mixed back into their respective
              pool &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 21.6462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >(naval or caravan) as part of the Card Draw Phase. If during the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 22.5962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.048em"
              >Action Phase or Headline Event Segment you receive a resource
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7503em; top: 23.5462em; z-index: 952"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.004em"
              >that awards a card, draw the card immediately. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.1574em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.037em"
              >2) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0371em"
              >Resources that arrive during other phases of the game, either by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.1074em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >event play or various actions: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 18.3075em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.033em"
              >◊ By a roll resulting in an extra reward from a leader captured
              in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 19.2575em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >their dungeon. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 20.4577em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >◊ As a Nao returns to the Built Naos Box with resources gained
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5832em; top: 21.4077em; z-index: 2297"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_213" style="word-spacing: 0.0184em"
              >by piracy. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 22.6079em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0175em"
              >◊ For receiving a ransom payment. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 23.808em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: -0.0217em"
              >◊ At the end of a Spanish impulse if Spain is supporting the War
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 24.758em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in Brittany (20.5). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.8333em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_65" style="word-spacing: 0.0027em"
              >Awarding Resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 25.9582em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0125em"
              >◊ Event cards that specifically award a resource. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.0795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0221em"
              >One naval </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0.0324em"
              >Resource </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >marker is removed from the pool and placed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.0295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1231em"
              >at each settlement during the Card Draw Phase (8.4). They are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.9795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0308em"
              >also added to each new settlement when it is founded. A caravan
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.9295em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0.0764em"
              >Resource </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0659em"
              >marker is placed in both the Marrakesh and Fez boxes &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.8795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0105em"
              >during the Card Draw Phase of Turns 1, 2, and 3; place a caravan
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.8295em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_274" style="word-spacing: -0.0523em"
              >Resource </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_62" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >marker in all three caravan boxes starting on Turn 4. Play-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.7795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0142em"
              >ers can check the back of resources at their settlements or
              caravan &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.7295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >boxes at any time. Naval resources may also be received directly
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.6795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0022em"
              >to the Warehouse on a Player Card from these special sources:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.3246em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.1088em"
              >Resources that arrive outside the Winter Phase follow the same
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.2746em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0839em"
              >process described in the Reveal Resources paragraph of Section
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.2246em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0035em"
              >18.8. The one exception are the Gain 1 Card resources; if that
              oc- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.1746em; z-index: 2640"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0035em"
              >curs, the player should draw that card immediately. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.4608em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_275" style="word-spacing: 0.0055em"
              >Resource Usage &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.707em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0397em"
              >Resources that provide CP cannot be stored from turn to turn, so
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.657em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0185em"
              >those that are not spent must be discarded in the Winter Phase.
              CP &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_199" style="word-spacing: 0.0025em"
              >resources remain in the player’s Warehouse until used to:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 34.8797em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.034em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >the French player succeeds in rolls on the French Mediter-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 35.8297em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >ranean Trade table or the French North Sea Trade table.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 35.8072em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Extend</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: 0.0062em"
              >an impulse (11.0) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 37.0074em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Pay</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >declarations of war (9.4) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 38.2075em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Pay</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >a ransom (9.3) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 37.0299em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the Spanish player succeeds in rolls on the Mesta table.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 38.23em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_276" style="word-spacing: 0.1333em"
              >• If the player that controls Ragusa succeeds in rolls on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 39.18em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Ragusa table. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.4942em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_60" style="word-spacing: 0.0014em"
              >Mixed Hand of Cards and Resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 40.3802em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• When</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0111em"
              >a Nao moves into the Naos Built box after successfully
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 41.3302em; z-index: 1733"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_126" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >gaining a resource through piracy. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.7404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0949em"
              >Events, ransoms, and piracy on the Main Map force a player to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.6904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0504em"
              >have a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_277" style="word-spacing: -0.026em"
              >card </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0501em"
              >drawn out of his hand at random. If a player has a hand
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.6404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0359em"
              >that consists of both cards and resources, the random draw could
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.5904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0389em"
              >be either a card or a resource, even though the text always
              refers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.5404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.047em"
              >to drawing a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_179">card</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.046em"
              >. Whether the random choice is from the target &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.4904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0513em"
              >power’s cards or resources depends on the number of each of these
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.4404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0023em"
              >two types of items in the target power’s hand: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 42.5304em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.2321em"
              >• For</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0321em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >a roll resulting in an extra reward from a leader captured
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 43.4804em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in their dungeon. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 47.6405em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.132em"
              >• If the target has more cards than resources, draw randomly
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 48.5905em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >from the cards (ignoring the resources) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 49.7907em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.2359em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: -0.0602em"
              >the target has more resources than cards, or an equal number,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 50.7407em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >draw randomly from the resources (ignoring the cards)
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.1071em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0081em"
              >When paying a ransom, the player who is paying decides whether
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.0571em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >to give up one card or one resource. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_12" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">13 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_265" style="word-spacing: -0.0318em"
              >5. Winter Phase &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.055em">
            <span class="stl_198 stl_08 stl_133" style="word-spacing: -0.0155em"
              >7. Sequence of Play &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Resolve specific Mandatory Events if they have not been played.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.5528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0909em"
              >The game is played in seven or fewer turns. Each turn covers a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.5028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0645em"
              >period of six to eight years. Each turn consists of seven phases.
              The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.4528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0442em"
              >fourth phase, the Action Phase, is the most time-consuming phase,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.4028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >for it includes a variable number of rounds where each player
              plays &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.3529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0292em"
              >one card. Each such card play is called an </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">impulse</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >. Players use the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.3029em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0366em"
              >final phase, the Victory Determination Phase, to decide if a
              winner &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.2529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0577em"
              >can be declared or if another turn is required. A summary of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.2029em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >sequence of play can be found below: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 6.6819em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0649em"
              >Roll for Military Order reduction of corsair piracy and Nasrid
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 7.6319em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >spaces that have lost their home characteristic. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 8.7901em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Discard unused resources. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 9.9483em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Remove </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Loaned </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0004em"
              >naval unit markers. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 11.1065em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Check for deaths from Plague; remove </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Plague </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">markers. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 12.2647em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Resolve the return of noble militia troops to their homes.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 13.4229em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Leaders and units (except in the Canary Islands) return to
              fortified &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 14.3729em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >spaces, possibly suffering attrition (Moriscos 20.1).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.49em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_11" style="word-spacing: -0.0124em"
              >1. Card Draw Phase &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 15.5312em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >Each major power adds 1 regular unit (or 1 cavalry if the Nasrid)
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 16.4812em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_140" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >to a controlled home key. (Berbers may receive a corsair if they
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 17.4312em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0549em"
              >control Algiers). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5em; top: 15.7362em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_276" style="word-spacing: 0.1236em"
              >Add leaders, naval units, and if this is Turn 4, the Tlemcen
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0835em; top: 16.6862em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Berbers. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5em; top: 17.8863em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_243" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Add suitors and children of the Catholic Monarchs that are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0835em; top: 18.8363em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >eligible to wed. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 18.5894em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Spread effects of Morisco Uprising. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 19.7476em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0502em"
              >Return Naos to settlements or roll a Navigation Check to remain
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 20.6976em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >at sea. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5em; top: 20.0365em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_160" style="word-spacing: -0.0628em"
              >Add 1 </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_279" style="word-spacing: -0.0526em"
              >Fortress </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >marker to each Player card, if there is a vacant box.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5em; top: 21.2367em; z-index: 707">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Place the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Mesta </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_218">marker. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 21.8558em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Naval squadrons return to Main Map ports. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5em; top: 22.4368em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Receive Home cards for the turn and award the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_240">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_128">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_280">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_128">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0581em"
              >l </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_61">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_33" style="word-spacing: -0.0615em"
              >ull </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79">card. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5em; top: 23.5951em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Add new cards to the deck. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 23.014em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Receive resources from settlements and caravans. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 24.1722em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0539em"
