          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.7285em; top: 21.9165em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18">3</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.7293em; top: 23.1318em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18">3</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.73em; top: 24.347em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18">3</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.7279em; top: 25.5635em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18">3</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.7278em; top: 26.7788em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18">4</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.3941em; top: 21.9292em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Aragon &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.3949em; top: 23.1444em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Castile &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.3957em; top: 24.3596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Nasrid &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.7744em; top: 21.9292em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0183em"
              >John II of Aragon &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.7752em; top: 23.1444em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Great Captain &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.776em; top: 24.3596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Muley Hacén &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.1297em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_45" style="word-spacing: 0.001em"
              >8.3 Add New Cards to Deck/Deal Cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 17.7355em; top: 23.1444em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131">Add &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.7095em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0014em"
              >If this is Turn 2 or later, new cards may be added to the deck.
              The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.6595em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0612em"
              >deck is then shuffled and cards are dealt to each player as
              described &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.6095em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in Section 6.2. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_289" style="left: 17.7333em; top: 24.3607em">
            <span class="stl_290 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >Replace with Boabdil &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.3936em; top: 25.5762em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.667em"
              >Beltranejos </span
            ><span class="stl_291 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >Archbishop Carrillo</span
            ><span class="stl_291 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.604em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Remove &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.3935em; top: 26.7915em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Castile &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.7738em; top: 26.7915em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Isabella &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 17.7341em; top: 26.7915em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Replace with Duke &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 17.7341em; top: 27.7415em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >of Alva &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.9759em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >Each player is dealt a number of cards equal to his ruler´s
              Charisma &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.9259em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0039em"
              >attribute and possible bonus cards (if Spain or France) from
              these &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.8759em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">sources: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.7286em; top: 28.9441em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18">4</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 6.3943em; top: 28.9567em; z-index: 923"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >N. African</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 1.012em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.037em"
              >Ibn </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_292">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">hya &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 17.7349em; top: 28.9567em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0276em"
              >Replace with Al &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 17.7349em; top: 29.9067em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Burtuqali &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 30.0761em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Spain</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >(20.6, </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0034em"
              >One Crown for Several Kingdoms</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0034em"
              >) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.7294em; top: 31.1093em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18">5</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.7302em; top: 32.3245em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_18">5</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.3951em; top: 31.1219em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Nasrid &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.7754em; top: 31.1219em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >El Zagal &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 17.7357em; top: 31.1219em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Remove &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 17.7365em; top: 32.3371em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131">Add &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 31.2763em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• France</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >(20.7, </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0026em"
              >Consolidating the Power of the Monarch</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0026em"
              >) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.3959em; top: 32.3371em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >N. African</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 1.012em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0551em"
              >Abu Abdallah &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.6427em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.1285em"
              >To this base number of cards, add and subtract cards from this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.5927em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: -0.0616em"
              >player’s total as indicated by any </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_205" style="word-spacing: -0.0525em"
              >+1/–1 Card </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0634em"
              >markers accumulated &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.5427em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0541em"
              >on your Player Card. Once the card total has been updated, remove
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.4927em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >all </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_90" style="word-spacing: 0.0105em"
              >+1/–1 Card </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >markers that are not permanent. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7533em; top: 33.7455em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >All other changes in leaders occur as indicated on the various
              event &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7533em; top: 34.6955em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0562em"
              >cards. New army leaders (or those removed to the Turn Track in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7533em; top: 35.6455em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1169em"
              >previous turns) are placed in any controlled home space in this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7533em; top: 36.5955em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0525em"
              >priority order: key, fortress, strategic space. If none of these
              spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7533em; top: 37.5455em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: 0.1251em"
              >are available, leave the leader on the Turn Track and try again
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7533em; top: 38.4955em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0224em"
              >next turn. When a leader is being replaced, add the new leader to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7533em; top: 39.4455em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >the exact space occupied by the leader being replaced (unless
              that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7533em; top: 40.3955em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0038em"
              >leader was captured, in which case the replacement is treated as
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7533em; top: 41.3455em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >newly arriving leader). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.8591em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0171em"
              >These newly dealt cards are combined with the Home cards of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.8091em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0093em"
              >player’s powers, the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_83">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_252">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0159em"
              >l </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0075em"
              >ull </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >card (if you are Portugal, Spain, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.7591em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >or France and allied with the Papacy), and any unused cards from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.7091em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_65" style="word-spacing: -0.0613em"
              >the previous turn to form the player’s “hand” for the upcoming
              turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.6591em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0631em"
              >Note that two of these cards will be expended before the Action
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.6091em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.017em"
              >Phase as part of the Headline Event Segment (10.0, Spring Phase
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.5591em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Procedure, Step 1). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.6341em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_228" style="word-spacing: -0.0044em"
              >Marriage Candidates &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.5374em; top: 43.8803em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_294" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Place the counters of any children of the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.5184em; top: 44.8303em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Catholic Monarchs and their suitors that arrive &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.5184em; top: 45.7803em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0042em"
              >this turn on the Wedding table. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.2963em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >8.4 Draw Resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.8762em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0439em"
              >Refresh the pools of naval and caravan resources as described in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.8262em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_146" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Section 6.3. For each settlement that does not currently hold a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.7762em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0489em"
              >resource, randomly draw a naval </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_90" style="word-spacing: 0.0597em"
              >Resource </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.049em"
              >marker from the pool &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.7262em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0649em"
              >and place it on the settlement. Then add a caravan </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_65" style="word-spacing: -0.0833em"
              >Resource </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109">marker &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.6762em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0286em"
              >to both the Marrakesh and Fez boxes. If this is Turn 4 or later,
              also &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.6262em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0027em"
              >add a caravan resource to the Tlemcen box. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.5674em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_36" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Naval Leaders and Units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 48.8136em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0609em"
              >Naval leaders eliminated from play are also brought back at this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 49.7636em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >time. Place them in any home port under friendly control. If no
              such &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 50.7136em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >space exists, the leader remains on the Turn Track until next
              turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.9926em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0979em"
              >Now, for each leader still in your dungeon, draw a CP resource
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.9426em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1217em"
              >(18.8). If any resource awards a non-CP award, return it to the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.8926em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.078em"
              >reserve and take another until you have received a resource that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.8426em; z-index: 4020"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >awards C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.08em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0142em"
              >Naval units eliminated in a previous turn are also returned to
              each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.03em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >power’s pool of units available to be constructed. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.3174em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_27" style="word-spacing: -0.0015em"
              >Tlemcen Berbers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.5636em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_186" style="word-spacing: -0.0609em"
              >On Turn 4 the Tlemcen Berbers enter play. Place the units
              specified &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.5136em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0289em"
              >in Section 20.2 onto the map and add the appropriate units to the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 57.4636em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0561em"
              >North African force pool. All Berber spaces now come into play as
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 58.4136em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >home spaces of the Nort</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_295">h</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_37">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >frican power (Algiers begins as an inde- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 59.3636em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0375em"
              >pendent space until the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0229em"
              >lgiers </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0225em"
              >egency </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0229em"
              >event occurs, see 20.2). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_14" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">15 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0062em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0389em"
              >player may agree to give another player up to two random
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >card draws from their hand. Such a card must always be chosen
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.004em"
              >at random; players cannot exchange specific cards. Two play</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.004em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >ers may not give each other card draws in the same turn; such
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >an exchange can only occur in one direction on a given turn.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 9.0935em; z-index: 2518"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >(Remember that Home cards and </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_297">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_28">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_298">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_28">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >l </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_90" style="word-spacing: -0.0815em"
              >ull </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >are ignored when &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 10.0435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_265" style="word-spacing: 0.0012em"
              >drawing randomly from a player’s hand.) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.055em">
            <span class="stl_198 stl_08 stl_199" style="word-spacing: -0.0202em"
              >9. Diplomacy Phase &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.5528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >The second phase of each turn is the Diplomacy Phase. Skip this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.5028em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0005em"
              >phase entirely on Turn 1 of the game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.2396em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_140" style="word-spacing: -0.001em"
              >9.1 Negotiation Phase &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.8195em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >The first segment of the Diplomacy Phase allows players to
              conduct &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.7695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0679em"
              >secret negotiations away from the game board with one or more
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.7195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0652em"
              >opponents. This portion of the turn is the only time players may
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.6695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >make deals in private; all other discussions must take place in
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.6195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0501em"
              >presence of all players. Players are free to discuss general
              strategic &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.5695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >considerations during negotiations. Cards or resources in your
              hand &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.5195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0353em"
              >may be revealed to other players if desired. They may also make
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.4695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0839em"
              >a limited set of agreements that alter the position of units,
              lead- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.4195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0611em"
              >ers, cards, or markers in play. Such a change is considered to be
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.3695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0242em"
              >a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0174em"
              >change in the current game state</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0093em"
              >. The only agreements allowed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.3195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >that change the game state are: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 11.2436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0782em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >player may agree to give another player up to two randomly
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 12.1936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >drawn resources from their hand (using the same rules as for
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 13.1436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >drawing cards in the previous bullet). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 14.3438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_299" style="word-spacing: 0.3019em"
              >• Two</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.045em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >players may agree that the die will not be rolled for pos-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 15.2938em; z-index: 2796"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0032em"
              >sible benefits from a specific captured leader. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 16.494em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_299" style="word-spacing: 0.3019em"
              >• Two</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.048em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >players may agree to return or exchange Naos and naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 17.444em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >squadrons of the opponent they have captured. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 18.6441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0692em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0242em"
              >player may cede to another player up to two levels of diplo-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 19.5941em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >matic influence over any minor power not allied to the granting
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 20.5441em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0847em"
              >player. This means one level on two different minor powers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 21.4941em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0388em"
              >or two levels on a single minor power. Lower your influence
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 22.4441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0232em"
              >marker when ceding levels; the receiver then raises his level a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 23.3941em; z-index: 3179"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0033em"
              >corresponding amount on that same minor power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 21.5197em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_299" style="word-spacing: 0.3019em"
              >• Two</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.017em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0231em"
              >powers may agree to end a war they are fighting. End the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 22.4697em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0071em"
              >war by removing the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0072em"
              >At </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_252">W</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0028em"
              >r </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.007em"
              >marker from the appropriate box &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 23.4197em; z-index: 883"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.0052em"
              >on the Diplomatic Status Display. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 24.5367em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0421em"
              >Exceptions: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.024em"
              >The Portuguese player may never choose to have &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 25.4867em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0878em"
              >the Beltranejos make peace with Castile. The French player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 26.4367em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >may never choose to have the Principality of Catalonia make
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 27.3867em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.028em"
              >peace with Aragon. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 24.5943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_299" style="word-spacing: 0.3019em"
              >• Two</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.039em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0011em"
              >powers that are not at war may agree to trade up to three
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 25.5443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0968em"
              >militias. Two powers may not give each other militia in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 26.4943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0389em"
              >same turn; such an exchange can only occur in one direction
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 27.4443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0259em"
              >in a given turn. The power granting militia removes the speci-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 28.3943em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >fied number of militia from any single space or combination of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 29.3443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0166em"
              >spaces. The power receiving militia then takes the equivalent
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 30.2943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0159em"
              >number of militia from his force pool and distributes them as
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 31.2443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >desired among its home keys or home strategic spaces—as long
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 32.1943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >as each space chosen is free of unrest, controlled by the receiv-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 33.1443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0547em"
              >ing power, and meets, after placing the militias, the stacking
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 34.0943em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >limits in effect during a Winter Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 28.5869em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_299" style="word-spacing: 0.3019em"
              >• Two</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.081em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0409em"
              >powers may form an alliance for exactly one turn (9.2),
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 29.5369em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0211em"
              >but not if they are currently at war and are not agreeing to end
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 30.4869em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >that war (see above). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 31.6871em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0818em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_300" style="word-spacing: 0.1258em"
              >power entering an alliance may loan their power’s naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 32.6371em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0441em"
              >squadrons to the other power in that same alliance for one turn
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 33.5871em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0499em"
              >(9.2). Neither minor power squadrons nor naval leaders may
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 34.5371em; z-index: 1333"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0101em"
              >be lent however. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 35.4607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >Players should agree on a time limit for the Negotiation Segment
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 36.4107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >before discussions begin. Suggested limits are: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 35.7372em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_166">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_62">c</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70">aptured</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >army leader may be returned. Place that army leader &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 36.6872em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >in a home key if possible. If not, place him in a friendly home
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 37.6372em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >fortress or strategic space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 37.6109em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• 10</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >minutes in a face-to-face game &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 38.8111em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• 48</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >hours in a game by email &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 38.8374em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0598em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1049em"
              >power may yield political control of spaces it controls to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 39.7874em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.1049em"
              >another major power. Any units occupying these spaces are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 40.7374em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >displaced (12.5). However, this granting of a space can only
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 41.6874em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >occur if one of the following conditions is true: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.0972em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_199">Declarations &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0018em"
              >When this time limit is reached (or discussions have ended), each
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.2935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0098em"
              >player (in Impulse Order) declares any agreements made with his
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >powers that will result in a change in the game state</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_301">.</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_302">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214">nnouncements &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.1934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0058em"
              >can be made as individual items, or as a group of agreements that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.1434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >need to be ratified together. All powers involved in an agreement
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.0934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0191em"
              >that follow later in Impulse Order must confirm all the contents
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.0434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0304em"
              >this declaration when it is their turn in the Impulse Order. If
              they &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.9934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0809em"
              >do not confirm the full deal, none of the items in the agreement
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.9434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0441em"
              >take effect. If the agreement is confirmed by all parties, the
              players &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.8934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >immediately change the game state by updating diplomatic status,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.8434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_111" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >returning military leaders, Naos and naval squadrons captured,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.7934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >loaning out fleets, changing political control of a space,
              randomly &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.7434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >drawing cards or resources, and surrendering Militia units.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.1663em; top: 42.8044em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.27em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0208em"
              >The space is being given back to its home power (this in-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.2493em; top: 43.7544em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0108em"
              >cludes returning a minor power’s home space to its major
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.2493em; top: 44.7044em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >power ally; in this case add a control marker of that major
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.2493em; top: 45.6544em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >power to the space), &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.1663em; top: 46.8546em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.2143em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1019em"
              >The space is in Castile and is being exchanged between
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.2493em; top: 47.8046em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.069em"
              >Castile and Portugal (either direction, but not exchanged
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.2493em; top: 48.7546em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >with the Beltranejos), &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.1663em; top: 49.9548em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.3257em"
              >c) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0778em"
              >The space is in Aragon and is being exchanged between
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.2493em; top: 50.9048em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Aragon and France (either direction, but not exchanged
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.2493em; top: 51.8548em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >with Catalan), &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.1663em; top: 53.0549em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.2143em"
              >d) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >The space is an independent space, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.1663em; top: 54.2551em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.3257em"
              >e) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >The space is in Navarre and is exchanged between France
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.2493em; top: 55.2051em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >and Spain, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.1663em; top: 56.4053em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.437em"
              >f) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_145" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >The space is in Italy, is not of a minor ally, and is exchanged
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.2493em; top: 57.3553em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >in any direction between two of these three powers</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_303">:</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_304">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_182">ragon, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.2493em; top: 58.3053em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Muslim, France. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_15" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">16 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0041em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0012em"
              >Beltranejos Faction is automatically allied with France if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >Portugal and France are allied prior to the signing of the Peace
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0551em"
              >of Alcaçovas. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_199">Restrictions &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_152" style="word-spacing: 0.2416em"
              >• Each</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >agreement included in an announcement must be possible
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0333em"
              >at the time it is declared. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_292">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >u may make more announcements &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 7.4237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0048em"
              >than can possibly be accepted (as long as each individual one
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 8.3737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >is valid.) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 7.4436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Castile</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0431em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0319em"
              >and Aragon have a joint foreign policy so an alliance
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 8.3936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >with one of these powers always applies to the other as well.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 9.5739em">
            <span class="stl_208 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >EXAMPLE: </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: -0.0641em"
              >The power A has two naval squadrons on the map &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 10.5239em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >and is allied with power B and power C. It is valid for the power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 11.4739em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0326em"
              >A to announce an agreement to lend the squadrons to power B
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 12.4239em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >and another agreement to lend them to power C. In this case
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 13.3739em">
            <span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_307" style="word-spacing: -0.061em"
              >the f irst power to conf irm the deal will make it impossible for
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 14.3239em">
            <span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: -0.0313em"
              >later power to conf irm the other deal that involves those same
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 15.2739em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >naval squadrons. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 9.5938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• France</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0339em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0391em"
              >can ally with Portugal or Spain but not with both in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 10.5438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >same turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 11.744em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Principality of Catalonia can only be allied with France.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.0306em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_171">Eﬀects &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.2768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >An alliance produces these benefits: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 15.4769em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1363em"
              >• Spaces controlled by either power become friendly to both
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 16.427em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0652em"
              >powers. This means that land units may enter spaces controlled
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 17.377em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >by their ally during movement and retreat. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 16.474em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_282" style="word-spacing: 0.1343em"
              >• Conditional announcements (i.e., ones where you place a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 17.424em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >caveat on whether or not an agreement goes through based on
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 18.374em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0092em"
              >the diplomatic actions of powers coming after you in Impulse
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 19.3241em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Order) are not permitted in any form. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 18.5771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">•</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.9591em; top: 18.5768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Naval squadrons (other than corsairs and Naos) may &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.9583em; top: 19.5268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >be loaned to an ally for one turn subject to the fol-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.9583em; top: 20.4768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >lowing conditions: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 20.5242em">
            <span class="stl_208 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0519em"
              >EXAMPLE: </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.052em"
              >Portugal may not announce a deal lending two &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 21.4742em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_308" style="word-spacing: -0.0593em"
              >naval squadrons to France if France agrees to make peace with
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 22.4242em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13">Aragon. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.6666em; top: 21.7601em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.06em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0121em"
              >Portugal and Spain can never lend each other naval squad-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.5833em; top: 22.7101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0558em"
              >rons while the Peace of Alcaçovas is in effect as they are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.5833em; top: 23.6601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >under a state of war at sea. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.5442em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_186" style="word-spacing: -0.0036em"
              >Non-binding Agreements &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.7904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >The only portion of an agreement that is binding between powers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.7404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0531em"
              >is the portion that changes the current game state. Since items
              such &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.6904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0171em"
              >as a diplomatic action on a future turn, a promised card play, or
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.6404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >coordinated movement of troops cannot be executed at this time,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.5904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0509em"
              >they do not change the current game state and are examples of a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.5404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >non-binding portion of an agreement. Non-binding agreements can
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.4904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0531em"
              >be made at any time between players but they are never announced
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.4404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >and there is never any repercussion within the game mechanics for
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.3904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.003em"
              >breaking them (though there might be some repercussions at your
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.3404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >gaming table!). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.6666em; top: 24.8602em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.0043em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0449em"
              >Naval squadrons currently on the Exploration Map, naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.5833em; top: 25.8102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >leaders, and naval squadrons of allied Minor Powers cannot
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.5833em; top: 26.7602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >be lent. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.6666em; top: 27.9604em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.1157em"
              >c) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >Naval squadrons may be lent between major powers con-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.5833em; top: 28.9104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >trolled by the same player in order to move squadrons to a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 28.5833em; top: 29.8604em; z-index: 3354"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.0039em"
              >controlled port of the receiving power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 31.0606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0509em"
              >Such a loan must be announced at the same time as the alliance;
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 32.0106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0347em"
              >naval squadrons may not be loaned later in the turn. Two players
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 32.9606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >may not loan each other naval units in the same turn; such an ex-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 33.9106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >change can only occur in one direction on a given turn. Place one
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 34.8606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0499em"
              >the receiving power’s </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.052em"
              >Loaned </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0556em"
              >markers on each unit received. Then &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 35.8106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >move the loaned unit to the nearest port controlled by the
              receiving &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 36.7606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0209em"
              >power, counting each Sea Zone traversed as 1 space along such a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 37.7106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >path (2.4 Sea Zones). A loaned squadron is treated like any other
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 38.6606em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.048em"
              >naval squadron of the receiving power (it moves, fights,
              retreats, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 39.6106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_68" style="word-spacing: -0.0628em"
              >and intercepts as if it was one of that power’s naval squadrons).
              The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 40.5606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.018em"
              >naval squadrons stacked in a single port do not have to be loaned
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 41.5106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >out as a complete group. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.0772em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_140" style="word-spacing: -0.001em"
              >9.2 Alliances &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.0813em; top: 36.657em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.0268em"
              >Alliances are agreements between two major powers to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.1249em; top: 37.607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0112em"
              >cooperate for one turn. Alliances must be announced by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.1249em; top: 38.557em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.0699em"
              >all players involved at the end of the Negotiation Seg-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.1249em; top: 39.507em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.021em"
              >ment. A single power may be part of more than one alli-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.457em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_216" style="word-spacing: -0.0522em"
              >ance in the same turn. Two or more powers each in alliance with
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.407em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_42" style="word-spacing: 0.0058em"
              >same power need not be allied with each other. The restrictions
              on &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.357em; z-index: 1736"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_309" style="word-spacing: -0.0595em"
              >creating an alliance and the effects of forming one are detailed
              below. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 42.7107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0758em"
              >If a stack of land units from two major powers is attacked, they
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 43.6607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_146" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >combine their units and army leaders into one defensive force.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 44.6107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0071em"
              >Either power may retreat their units and/or leaders from the
              space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 45.5607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.119em"
              >(with each power making a separate Avoid Battle roll). If units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 46.5107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0367em"
              >from two major powers defend together, battle and assault losses
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 47.4607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0719em"
              >are split evenly between the powers until a power is eliminated;
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 48.4107em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0245em"
              >roll randomly to see who suffers any odd loss. This equal split
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 49.3607em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >casualties also applies in field battle (not assault), to
              attacking units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 50.3107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >whose formation contains units from two powers allied to the same
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 51.2607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0012em"
              >player and leaders who allow this to happen (see below). Units of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 52.2107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0319em"
              >an allied minor power are considered to be units of their
              control- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 53.1607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >ling major power (for the Spanish player, indistinctly Aragonese
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 54.1107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >or Castilian as decided by their owner). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.6442em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_199">Restrictions &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 44.8904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Alliances</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0383em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0431em"
              >do not need to be made by two powers controlled by &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 45.8404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >the same player; those powers are always assumed to be allied.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 47.0405em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.2322em"
              >• An</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0338em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0391em"
              >alliance may not be created if the two powers are currently
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 47.9905em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >at war (even if it is only war at sea). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 49.1907em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_242" style="word-spacing: 0.135em"
              >• An alliance of Portugal, Spain, or France with the Muslim
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 50.1407em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0409em"
              >player prevents these Christian powers from allying with the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 51.0907em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0839em"
              >Papacy unless unless those Christian powers take control of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 52.0407em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0409em"
              >Rome militarily (21.7. Enemy of Islam). Moreover, if any of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 52.9907em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0109em"
              >these powers were allied with the Papacy, this minor power is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 53.9407em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0048em"
              >immediately deactivated when their alliance with the Muslim
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 54.8907em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >player comes into effect. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 55.4771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.003em"
              >Add an </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0033em"
              >Allied </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >marker to the space that serves as a cross-reference &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 56.4271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0729em"
              >between these powers on the Diplomatic Status Display. The al-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 57.3771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1158em"
              >liance is always terminated at the end of the turn. Alliances do
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 58.3271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >not allow land units from allied powers to move, conduct sieges,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2503em; top: 59.2771em; z-index: 4920"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.003em"
              >assaults, intercept, or avoid battle together. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 56.0909em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0321em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0267em"
              >Beltranejos Faction is automatically allied with Portugal
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 57.0409em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0325em"
              >until the signing of the Peace of Alcaçovas (after which they
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 57.9909em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >can no longer ally). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_16" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">17 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >Exceptions: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >Multi-power formations can be formed as per 5.0 by: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 5.5436em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0175em"
              >◊ Great Captain (Aragon and Castile), &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_63" style="word-spacing: 0.0039em"
              >Declaration of War (DO</span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_311">W</span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_18">) </span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_312">P</span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_65">rocedure: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0522em"
              >1. DOW on Major Powers: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0599em"
              >The player announces which of his &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >powers declares war on one or more major powers. For each such
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.4237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0888em"
              >declaration, add an </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >At </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_252">W</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0988em"
              >r </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >marker to the appropriate box in the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.3737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_185" style="word-spacing: -0.061em"
              >Diplomatic Status Display. These powers are now at war until
              peace &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.3237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >is agreed to in a future Diplomacy Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 6.7438em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >◊ Ferdinand (Aragon and Castile), &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 7.9439em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >◊ Anjou (French and Catalan), &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 9.1441em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0046em"
              >◊ Any Nasrid leader (North African and Nasrid). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 10.3443em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0104em"
              >◊ Afonso V (Beltranejos and Portuguese) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.6108em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_56" style="word-spacing: -0.0018em"
              >Special Cases: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.5444em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0499em"
              >Furthermore, alliances do not create a new state of war with any
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.4944em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >third party power (i.e., a power does not add an </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >At </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_313">W</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_162">a</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0542em"
              >r </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >marker with &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.4444em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_314" style="word-spacing: -0.0584em"
              >its new ally’s enemies). However, as described above, all allied
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.3944em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.045em"
              >will add to the defense of a space even if only one of the
              defending &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.3444em; z-index: 529"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_199" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >powers is at war with the attacker. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 11.857em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.165em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.0281em"
              >If one of the powers controlled by the Muslim player is tar-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9999em; top: 12.807em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_126" style="word-spacing: -0.0389em"
              >geted by a DOW, the Muslim may decide to include his other
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9999em; top: 13.757em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0426em"
              >major power in the war for free. The power that declared war
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9999em; top: 14.707em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0543em"
              >is now at war with both Muslim powers. This option is not
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9999em; top: 15.657em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >available with the automatic declaration caused by the event
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9999em; top: 16.607em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0007em"
              >uley </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">ac</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_173">é</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0099em"
              >n </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_131">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ei</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0004em"
              >es </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">Z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315">ahara</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_315">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.0802em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >9.3 Ransom of Leaders and Captured Leaders &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 17.8072em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.1093em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0287em"
              >If a Muslim power declares war during the War Segment or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.9999em; top: 18.7572em; z-index: 2847"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >with the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191">o</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_316">l</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0078em"
              >y </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_192">W</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0005em"
              >ar </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >event, the Muslim player may choose to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9999em; top: 19.7072em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >do so with both of his powers. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.6601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.091em"
              >The second segment of the Diplomacy Phase allows a power to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.6101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >regain a captured army leader whose return was not negotiated in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.5601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0806em"
              >the Negotiation Segment. The power regaining its leader choses
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.5101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >whether to pay one resource or one card from its hand. If it’s a
              re- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.4601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >source, the power receiving ransom randomly selects one resource
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.4101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0354em"
              >from the ransom payer. If it is a card, the player paying the
              ransom &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.3601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0382em"
              >selects a card from his hand and gives it to the player receiving
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1289em"
              >ransom. Place</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0579em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.065em"
              >the army leader back on a controlled home key. Any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.2601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_314" style="word-spacing: -0.0603em"
              >number of army leaders may be ransomed in this segment. However,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.2101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >there is never any requirement to ransom an army leader, a power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.1601em; z-index: 1147"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0036em"
              >may choose to let him remain a captive indefinitely. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27em; top: 20.9074em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.2207em"
              >c) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.005em"
              >Castile and Aragon have a joint foreign policy so a war dec-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9999em; top: 21.8574em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0531em"
              >laration on one of these two powers or by one of them always
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9999em; top: 22.8074em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >applies to the other power as well. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2495em; top: 24.0075em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0499em"
              >2. Declaration on Neutral Minor Powers: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0527em"
              >This player then an- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2495em; top: 24.9575em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >nounces whether or not he wishes to declare war on one or more
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2495em; top: 25.9075em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >minor powers. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 27.4893em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: -0.0063em"
              >SPECIAL CASE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0209em"
              >If a Muslim power is declaring war on Na- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 28.4393em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0179em"
              >varre, the Muslim player may choose to do so with both of his
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.7083em; top: 29.3893em; z-index: 3268"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >powers but the cost remains 3 C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.4472em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_27" style="word-spacing: -0.0014em"
              >Captured Leaders &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.6934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0198em"
              >If any army leader is still captured at the end of this segment,
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.6434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0639em"
              >capturing player has the option to roll one die for each leader
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.5934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0551em"
              >see if he receives any extra benefit for its capture. (The two
              players &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.5434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: -0.0309em"
              >involved may want to discuss whether or not to make this roll
              dur- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.4934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.0234em"
              >ing the Negotiation Phase). Add the captive leader’s Battle
              Rating &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.4434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0399em"
              >to the roll. If the modified roll is a 5, 6, or more, you can
              draw a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.3934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1101em"
              >resource from the resource pool (18.8) or place </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_205" style="word-spacing: 0.1247em"
              >Unrest </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">markers &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0509em"
              >on up to three home spaces of the power belonging to the leader
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >(including occupied spaces). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.0987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.023em"
              >For each declaration, add an </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0221em"
              >At </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_252">W</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0122em"
              >r </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0221em"
              >marker to the appropriate box &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.0487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0071em"
              >in the Diplomatic Status Display. A declaration of war on a minor
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.9987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0351em"
              >power (other than the Papacy) triggers the resolution of that
              minor &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.9487em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >power´s diplomatic status, possibly allowing a major power to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.8987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: -0.0384em"
              >intervene on behalf of this minor power, see Step 4. Finally,
              unless &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.8487em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_62" style="word-spacing: -0.0585em"
              >this minor power is the Papacy, remove the declaring power’s
              influ</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_62" style="word-spacing: -0.0585em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.7987em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0659em"
              >ence marker from this minor power´s column on the Diplomatic
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.7487em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >Influence table; this player may not influence this minor power
              for &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.6987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >the rest of the game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 39.8757em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.053em"
              >DESIGNER´S NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.045em"
              >These spaces entering Unrest represent &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 40.8257em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the unhappiness that the leader has not been rescued.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.0651em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.0164em"
              >3. Pay Declaration of War Costs: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0208em"
              >The player now computes the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.0151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.051em"
              >total CP cost of the declarations he made in Steps 1 and 2. The
              cost &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.9651em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0601em"
              >of each declaration is found by cross-referencing these two
              powers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.9151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0171em"
              >in the Diplomatic Status Display and looking at the number found
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.8651em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >in the appropriate box (this cost varies between Portugal and
              Castile &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.8151em; z-index: 4050"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.043em"
              >depending on whether or not the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0708em"
              >eace of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315">lcaço</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_317">v</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >s </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >and </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">re</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">y &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.7651em">
            <span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_233" style="word-spacing: -0.0804em"
              >of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_318">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_218" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >ordesillas </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >events have been played). In the case that more than &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.7151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0239em"
              >one power of the same player has declared war on a single major
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.6651em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.0878em"
              >or minor power, only the higher cost, if any, must be paid. This
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.6151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >power must play one or more cards or resources from his hand with
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.5651em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0408em"
              >a CP value that is equal to or greater than the total CP
              expenditure. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.5151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0019em"
              >Those cards and resources are placed in the proper discard pile
              as &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.4651em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0533em"
              >if they had been played for CP in the Action Phase. Home cards
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.4151em; z-index: 4473"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0159em"
              >and Mandatory Events may not be used to declare war. If the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_192">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_265">ar &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.3651em; z-index: 4483"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">re</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_252">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315">r</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0048em"
              >ions </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >card is played it covers the cost of all wars without
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.3151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >having to use other cards or resources. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.4851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0739em"
              >If a captured leader dies due to a Mandatory Event his power is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.4351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: -0.0613em"
              >removed from the game, or the leader is replaced by another
              leader, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.3851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >he is removed from the dungeon without further consequence at
              that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.3351em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0081em"
              >time. Additional rolls for the extra benefit are made in the
              Victory &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.2851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Determination Phase of Turn 7; Unrest is not placed in this case.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 48.0219em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_145" style="word-spacing: 0.002em"
              >9.4 Declarations of War &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.1207em; top: 49.6018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_161" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >The third segment of the Diplomacy Phase allows a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.1247em; top: 50.5518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_136" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >power to declare war on one or more other powers, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.1247em; top: 51.5018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_319" style="word-spacing: 0.1298em"
              >major or minor. Follow the DOW procedure below, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.1247em; top: 52.4518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0612em"
              >completing it in full for each of a player’s powers before
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7498em; top: 53.4018em; z-index: 2233"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0027em"
              >starting the procedure for the next player in Impulse Order.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.6815em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0253em"
              >4. Intervention on Behalf of a Minor Power: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.023em"
              >If one or more war &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.6315em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_62" style="word-spacing: -0.0614em"
              >declarations were directed at a minor power, resolve the
              Diplomatic &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.5815em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Status (21.6) of each minor power (if more than one minor power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.5315em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0927em"
              >was the target of a declaration of war, the order of resolution
              is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.4815em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0471em"
              >chosen by the active player). Remove the power declaring war and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 60.4315em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0541em"
              >any power listed as a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.054em"
              >Deactivate </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0518em"
              >power from those considered dur- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_17" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">18 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0301em"
              >ing this Diplomatic Status check. The player who wins the status
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0576em"
              >check earns the right to intervene on behalf of the Minor Power.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >That player must choose one of these options: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_308" style="word-spacing: -0.0614em"
              >respectively). However, there are special cases described below
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0408em"
              >in which you can attack units of these limited major powers,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >even without being at war with them. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 7.4436em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Intervention:</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.084em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0788em"
              >The minor becomes an ally of the power that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 8.3936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.018em"
              >won the Diplomatic Status check. That winning power is now
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 9.3436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0689em"
              >at war with the major power that declared war on the minor
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 10.2936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >power (even if those two powers had earlier declared an alliance
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 11.2436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >for the turn). If units from those powers share a space, displace
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 12.1936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >all units that are not in a space their power controls (12.5).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9168em; top: 7.4436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0349em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0538em"
              >North African Alliance cannot declare war on the Spanish
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 8.3936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0008em"
              >player if the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0017em"
              >uley </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">ac</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_173">é</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >n </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ei</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0014em"
              >es </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">Z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >ahara </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >Event has not yet &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 9.3436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >been played. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9168em; top: 10.5438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0521em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0469em"
              >Nasrid Kingdom and Spain may only go to war through &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 11.4938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >play of the Mandatory Event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0347em"
              >uley </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">ac</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_173">é</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0439em"
              >n </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ei</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0344em"
              >es </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">Z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315">ahara</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_315">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 12.4438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >This state of war is permanent for the rest of the game. (</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13">Ex- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 13.3938em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_266" style="word-spacing: 0.1209em"
              >ception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_135" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >If any Muslim power conquers Rome before the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 14.3438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.02em"
              >Mandatory Event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0207em"
              >uley </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">ac</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_173">é</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >n </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ei</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0204em"
              >es </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">Z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315" style="word-spacing: 0.0199em"
              >ahara </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0197em"
              >is played, it &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 15.2938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0139em"
              >will trigger the mandatory play of this card. Draw it from the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 16.2438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >deck and execute it; if it is in a player’s hand it is now played
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 17.1938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >and that player draws another card from the deck instead).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 13.3938em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Isolation:</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.013em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0182em"
              >The winning power declines its option to go to war &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 14.3438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_231" style="word-spacing: -0.0619em"
              >with the power that declared war on the minor power. The minor
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 15.2938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0038em"
              >power remains inactive, facing the major power that declared
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 16.2438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >war on it alone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.6102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0382em"
              >No matter which option is chosen, all players lose their
              diplomatic &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.5602em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >influence with this minor power (since it was reset during the
              Dip</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.5102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >lomatic Status procedure). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.4806em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_123" style="word-spacing: -0.0059em"
              >Restrictions during Diplomacy Phase &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.7268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_321">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >u can not declare war on: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.7972em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_44" style="word-spacing: -0.0012em"
              >Declaration of War during the Action Phase &amp; Headline
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.7972em; z-index: 886"
          >
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_43">Event &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 20.9269em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0678em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.113em"
              >power that you have made peace with during the current
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 21.8769em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Diplomacy Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.0434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0561em"
              >The following occurrences can place two major powers into a state
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.9934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.011em"
              >of war during the Action Phase: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 23.0771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0812em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0345em"
              >power that you have formed an alliance with during the cur-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 24.0271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >rent Diplomacy Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 25.1936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Home card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_322" style="word-spacing: 0.07em"
              >ultanate of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0102em"
              >z </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >or the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_83">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_252">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0099em"
              >l </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0005em"
              >ull </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">card. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 25.2273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0349em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0538em"
              >North African Alliance cannot declare war on the Spanish
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 26.1773em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0758em"
              >player if it is the Declaration of War Phase of the second or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 27.1273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >third turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 26.3938em; z-index: 1033"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0102em"
              >normal events </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191">o</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_316">l</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0178em"
              >y </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_192">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">ar</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0283em"
              >, W</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0099em"
              >ithout </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0102em"
              >revious </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">eclara</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 27.3438em; z-index: 1089"
          >
            <span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">tion</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: -0.0927em"
              >, A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0378em"
              >rgmagnac </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: -0.04em"
              >ebels </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0382em"
              >and </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80">achi</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_189">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">v</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_102">elli</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">’</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0281em"
              >s </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">“T</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >he </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">rince</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">”</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 28.544em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Mandatory Event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0007em"
              >uley </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">ac</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_173">é</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0099em"
              >n </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ei</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0004em"
              >es </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">Z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315">ahara</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_315">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.4139em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_42" style="word-spacing: 0.0024em"
              >Special Cases with Limited Major Power Units: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.6601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0888em"
              >Beltranejos units, Catalan units, and also Morisco units (includ-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.6101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >ing Morisco rebellion militias after the surrender of the Nasrid
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.5601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1178em"
              >Kingdom) can be attacked by units of major powers other than
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.5101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0909em"
              >Castile and Aragon under the special circumstances specified in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.4601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >this rule—even if they are not officially enemy units (since
              these &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.4101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0089em"
              >powers are not at war). Special rules also govern the spaces
              these &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.3601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_216" style="word-spacing: -0.0626em"
              >units may control and enter, especially while attacking. The
              specific &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >cases are detailed below: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 29.7441em; z-index: 1173"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Activation</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_45" style="word-spacing: 0.011em"
              >of a minor power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 30.9443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0987em"
              >• Declaration of war by a Christian power against the Papacy
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 31.8943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">(21.7). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.2607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >In any of these cases, add an </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_167" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >At </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_260">W</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_130">a</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0662em"
              >r </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >marker to the Diplomatic Status &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.2107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0573em"
              >Display. If naval units of the two powers now at war occupy the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.1607em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >same Sea Zone, fight an immediate naval battle between the two
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.1107em; z-index: 1441"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0025em"
              >powers with the power earlier in Impulse order as the attacker.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 37.5103em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.2358em"
              >• France,</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >Nasrid Kingdom, and Nort</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_323">h</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >frican powers—if at war &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 38.4603em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0364em"
              >with Spain—may enter, control spaces, and attack Beltranejos
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 39.4103em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1108em"
              >units in Castilian and/or Beltranejos home spaces, provided
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 40.3603em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1158em"
              >that the Peace of Alcaçovas has been signed (and therefore
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5832em; top: 41.3103em; z-index: 3997"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0311em"
              >the Beltranejos and Portugal are not allies). In the same way,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 42.2603em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0304em"
              >Beltranejos can enter, control spaces, and attack units of those
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 43.2103em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0149em"
              >powers, exclusively in Beltranejos’ home spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.3972em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_49" style="word-spacing: -0.0016em"
              >Restrictions on Declarations of War &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.6434em; z-index: 1529"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0382em"
              >There are several restrictions which apply to declarations of
              war. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.5934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1219em"
              >Some of those restrictions apply at all times; others only apply
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.5434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.0858em"
              >to declarations made during the War Segment of the Diplomacy
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.4934em; z-index: 1656"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_201" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >Phase, as detailed below. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.7806em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_123" style="word-spacing: -0.0209em"
              >Restrictions at All Times &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.0268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_321">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >u cannot declare war on: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 44.4104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1148em"
              >• Portugal, Nasrid Kingdom and North African powers—if at
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 45.3604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0613em"
              >war with Spain—may enter, control spaces, and attack Catalan
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 46.3104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0568em"
              >units in Aragonese and/or Catalan home spaces. In the same
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 47.2604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.0457em"
              >way, Catalan units can enter, control spaces, and attack units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 48.2104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0027em"
              >of those powers, exclusively in Catalan’s home spaces.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 45.2269em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0838em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_227" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >power whose box on the Diplomatic Status Display lists
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 46.1769em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >“N/A” or “Allied” as the cost of a war declaration. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 47.3771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0438em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >minor power that is allied to a major power (you have to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 48.3271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >declare war on the major power instead). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 49.4106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0941em"
              >• Portugal and France—if at war with North Africans and the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 50.3606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.043em"
              >Nasrid Kingdom does not exist because it has surrendered—
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 51.3106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0364em"
              >may enter, control spaces, and attack Morisco units (including
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 52.2606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Moorish rebellion militias after the surrender of the Nasrid
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 53.2106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Kingdom), in Castilian and/or Nasrid home spaces. In the same
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 54.1606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: -0.0284em"
              >way, Moriscos units can enter, control spaces, and attack units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 55.1106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >of those powers, exclusively in Nasrid’s home spaces.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 49.5273em; z-index: 1916"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0452em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: 0.0037em"
              >power (major or minor) that is currently your ally. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 50.7275em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1352em"
              >• An independent space, as these spaces may be besieged or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 51.6774em; z-index: 2017"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_90" style="word-spacing: -0.0604em"
              >controlled by a power without the need for a declaration of war.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 52.8776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0491em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0439em"
              >Guanches, as they can be attacked without a declaration
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 53.8276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >of war like the Independents. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 55.0278em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Navarre,</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.013em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >unless the influence marker on Navarre of the player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 55.9778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_324" style="word-spacing: 0.1258em"
              >declaring war is at least two levels below another player’s
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 56.9278em; z-index: 2203"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_218">marker. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 56.3108em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: 0.2437em"
              >• Beltranejos</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0643em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.0609em"
              >are only allowed to enter, control spaces, and attack
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 57.2608em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.019em"
              >Castilian and Aragonese units in Castilian and/or Beltranejos
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 58.2108em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_182" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >home spaces. If the Peace o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_325">f</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_304">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >lcaçovas has not been signed—in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 59.1608em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0779em"
              >which case the Beltranejos are allies of Portugal—they may
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 60.1108em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1039em"
              >attack in Portuguese home spaces, always regaining control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 58.1279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1277em"
              >• The Beltranejos or the Principality of Catalonia. These two
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 59.078em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >factions are also never allowed to declare war on another power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 60.0279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0525em"
              >(they are locked into their initial wars with Castile and Aragon
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
