            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_182" style="word-spacing: -0.0618em"
              >one </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_274" style="word-spacing: -0.0608em"
              >space on the Diplomatic Influence Table. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4168em; top: 7.4436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Catalans</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0237em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.0211em"
              >are only allowed to enter, control spaces, and attack
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 8.3936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_146" style="word-spacing: 0.1092em"
              >Castilian and Aragonese units in Catalan and/or Aragonese
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 9.3436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >home spaces. Being allies of France, they may attack in French
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 10.2936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >home spaces, always regaining control of the space for France in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 11.2436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0351em"
              >assaults (and awarding control of spaces to France if they take
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 12.1936em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >a Control Unfortified Space action in a French home space).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 8.81em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_327" style="word-spacing: 0.1278em"
              >Finally, all cards selected by the players are discarded. If any
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 9.76em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0011em"
              >executed headline event indicates that it is removed when played,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 10.71em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >remove the card instead. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 12.2924em">
            <span class="stl_328 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0151em"
              >Important: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0328em"
              >The headline events can never be cancelled or af- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 13.2424em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.017em"
              >fected by any other card. However, if through the use of CPs in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 14.1924em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0372em"
              >the event, movements are made or combat is generated, combat
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 15.1424em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_146" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >or response cards that affect movement, interceptions, avoid
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 16.0924em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >battle, or combat may be used. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.9302em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_185" style="word-spacing: 0.0038em"
              >9.5 War between Castile and Portugal &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.5101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >The one exception to the declaration of war rules listed above is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.4601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >for declarations of war between Portugal and Castile. These two
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.4101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >powers began the period represented in </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_83">T</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.3601em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.0462em"
              >Isabella and Ferdinand </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0418em"
              >as bitter enemies at war over the succes- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0111em"
              >sion of the crown of Castile, but both powers ended up eventually
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.2601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.0008em"
              >signing the Peace of Alcaçovas and the Treaty of Tordesillas. The
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.2101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >decrease in tensions between these powers means that the cost of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.1601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0421em"
              >a declaration of war between these powers varies during the game.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.1101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >The following events change the cost: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.9851em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.077em"
              >2. Naval Escort Segment: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0769em"
              >Each power with an explored Ocean &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.9351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.03em"
              >Zone may move 1 naval squadron from a home port on the Main
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.8851em; z-index: 3193"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0186em"
              >Map to one of the Ocean Zones they have explored. Alternatively,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.8351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0759em"
              >they may return one squadron in an Ocean Zone to a home port
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.7851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >on the Main Map. In either case this movement is made without
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.7351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >needing to pass a Navigation Check. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.1015em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_68" style="word-spacing: 0.0607em"
              >3. Troop Deployment Segment: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >All major powers with a home &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.0515em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.013em"
              >key under their control may move a single formation from one of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.0015em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >these keys to a friendly-controlled space. This special move
              costs &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.9515em; z-index: 3483"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >no C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.008em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >he following restrictions apply: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 24.3103em; z-index: 1024"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0129em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0463em"
              >eace of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315">lcaço</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_317">v</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0081em"
              >s </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0232em"
              >event sets the cost at 4 CP although &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 25.2603em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >it allows for war at sea (including piracy on the Main Map).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 26.4605em; z-index: 1112"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0161em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">re</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >y of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_154">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0288em"
              >ordesillas </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0289em"
              >event increases the cost to 6 CP &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 27.4105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >and the war at sea ends. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.2389em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_199">Restrictions &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 29.4851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.2359em"
              >• Only</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.059em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >land units and army leaders that start this phase in a home
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 30.4351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >key may use the Spring deployment. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.2789em">
            <span class="stl_198 stl_08 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0228em"
              >10. Spring Phase &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 31.6353em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0059em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0111em"
              >power must be able to trace a path of any length from the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 32.5853em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0359em"
              >key the formation occupies to the destination space. All land
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 33.5353em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >spaces on the path must be friendly-controlled and no land
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 34.4853em; z-index: 3807"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0491em"
              >space on the path may be in unrest or contain a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.049em"
              >Plague </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_218">marker. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 35.4353em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.028em"
              >The path may also cross one Sea Zone (only) following a path
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 36.3853em; z-index: 3909"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0234em"
              >from one friendly-controlled port on that Sea Zone to another.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.7768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0383em"
              >The third phase of each turn is the Spring Phase. At this time,
              each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.7268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1218em"
              >major power undertakes a series of activities to prepare for the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0097em"
              >upcoming Action Phase. In each segment, each player in Impulse
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.6268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >Order completes all of the steps listed below for their powers
              before &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.5768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >moving on to the next segment. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.8639em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_67" style="word-spacing: -0.0015em"
              >Spring Phase Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 37.5854em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >destination space cannot contain enemy units. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.5192em; top: 38.1101em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_329" style="word-spacing: 0.1245em"
              >1. Headline Event Segment: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_330" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >Each player secretly &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.505em; top: 39.0601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_203" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >chooses a Home card, Mandatory Event, or normal &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.505em; top: 40.0101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1209em"
              >event card from his hand in an attempt to have that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.505em; top: 40.9601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0609em"
              >event executed in this segment (the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.061em"
              >Headline Event</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 41.9101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0615em"
              >Each player then chooses a second card, which cannot be a Manda-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 42.8601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0382em"
              >tory Event, to support the first card with its CP value. All
              cards are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 43.8101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0999em"
              >revealed simultaneously and the headline event submissions are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 44.7601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0571em"
              >ranked in order from highest CP value of the supporting card to
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 45.7101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.006em"
              >lowest. In the case of a tie, the player with less VP goes first
              (and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 46.6601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >if there is still a tie, then the player earlier in Impulse Order
              is placed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 47.6101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">first). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 38.7856em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1053em"
              >• The number of land units in the formation is limited by the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 39.7356em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >command rating of any army leaders present. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 40.9358em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >path may not cross a Pass. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 42.1359em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >path may not enter a space containing units from another
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 43.0859em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0169em"
              >power unless all the units in that space are friendly to the de-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 44.0359em; z-index: 4180"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0099em"
              >ploying power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 45.2361em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.2322em"
              >• No</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0232em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0168em"
              >more than five land units (plus army leaders) may cross a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 46.1861em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Sea Zone during spring deployment. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 47.3863em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: 0.2399em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >another major power has naval squadrons (that have not been
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 48.3363em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >lent to the deploying power) in ports that border the Sea Zone
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 49.2863em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >being crossed, the path is blocked if either of these is true:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7501em; top: 48.9765em; z-index: 2016"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.1013em"
              >The players then receive the following benefits in ranked order.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 49.9265em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0495em"
              >(Treat this segment as a normal impulse for the purposes of
              resolv- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 50.8765em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >ing the event; this event can never be extended): &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 50.4864em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.1949em"
              >◊ If</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.058em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >this other major power is at war with the deploying power,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.333em; top: 51.4364em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">or &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 52.0767em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_218" style="word-spacing: 0.2501em"
              >• FIRST</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0839em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_179" style="word-spacing: -0.0629em"
              >PLACE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_179" style="word-spacing: -0.0715em"
              >Gain 1 V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_132">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_179">f</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0665em"
              >or a Headline Event. Then execute &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 53.0267em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >your selected event. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 52.6366em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1929em"
              >◊ If</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.027em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.032em"
              >the deploying power does not have one of his own squad</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.032em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.333em; top: 53.5866em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0319em"
              >rons either in the Sea Zone or in a port adjacent to the Sea
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.333em; top: 54.5366em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Zone. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 54.2269em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.232em"
              >• SECOND</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0419em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0371em"
              >PLACE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0403em"
              >Roll one die. If the result is 5 or higher, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 55.1769em; z-index: 2234"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0419em"
              >gain 1 V</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.007em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0509em"
              >fter rolling the die a player may sacrifice points &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 56.1269em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0072em"
              >from their ruler’s Admin Rating for this turn to improve their
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 57.0769em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_137" style="word-spacing: 0.1188em"
              >die roll; each point they subtract from their Admin Rating
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 58.0269em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.038em"
              >adds one pip to their roll as they attempt to reach a 5. A
              ruler’s &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 58.9769em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >Admin Rating may never be reduced below 0. Then execute
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 59.9269em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >your selected event. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2493em; top: 55.903em; z-index: 4582"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.099em"
              >The </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_192">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: 0.1165em"
              >ar </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">re</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_252">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315">r</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1167em"
              >ions </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1103em"
              >normal event, the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.1169em"
              >he </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1166em"
              >ise of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_131">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315">rance &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 56.853em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.065em"
              >Home card, and the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191" style="word-spacing: 0.0364em"
              >rown of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0645em"
              >ragon </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0649em"
              >Home card allow some &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 57.803em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0541em"
              >of these restrictions to be ignored. Units from different powers
              that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 58.753em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0131em"
              >start the phase stacked with a leader that can command units from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 59.703em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1119em"
              >multiple powers may move together with that leader for one of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 60.653em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0676em"
              >that player’s deployments. Spring deployments with a formation
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_19" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">20 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >containing units from more than one power are considered as the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.01em"
              >spring deployment of the power owning the space from which the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >movement began. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >value (from 2 to 5) allow a player to perform actions just as if
              they &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2934em; z-index: 2485"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.028em"
              >were playing a card for C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.017em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_199" style="word-spacing: 0.0328em"
              >dditionally, the Spanish player may &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0789em"
              >extend the impulse either by moving a leader to the Canaries or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.051em"
              >by rolling on the Mesta Table in the case indicated in the War of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0621em"
              >Brittany. The French player also may extend the impulse to sign
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0006em"
              >the Treaty of Barcelona and/or the Treaty of Senlis. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.1122em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_27" style="word-spacing: -0.0165em"
              >11. Action Phase &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.4599em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0739em"
              >Limitation: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0739em"
              >If the player used any card other than a Home card &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.4099em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0391em"
              >or a Mandatory Event for its CP value during the first part of
              his &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.3599em; z-index: 2876"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0378em"
              >impulse, remember which actions he chose during this card play.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.3099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0306em"
              >Then, if any of these actions are repeated when CP are expended
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.2599em; z-index: 2987"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >from the resource, the cost of each repeated action is 1
              additional C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_332">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_332">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.6101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0914em"
              >During the Action Phase, the players take impulses in the order
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.5601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0649em"
              >described in Section 3.1. The power initiating an activity is
              referred &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.5101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >to as the active power throughout these rules. Each impulse
              consists &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.4601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >of one of the following three activities: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 14.6603em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Play</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >a card for Command Points (CP). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 15.8605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Play</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >a card as an event, if the card has an event. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 17.0606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Passing,</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >if the conditions are right. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.6263em">
            <span class="stl_208 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >EXAMPLE: </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_25" style="word-spacing: -0.0615em"
              >The Spanish player plays a 3 CP card at the beginning
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.5763em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0357em"
              >of his impulse. He builds a Castilian naval squadron in Corunna
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.5263em">
            <span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0547em"
              >for 2 CP and spends 1 CP to raise his diplomatic inf</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0999em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0165em"
              >l uence over &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.4763em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0604em"
              >Genoa by 1 level. He then declares that he extends his impulse
              with &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.4263em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_140" style="word-spacing: -0.0213em"
              >a 4 CP resource. If he builds a naval squadron with the resource
              it &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.3763em">
            <span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0039em"
              >will cost him 3 CP; if he tries to raise diplomatic inf l uence
              levels &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.3263em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0017em"
              >it will also cost him 1 additional CP for each such action.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.427em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Unless the power passed, he may then extend his impulse by
              playing &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.377em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >a resource (Spanish and French players see below). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.7434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_333" style="word-spacing: 0.1146em"
              >Playing a card for Command Points (CP): </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_245" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >All cards except &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.6935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0149em"
              >Mandatory Event cards can be played for CPs during an impulse.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.6435em; z-index: 736"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0261em"
              >When played for C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0159em"
              >, a </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">c</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0261em"
              >ard provides a number of CPs equal to the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.5934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0256em"
              >number in the shield in the upper-left corner of the card. These
              CP &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.5434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0039em"
              >are then expended to perform one or more of the actions listed on
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.4934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.009em"
              >that player’s Player Card. The card played is placed in the
              discard &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.4434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >pile and will be used again in future turns. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.0636em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_39" style="word-spacing: 0.0011em"
              >11.1 Actions &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.6434em; z-index: 3401"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0289em"
              >Each action in the game costs from 1 to 4 C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.039em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">E</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0289em"
              >xact rules for the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.5934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0351em"
              >execution of each action are found throughout sections 12 through
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.5434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0904em"
              >20. Some actions cost a variable number of CPs (e.g., the Wed-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.4934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0114em"
              >ding Dowry). CPs are spent on one action at a time. That action
              is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.4434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0627em"
              >then executed to completion before any remaining CP are spent.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.3934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1182em"
              >CP may not be accumulated from one impulse to another; they
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.004em"
              >must be spent (or discarded) in the impulse in which the card
              that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0215em"
              >provided the CP was played. A power may choose to execute the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0432em"
              >same action back-to-back within an impulse. This is very common
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.1934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0979em"
              >with movement actions so units can move multiple spaces. It is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.1434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0558em"
              >also common when constructing units and when playing CP to buy
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.0934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Diplomatic Influence. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.8099em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.096em"
              >Play a card as an event: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.097em"
              >Mandatory Event cards, Home cards, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.7599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.024em"
              >normal event cards, and Response cards (but never Combat cards)
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.7099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >may be played as events during a player’s impulse. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 31.2924em">
            <span class="stl_334 stl_17 stl_335" style="word-spacing: -0.0639em"
              >Important: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_241" style="word-spacing: -0.0641em"
              >Some events may only be played by powers specified &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 32.2424em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >on the card, or if certain conditions have been met. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.9018em; z-index: 1270"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0593em"
              >Read the printed effects on the card and execute them
              immediately. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.8518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.001em"
              >Note that some Home and normal event cards (and all Mandatory
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.8018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.057em"
              >Event cards) award CPs that can be used with that event; these
              CPs &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.7518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0552em"
              >are spent to perform any of the actions listed on that major
              power’s &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.7018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0043em"
              >Power Card. After being played as an event, the card is placed on
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.6518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0939em"
              >the discard pile, unless the card text states </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: 0.1001em"
              >Remove from deck if &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.6018em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0112em"
              >played as an event; </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0111em"
              >such cards are permanently removed from the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.5518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0702em"
              >game. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_321">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0332em"
              >u may play an event that directs another power to take an
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.5018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >action; in this case, the player listed on the card resolves the
              action, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.4518em; z-index: 1723"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_66" style="word-spacing: 0.0073em"
              >not the active player. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.9622em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_90" style="word-spacing: -0.0093em"
              >12. Control and Unrest &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.4601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Political control of spaces can change based on actions (i.e.,
              Control &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.4101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >Unfortified Space, or a successful assault), negotiation, or
              event card &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.3601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >play. A line of communication (LOC) from a fortified home space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0529em"
              >is required to initiate actions that change space control; rules
              for &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.2601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0358em"
              >LOC are therefore included in this section. Spaces can also enter
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.2101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0491em"
              >unrest through Event card play. If unrest is present in a space,
              most &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.1601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0371em"
              >of the benefits of controlling that space are lost. Unrest is
              removed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.1101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0969em"
              >through the same action that is used to gain control of a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">simple &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.0601em">
            <span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: -0.0545em"
              >unfortif ied space</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: -0.0545em"
              >. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.8182em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.015em"
              >Passing: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0094em"
              >Late in the Action Phase, powers may pass for their im-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.7682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >pulse. Players may never pass if: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 45.9684em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• They</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.035em"
              >have in their hand either a Home card or the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_83">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_252">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0241em"
              >l </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ull &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 46.9184em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">card, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 48.1185em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0202em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0249em"
              >Mandatory Event is in their hand that has not been played,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 49.0685em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">or &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.7969em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >12.1 Line of Communication (LOC) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 50.2687em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• They</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0549em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0438em"
              >have more cards in their hand than their ruler´s Admin
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 51.2187em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Rating &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0186em"
              >A power has an LOC to a space if it can trace a path of spaces
              and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.3268em; z-index: 4591"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_336" style="word-spacing: -0.0588em"
              >Sea Zones to that space from a friendly-controlled fortified or
              strate</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_336" style="word-spacing: -0.0588em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.2768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >gic space that is a home space for that power or one of its
              allies (this &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.2268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0242em"
              >includes home spaces of major or minor allied powers). LOC may
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.1768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0316em"
              >also be traced from any port you control in the Canary Islands.
              All &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.1268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.038em"
              >spaces on the path (except the space where the path ends) must
              be: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.5851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0421em"
              >A power must pass if it has no cards left in its hand. A power
              hold- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.5351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0241em"
              >ing one or more cards that passes during an impulse does not have
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.4851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0295em"
              >to continue to pass. This power may play one of these held cards
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.4351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1109em"
              >when their turn for an impulse arises later in the Action Phase.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.3851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_104" style="word-spacing: 0.1199em"
              >The Action Phase is over when all four players have passed in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 57.3351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >consecutive impulses. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 56.3269em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Friendly-controlled, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 57.5271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Free</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0052em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >of enemy units (including naval units and leaders), and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 58.7273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Free</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0052em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >of </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_164" style="word-spacing: 0.0151em"
              >Unrest </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >and </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Plague </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">markers. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 58.7015em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0475em"
              >Extending the impulse with a resource: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0549em"
              >A player with a resource &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 59.6515em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0218em"
              >in his Warehouse and who has played a card may now extend the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 60.6015em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.011em"
              >impulse by playing one of those resources. Resources listing a CP
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_20" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">21 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0459em"
              >One or more adjacent Sea Zones may be part of the LOC if they
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0057em"
              >each contain a friendly naval unit. The path must connect to
              these &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_111" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >Sea Zones through a friendly-controlled port (except the space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.034em"
              >where the path ends, which can be a non-friendly port). An LOC
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.017em"
              >is required for the Assault and Control Unfortified Space
              actions. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0399em"
              >Guanches never need to trace LOCs to assault or remove control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.0435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >of spaces (21.8). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.233em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_39" style="word-spacing: 0.0012em"
              >12.4 Unrest &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.649em; top: 5.8129em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_164" style="word-spacing: 0.0451em"
              >Unrest </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >markers are placed on spaces due to event card &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.645em; top: 6.7629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.0046em"
              >play. Unrest has the following effects: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.1666em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_67">Eﬀects: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 10.4129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0318em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >may not use spring deployment, retreat, or avoid battle
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 11.3629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >into or through a space in unrest. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.7802em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_128" style="word-spacing: -0.0049em"
              >12.2 Unfortiﬁed Space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 12.563em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.2322em"
              >• No</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0052em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >LOC can be traced through a space in unrest. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.3601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0074em"
              >A power may spend 1 CP on the Control Unfortified Space action
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0649em"
              >to gain political control of a space if the following
              requirements &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.2601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >are all met: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 13.7632em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.2322em"
              >• No</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0168em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0221em"
              >units or fortresses may be constructed in a space in unrest.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 14.9634em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0602em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.015em"
              >key space or a strategic space in unrest is not counted when
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 15.9134em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0109em"
              >tracking the number of VP earned. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.5472em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_44">Requirements: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 17.1135em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• During</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.026em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0312em"
              >the Winter Phase, passing over spaces in unrest causes
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 18.0635em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">attrition. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 17.7934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_338" style="word-spacing: 0.1362em"
              >• The space is independent, controlled by an enemy power,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 18.7434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >controlled by the Beltranejos (if control is being gained by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 19.6935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0038em"
              >Portugal), or controlled by Catalan (if control is being gained
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 20.6435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >by France). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 19.2637em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0702em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.025em"
              >fortress in unrest does not roll a die against a piracy attempt
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 20.2137em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in an adjacent Sea Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 21.4139em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_268" style="word-spacing: 0.2519em"
              >• Some</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0669em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_339" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >spaces may subtract 1 from a Ruler’s Charisma or prevent
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 22.3639em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >die rolls to obtain cards if they are in unrest (20.0).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 21.8436em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >space is unfortified. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 23.0438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >active power has an LOC to the space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 23.564em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0312em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.014em"
              >space in unrest may not be counted by a player toward any
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 24.514em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >objective that requires control of one or more spaces.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 24.244em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0671em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >space is not occupied by land units from another power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 25.194em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >(unless those units are allies of the active power). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 25.8804em">
            <span class="stl_340 stl_17 stl_341" style="word-spacing: 0.0618em"
              >EXAMPLE: </span
            ><span class="stl_342 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.1201em"
              >Spaces along the Atlantic coast of Africa for &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 26.8304em">
            <span class="stl_342 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0046em"
              >“Portugal, Owner of the Atlantic”. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 26.5604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0791em"
              >To gain control of a strategic space, the Control Strategic Space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7501em; top: 27.5104em; z-index: 939"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0281em"
              >action is used at a cost of 1 C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.018em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">L</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0282em"
              >and units controlled by the active &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 28.4604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >power must currently occupy the strategic space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.1167em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_67" style="word-spacing: -0.0016em"
              >Remove </span
            ><span class="stl_343 stl_08 stl_67" style="word-spacing: -0.0016em"
              >Unrest </span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_27">Markers: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.3629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_110" style="word-spacing: 0.1156em"
              >A power may spend 1 CP on the Control a Simple Unfortified
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.3129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.093em"
              >Space action to remove unrest from any space if at least one of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.2629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >these conditions is met: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 29.8268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.0418em"
              >To gain control of a simple space, the Control Simple Space
              action &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7501em; top: 30.7768em; z-index: 1090"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >is used, also at a cost of 1 C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.05em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">E</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0602em"
              >ither (a) land units controlled by the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 31.7268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >active power must occupy the space, or (b) land units controlled
              by &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 32.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0421em"
              >the active power must be adjacent to the space with no enemy land
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 33.6268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0347em"
              >units adjacent. </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.0393em"
              >[For the purposes of this requirement, two spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 34.5768em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.0043em"
              >connected by a pass are not considered adjacent.] &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 32.463em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Land</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >units controlled by the active power occupy the space,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 33.6632em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Land</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >units controlled by the active power are adjacent to the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 34.6132em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0411em"
              >space and land units of an enemy power are not adjacent. </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">[For &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 35.5632em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0431em"
              >the purposes of this condition, two spaces connected by a pass
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 36.5132em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >should not be considered adjacent.] &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 36.159em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_344" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_345" style="word-spacing: 0.1264em"
              >In case (b) above, land units controlled by the ac- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 37.109em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.063em"
              >tive power adjacent to the space do not have to have an LOC
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 38.059em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >themselves; the LOC requirement is only to the space being
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 39.009em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >converted. Units conducting a siege and under siege must all
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 39.959em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >still be considered when evaluating case (b). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.8796em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.09em"
              >Removing unrest does not require an LOC to that space (unlike
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.8296em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0322em"
              >gaining political control of an unfortified space where an LOC is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.7796em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">required). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.6851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_282" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Place a new control marker on the space to indicate the new
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.6351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0211em"
              >owner (unless it is reverting to its original owner and no marker
              is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.5851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0319em"
              >required). (Guanches never control spaces but do remove control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.5351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0278em"
              >markers from players with this action). If this space is a port
              that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.4851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >contains naval units, those naval units must immediately retreat
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.4351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >a Sea Zone adjacent to that port following the instructions found
              in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.3851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0507em"
              >Step 9 of the Naval Combat Procedure. When the active player has
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 48.3351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >units from more than one of his powers in a space being
              controlled, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 49.2851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >that player chooses which power gains control. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.5163em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_44" style="word-spacing: 0.0007em"
              >12.5 Displacement &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.0962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >If control of a space changes due to negotiation, intervention
              after &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.0462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: 0.0751em"
              >DOW on a minor power, or an event card play, units friendly to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.9962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0081em"
              >the previous owner of the space may be displaced as described on
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.9462em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0471em"
              >specific cards and in rule sections. When displacement occurs,
              any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.8962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0278em"
              >land units and army leaders occupying these spaces are placed in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.8462em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0669em"
              >the nearest fortified space controlled by their power or in a
              con</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0669em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.7962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0232em"
              >trolled home key. Naval units and leaders are placed in the
              nearest &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.7462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0616em"
              >port controlled by their power. Count Sea Zones as spaces when
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.6962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1069em"
              >determining the shortest path. If two spaces are equidistant, the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.6462em; z-index: 3987"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0045em"
              >space is chosen by the owning player. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.0219em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_44" style="word-spacing: 0.0007em"
              >12.3 Fortiﬁed Space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.6018em; z-index: 2119"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0625em"
              >Political control of fortified spaces only changes based on
              Negoti</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_346">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_346">- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.5518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0127em"
              >tion (9.1), Assault (15.1), and event card play. See the
              appropriate &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.5018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >section for further details. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.0126em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >If as a result of an event, any unit is required to be moved to
              another &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.9626em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0874em"
              >location, make that move regardless of the unit’s location at the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.9126em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0173em"
              >origin, be it a captured leader, a space under a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.02em"
              >Plague </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_68" style="word-spacing: -0.0113em"
              >marker, that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.8626em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the unit is besieged, etc. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_21" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">22 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: 0.1986em"
              >◊ This</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0603em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >is a fortified space under siege where either: (a) all units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.333em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0202em"
              >inside the fortification are allied to the active power, and all
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.333em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.07em"
              >besieging units are enemies of the active power, or (b) all
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.333em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0603em"
              >units inside the fortification are enemies of the active power,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 28.333em; top: 8.1435em; z-index: 2435"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >and all besieging units are allied to the active power.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.233em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_36" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >12.6 Control of an Island &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.129em; top: 6.7712em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1189em"
              >Players must also track control of Canary Islands for
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.125em; top: 7.7212em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >these purposes: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 8.9214em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0249em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0295em"
              >islands of Gran Canaria and Tenerife are each worth 1 VP
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 9.8714em; z-index: 237"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: 0.006em"
              >to the controlling power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2494em; top: 9.3436em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Independent regulars in a fortified space never prevent the entry
              of a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2494em; top: 10.2936em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >formation, though that formation might have to fight off troops
              from &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2494em; top: 11.2436em; z-index: 2604"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0031em"
              >an enemy power before being able to siege the independent key.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4167em; top: 11.0715em; z-index: 280"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0452em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0024em"
              >power that controls all seven islands gains 1 V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 12.2717em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0268em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0719em"
              >Spanish player who controls five islands does not have to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 13.2217em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >make Navigation Checks between Zone 1 and Zon</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_348">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_183">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >nd does &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 14.1717em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0471em"
              >not suffer Plunder during the Winter Phase, if he controls all
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 15.1217em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >the Canary Islands (21.8, Conquest Of Canary Islands).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.916em; top: 12.4438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1154em"
              >• No army leader or unit may participate in a Move action if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 13.3938em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >they were part of a formation that lost a field battle earlier in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 14.3438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >the impulse. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.916em; top: 15.544em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.2322em"
              >• No</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0322em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >army leader or unit may participate in a Move action if it
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 16.494em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >occupies an enemy fortified space that their power placed under
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 17.444em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >siege (15.0) earlier in the impulse. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 16.4881em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_321">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0431em"
              >u gain control of an island if you control all the spaces that
              are a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 17.4381em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0206em"
              >part of that island. All islands have a single space except
              Tenerife, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 18.3881em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >which has four spaces, and Gran Canaria, which has three spaces.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.916em; top: 18.6441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.2321em"
              >• One</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0432em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >or more army leaders may move without accompanying &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 19.5941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0032em"
              >land units as long as they don’t enter a space controlled by an
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 20.5441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0198em"
              >enemy power or containing enemy units. If an army leader is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 21.4941em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0501em"
              >ever alone in an unfortified space when enemy land units enter
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 22.4441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0392em"
              >due to enemy movement, retreat, or interception, that leader is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 23.3941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >captured. Place the captured leader on the enemy Player Card.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 24.3441em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1063em"
              >The enemy player gains 1 VP if this is the first leader they
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 25.2941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0048em"
              >have captured in the game. The leader may be regained in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 26.2441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Diplomacy Phase of an upcoming turn (9.0). If a naval leader
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 27.1941em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0839em"
              >is ever alone in an unfortified space when enemy land units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 28.1441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0518em"
              >enter due to enemy movement, retreat, or interception, place
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 29.0941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: 0.0006em"
              >that leader on the Turn Track to reenter play on the next turn.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.2567em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_28" style="word-spacing: -0.0309em"
              >13. Movement &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.7545em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >A power may move land units with either the Move Formation In
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.7045em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Clear action (1 CP) or the Move Formation Over Pass action (2
              CP). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.6545em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0241em"
              >All land movement is restricted by the formation rules (5.1).
              Land &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.6045em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >movement may trigger interception attempts by enemy formations.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.5545em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0132em"
              >Enemy stacks are also allowed to try to avoid battle and withdraw
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.5045em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >into fortifications in response to Move actions. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.2413em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_42" style="word-spacing: 0.0025em"
              >13.1 Land Movement Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.916em; top: 30.2943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.2322em"
              >• No</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0158em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0211em"
              >unit may enter a space with a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.021em"
              >Plague </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_56" style="word-spacing: -0.0127em"
              >marker. Each land or &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 31.2443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0089em"
              >naval unit that attempts to move out of a space with a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80">Plague &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 32.1943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0555em"
              >marker (in either the Spring or Action Phases) must roll one
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 33.1443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >die: if they roll a 1, 2 or 3 they are eliminated. If several
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 34.0943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.031em"
              >move out of a Plague space together roll dice for all units si-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 35.0443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >multaneously; the moving player may then decide which ones
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 35.9943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >to lose for each roll of a 1, 2, or 3. Roll a separate die for
              each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 36.9443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >leader moving from a Plague space; if they roll a 1 or 2 place
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 37.8943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0006em"
              >them on the Turn Track to reenter play next turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.8212em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >The following restrictions limit the use of a Move action.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.1083em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_128">Restrictions: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 33.3545em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1073em"
              >• All land units and army leaders being moved must start the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 34.3045em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >action in the same space, and it must be permissible to move
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 35.2545em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >them in a single formation. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 36.4547em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Formations</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0042em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0091em"
              >may always move into a space controlled by their &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 37.4047em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1066em"
              >power or into an independent space. A formation may only
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 38.3547em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >move into a space controlled by another power if either:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2494em; top: 39.2607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >The two Move actions follow the same procedure: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 39.5549em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0783em"
              >◊ The active power is at war with the power controlling the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 40.5049em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >destination space, or &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.5473em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_184" style="word-spacing: 0.0027em"
              >Land Movement Procedure: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 41.705em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1119em"
              >◊ The active power is allied with the power controlling the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.7935em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_60" style="word-spacing: -0.0582em"
              >1. Declare Formation: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >The active power declares which formation &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 42.655em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >destination space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.7434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >of land units and army leaders will be moved. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 43.8552em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Formations</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0518em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0469em"
              >may not move into a space containing land units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 44.8052em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_225" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >from another power unless the space satisfies one of these
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 45.7552em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">conditions: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.1099em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_349" style="word-spacing: -0.087em"
              >2. Declare</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.1477em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_350" style="word-spacing: 0.1229em"
              >Destination Space: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_351" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >The active power declares the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 45.0599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >destination space for the move. The destination must be adjacent
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 46.0099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0045em"
              >to the formation’s current space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 46.9554em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1929em"
              >◊ All</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0238em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >units in the space are allies of the active power (and this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 47.9054em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0431em"
              >is not a fortified space where one ally has another ally under
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 48.8554em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">siege); &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 47.3763em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.005em"
              >3. Expend CP: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.0365em"
              >Two CP are expended if the move is over a pass; &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2492em; top: 48.3263em; z-index: 4262"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >otherwise the cost is just one C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 49.6927em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0682em"
              >4. Play</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.1059em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.1022em"
              >Response Cards: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1019em"
              >Other powers may play the Response &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2484em; top: 50.6427em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0182em"
              >card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_154">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >orrential </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >ains </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >to disrupt this Move action. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 50.0555em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1929em"
              >◊ All</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0222em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.017em"
              >units in the space are enemies of the active power (and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 51.0055em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0551em"
              >this is neither a fortified space where one enemy has another
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 51.9555em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >enemy under siege nor a fortified space controlled by an ally
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 52.9055em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0389em"
              >of both the active power and all powers with units already
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 53.8555em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in the space); &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2484em; top: 52.0091em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >5. Conduct any Interceptions: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0198em"
              >Interceptions (13.2) may occur if &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2484em; top: 52.9591em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0228em"
              >an enemy stack is adjacent to the destination space.
              Interceptions &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2484em; top: 53.9091em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0108em"
              >may add enemy units to the space being entered. Any player may
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2484em; top: 54.8591em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0163em"
              >play the response card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >mbush </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >to ensure that an interception suc- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2484em; top: 55.8091em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1019em"
              >ceeds. Once all interceptions have been resolved, the land units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2484em; top: 56.7591em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0262em"
              >and army leaders being moved are placed in the destination space.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2484em; top: 57.7091em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0489em"
              >If any interceptions succeeded, skip to Step 8 and resolve a
              field &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2484em; top: 58.6591em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">battle. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 55.0557em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1926em"
              >◊ This</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0037em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0013em"
              >is a space controlled by an enemy power, and all units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 56.0057em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0639em"
              >in the space are either from that enemy power or allied to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 56.9557em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0644em"
              >them. When resolving this movement, treat the units already
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 57.9057em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >in the space as </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >enemy units </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0058em"
              >for all purposes. Adjacent units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 58.8557em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.003em"
              >from a power with units in the space are also considered as
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.833em; top: 59.8057em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >enemy units and may intercept into the space if desired;
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_22" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">23 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_68" style="word-spacing: -0.0406em"
              >6. Conduct Avoid Battle: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0251em"
              >If the destination space contains enemy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0143em"
              >land units, all or some of them may try to avoid battle (13.3).
              Any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em; z-index: 217">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >player may play the response card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">rgani</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0025em"
              >ed </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">etre</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.011em"
              >t </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.003em"
              >to ensure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_201" style="word-spacing: -0.0068em"
              >that an Avoid Battle succeeds. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_277" style="word-spacing: 0.2558em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0702em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >may not intercept into a space controlled by another power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0541em"
              >unless the power controlling the space is either an enemy or an
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >ally of the intercepting units. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.5306em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_259" style="word-spacing: 0.0033em"
              >Interception Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.5599em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0546em"
              >7. Withdraw into Fortification: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0521em"
              >If after unsuccessful interception &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.5099em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0978em"
              >and avoid battle attempts (if any) the enemy stack in a fortified
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.4599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >destination space has four or fewer units present, those enemy
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.4099em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >have the option of withdrawing into fortifications (13.4).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.7768em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0655em"
              >1. Declare Formation: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >An intercepting power with land units and/ &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.7268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >or army leaders in a space adjacent to the movement destination
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0604em"
              >declares which formation will attempt an interception. This
              forma- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.6268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >tion does not need to include all of the units present.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.7763em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0218em"
              >8. Fight Field Battle: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0519em"
              >If enemy land units are still present in the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.7263em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0401em"
              >space, and those land units are not inside fortifications, then a
              field &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.6763em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >battle occurs in this space (14.0). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.9932em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.011em"
              >2. Roll Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0509em"
              >The intercepting power rolls two dice and adds the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 13.9432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.0851em"
              >best single Battle Rating of an army leader (if any) in the
              inter- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 14.8932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0157em"
              >cepting formation to the dice sum. Add 1 to the result if there
              are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 15.8432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >more cavalry units in the intercepting formation than in the
              moving &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 16.7932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >formation. Subtract 1 from the result if there are more cavalry
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 17.7432em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0089em"
              >in the moving formation. If the modified die roll is 9 or more,
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 18.6932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0252em"
              >interception attempt is successful. If it failed, any player may
              play &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 19.6432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0186em"
              >the response card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >mbush </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >to force it to succeed. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.4136em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_36" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >13.2 Interception &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.9934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0006em"
              >An enemy power with land units adjacent to a Move action’s des-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.9435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0609em"
              >tination space may attempt to intercept the moving formation. If
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.8935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >multiple enemy stacks are adjacent to the destination space, each
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.8435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_137" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >may attempt to intercept. Each such attempt is announced and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.7935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0799em"
              >resolved before announcing and resolving any other attempts. If
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.7435em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >multiple stacks from different enemy powers all want to
              intercept, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.6935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_49" style="word-spacing: -0.0607em"
              >resolve the interception attempts in Impulse Order. Once one
              power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.6435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_111" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >succeeds, no other power may attempt an interception (even if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.5935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >that other power is an ally of the intercepting power).
              Formations &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.5435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >belonging to the successful intercepting power may however con-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.4935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >tinue to attempt to intercept from any number of adjacent spaces.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 21.0096em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_353" style="word-spacing: -0.0595em"
              >3. Place in Destination Space: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_241" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >If successful, the intercepting forma- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 21.9596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0179em"
              >tion is placed in the destination space. This formation is
              treated as &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 22.9096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.057em"
              >if it were present in the space before the moving formation
              arrived. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 23.8596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Once one power succeeds, no other power may attempt an intercept
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 24.8096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >(even if that other power is an ally of the intercepting power).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 26.1761em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0288em"
              >4. Repeat for other Formations: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >Return to Steps 1-3 and resolve &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 27.1261em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1111em"
              >interception attempts from any other adjacent space. Additional
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 28.076em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >attempts from a space already chosen in Step 1 are not permitted.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.7806em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_199">Restrictions &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 29.4425em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0132em"
              >5. Fight Field Battle: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >If any of the interceptions were successful, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 30.3925em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0659em"
              >fight a field battle (14.0) in the destination space. All units
              from &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 31.3425em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0411em"
              >the intercepting power must participate in this battle; they may
              not &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 32.2925em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >avoid battle or withdraw into a fortification. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 30.0268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Formations</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0598em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0548em"
              >moving due to avoid battle, interception, and re- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 30.9768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >treats may not be intercepted. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 32.1769em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Formations</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0048em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >may never intercept across a pass. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 33.3771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Only</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.028em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >units of a power that is at war with the active power may
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 34.3271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">intercept. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.0302em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_354" style="word-spacing: 0.0052em"
              >13.3 Avoid Battle &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 35.5273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0708em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0658em"
              >and army leaders that have already tried to intercept a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 36.4773em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_111" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >movement in this same impulse (whether or not they were
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 37.4273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >successful) may not try to intercept again. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.6101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1049em"
              >When a power enters a space containing a stack of enemy land
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.5601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0129em"
              >units, some or all of those enemy units may try to move to an ad-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.5101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >jacent space to avoid battle. If the destination space contains
              land &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.4601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0561em"
              >units from more than one major power (who are allies), each major
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.4101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_90" style="word-spacing: -0.0574em"
              >power may, in Impulse Order, announce and resolve an avoid battle
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.3601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0249em"
              >attempt. Each such attempt is announced and resolved before an-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0058em"
              >nouncing and resolving any other attempts. Minor power allies in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.2601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >that space avoid battle as a single group with units of their
              affiliated &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.2101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0079em"
              >major power. A power is never required to try to avoid battle; it
              is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.1601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >always optional. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 38.6275em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0778em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0729em"
              >and army leaders currently under siege may not try to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 39.5774em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >intercept. If a besieging force moves out of a space under siege,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 40.5274em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.028em"
              >the stack formerly under siege may not intercept the move out
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 41.4774em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >of that fortified space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 42.6776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• All</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0362em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0308em"
              >land units and army leaders allocated in Step 1 of the In-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 43.6276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.056em"
              >terception Procedure (see below) must start the Move action
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 44.5776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >in the same space and it must be permissible to move them in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 45.5276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >a single formation. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.4472em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_128">Restrictions: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 46.6934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: 0.2398em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0612em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >may not avoid battle into an independent space or a space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 47.6434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0392em"
              >controlled by another power unless that power is an ally of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 48.5934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >power avoiding battle. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 46.7278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: 0.2377em"
              >• Leaders</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0603em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >may not intercept by themselves unless the destination
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 47.6778em; z-index: 1998"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0033em"
              >space contains units friendly to that leader. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 48.8779em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Formations</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0748em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0699em"
              >moving into a friendly fortified space that is not &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 49.7936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0402em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >may not avoid battle into a space in Unrest, with Plague,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 50.7436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >or a space containing enemy units. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 49.8279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >under siege may not be intercepted. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 51.0281em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: 0.2458em"
              >• Formations</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0642em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >moving into a space that already contains land units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 51.9781em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0132em"
              >may only be intercepted if the intercepting units belong to the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 52.9281em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0361em"
              >same power as the units in the destination space, or to a power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 53.8781em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >allied to the units in the destination space. Such an
              interception &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 54.8281em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0019em"
              >is not allowed if there are units under siege (from any power)
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 55.7781em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.032em"
              >in that space at the start of the active formation’s move. This
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 56.7281em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0267em"
              >rule also prevents intercepts into an empty, fortified space by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 57.6781em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0251em"
              >units that are not either from the power that controls the space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 58.6281em; z-index: 2537"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0045em"
              >or an ally of that controlling power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 51.9438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Land</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >units may not avoid battle into a Sea Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 53.1439em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0468em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0419em"
              >may not avoid battle into the space just vacated by the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 54.0939em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >enemy formation the units are trying to avoid. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 55.2941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0768em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0719em"
              >and army leaders currently under siege may not avoid &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 56.2441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">battle. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 57.4443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.2358em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0592em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >of a power may not avoid battle if any units of that power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 58.3943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >intercepted into the battle space during this Move action.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_23" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">24 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0372em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >leader alone in a space may not avoid battle. If the space is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.044em"
              >1. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0472em"
              >If there are CP remaining to be played in this impulse, the
              active &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >formation may spend 1 CP (or 2 CP if the move is over a pass) to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.2434em; z-index: 2808"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >continue movement into an adjacent space. </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">[Howeve</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_194">r</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.048em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99">i</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_210" style="word-spacing: 0.0529em"
              >f they are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_201" style="word-spacing: 0.061em"
              >later forced to retreat from this new space back into the
              fortif</span
            ><span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0963em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_356">ied &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0034em"
              >space, they are eliminated.] &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0669em"
              >unfortified, he is captured (13.1); if the space is fortified, he
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >must withdraw inside. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.5306em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_357" style="word-spacing: 0.0072em"
              >Avoid Battle Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.7768em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.1068em"
              >1. Declare Attempts: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1228em"
              >Each major power with land units in the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.7268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >destination space of the Move action may declare and resolve (in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0019em"
              >Impulse Order) an avoid battle attempt. Follow steps 2-5 for each
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.6268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >such power before going on to the next. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.5099em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.009em"
              >2. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.009em"
              >Otherwise the active formation must retreat back into the space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.4599em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0367em"
              >from which it entered the fortified space. This retreat does not
              cost &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.4099em; z-index: 3018"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >any C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.038em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">b</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >ut the retreat must abide by all retreat restrictions listed
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.3599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in Section 14.1. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.9932em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_268" style="word-spacing: -0.0665em"
              >2. Designate Destination Space: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >This power designates an adjacent &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.9432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0802em"
              >space into which the units avoiding battle will try to move. The
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.8932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >space must satisfy the restrictions listed above. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.2289em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0223em"
              >14. Field Battle &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.2596em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0435em"
              >3. Choose Units: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0429em"
              >The power chooses which land units and army &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.2096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0638em"
              >leaders will attempt to avoid battle. The total number of units
              chosen &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.1596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0259em"
              >may exceed the number that can be moved as a single formation.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.1096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0739em"
              >Any number of units may be left out of the avoid battle attempt
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.0596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0422em"
              >(you can even leave out all land units to have an army leader
              avoid &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.0096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >battle by himself). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.7268em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0493em"
              >A field battle occurs due to a Move action into a space occupied
              by &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >an enemy formation or because of a successful interception. Each
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.6268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >power involved adds up how many battle dice they will roll, a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.5768em; z-index: 3313"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: -0.0594em"
              >number that may change if they decide to charge with their
              cavalry. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.5268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0488em"
              >This number of dice is then rolled to see how many </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0484em"
              >hits </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0479em"
              >are scored. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.4768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0313em"
              >Each hit inflicts a casualty on the opponent. The side which
              scores &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.4268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0645em"
              >the most hits on its opponent is the victor and retains the
              space. The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >defeated force must then retreat to an adjacent space.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.376em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.064em"
              >4. Roll Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >The power avoiding battle rolls two dice and adds the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.326em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >best single Battle Rating of an army leader (if any) present in
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.04em"
              >stack of units leaving the space to the dice sum. Add 1 to the
              result &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.226em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >if there are more cavalry units in the formation avoiding battle
              than &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.176em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0249em"
              >in the formation from which they are trying to escape. Subtract 1
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.126em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0729em"
              >from the result if the reverse is true. If it failed, any player
              may &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.076em; z-index: 1219"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.021em"
              >play the response card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">rgani</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0205em"
              >ed </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">etre</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.011em"
              >t </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0211em"
              >to force it to succeed. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.026em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0159em"
              >If the modified die roll is 9 or more, the attempt to avoid
              battle is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.976em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.039em"
              >successful. </span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0391em"
              >Exception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0391em"
              >If every unit in the formation attempting to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.926em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0432em"
              >Avoid Battle has already lost a field battle during this impulse,
              it &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.876em; z-index: 1458"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_186" style="word-spacing: -0.0014em"
              >may Avoid Battle automatically—no dice roll is necessary.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.6639em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_68" style="word-spacing: -0.0012em"
              >Field Battle Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.9101em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0066em"
              >1. Play Response Cards: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0209em"
              >Any player in Impulse Order may play &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.8601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_242" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >a response card such as </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_204">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_146" style="word-spacing: 0.1236em"
              >obles </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_242">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_358" style="word-spacing: 0.1241em"
              >eturn </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_204">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_359" style="word-spacing: 0.1239em"
              >ome </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_242" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >or </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_204">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_52">ercenary &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.8101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >ilitias </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >to change the number of units in the space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.1765em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0944em"
              >2. Attacker Adds Up Battle Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1188em"
              >The active player is always &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.1265em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0442em"
              >considered the attacker in a field battle. The attacker adds up
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.0765em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >number of dice he will roll as follows: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 32.4429em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.029em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0391em"
              >die for each infantry or cavalry unit in the moving formation
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 33.3929em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >(do not count siege artillery) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.2425em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0073em"
              >5. Place in Destination Space: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0081em"
              >If successful, the units selected to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.1925em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >avoid battle are placed in the chosen adjacent space.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 34.5931em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.053em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >die for each Battle Rating point from the highest-rated leader
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 35.5431em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in the attacking force &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.5589em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1118em"
              >6. Repeat for other Formations: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1188em"
              >Return to Steps 2-5 for each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.5089em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0439em"
              >remaining power with units in the destination space of the Move
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.4589em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">action. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 36.7433em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0008em"
              >the attacker decides to undertake a cavalry charge add:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 37.9434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2029em"
              >◊ 1</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Extra die for the first cavalry unit &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 39.1436em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2029em"
              >◊ 1</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Extra die for every two full cavalry units beyond the first
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.1969em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_66" style="word-spacing: -0.0077em"
              >13.4 Withdrawing into Fortiﬁcations &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.3329em; top: 40.3438em">
            <span class="stl_208 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0671em"
              >EXAMPLE: </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_33" style="word-spacing: -0.0585em"
              >If either three or four cavalry units charge, two &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.3329em; top: 41.2938em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_14" style="word-spacing: 0.0075em"
              >dice are added. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.7768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_104" style="word-spacing: 0.127em"
              >Enemy units in the destination space may withdraw inside for-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.7268em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0719em"
              >tifications in Step 7 of the movement procedure if the following
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >conditions are all met: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 42.494em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0186em"
              >3. Defender Adds Up Battle Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >The intercepting player or the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 43.4439em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0979em"
              >player with the stack of units in the destination space is always
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 44.3939em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0158em"
              >considered the defender in a field battle. The defender adds up
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2492em; top: 45.3439em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >number of dice he will roll as follows: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 43.8769em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >destination space is fortified, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 45.0771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0429em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0481em"
              >enemy power (or an ally of the enemy power) controls the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 46.0271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >destination space, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9158em; top: 46.7104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.042em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0319em"
              >die for each defending infantry or cavalry unit in the space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5824em; top: 47.6604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >(do not count siege artillery) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 47.2273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_360" style="word-spacing: 0.1332em"
              >• There were four or fewer units (plus any number of army
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 48.1773em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0551em"
              >leaders) present in the space after interception and avoid battle
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 49.1273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0259em"
              >attempts were resolved. Artillery and cavalry units are always
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 50.0773em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >counted against this limit of four units. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9158em; top: 48.8605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.053em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >die for each Battle Rating point from the highest-rated leader
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5824em; top: 49.8105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in the defending force &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9158em; top: 51.0107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >die for being the defender &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.4437em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0298em"
              >A power is never required to withdraw into its fortifications; it
              is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.3937em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0188em"
              >always optional. If they do withdraw, all units present must
              with- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.3437em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: -0.0596em"
              >draw together. If units from more than one power are defending
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.2937em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >space when the active formation enters, the power controlling the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.2437em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0211em"
              >space decides whether or not to withdraw into the fortifications.
              If &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.1937em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0499em"
              >the units decide to withdraw inside fortifications, a field
              battle is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 57.1437em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0491em"
              >avoided during this impulse. If the active formation has more
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 58.0937em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0503em"
              >than the number of units inside the fortification, this
              fortification is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 59.0437em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0491em"
              >now under siege (15.0). If the active formation does not have
              more &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 59.9937em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >units, it has two choices: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9158em; top: 52.2109em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.008em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >die if the field battle space is a strategic space controlled by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5824em; top: 53.1609em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >the defender &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9158em; top: 54.361em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0008em"
              >the defender decides to undertake a cavalry charge add:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5824em; top: 55.5612em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2029em"
              >◊ 1</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Extra die for the first cavalry unit &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5824em; top: 56.7614em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2029em"
              >◊ 1</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Extra die for every two full cavalry units beyond the first
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2484em; top: 57.9615em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0584em"
              >4. Attacker Declares Combat cards: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0748em"
              >The attacker declares any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2484em; top: 58.9115em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Combat cards he wants to play as events to affect the battle.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_24" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">25 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0006em"
              >5. Defender Declares Combat cards: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0058em"
              >The defender declares any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >Combat cards he wants to play as events to affect the battle. If
              more &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0532em"
              >than one player is controlling defending units in this space,
              each of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >these players may play Combat cards. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.233em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >14.1 Retreat &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.8129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >All remaining units and army leaders from the losing power must
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.7629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >retreat (exception: Independent units see 21.8). If the battle
              occurred &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.7129em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0539em"
              >in a fortified space, and the power controlling that space lost
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.6629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0918em"
              >battle, then any number of land units up to four (at the owner’s
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.6129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0528em"
              >discretion), and any number of army leaders, may withdraw into
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.5629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.085em"
              >the fortifications. Artillery and cavalry units are always
              counted &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.5129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0638em"
              >against this limit of four units. The stack of units remaining
              outside &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.4629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0301em"
              >the fortifications after such a withdrawal (or all losing power
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.4129em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >if the battle did not occur in a fortified space) must then
              retreat to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.3629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0554em"
              >a single adjacent space chosen by the owner of those units. That
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.3129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0068em"
              >space must meet all the restrictions listed below. If no legal
              space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.2629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >exists, all units in that stack are eliminated; any army leaders
              pres- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.2129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >ent are captured. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.5599em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >6. Roll the dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Both sides roll their dice. Each roll of “5” or “6” is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.5099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >considered to be a hit. Rolls of a “4” may be a hit in these
              situations: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 10.71em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.063em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.058em"
              >your side rolled two dice from regular units, from cavalry
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 11.66em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0612em"
              >units, from being the defender, or from defending in a strategic
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 12.61em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.027em"
              >space, the first die roll of “4” is a hit (do not include dice
              for &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 13.56em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0024em"
              >cavalry charges). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 14.7602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.065em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.06em"
              >your side rolled four or more dice from these sources, the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 15.7102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >second die roll of “4” is also a hit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 16.9104em">
            <span class="stl_342 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0491em"
              >EXAMPLE: A player that is defending a controlled strategic
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 17.8604em">
            <span class="stl_342 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: -0.0356em"
              >space with a single militia rolls three dice and will hit with
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 18.8104em">
            <span class="stl_362 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.017em"
              >f irst die roll of “4”. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.5em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_128">Restrictions: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 19.7462em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1328em"
              >• Units may not retreat into an independent space or a space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 20.6962em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0392em"
              >controlled by another power unless that power is an ally of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 21.6462em; z-index: 3503"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0077em"
              >retreating power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 20.0105em; z-index: 769"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0157em"
              >The response cards </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_189">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_317">v</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_363" style="word-spacing: 0.0399em"
              >lry </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">P</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_102"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0156em"
              >ursuit </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >and/or </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">L</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0159em"
              >eadership </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">may &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 20.9605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >be used at this time to modify the combat results. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.1607em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: -0.0155em"
              >7. Declare Winner: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0091em"
              >The side scoring the most hits is declared the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.1107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0429em"
              >winner of the battle. In the case of a tie, the defender is
              declared &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.0607em; z-index: 958"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_167" style="word-spacing: 0.0138em"
              >the winner. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 22.8464em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1302em"
              >• Units may not retreat into a space in unrest, with a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80">Plague &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 23.7964em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.003em"
              >marker, or containing enemy units. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 24.9965em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Land</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >units may not retreat into a Sea Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.4271em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.07em"
              >8. </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_252">T</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0529em"
              >ke Casualties: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0522em"
              >Each side eliminates one land unit for each hit &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.3771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0449em"
              >scored by the opposing side. If your side received any extra dice
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.3271em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_364" style="word-spacing: -0.0613em"
              >from a cavalry charge, the first casualty it must take is a
              cavalry unit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.2771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >Of the remaining losses, at least half (rounded down) must be
              taken &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.2271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0461em"
              >from regulars or cavalry units if possible. In addition, if there
              were &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.1771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0311em"
              >units of more than one power on either side, the number of
              casual- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.1271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0581em"
              >ties must be split between them as evenly as possible, regardless
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.0771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0191em"
              >type. The two requirements above on how to distribute losses are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.0271em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0032em"
              >ignored in field battles involving relief forces (15.2). If both
              sides &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.9771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >are completely eliminated, the side that rolled more dice retains
              one &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.9271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_33" style="word-spacing: -0.0613em"
              >unit (cavalry units that charged may only be chosen if they were
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.8771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >only unit in that combat). If both sides are eliminated and the
              two &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.8271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >sides rolled the same number of dice, the defender retains 1
              unit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 26.1967em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.033em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >the defender lost the battle, his units may not retreat into the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 27.1467em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >space from which the enemy entered. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 28.3469em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >the active power lost the battle, the space chosen must be the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 29.2969em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >space from which this formation entered the battle. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.165em">
            <span class="stl_198 stl_08 stl_33" style="word-spacing: -0.0333em"
              >15. Siege &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.6629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >Land units in a fortified space are placed under siege if they
              with</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.6129em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0308em"
              >draw into fortifications during enemy movement (13.4) or after a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.5629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0689em"
              >field battle (14.1) and enemy land units in that space outnumber
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.5129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >them. The land units under siege may not move, attack, intercept,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.4629em; z-index: 4080"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0909em"
              >or avoid battle until the siege is broken (15.3). </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">(Howeve</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_194">r</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.101em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">n</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13">aval &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.4129em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.015em"
              >units in a port under siege may move.) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.015em"
              >Note that it is possible for &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.3629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.022em"
              >a fortified space to be under siege by two powers at once if
              those &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.3129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0131em"
              >powers are allies, both are at war with the power that controls
              this &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.2629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >fortified space, and each power possesses more units in the space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.2129em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >than the power inside the fortifications. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.1935em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.015em"
              >9. Capture Leaders: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.013em"
              >If one or more leaders are present on a side &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_205" style="word-spacing: -0.0595em"
              >that is completely eliminated, they are captured by the enemy.
              Place &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0107em"
              >the captured leaders in the dungeon on the winning player’s card.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.0435em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0256em"
              >That player also scores 1 VP if this is the first leader captured
              by &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.9935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >him in the game (even if he is an independent leader). Captured
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.9435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >leaders may be recovered in the Diplomacy Phase of an upcoming
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.8935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0419em"
              >turn (9.0). Guanche leader Bencomo, Maximilian and mercenary
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.8435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_231" style="word-spacing: -0.0623em"
              >leader Cesare Borgia if captured are simply removed from the
              board. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.7935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0481em"
              >If the eliminated side is a formation of a player against a
              formation &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.7435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0494em"
              >of Independents, place the player’s leader on the Turn Track and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.6935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >he will return next turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.9497em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >15.1 Assault &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.5295em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0373em"
              >A besieging power may spend 1 CP on the Assault Fortified Space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.4795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1059em"
              >action in an attempt to gain control of the space, but not in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.4295em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.008em"
              >same impulse in which the space was first put under siege by that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.3795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0698em"
              >power. A space may only be subjected to one assault in a single
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.3295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0921em"
              >impulse (</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0919em"
              >Exception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0918em"
              >See 20.4 for the Beltranejos units after the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.2795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >Peace o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_365">f</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >lcaçovas), though a power may initiate multiple assaults
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.2295em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0246em"
              >in different spaces in the same impulse. Assaults are conducted
              by &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.1795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0179em"
              >a single formation of units and army leaders in the same space as
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.1295em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >the fortification. Requirements for a</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_200">n</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84">A</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >ssault action are as follows: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 49.06em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0976em"
              >10. Conduct Retreats: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1009em"
              >The units of the losing power retreat as &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 50.0099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >described in 14.1 (unless they were all eliminated). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.3764em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.1259em"
              >11. Check for Siege: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1239em"
              >If the battle occurred in a fortified space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.3264em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0171em"
              >and the active player won, check to see if the active formation
              has &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.2764em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0511em"
              >more units than the losing player has inside the fortifications.
              If so, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.2264em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0091em"
              >this space is now under siege (15.0). If not, the active player
              must &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.1764em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0229em"
              >retreat his force as specified in Section 15.3, Breaking a Siege.
              If &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.1264em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >it was a relief force, see 15.2. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.4167em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_44">Requirements: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 55.6629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_111" style="word-spacing: 0.1348em"
              >• Units controlled by the active power must have placed the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 56.6129em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >space under siege during a previous impulse. Fortified spaces
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 57.5629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.009em"
              >that are empty also have to be put under siege in one impulse
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 58.5129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0429em"
              >before they can be assaulted in a later impulse. (</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13">Exceptions: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 59.4629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.021em"
              >Guanches, Beltranejo units after the Peace of Alcaçovas, and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 60.4129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0031em"
              >Maximilian’s forces, see Section 20.4 and 21.8) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_25" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">26 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >assaulting power has an LOC to the space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.048em"
              >7. Roll Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >Both players roll their dice and add up the number &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0719em"
              >of hits they have scored. Each roll of a “5” or “6” is considered
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >to be a hit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 5.5436em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1274em"
              >• The power that controls the fortified space does not have a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 6.4936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >naval unit in an adjacent Sea Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.6099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Rolls of a “4” </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >by the defender </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >may be a hit in these situations: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 7.6938em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_335" style="word-spacing: 0.2579em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.071em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_335" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >the power controlling the fortified space has naval squadron(s)
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 8.6438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >in that space there is a greater number of naval squadrons from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 9.5938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >the assaulting power in adjacent Sea Zone(s). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 8.81em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.039em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0441em"
              >the defender rolled two dice from regulars or from being the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 9.76em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.003em"
              >defender, the first die roll of “4” is a hit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 10.794em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_203" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Corsairs are always ignored for the purposes of these last two
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 11.744em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >requirements (naval blockade). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 10.9602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.052em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.057em"
              >the defender rolled four or more dice from these sources, the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 11.9102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >second die roll of “4” is also a hit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.1104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_182" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >The response cards </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_304">M</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_170"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >aster of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_304">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_364">ieg</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_367">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_304">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_368" style="word-spacing: -0.045em"
              >rtillery </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >and/or </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_308">L</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_182">eadership &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.0604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >may be used at this time to modify the combat results.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.0306em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_25" style="word-spacing: 0.0043em"
              >Assault Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.2768em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0545em"
              >1. Declare Formation: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0588em"
              >The active player declares which forma- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.2268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0136em"
              >tion of land units and army leaders will be making the assault.
              All &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.1768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >requirements listed above must be met at this time. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.4268em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.022em"
              >8. </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_252">T</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0044em"
              >ke Casualties: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >Each side eliminates one land unit from their &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0211em"
              >stack of units in the space for each hit scored by the opposing
              side &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.3268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0568em"
              >(cavalry and artillery units may be taken as losses). If
              defending &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.2768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >units (does not apply to the attacking formation) are composed of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.2268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0609em"
              >units from more than one allied power, losses must be as evenly
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.1768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >split as possible. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.5432em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0824em"
              >2. Play Response Cards: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0819em"
              >Other players may play the Response &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.4932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0052em"
              >card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_154">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0117em"
              >orrential </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0128em"
              >ains </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0054em"
              >to disrupt this Assault action. Any player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.4432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >in Impulse Order may play a response card such as </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_67">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0624em"
              >obles </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_171">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_56">eturn &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.3932em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: 0.0669em"
              >ome </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.068em"
              >or </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_275" style="word-spacing: 0.0837em"
              >ercenary </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.068em"
              >ilitias </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0679em"
              >to change the number of units in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.3432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >the space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.5432em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0078em"
              >9. Successful Assault: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0259em"
              >If the attacker scored at least 1 hit, no de- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.4932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0422em"
              >fending land units remain in the space, and at least 1 attacking
              unit &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.4432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0589em"
              >survived the battle, the assault is successful. The attacker
              gains po- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.3932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0526em"
              >litical control of the space. All besieged army leaders are
              captured. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.3432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0866em"
              >Place a captured leader in the dungeon of the opponent’s power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.2932em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >card. The opponent scores 1 VP if this is their first leader
              captured &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.2432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0088em"
              >in the game. Captured leaders can be recovered in the Diplomacy
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.1932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >Phase of an upcoming turn (9.0). If the Guanche leader Bencomo,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.1432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0637em"
              >Maximilian or the mercenary leader Cesare Borgia are captured,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.0932em; z-index: 3626"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: -0.0108em"
              >remove them from the board. If a leader is captured fighting a
              for</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: -0.0108em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.0432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0125em"
              >mation of Independent units, place the player’s leader on the
              Turn &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.9932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0144em"
              >Track; he will return next turn. If the defender has naval units
              or a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.9432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0204em"
              >naval leader in the space, place them on the next turn of the
              Turn &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.8932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0496em"
              >Track. In a future turn, the leader will reenter play and the
              naval &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.8432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >units may be rebuilt. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.7096em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18">3</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_369">.</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_37">A</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_37" style="word-spacing: -0.0618em"
              >dd U</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_166">p</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_37">A</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_259" style="word-spacing: -0.0618em"
              >ttacker’s Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >The active player is always considered &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.6596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0177em"
              >the attacker in an assault. The attacker adds up the number of
              dice &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.6096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >he will roll as follows: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.976em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >If it is against a fortified space with no defending land units:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 27.1762em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.053em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >die for each infantry unit in the assaulting formation (cavalry
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 28.1262em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0411em"
              >units are ignored, although there is a possibility of
              irreversible &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 29.0762em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >dismount by the cavalry units at this time). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 30.2764em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 2</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >dice for each siege artillery unit (Aragon and France only).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 31.4765em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.053em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >die for each Battle Rating point from the highest-rated leader
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 32.4265em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in the assaulting force. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.793em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1129em"
              >If against a fortified space with 1 or more defending land units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.743em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >(even if all units are cavalry): &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 35.9431em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.048em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >die for every two infantry units in the assaulting formation
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 36.8931em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: -0.025em"
              >(cavalry units are ignored, although there is a possibility of
              ir- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 37.8431em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >reversible dismount by the cavalry units at this time), rounding
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 38.7931em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">up. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.2096em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0398em"
              >10. Unsuccessful Assault: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0578em"
              >If no attacking land units remain, the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.1596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0519em"
              >attacker did not score at least one hit, or any besieged land
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.1096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >remain, the assault is unsuccessful. If the number of besieging
              land &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.0596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0629em"
              >units still exceeds the number of defending land units, the space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.0096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >remains under siege. If not, the attacking force must retreat as
              de- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.9596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >scribed in 15.3. If all attacking land units are eliminated,
              surviving &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.9096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >attacking army leaders are displaced (12.5). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 39.9933em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >die for each siege artillery unit (Aragon and France only).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 41.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.053em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >die for each Battle Rating point from the highest-rated leader
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 42.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in the assaulting force. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0628em"
              >If, earlier in the impulse, units and leaders joined a stack of
              that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.226em; z-index: 4356"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.0321em"
              >power’s units already besieging a fortified space, those newly
              ar</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.0321em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.176em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0678em"
              >rived units and leaders may participate in the assault and can be
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.126em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0616em"
              >included in the calculation in Step 3 (provided that the full
              comple- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.076em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >ment of attacking forces used can fit within a single formation).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.5099em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0391em"
              >4. Add Up Defender’s Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0509em"
              >The player controlling the space is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.4599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.062em"
              >always considered the defender in an assault. The defender adds
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.4099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >up the number of dice he will roll as follows: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 46.61em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.101em"
              >• 1 die for each defending infantry unit in the space (artillery
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 47.56em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0729em"
              >and cavalry units are ignored, although there is a possibility
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 48.51em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >of irreversible dismount by the cavalry units at this time).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.8136em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_145" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >15.2 Relief Forces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 49.7102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.053em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >die for each Battle Rating point from the highest-rated leader
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 50.6602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in the defending stack. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.3934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0718em"
              >A formation friendly to the units in the fortification may enter
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.3434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >fortified space under siege and initiate a field battle in an
              attempt to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0616em"
              >break the siege. In this relief force situation, units and army
              leaders &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.2434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0511em"
              >inside the fortification that are controlled by the same major
              power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.1934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0182em"
              >as the relief force may participate in the field battle. These
              forces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.1434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >inside the fortification may participate even if the total number
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.0934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0609em"
              >of units now exceeds the allowable formation size (based on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.0434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >leaders present in that space). The player may choose to withhold
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.9934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0241em"
              >units that started the impulse within the fortification from the
              field &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.9434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >battle if he does not want to risk losing them. In relief force
              situ- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.8934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0399em"
              >ations, the requirements to take half of your losses from
              regulars &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 51.8604em; z-index: 2045"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: 0.0061em"
              >die for being the defender. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.2268em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0236em"
              >5. Attacker Declares Combat Cards: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0408em"
              >The attacker declares any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.1768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Combat cards he wants to play as events to affect the assault.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.5432em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0348em"
              >6. Defender Declares Combat Cards: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0292em"
              >The defender declares any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.4932em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0759em"
              >Combat cards he wants to play as events to affect the assault. If
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 57.4432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0288em"
              >more than one player is controlling defending units in this
              space, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 58.3932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >each of these players may play Combat cards. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_26" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">27 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0609em"
              >and cavalry and to distribute your losses between powers do not
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0037em"
              >have to be met (14.0, Step 8). </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_321">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.009em"
              >u are free to distribute the losses &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0266em"
              >as you see fit between the besieged and the relief forces. There
              are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >three possible results in this relief force situation:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_321">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0449em"
              >u can also send naval escort squadrons to previously explored
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Ocean Zones to defend settlements. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.0302em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_67" style="word-spacing: -0.0016em"
              >16.1 Naval Movement and Escorts &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 8.3936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_188" style="word-spacing: 0.2539em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.068em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >the active player wins the resulting battle, the besieging forces
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 9.3436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >retreat and the siege is broken. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.6101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_371">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171">p</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_52" style="word-spacing: -0.0616em"
              >layer moves naval units with the Naval Move action (1 CP). Un-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.5601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >like land movement (where a Move action allows just one formation
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.5101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0625em"
              >to move), the Naval Move action allows </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >all </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >naval units and Naos of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.4601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >a single Major Power (and their activated Minor Power allies and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.4101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0039em"
              >any lent fleets) to perform a move, wherever they are on the map.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.3601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0649em"
              >Naval units on the Main Map and Naos on the Exploration Map
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0186em"
              >may each move based on the expenditure of the same CP (except
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.2601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >escorting squadrons which never move from the Ocean Zone where
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.2101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0417em"
              >they are located). As per Section 5.4, the naval units of Castile
              and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.1601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: -0.0296em"
              >Aragon move and fight as a united Spanish navy, so a Naval Move
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.1101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0392em"
              >by Spain allows all naval units that player controls to move. The
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.0601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0229em"
              >Muslim and French players however do have to specify which of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.0101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1068em"
              >their two Major Powers is moving each time they undertaken a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.9601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.016em"
              >naval move (</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >Exception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0158em"
              >On Turn 1 the Catalan and French navies &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.9101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >are considered to be a single force, like Spain above). Muslim
              Naos &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.8601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >move when a Naval Move is initiated for the Nort</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_372">h</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_193">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235">frica</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_372">n</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_193">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235">lliance. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 10.5438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.2439em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.064em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >the active player loses the battle but the number of hits scored
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 11.4938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0012em"
              >by both sides is equal, the active player may choose to retreat
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 12.4438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0928em"
              >any units or army leaders that participated in the battle into
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 13.3938em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0809em"
              >the fortifications (including units that were part of the relief
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 14.3438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0039em"
              >force that entered the space). The total number of units inside
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 15.2938em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0486em"
              >the fortification may never exceed four after such a retreat. All
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 16.2438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0498em"
              >other attacking units, including any desired units that started
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 17.1938em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0401em"
              >the impulse inside the fortification, retreat as per Section
              14.1. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 18.394em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.036em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >the active player loses the battle and the number of hits he
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 19.344em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >scored was less than his opponent, units and leaders that started
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 20.294em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0681em"
              >the impulse inside the fortification must retreat back inside.
              All &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 21.244em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >other attacking units retreat as per Section 14.1. If all
              attacking &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 22.194em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0678em"
              >units in the relief force were eliminated, any attacking army
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 23.144em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >leaders in the relief force are captured and there is no retreat.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.2266em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >Naval movement into Sea Zones (but not Ocean Zones) may trig-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.1766em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0502em"
              >ger interception attempts by enemy naval units. Enemy naval units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.1266em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0089em"
              >in Sea Zones are also allowed to try to avoid battle in response
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.0766em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >Naval Move actions. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.8802em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_28" style="word-spacing: -0.0007em"
              >15.3 Breaking a Siege &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.4601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1193em"
              >A siege is broken immediately if the besieging stack no longer
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.4101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0258em"
              >contains more land units than are in the fortification (cavalry
              and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.3601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0228em"
              >artillery units are included in these counts). This may occur if
              part &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0529em"
              >of the besieging force leaves the space as part of a Move action,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.2601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.075em"
              >a successful interception, or a successful avoid battle attempt.
              It &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.2101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >may also occur if the besieging stack takes severe losses during
              an &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.1601em; z-index: 1535"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0352em"
              >assault or battle against a relief force, or due to an Event card
              play. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.1101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >When the siege is broken, the stack must retreat to any adjacent
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.0601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0729em"
              >space that meets the following restrictions. This retreat does
              not &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.0101em; z-index: 1655"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.031em"
              >cost any C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.021em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">I</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0311em"
              >f no such legal space exists, all units in that stack are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.9601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >eliminated; any army leaders present are captured. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >All naval movements are to an </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >adjacent </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >location. Ports are adjacent &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.393em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >to one or two Sea Zones, as marked with the anchor symbol. Sea
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.343em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0308em"
              >Zones are adjacent to all ports with symbols in their zone and
              all &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.293em; z-index: 3877"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0041em"
              >Sea Zones that share a common Sea Zone boundary. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 32.8765em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.08em"
              >NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.0629em"
              >The Sea Zone </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >Cabo Bojador </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >borders the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.0628em"
              >Canary Islands &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 33.8265em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Sea Zone normally despite the Canary Islands appearing in a box
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 34.7765em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >extending the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Main Map</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.6518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0394em"
              >Only Naos can move between Ocean Zones. Ocean Zones and Sea
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.6018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0368em"
              >Zones are never adjacent. Ocean Zones are adjacent to all Ocean
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.5518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0263em"
              >Zones with which they share a common boundary. Ocean Zone 1
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.5018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >is also adjacent to the Built Naos Box. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.2472em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_128">Restrictions: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 38.4934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0778em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0729em"
              >may not retreat into a space in unrest, with Plague, or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 39.4434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1179em"
              >a space containing units that are not from (or allied to) the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 40.3934em; z-index: 1876"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0077em"
              >retreating power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.8682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0724em"
              >On Turns 1 and 2, only Portugal can possess Naos and they can
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.8182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.074em"
              >move them to the Ocean Zone corresponding to the current turn
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.7682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.0556em"
              >number (to Zone 1 on Turn 1; to Zone 2 on Turn 2). During this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.7182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0012em"
              >time, Portugal may only found settlements on spaces printed with
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.6682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.1012em"
              >the color of their home power. If the event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: 0.0961em"
              >chool of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_131">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">agres</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.6182em; z-index: 4452"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_188" style="word-spacing: 0.087em"
              >enry the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_189">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">v</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ig</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_141">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">or</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0648em"
              >, is played, Portugal may enter any of the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.5682em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_268" style="word-spacing: -0.0619em"
              >first three </span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_272">z</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >ones and may found settlements there without restriction.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.5182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0084em"
              >Starting with Turn 3, Ocean Zones 1, 2, and 3 can be explored by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.4682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0477em"
              >any power; Ocean Zones 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, A, and B can only be
              crossed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.4182em; z-index: 4684"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1em"
              >when the mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0808em"
              >verseas </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">V</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191">o</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_192">y</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.1005em"
              >ges </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0998em"
              >has been played. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.3682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.1089em"
              >To remind players of this restriction, the area containing Ocean
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.3182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >Zones 1, 2, and 3 is highlighted with a red border. All
              settlements &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.2682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >are considered to be adjacent to the Ocean Zone contained in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.2182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >same Exploration Map box. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 41.5936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0048em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >may not retreat into a Sea Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 42.7938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1328em"
              >• Units may not retreat into an independent space or a space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 43.7438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0392em"
              >controlled by another power unless that power is an ally of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 44.6938em; z-index: 2025"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0077em"
              >retreating power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.5622em">
            <span class="stl_198 stl_08 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0132em"
              >16. Naval Aﬀairs &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 49.0601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Naval units move, fight, intercept, and avoid battle in the Sea
              Zones &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 50.0101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >and ports of the map, much as land units do in the spaces of the
              map. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 50.9601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Naval units also provide a transport capability that allows land
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.9101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0418em"
              >to traverse Sea Zones (as long as that movement takes place in a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.8601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0289em"
              >single impulse). Naval units can also initiate piracy in Sea
              Zones &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.8101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.114em"
              >against enemy ports (or against any port in the case of Muslim
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.7601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0251em"
              >corsairs and France´s naval units with Casanove leader). Naos use
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.7101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0729em"
              >naval movement to traverse the Ocean Zones of the Exploration
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.6601em; z-index: 2539"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_302" style="word-spacing: -0.0596em"
              >Map attempting to explore, to found settlements, or to initiate
              piracy. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.5846em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.046em"
              >Naval units of two different powers that are not at war may
              occupy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.5346em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0159em"
              >the same Sea Zone after a move. (Naos and naval squadrons may
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.4846em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0251em"
              >occupy the same Ocean Zone even if their two powers are at war).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.4346em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0151em"
              >Interception attempts, avoid battle attempts, and naval combat
              are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.3846em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0139em"
              >only triggered against enemy naval units in the Main Map. Naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.3346em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >movements must comply with the following restrictions:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_27" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">28 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0148em"
              >4. Conduct interceptions: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0129em"
              >Stacks of naval units that are oriented &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1068em"
              >vertically on the main map may be intercepted by enemy naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0442em"
              >units in an adjacent location. If multiple enemy stacks are
              adjacent &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0151em"
              >to the destination space, one or more naval units (owning
              player´s &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >choice) from each stack may attempt to intercept as a single
              stack. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0969em"
              >Each such attempt is resolved separately and the owning player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.0435em; z-index: 2950"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0241em"
              >chooses the order of those attempts. If multiple stacks from
              diffe</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_313">r</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_313">- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.9935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0081em"
              >ent enemy players all want to intercept, resolve intercept
              attempts &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.9435em; z-index: 3023"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_28" style="word-spacing: 0.0092em"
              >in Impulse Order. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_128">Restrictions: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Naval</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0129em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >units must always move to an adjacent location. Move-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: 0.1195em"
              >ment between the Alboran Sea and the Gulf of Cadiz and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 7.4237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_86" style="word-spacing: 0.1258em"
              >between the Tyrrhenian Sea and Central Mediterranean are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 8.3737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0151em"
              >only possible if the appropriate condition listed in Section 2.4
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 9.3237em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.022em"
              >(Sea Zones) for control of a specific space or permission from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 10.2737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >an ally are met. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 11.4739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_277" style="word-spacing: 0.2558em"
              >• Naval</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0689em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >units may only move to ports controlled by another player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 12.4239em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0229em"
              >if enemy naval units are present in that port. (This restriction
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 13.3739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0231em"
              >prohibits naval moves into a port controlled by a major power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 14.3239em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_241">ally.) &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.2306em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_128">Restrictions: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 14.4768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Once</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0078em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0131em"
              >one power succeeds, no other power may attempt an in-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 15.4268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >terception (even if that other power is an ally of the
              intercepting &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 16.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">power). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 15.524em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Naval</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0511em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0459em"
              >leaders must be in the same stack as a naval unit con-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 16.474em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >trolled by the same power whenever possible (and never on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 17.424em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0828em"
              >Exploration Map). Naval leaders may accompany any naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 18.374em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.029em"
              >unit that is moving from the naval leader´s port or Sea Zone.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 19.3241em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0437em"
              >If naval movement is going to empty the naval leader´s port or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 20.2741em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >Sea Zone, then that naval leader must accompany one of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 21.2241em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >naval units that is leaving. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 17.5769em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.2397em"
              >• Interception</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >may not be attempted by naval unit(s) in a location &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 18.527em; z-index: 3247"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.003em"
              >that now contains naval units from the active power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 19.7271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Interception</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0551em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0601em"
              >may not be attempted into a destination space that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 20.6771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_52" style="word-spacing: -0.0616em"
              >contains one or more enemy naval units hostile to the intercept-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 21.6271em; z-index: 3393"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.0043em"
              >ing power that are still oriented normally. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 22.4242em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.2322em"
              >• No</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0422em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >naval unit may participate in a Naval Move if it was part
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 23.3742em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >of a stack of naval units that lost a naval combat earlier in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 24.3242em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">impulse. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 22.9935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >The intercepting power rolls two dice and adds the Battle Rating
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 23.9435em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >the best naval leader present to the dice sum. A modified result
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 24.8935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >9 or greater indicates success. If successful, the intercepting
              naval &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2501em; top: 25.8435em; z-index: 3621"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.1016em"
              >units are placed in the destination space and oriented
              vertically. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 26.7935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >All stacks that successfully intercept are combined into a single
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 27.7435em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >stack (and will fight as a combined force in the naval combat, in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 28.6935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Step 9 below). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 25.5244em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0342em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0091em"
              >single player may never have more than TWO Naos on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 26.4744em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1079em"
              >Exploration Map, although he may have any number in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 27.4244em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0343em"
              >Built Naos box from Turn 3 onwards (Portugal has exceptions
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 28.3744em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0245em"
              >to this during Turns 1 and 2 or when the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: 0.0221em"
              >chool of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">agres</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 29.3244em; z-index: 1156"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_188" style="word-spacing: 0.022em"
              >enry the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_189">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">v</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ig</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_141">t</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0006em"
              >or </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >event has been played as above). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 30.06em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_265" style="word-spacing: 0.1164em"
              >5. Play Response cards to interception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1148em"
              >Any player may play &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 31.01em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0961em"
              >the response card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0959em"
              >ea </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191" style="word-spacing: 0.0946em"
              >og </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.096em"
              >to cancel the successful interception &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 31.96em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0188em"
              >roll. No further interception attempts may be made into that zone
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 32.91em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >this impulse. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.6108em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_107" style="word-spacing: 0.0038em"
              >Naval Movement Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.857em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0496em"
              >1. Declare Naval Move: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >The active power declares which naval &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.807em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0461em"
              >units and leaders will be moving and designates the destination
              for &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.757em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0071em"
              >each of these units. Each unit´s destination must be adjacent to
              its &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.707em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >current location. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 34.2764em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_68" style="word-spacing: 0.0727em"
              >6. Conduct Avoid Battle: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0779em"
              >Enemy naval units in Sea Zones (not &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 35.2264em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0539em"
              >ports) may try to avoid battle if both of these conditions are
              met &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 36.1764em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.051em"
              >(these conditions represent a Sea Zone entered by the active
              power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 37.1264em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in Step 2 in which no intercept occurred in Step 4): &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.0734em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_360" style="word-spacing: 0.1208em"
              >2. Execute Naval Move: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_161" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >The active power executes all naval &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.0234em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0653em"
              >moves. The order of execution is not important as all moves are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.9734em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0859em"
              >considered simultaneous. Stack the newly arriving unit(s) in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.9234em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >destination port, Sea Zone, Ocean Zone, or settlement as follows:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.9167em; top: 38.3265em; z-index: 4154"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• All</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0052em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.0043em"
              >enemy naval units are oriented normally. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.9167em; top: 39.5267em; z-index: 4206"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0032em"
              >naval units of the active power are oriented vertically.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 40.1236em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0561em"
              >arriving in a port: the arriving naval unit(s) are placed below
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 41.0736em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_111" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >any land units and army leaders and are oriented normally
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 42.0236em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">(horizontally). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 40.8931em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0346em"
              >Resolve avoid battle attempts in Impulse Order. The enemy power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 41.8431em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >attempting to avoid battle designates an adjacent location into
              which &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 42.7931em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0321em"
              >the naval units will try to move. Adjacent ports must be
              controlled &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 43.7431em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0171em"
              >by the power avoiding battle; adjacent Sea Zones may not contain
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 44.6931em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0809em"
              >units from a power at war with any of the units avoiding battle.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 45.6431em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0359em"
              >All of this power´s naval units in the Sea Zone must avoid battle
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 46.5931em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.1057em"
              >together. The power avoiding battle rolls two dice and adds the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 47.5431em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0759em"
              >Battle Rating of any naval leader present to the dice sum. If the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 48.4931em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.0087em"
              >modified roll is 9 or more, the Avoid Battle Attempt is
              successful. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 49.4431em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >If successful, the units are placed in the chosen adjacent
              location. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 43.2238em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
