            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0028em"
              >squadrons, each remaining hit eliminates one corsair. Odd hits
              re- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.6263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >maining against the losing side eliminate one extra naval
              squadron; &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.5763em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0531em"
              >odd hits remaining against the winner are ignored. If both sides
              are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.5263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >completely eliminated, the side that rolled the most dice retains
              one &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.4763em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0231em"
              >unit. If both sides are eliminated and the two sides rolled the
              same &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.4263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >number of dice, the defender retains one unit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.7268em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0093em"
              >1. Declare Escort Move: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0081em"
              >The active player declares which single &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >naval unit that he controls on the Main Map will be moving and
              des- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.6268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0131em"
              >ignates a previously explored Ocean Zone as the destination. This
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.5768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >destination zone can be any explored zone regardless of distance.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.9432em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0067em"
              >2. Execute Escort Move: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0119em"
              >The active player places the unit in the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.8932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_137" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >destination Ocean Zone. No Navigation Check is required and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.8432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >interception is not possible. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.7927em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0282em"
              >9. One Power Retreats: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >If the combat occurred in a port, the at- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.7427em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0259em"
              >tacker retreats to a Sea Zone connected to that port that is free
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.6927em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >enemy naval units. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.0433em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Escorts may also travel to Ocean Zones during Spring Deployment
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.9933em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >(10.0) or with the Build Naval Escort action (17.3). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 24.2757em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.077em"
              >NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0948em"
              >The attacker retreats regardless of whether or not he
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 25.2257em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >won the battle. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.6469em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_62" style="word-spacing: 0.0017em"
              >16.2 Naval Combat &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.2268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.004em"
              >Naval combat occurs due to a Naval Move action into a Sea Zone
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.1768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0229em"
              >or port occupied by enemy naval units or because of a successful
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.1268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0248em"
              >interception. Each player involved adds up their combat dice and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.0768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0598em"
              >rolls to see how many hits they score. Hits may cause casualties
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.0268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0806em"
              >on the opponent. The side with the most hits is the victor. After
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.9768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the combat, one side´s units must retreat to an adjacent
              location. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.8851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >If the combat occurred in a Sea Zone, the loser retreats to an
              adjacent &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.8351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0521em"
              >port under its control or an adjacent Sea Zone (free of enemy
              naval &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.7851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >units). If no such location exists, the naval units are
              eliminated. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.1515em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0097em"
              >10. Place Units on </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_252">T</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_378" style="word-spacing: 0.0265em"
              >urn Track: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0149em"
              >If one or more naval leaders are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.1015em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0121em"
              >present on a side that is completely eliminated, they are placed
              on &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.0515em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0116em"
              >the next turn of the Turn Track. All naval units lost in the
              combat &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.0015em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0209em"
              >are also placed there. In a future turn, the leader will reenter
              play &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.9515em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >and the naval units may be rebuilt (8.1). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.1806em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_210" style="word-spacing: 0.0047em"
              >Naval Combat Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.4268em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.115em"
              >1. Attacke</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_303">r</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0661em"
              >dds Up Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0612em"
              >The active player is always considered &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0356em"
              >the attacker in a naval combat. The attacker adds up the number
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.3268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >dice he will roll as follows: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.6886em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_379" style="word-spacing: -0.0132em"
              >16.3 Naval Transport &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 36.4438em; z-index: 1486"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0078em"
              >die for each corsair. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.2684em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >If a power has naval squadrons or corsairs in one or more
              adjacent &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.2184em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >Sea Zones, it may make a special move of land units across those
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.1684em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_161" style="word-spacing: 0.1223em"
              >Sea Zones. This special move is called </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_360" style="word-spacing: 0.1252em"
              >naval transport </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_161" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >and is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.1184em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >considered a special case of the Move Formation in Clear action.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 37.644em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 2</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >dice for each naval squadron &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 38.8442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >die for each Battle Rating point from their highest-rated naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 39.7942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >leader in the Sea Zone or port. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.1606em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0172em"
              >2. Defender Adds Up Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >The intercepting player or the player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.1106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0929em"
              >with the stack of units that began the Naval Move action in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.0606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0518em"
              >destination location is always considered the defender in a naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.0106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">combat: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.4056em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_267" style="word-spacing: -0.0124em"
              >Naval Transport Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.6518em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >1. Spend CP and Move: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.044em"
              >The active power must have at least 2 CP &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.6018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >remaining to spend in the curren</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_380">t</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_37">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >ction Phase. If so, a formation of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.5518em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0071em"
              >five or fewer land units (plus army leaders) in a port may move
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.5018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >an adjacent Sea Zone containing naval units controlled by the
              active &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.4518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0071em"
              >power. Artillery and cavalry units are always counted against
              this &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.4018em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.004em"
              >limit of five units. This move costs 1 CP and is considered to be
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.3518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0121em"
              >Move Formation in Clear action. Units moving by naval transport
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.3018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0461em"
              >may not be intercepted at sea. Other players may play the
              response &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.2518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1048em"
              >card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_381">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1237em"
              >orrential </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_227">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_227" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >ains </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1029em"
              >to disrupt naval transport. A formation &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.2018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >under siege may not be moved by naval transport. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 45.1276em; z-index: 1780"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0078em"
              >die for each corsair. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 46.3278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 2</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >dice for each naval squadron &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 47.5279em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >die for each Battle Rating point from their highest-rated naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 48.478em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >leader in the Sea Zone or port. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 49.6781em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.033em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.025em"
              >die for being the defender, but only if this combat is taking
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 50.6281em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >place in a port (21.8 Ragusa) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.9945em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.025em"
              >3. Attacker Declares Combat Cards: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0378em"
              >The attacker declares any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.5682em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_146" style="word-spacing: 0.1285em"
              >2. Multi-zone Transport: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_276" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >The active power then continues to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.5182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.014em"
              >move the formation to an adjacent Sea Zone or port at the cost of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.4682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0689em"
              >1 CP for each such move. Moves from one Sea Zone to another
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.4182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0919em"
              >are permitted as long as the power has a naval unit in each Sea
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.3682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0938em"
              >Zone and enough CP to get the formation back to a port before
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.3182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0146em"
              >the impulse is over. Formations may never end an impulse at sea.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.2682em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_321">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.019em"
              >u must end a naval transport with one formation before starting
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.2182em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >another one later in the impulse. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.9445em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Combat cards they want to play as events to affect the combat.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.3109em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0334em"
              >4. Defender Declares Combat Cards: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0312em"
              >The defender declares any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.2609em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Combat cards they want to play as events to affect the combat.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.6274em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0683em"
              >5. Roll Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0688em"
              >Both players roll their dice. Each side adds up the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 57.5774em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1089em"
              >number of hits they have scored. Each roll of a “5” or a “6” is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 58.5274em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >considered to be a hit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_29" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">30 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0526em"
              >3. End in Port: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0529em"
              >Formations end their naval transport by moving &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0314em"
              >to a port adjacent to the last Sea Zone they entered. That port
              must &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >conform to the following restrictions: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2497em; top: 4.3429em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0391em"
              >Zones; do not include actions where Piracy markers are not placed
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2497em; top: 5.2929em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >per the exception above). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2497em; top: 6.6594em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.081em"
              >2. </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_313">T</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0633em"
              >rgeted Powe</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_383">r</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0737em"
              >dds Up Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0612em"
              >The targeted power adds up the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2497em; top: 7.6094em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >number of dice they will roll in defense. They receive:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 7.4436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >port may not contain any enemy naval units. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 8.6438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• It</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0508em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.056em"
              >must be a space into which the power could move using land
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 9.5938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.034em"
              >movement (i.e., it cannot be a port of a power that the active
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 10.5438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >power is neither allied with nor at war with). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9163em; top: 8.8095em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.1314em"
              >• 2 dice for each naval unit of the targeted power in the Sea
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5829em; top: 9.7595em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.046em"
              >Zone where piracy is occurring (only possible if the Muslim is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5829em; top: 10.7095em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0582em"
              >initiating piracy only with corsairs or the French has the leader
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5829em; top: 11.6595em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >Casenove with naval squadrons). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.9102em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_14" style="word-spacing: -0.0605em"
              >Treat this movement into the final space as if it were a Move
              action. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.8602em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0548em"
              >Enemy units may intercept, avoid battle, withdraw into
              fortifica</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0548em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.8102em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >tions, or stay and force a field battle. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9163em; top: 12.7766em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.029em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0198em"
              >die for each naval unit (other than a corsair) of the targeted
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5829em; top: 13.7266em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >power (or another power at war with the active power) in a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5829em; top: 14.6766em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0955em"
              >port (without a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.096em"
              >Plague </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0959em"
              >marker) or Sea Zone adjacent to the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5829em; top: 15.6266em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Sea Zone where piracy is occurring. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.1766em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: -0.0029em"
              >4. Naval Transport and Field Battles: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.005em"
              >If the active power losses &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.1266em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1139em"
              >a field battle in the port space at the end of naval transport,
              all &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.0766em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0208em"
              >transported units are eliminated and any army leaders present are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.0266em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">captured. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9163em; top: 16.7436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.1301em"
              >• 1 die for each fortress controlled by the targeted power (or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5829em; top: 17.6936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >another power at war with the active power) adjacent to the Sea
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5829em; top: 18.6436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0501em"
              >Zone where piracy is occurring. This fortress must be adjacent
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5829em; top: 19.5936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >to the zone where piracy is occurring and may not be in unrest
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5829em; top: 20.5436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >or under siege. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.3139em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_44" style="word-spacing: -0.0068em"
              >Special Naval Transport to the Canary Islands &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.5601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >Castile may undertake a special naval transport move that allows
              up &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.5101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0032em"
              >to five Castilian land units (and any leader) to move directly
              from &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.4601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.023em"
              >a controlled home port adjacent to the Gulf of Cadiz Sea Zone to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.4101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.067em"
              >a Castilian-controlled port space in the Canary Islands. The cost
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.3601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0076em"
              >of this action is 4 CP and no naval units need to be present for
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >move to take place. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.0417em; top: 21.959em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.075em"
              >NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0929em"
              >This die is for fortresses, not fortified spaces, so &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.0417em; top: 22.909em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >keys do not give you these dice. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 24.4018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.057em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >die if this is piracy by the Muslim and a unit from the Spanish
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 25.3518em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0119em"
              >Military Orders is in a port adjacent to the zone where piracy
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 26.3018em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >is occurring. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.6765em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0188em"
              >A single Castilian leader may move at no CP cost to one of these
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.6265em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Canary Island port spaces controlled from any Castilian home
              space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.5765em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0169em"
              >at the end of a Spanish impulse instead of extending that impulse
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.5265em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >with a resource. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 27.5851em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.057em"
              >3. Roll Dic</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_384">e</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0586em"
              >gainst Pirates: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0556em"
              >The targeted power rolls the number &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 28.5351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >of dice computed above. Each roll of “5” or a “6” is considered
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 29.4851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >be a hit. Hits are applied as follows: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9998em; top: 30.6852em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.165em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0551em"
              >If the Muslim initiated piracy with corsairs, start by eliminat-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.2636em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_228" style="word-spacing: -0.0044em"
              >16.4 Piracy on the Main Map &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9997em; top: 31.6352em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >ing one corsair for each hit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9998em; top: 32.7523em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.1093em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1029em"
              >If hits remain after Step (a), eliminate one naval squadron
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9997em; top: 33.7023em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0512em"
              >from the active power’s stack for every two hits scored (units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9997em; top: 34.6523em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >eliminated are chosen by active player). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.149em; top: 32.8434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >If a power has naval units in a Sea Zone, he may spend
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.145em; top: 33.7935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0501em"
              >2 CPs on the Initiate Piracy action and target any enemy
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.145em; top: 34.7434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >power that controls a port space adjacent to that Sea
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.145em; top: 35.6934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0361em"
              >Zone. In addition, if a Muslim power has corsairs or the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 36.6434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >French has the leader Casenove with naval squadrons in a Sea
              Zone, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 37.5934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >he may initiate piracy against a major power even if the two pow-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7503em; top: 38.5434em; z-index: 1549"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_45" style="word-spacing: 0.011em"
              >ers are not at war. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9998em; top: 35.7693em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.2207em"
              >c) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >If exactly one hit remains after step (b), eliminate one extra
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9997em; top: 36.7193em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >naval squadron (again chosen by active player). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 37.9195em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0735em"
              >4. Adds Up Piracy Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >If one or more naval units from the active &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 38.8695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >power remain in the Sea Zone after Step 3 (and at least one
              corsair &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 39.8195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0613em"
              >remains if targeting a non-enemy power), the active power will
              roll &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 40.7695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0012em"
              >for piracy. That power receives base dice as follows:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.8306em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_152" style="word-spacing: -0.0004em"
              >Main Map Piracy Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.0768em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.053em"
              >1. Declare Piracy: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0552em"
              >An active power declares that his naval units in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.0268em; z-index: 1655"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: -0.0624em"
              >a Sea Zone are initiating piracy. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_224">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">m</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >ajor power that controls one or &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.9768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.007em"
              >more port spaces connected to that Sea Zone must be specified as
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.9268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: -0.0587em"
              >the target for the piracy. Unless the Muslim is initiating piracy
              with &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.8768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_188" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >corsairs or the French has the leader Casenove with naval
              squadrons, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.8268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0204em"
              >the active and target powers must be at war. Each player may only
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.7768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0121em"
              >initiate piracy in a given Sea Zone once per turn; place one of
              this &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.7268em; z-index: 2004"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.0041em"
              >player’s piracy markers in this zone as a reminder. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9159em; top: 41.9697em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0176em"
              >1 die: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >if there is only one naval unit of the active power in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 42.9197em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >Sea Zone or only one port of the targeted power connected to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 43.8697em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >the zone &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9159em; top: 44.9867em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >2 dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">otherwise &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 46.1037em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0429em"
              >The active power then adds the Piracy rating of any naval leader
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 47.0537em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >present in the </span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >one to get the final number of dice. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 48.4202em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0386em"
              >5. Roll Piracy Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0438em"
              >The active player rolls this number of dice. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 49.3702em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0459em"
              >Each roll of a “5” or a “6” is considered to be a hit. For each
              hit &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2493em; top: 50.3202em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0442em"
              >scored, the targeted power must choose to do one of the
              following: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.125em; top: 49.2257em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_243" style="word-spacing: 0.1069em"
              >Exception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_385" style="word-spacing: 0.1423em"
              >Two events (</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_338">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: 0.1455em"
              >arbary </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_386">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_338">ir</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_387">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_338">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_243" style="word-spacing: 0.1145em"
              >es of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_122">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_338" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >lemcen </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_243">and &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.125em; top: 50.1757em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0171em"
              >lgiers </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131">egency</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0179em"
              >) allow the Muslim player to conduct piracy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.125em; top: 51.1257em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.0442em"
              >without placing a piracy marker in the target zone. Note that the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.125em; top: 52.0757em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0039em"
              >lgiers </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0035em"
              >egency </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >card has the additional property of allowing &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.125em; top: 53.0257em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >piracy in zones where a Muslim piracy marker is already present.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.125em; top: 53.9757em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0363em"
              >A single zone may only be targeted once during the execution
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.125em; top: 54.9257em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >of either event. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.999em; top: 51.5203em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.165em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >Eliminate a naval unit that they control in or adjacent to the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9989em; top: 52.4703em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0027em"
              >targeted Sea Zone, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.999em; top: 53.5874em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.1093em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >Allow the active power to draw at random and keep one card
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9989em; top: 54.5374em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.031em"
              >from his hand (it cannot be played until a future impulse; see
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9989em; top: 55.4874em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >6.3 if the player also has resources in his hand), &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.999em; top: 56.6044em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.2207em"
              >c) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_83">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">w</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: -0.0017em"
              >ard the active player 1 VP for piracy, or &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 56.6681em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Piracy markers are used to enforce these per turn piracy
              limits:</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.1201em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_167">each &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 57.6181em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >Sea Zone can be targeted for piracy by no more than two players
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 58.5681em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0028em"
              >per turn and each player is limited to three piracy actions per
              turn &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7498em; top: 59.5181em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >(spread across both his major powers and across all sea and Ocean
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.999em; top: 57.7214em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.1093em"
              >d) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_277" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >Remove one Spanish Military Order unit from the map if Spain
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9989em; top: 58.6714em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0531em"
              >was targeted and a unit from a Military Order was adjacent to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9989em; top: 59.6214em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >the Sea Zone where piracy occurred. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_30" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">31 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >The active player may not be awarded a card draw if no cards are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0741em"
              >left to be drawn from the target power’s hand. The target power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >must always try and award one of these four awards for each hit.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >Picking an award of no benefit to the active player is not
              permitted &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >if another selection is available. If more than one hit is scored
              on the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.0603em"
              >same piracy action, the target power must divide the hits as
              equally &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.0435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >as possible between valid awards (i.e., an award cannot be chosen
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.9935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >for a second time until all possible awards are granted at least
              once). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 2</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.018em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0078em"
              >dice if the Nao initiating piracy is not damaged and there is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.0322em"
              >more than one settlement controlled by the target player in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Ocean Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 7.6099em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0386em"
              >5. Roll Piracy Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0438em"
              >The active player rolls this number of dice. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 8.5599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0459em"
              >Each roll of a “5” or a “6” is considered to be a hit. For each
              hit &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 9.5099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0442em"
              >scored, the targeted player must choose to do one of the
              following: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 10.71em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2316em"
              >• Eliminate</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.009em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >a naval squadron in or adjacent to this Ocean Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 11.9102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Allow</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0432em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0481em"
              >the active player to draw at random and keep a resource
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 12.8602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0204em"
              >from one of the target player’s settlements in the Ocean Zone.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 13.8102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0519em"
              >If the target player rolled at least one die for the presence of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 14.7602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0019em"
              >a fortress in this Ocean Zone, the owner chooses the resource
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 15.7102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0198em"
              >from his available settlements (rather than being subjected to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 16.6602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >a random draw). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.2806em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_128">Restrictions: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 13.5268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.013em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0227em"
              >the piracy is by corsairs, record any VP scored on the Track
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 14.4768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0291em"
              >on the Muslim Player Card (until a maximum of 12 VP have
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 15.4268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >been recorded). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 16.627em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.037em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0481em"
              >piracy VP are earned by naval squadrons and/or Naos, place
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 17.577em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0058em"
              >a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0162em"
              >1 VP </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0223em"
              >piracy marker on your Player card for each VP earned.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 18.527em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0354em"
              >A player may earn a maximum of 6 VPs in this fashion. The
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 19.477em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0446em"
              >Muslim player may receive these VP in addition to those re-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 20.427em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >corded on his Player Card due to piracy by corsairs. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 17.8604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_83" style="word-spacing: 0.4142em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">w</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">ard</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0389em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.0333em"
              >the active player with 1 VP for Piracy. Place a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80">Piracy &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 18.8104em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.1098em"
              >VP </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1099em"
              >marker on the appropriate Player Card keeping in mind
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 19.7604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0339em"
              >that no player may obtain more than 6 Piracy VP from naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 20.7104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >squadrons and/or Naos. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 22.0768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_389" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >The active player may not be awarded a resource draw if no
              resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 23.0268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_62" style="word-spacing: -0.059em"
              >are owned by the target player in this Ocean Zone. The target
              power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 23.9768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.0288em"
              >must always try and award one of these three awards for each hit.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 24.9268em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0111em"
              >Picking an award of no benefit to the active player is not
              permitted &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 25.8768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >if another selection is available. If more than one hit is scored
              on the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 26.8268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_90" style="word-spacing: -0.0303em"
              >same piracy action, the target power must divide the hits as
              equally &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 27.7768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.0176em"
              >as possible between valid awards (i.e., an award cannot be chosen
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 28.7268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >for a second time until all possible awards are granted at least
              once). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.1636em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.0039em"
              >16.5 Piracy on the Exploration Map &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.7434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.097em"
              >If a power has a Nao in an Ocean Zone where one of the other
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.6934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0662em"
              >players owns a settlement, he may spend 2 CP on the Initiate
              Piracy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.6434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_265" style="word-spacing: 0.0014em"
              >action to target that settlement. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.9306em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_140" style="word-spacing: -0.001em"
              >Exploration Map Piracy Procedure: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.1768em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.085em"
              >1. Declare Piracy: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0828em"
              >An active player declares that his Nao in an &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.1268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Ocean Zone is initiating piracy against another player. The
              targeted &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.0768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0261em"
              >player must control a settlement adjacent to that Ocean Zone. One
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.0268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0541em"
              >of the Nao player’s powers does not need to be at war with a
              power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.9768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.0023em"
              >of the targeted player to initiate this piracy. The only
              restriction is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.9268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0171em"
              >that France cannot initiate piracy on the Exploration Map
              (against &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.8768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0859em"
              >any power) if France is at war with the North African Alliance.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.8268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0228em"
              >Each player may only initiate piracy in a given Ocean Zone once
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.7768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0292em"
              >per turn; place one of this player´s piracy markers in this </span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >one as a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.7268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0127em"
              >reminder. Piracy markers are used to enforce these per turn
              piracy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.1128em"
              >limits: each Ocean Zone can be targeted for piracy by no more
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.6268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0302em"
              >than two players per turn and each player is limited to three
              piracy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.5768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0438em"
              >actions per turn (spread across both his major powers and across
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.5268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >all sea and Ocean Zones). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 30.0932em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0634em"
              >6. Store Loot: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.0601em"
              >The resources earned in Step 5 are placed under- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 31.0432em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0094em"
              >neath the pirating Nao´s counter. Undamaged Naos can carry two
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 31.9932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >resources; damaged Naos only carry one. If after receiving
              resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 32.9432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0081em"
              >in step 5 (and combining them with any resources received by the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 33.8932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0518em"
              >Nao during earlier piracy attempts) the total number exceeds the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 34.8432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >storage capacity of the Nao, the owning player chooses which
              excess &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 35.7932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >resources are discarded. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 37.1596em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_227" style="word-spacing: 0.1197em"
              >7. Possible Return Home: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_227" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >The Nao can now choose to return &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 38.1096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >home immediately: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 39.3098em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.046em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: -0.0476em"
              >this option is chosen, add the Nao’s resources to the player’s
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 40.2598em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0518em"
              >warehouse (18.8) and place the Nao on the Turn Track to be
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 41.2098em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >available in future turns. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.8932em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.078em"
              >2. </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_252">T</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0603em"
              >rgeted Playe</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_303">r</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >dds Up Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0584em"
              >The target player computes the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.8432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >number of dice they will roll in defense: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 42.41em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >the Nao chooses to stay in the Ocean Zone, it must wait for
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 43.36em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.0953em"
              >a future piracy attempt or the Winter Phase to have another
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 44.31em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >opportunity to return home (or it may use naval movements to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 45.26em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0249em"
              >reach the Built Naos Box from Zone 1). In the latter case the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 46.21em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_11" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >Nao is only moved to the Turn Track if it is carrying a resource,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 47.16em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >otherwise it remains in that box for future use. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 44.0434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.033em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0238em"
              >die for each of the target power´s settlements in this Ocean
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 44.9934em; z-index: 1951"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Zone with a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0.0101em"
              >Fortress </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_218">marker. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 46.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.001em"
              >die for each naval squadron in the target Ocean Zone.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 47.3937em; z-index: 2014"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 2</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_140" style="word-spacing: 0.009em"
              >dice as defender. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 48.7601em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.057em"
              >3. Roll Dic</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_390">e</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >gainst Pirates: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_265" style="word-spacing: -0.0567em"
              >The targeted player rolls the number &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 49.7101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.0606em"
              >of dice computed above. Each roll of “5” or “6” is a hit. Two or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 50.6601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.097em"
              >more hits remove the pirating Nao from the game. One hit also
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.6101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0448em"
              >eliminates a Nao if it was damaged when piracy was initiated. If
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.5601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0121em"
              >one hit is scored against an undamaged Nao, flip its counter to
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.5101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Damaged side. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01 stl_75"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.8969em; z-index: 4646"
          >
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_201" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >16.6 Exploring the </span
            ><span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_391">T</span
            ><span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_18">e</span
            ><span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_152" style="word-spacing: -0.0154em"
              >rra Incognita, Founding &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01 stl_75"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.0969em; z-index: 4693"
          >
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_101" style="word-spacing: -0.0207em"
              >Settlements, and Cartography &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0765em"
              >Here at the start of the Age of Exploration, the powers of Tanto
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.6268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >Monta faced the challenge of navigating new coastlines and
              oceanic &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.5768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0601em"
              >waters, gradually mapping them out as they pushed further into
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.5268em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: -0.0557em"
              >unknown. To reflect this, all oceanic </span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0581em"
              >ones on the Exploration Map &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.4768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0091em"
              >are considered unexplored (Terra Incognita) and each player must
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.4268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.0118em"
              >attempt to explore them using the Terra Incognita Table whenever
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0429em"
              >they enter an unexplored zone with a Nao. In addition, you must
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.3268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >survive a Navigation Check whenever you attempt to cross a Haz-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.2768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >ardous Passage. Naos with higher crew ratings have a better
              chance &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 60.2268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >of success on these rolls. A Nao moving into an already-explored
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.8765em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0351em"
              >4. Nao Adds Up Piracy Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0262em"
              >If the Nao initiating piracy remains &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.8265em; z-index: 2401"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: -0.0592em"
              >in the Ocean Zone after Step 3, the active player will roll for
              piracy. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.7765em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >That player receives dice as follow: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 57.9767em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0452em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0032em"
              >number of dice equal to the Nao’s piracy (P) rating. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 59.1769em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• 1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >die if the Nao initiating piracy is damaged or there is only one
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 60.1269em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0007em"
              >settlement controlled by the target player in the Ocean Zone.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_31" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">32 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.057em"
              >Ocean Zone skips the Terra Incognita Table roll but is still
              required &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_276" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >to make a Navigation Check if they entered the zone across a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0339em"
              >Hazardous Passage. Follow the procedure listed below whenever
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >a Nao enters an Ocean Zone: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0886em"
              >4. Apply </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_252">T</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >rra Incognita Result: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >If a sunk or damaged result &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >occurs, apply the same effects listed for these results in step
              2. If &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >the damaged result does not sink the Nao, return it to the Ocean
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >Zone from which it started this move. If the Nao receives either
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.097em"
              >Successful Exploration </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0969em"
              >result, advance it to that zone and add a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0499em"
              >control marker from this power to this zone as a reminder that it
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.0435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >has been explored by that player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.4806em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_259" style="word-spacing: 0.0031em"
              >Ocean Naval Movement Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.7268em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0524em"
              >1. Check for Hazardous Passages: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0559em"
              >If the Nao moves through a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0509em"
              >Hazardous Passage arrow, it must survive one Navigation Check
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.6268em; z-index: 446"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0031em"
              >for each arrow it crosses. Repeat step 2 once for each such
              arrow. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 11.6257em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.006em"
              >NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0009em"
              >Use a North African control marker if this exploration
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.7083em; top: 12.5757em; z-index: 2370"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: 0.0068em"
              >was by the Muslim player. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.9932em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Exception: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >If a player controls five or more Canary Islands he skips
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.9432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >Navigation Checks for Naos traveling between Zone 1 and Zone
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.8932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0186em"
              >A (in either direction). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 14.2353em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.053em"
              >Place a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0524em"
              >1 VP Cartography </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0544em"
              >marker on the player’s card if the ap- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 15.1853em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >propriate result was obtained and any of the markers from that
              zone &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 16.1353em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >are still available. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.2596em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.093em"
              >2. Navigation Check(s): </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.0982em"
              >Roll two dice and add the Nao’s crew &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.2096em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0858em"
              >rating and the applicable modifiers listed below under the table.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.1596em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0314em"
              >Use the modified die roll to find the result in the Navigation
              Table. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 17.5017em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0899em"
              >If a player moves several Naos from the same Ocean Zone to a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 18.4517em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1239em"
              >single adjacent and unexplored Ocean Zone, the owner decides
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 19.4017em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_184" style="word-spacing: -0.0608em"
              >which Nao rolls on the Terra Incognita table. If successful, the
              other &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 20.3517em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Nao(s) move immediately into the newly explored zone along with
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 21.3017em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0443em"
              >the successful Nao. However, if unsuccessful, the other Naos must
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 22.2517em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >remain in their original Ocean Zone until a new Naval Move action
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 23.2017em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >is undertaken. Note that Navigation Checks may not be linked in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 24.1517em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >this fashion; each Nao must make its own Navigation Check when
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 25.1017em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >it crosses a Hazardous Passage. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.832em; top: 19.526em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102">N</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_393">A</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102">V</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: 0.0038em"
              >IGATION (Add factor “C” in the Nao) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 9.4344em; top: 20.9379em">
            <span class="stl_288 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >Roll 2D6 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.3789em; top: 22.1405em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">2-5 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 13.848em; top: 20.9379em">
            <span class="stl_288 stl_17 stl_13">Result &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 13.848em; top: 22.1531em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131">Sunk &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.3789em; top: 23.3557em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">6-7 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 13.848em; top: 23.3684em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Damaged &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 13.848em; top: 24.5836em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >No Effect &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.3924em; top: 24.5709em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0102em"
              >≥ 8 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.9801em">
            <span class="stl_54 stl_17 stl_80">Modifiers: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.3889em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_13">Cartography &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.1719em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_13">+1 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.1655em; top: 27.1718em">
            <span class="stl_47 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0165em"
              >if you are benefiting from the M</span
            ><span class="stl_394 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0075em"
              >aritime </span
            ><span class="stl_47 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_394 stl_17 stl_80">echnology &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.649em; top: 27.6351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0491em"
              >If a player has successfully explored an Ocean Zone but
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.645em; top: 28.5851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.0839em"
              >failed to get a 1 VP marker for Cartography, then—if &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.645em; top: 29.5351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_268" style="word-spacing: -0.0708em"
              >such a V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_132">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_272">m</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >arker is still available—a subsequent attempt &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.645em; top: 30.4851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.0668em"
              >to earn it may be attempted. To do so, the player uses
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 31.4351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >the naval movement of a Nao in that Ocean Zone to roll on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 32.3851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >Cartography table instead of to move. Roll on the following table
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 33.3351em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >and apply the corresponding modifiers: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.1618em; top: 28.0718em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_80">event. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 30.2048em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >+2 in Winter if a Nao is returning to the Built Naos box.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7503em; top: 31.2713em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.0006em"
              >+1 in Winter if there are two of your Naos staying in an Ocean
              Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
