            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_39" style="word-spacing: 0.0867em"
              >hristoPher </span
            ><span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_18">C</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_69" style="word-spacing: 0.0899em"
              >olumBus </span
            ><span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_36">D</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_175" style="word-spacing: 0.0968em"
              >isCovers the </span
            ><span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_36">N</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_408" style="word-spacing: 0.1143em"
              >ew </span
            ><span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_36">w</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_409" style="word-spacing: 0.1123em"
              >orlD </span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_18">and &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.2372em; z-index: 3061"
          >
            <span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_36">v</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_410" style="word-spacing: 0.1107em"
              >asCo Da </span
            ><span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_36">G</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0857em"
              >ama </span
            ><span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_36">a</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_364" style="word-spacing: 0.0923em"
              >rrives iN </span
            ><span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_36">i</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_18">NDia &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.1806em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_411" style="word-spacing: -0.0064em"
              >Overseas Voyages &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.4834em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0212em"
              >The events </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_127"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0167em"
              >hristopher </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0212em"
              >olumbus </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0213em"
              >iscovers the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.038em"
              >ew </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315">orld &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.4334em; z-index: 3117"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0102em"
              >and </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_393">V</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0082em"
              >asco da </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">G</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0463em"
              >ama </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >rrives in </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">I</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0097em"
              >ndia </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0089em"
              >allow Spain or Portugal to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.3834em; z-index: 3185"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0657em"
              >gain the full 2 Overseas </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_412">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.0651em"
              >yage VPs regardless of the progress they &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.3334em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >have made toward these goals to date. To play either of these two
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.2834em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0391em"
              >events you need to have a Nao on the map or in the Built Naos box
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.2334em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0648em"
              >and have a vacant space to place a settlement in the target zone.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.1834em; z-index: 3421"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_111" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Both events can be played even before the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_223">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_110" style="word-spacing: 0.1058em"
              >verseas </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_223">V</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_377">o</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_413">y</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_414">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_415">ges &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.1334em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >mandatory event is played. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7131em; top: 28.4268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0819em"
              >On the Exploration Map, Naos may not &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 29.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: 0.0658em"
              >move to the New World (zones A, B, 7, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 30.3268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >and 8) or to the Indian Ocean (zones 4, 5, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 31.2768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.035em"
              >and 6) until the Mandatory Event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80">ver</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 11.7092em; top: 32.2268em; z-index: 1161"
          >
            <span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0321em"
              >seas </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">V</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191">o</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_192">y</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0135em"
              >ges </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0142em"
              >has been played. Note that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 33.1768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >these boundaries are marked on the map &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 34.1268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0212em"
              >with red lines to remind players that they &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 35.0768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_245" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >are not traversable until this event has &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 36.0268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >occurred. Portugal and Spain may also be &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 36.9768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0602em"
              >limited in their movement by the terms of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 37.9268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0177em"
              >the Peace of Alcaçovas and/or the Treaty &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.4167em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0192em"
              >Execute these events by taking as many of these steps as
              possible: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 36.6168em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.004em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0107em"
              >Spain or Portugal has not yet received the appropriate 2 VP
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 37.5668em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: 0.0614em"
              >marker, award it to them now. If they have already achieved
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 38.5168em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0111em"
              >the 1 VP version, flip it to the 2 VP side. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7092em; top: 38.8768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_172" style="word-spacing: -0.0634em"
              >of Tordesillas (20.4). When the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">verseas &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 39.717em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.1303em"
              >• Move a Nao directly to the target zone. Now make the ex-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 40.667em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_265" style="word-spacing: 0.1263em"
              >ploration roll for Terra incognita if that zone is unexplored
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 41.617em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0549em"
              >considering any result less than 9 as a 9. Found a settlement
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 42.567em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >by removing the Nao as usual. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7505em; top: 39.8268em; z-index: 1428"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">V</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191">o</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_192">y</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0165em"
              >ges </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0053em"
              >event has been played, add Christopher Columbus’ Nao &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7505em; top: 40.7768em; z-index: 1493"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0395em"
              >in Ocean Zone 1 and </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.0482em"
              >sco da Gama’s Nao in Ocean Zone 3. If, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7505em; top: 41.7268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >when this event is played, the Spanish and Portuguese players
              have &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7505em; top: 42.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.069em"
              >not explored zones 1 and 3 respectively, place these Naos in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7505em; top: 43.6268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0319em"
              >Ocean Zone nearest to their intended entry position (or if Zone 1
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7505em; top: 44.5768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0173em"
              >has not been explored, then in the Built Naos box). These special
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7505em; top: 45.5268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.037em"
              >Naos do not count against the usual limit of two Naos per player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7505em; top: 46.4768em; z-index: 1814"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0764em"
              >on the Exploration Map. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.0714em"
              >sco da Gama’s and Columbus’ Naos &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7505em; top: 47.4268em; z-index: 1879"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >are only available by way of the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0112em"
              >verseas </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">V</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191">o</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_192">y</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0025em"
              >ges </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >event. If dis- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7505em; top: 48.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >mantled to found a settlement or sunk, remove them from the game.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7505em; top: 49.3268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0659em"
              >Both Naos may never be captured at any time by the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80">oarding &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7505em; top: 50.2768em">
            <span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0004em"
              >and </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0004em"
              >apture </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >response card. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 43.7672em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_172" style="word-spacing: 0.2381em"
              >• Add</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0609em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >the marker for this event to the corresponding Ocean Zone
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 44.7172em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >to show that this power receives a +1 die roll modifier to the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 45.6672em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >return of any resources from that Ocean Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.2368em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_90" style="word-spacing: -0.007em"
              >16.8 Seville, Inland River Port &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.8167em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0332em"
              >As an inland port, Seville has special properties as detailed
              below: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 50.0169em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0377em"
              >Naval movement limitation: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.038em"
              >No naval unit may move from &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 50.9669em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.068em"
              >the Gulf of Cadiz Sea Zone to Seville (or vice versa) unless
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 51.9169em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >that power controls Jerez or is allied to a power that controls
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 52.8669em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Jerez that allows you to pass through. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.5639em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_184" style="word-spacing: -0.0273em"
              >Columbus’ Nao: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 54.067em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_271" style="word-spacing: -0.0576em"
              >Naval Transport: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_403">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130">p</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >ower performing naval transport through &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 55.017em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0081em"
              >the Gulf of Cadiz may move units directly from Seville to the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5832em; top: 55.967em; z-index: 4351"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.106em"
              >Gulf of Cadiz (or vice versa) for just 1 C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.116em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">b</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1059em"
              >ut only if that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 56.917em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0191em"
              >power controls Jerez or is allied to a power that controls Jerez
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 57.867em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >that allows you to pass through. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.9209em; top: 54.3616em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_135" style="word-spacing: 0.1101em"
              >Christopher Columbus’ Nao enjoys the following &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.9051em; top: 55.3116em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >special properties: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.417em; top: 56.8451em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.2342em"
              >• On</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0578em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_162">Columbus</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_416">’</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_162">f</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >irst attempt to explore </span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_108">z</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_162">on</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_417">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84">A</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >, reduce the num</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 57.7951em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >ber of Navigation Checks required from two to one. (Control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 58.7451em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0168em"
              >of five Canary Islands by Spain reduces this to </span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_418" style="word-spacing: -0.0287em"
              >ero.) A Terra &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 59.6951em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Incognita roll is still required as usual. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_33" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">34 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0161em"
              >Assault: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.071em"
              >An assault may not be conducted against Seville if &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >the besieged power in the space controls Jerez. (</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_106">Exception</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_420">:</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101">An &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >assault may still be conducted if the assaulting power plays the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0096em"
              >Event card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_216">reachery</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 8.3936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: -0.0449em"
              >Assault: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0461em"
              >If a power besieged in Seville has naval squadrons in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 9.3436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0441em"
              >that space, to meet naval blockade requirements from the Gulf
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 10.2936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >of Cadiz the attacker must also control Jerez (or be allied to a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 11.2436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >power that is granting access). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9987em; top: 8.8559em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_13">Nasrid &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9607em; top: 14.3809em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_80">Castile &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 32.852em; top: 8.8559em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0182em"
              >N. Africa &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.0733em; top: 14.3809em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_13">Aragon &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 38.1347em; top: 8.8559em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_13">Portugal &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 38.3607em; top: 14.3809em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_13">France &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 43.1133em; top: 8.8559em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_80">Beltranejos &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 43.32em; top: 14.3809em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_80">Catalonia &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 12.4438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1048em"
              >Piracy: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1059em"
              >Seville can be the object of piracy attempts only if &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 13.3938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >the power that controls Jerez is either the same power that is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 14.3438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >initiating piracy against Seville or that power allows passage
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 15.2938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >through Jerez for the piracy attempt. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.6362em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.091em"
              >Regulars: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0909em"
              >All powers may spend 2 CPs on the Recruit Regular &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.5862em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1199em"
              >Infantry action. Add one regular unit to the map for each such
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.5362em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >action taken. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.9956em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_101" style="word-spacing: -0.0357em"
              >17. Construction &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.4479em; top: 18.9029em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0472em"
              >Militias: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.046em"
              >All powers may spend 1 CP &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.444em; top: 19.8529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >on the Recruit Militia Infantry action. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.444em; top: 20.8029em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1099em"
              >Add one militia unit to the map for &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.444em; top: 21.7529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >each action taken. Guanches units are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.444em; top: 22.7029em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0461em"
              >considered militias for cost purposes. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.4934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1009em"
              >There are a number of actions which allow powers to construct
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.4435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0401em"
              >new land units, naval units, Naos, or fortresses. New units must
              be &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.3935em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >constructed in one of your power´s home spaces that is currently
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.3435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.002em"
              >under your control (</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >Exceptions: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0022em"
              >The cards </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_275" style="word-spacing: 0.0147em"
              >ercenary </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131">ilitias</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_131">, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.2935em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">U</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.029em"
              >nexpected </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">einforcements</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.02em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0301em"
              >and some Home cards allow units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.2435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.025em"
              >to be built in a non-home friendly space or in a non-friendly
              space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1104em"
              >that contains your units.) Also, the Send Escort action allows a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0169em"
              >naval squadron to be constructed and directly placed in an Ocean
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0592em"
              >Zone. Units may never be constructed in a space with an </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_205">Unrest &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.0435em; z-index: 1143"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >or </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Plague </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_218">marker. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.4479em; top: 24.0695em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >Siege Artillery: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0899em"
              >Aragon and France &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.444em; top: 25.0195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >may spend 3 CPs on the Recrui</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_41">t</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106">rtil- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.444em; top: 25.9695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_161" style="word-spacing: 0.1139em"
              >lery action. Add one siege artillery &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.444em; top: 26.9195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0222em"
              >unit to the map for each action taken. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.7802em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_421" style="word-spacing: 0.0182em"
              >17.1 Force Pool &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.3601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >The counters provided with the game for each power are purposely
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.3101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0769em"
              >limited to reflect the total manpower of these powers during the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.2601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >period. Units may never be constructed in excess of the coun-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.2101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0888em"
              >ters available. Players may exchange different denominations of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.1601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0228em"
              >counters at any time to facilitate new builds. </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_338">(</span
            ><span
              class="stl_208 stl_17 stl_422"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0422em"
              >EXAMPLE: </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0231em"
              >If the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.1101em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >player has run out of “1” counters, he could still build in a
              space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.0601em; z-index: 1533"
          >
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0223em"
              >containing three units by replacing the units with a “4”
              counte</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_194">r</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13">.</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13">) &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.0101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.037em"
              >Since naval units for the Muslim player are two-sided, the Muslim
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.9601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >player should consider carefully which type of naval unit (naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.9101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >squadron or corsair) they want to construct. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9987em; top: 33.3893em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_13">Nasrid &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9607em; top: 39.1143em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_80">Castile &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 32.852em; top: 33.3893em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0182em"
              >N. Africa &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 38.1347em; top: 33.3893em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_13">Portugal &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 38.3607em; top: 39.1143em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_13">France &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 43.1133em; top: 33.3893em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_80">Beltranejos &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 43.32em; top: 39.1143em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_80">Catalonia &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.0733em; top: 39.1143em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_13">Aragon &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.3695em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_268" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Cavalry: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >All major powers may spend 3 CPs on the Recruit Cavalry
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.3195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0242em"
              >action. Add one cavalry unit to the map for each action taken.
              The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.2695em; z-index: 2792"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0092em"
              >cost to the Nasrid power (not the North African Alliance) is 2
              C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.6469em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_36" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >17.2 Land Units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.2268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0169em"
              >Land units may be constructed in any friendly home space that is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.1768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0024em"
              >not occupied by enemy units. The only exceptions are:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.0063em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_70" style="word-spacing: 0.0018em"
              >17.3 Naval Units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4997em; top: 45.4514em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">a) &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.1047em; top: 45.4516em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.051em"
              >The Moriscos are Nasrid regulars that are only &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.115em; top: 46.4016em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_276" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >recruited by play of the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_423">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_356" style="word-spacing: 0.1242em"
              >orisco </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_423">U</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_424">prising &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 10.115em; top: 47.3516em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >event (20.1). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.5862em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0139em"
              >Naval units may be built in any friendly home port that is not
              oc- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.5362em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >cupied by enemy units. Naval units lost in combat or assault
              cannot &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.4862em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0446em"
              >be rebuilt on the turn in which they were eliminated. When a
              naval &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.4362em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.021em"
              >unit is lost place it on the next turn of the Turn Track. During
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.3862em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0431em"
              >Card Draw Phase (8.1) these eliminated naval units are returned
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.3362em; z-index: 3129"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0028em"
              >the pool of units available to be constructed by that power.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4997em; top: 49.9934em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102">b) &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 14.7176em; top: 49.9931em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >The Military Orders of Santiago &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 14.7311em; top: 50.9431em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >and Calatrava are Spanish regu- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 14.7311em; top: 51.8931em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >lars that are only recruited by &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 14.7311em; top: 52.8431em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0361em"
              >play of the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0353em"
              >ardinal </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">isneros &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 14.7311em; top: 53.7931em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_335">R</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_425"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0625em"
              >egent </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_241" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >mandatory event (20.5). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.409em; top: 51.7029em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0745em"
              >Naval Squadrons: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.05em"
              >All powers may spend 2 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.405em; top: 52.6529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_227" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >CPs on the Build Naval Squadron action. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.405em; top: 53.6029em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.044em"
              >Add one naval squadron to the map in any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.405em; top: 54.5529em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >home port for each action taken. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7499em; top: 54.9932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_62" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >France and Portugal may also construct units on a Foreign War
              card &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7499em; top: 55.9432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >if one is in progress (20.9). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.4113em; top: 55.9195em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_242" style="word-spacing: 0.107em"
              >Corsairs: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_146" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >The Muslim player (only) may &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.405em; top: 56.8695em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0726em"
              >spend 1 CP on the Build Corsair action. Add &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.405em; top: 57.8195em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >one corsair to the map for each action taken. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
