          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.757em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0222em"
              >Land units in either unfortified spaces or fortified spaces not
              con</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0222em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.707em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >trolled by their major power must return to a fortified space
              that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.657em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0201em"
              >is controlled by their power (with a limit of four per space
              except &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.607em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >in home keys). Land units already in fortified spaces controlled
              by &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.557em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0371em"
              >their power that are not home keys have the option of returning
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.507em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_434" style="word-spacing: 0.0416em"
              >a home key. Land units already in a home key are the only ones
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.457em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.0119em"
              >that are prohibited from moving during this phase (all other land
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.407em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0055em"
              >units at least have the option to be moved at this time). There
              are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.3571em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_225" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >four exceptions: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5em; top: 14.4244em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >ardinal </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >isneros </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0005em"
              >egent </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">(#37) &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.9938em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_126" style="word-spacing: -0.0049em"
              >18.2 Military Order Activity Against Corsairs and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01 stl_75"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.1938em; z-index: 399"
          >
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_186" style="word-spacing: -0.0035em"
              >Loss of Nasrid Home Spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.9675em; top: 18.7737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >The Spanish player rolls as many dice &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.9809em; top: 19.7237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >as spaces he controls from the follow- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.9809em; top: 20.6737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >ing list that also contains at least one &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.9809em; top: 21.6237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Military Order unit: Badis, Melilla, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 22.5572em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.2321em"
              >• One</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0422em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0368em"
              >land unit may remain in each controlled strategic space,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 12.9809em; top: 22.5737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0739em"
              >Oran, Bejaía, and Algiers. Each “5” &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 23.5072em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >even though it is not fortified. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 23.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0233em"
              >or “6” is a hit that reduces the Muslim player’s corsair piracy
              VP &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 24.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >track by one space (but not less than 0). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 24.7074em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Land</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0129em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0078em"
              >units in the Canary Islands may remain there if desired,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 25.6574em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >even in non-controlled spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.209em; top: 25.8404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0647em"
              >Next, if Spain and the Nasrid Kingdom are at war, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.205em; top: 26.7904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >check if any Nasrid home space is controlled by Spain
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.205em; top: 27.7404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0639em"
              >and thus loses its property as a Nasrid home space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.205em; top: 28.6904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >(20.1). In each such space, remove the special control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.205em; top: 29.6404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >marker and place a Spanish one. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.9166em; top: 26.8575em; z-index: 2991"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_146" style="word-spacing: 0.1451em"
              >• After the mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_204">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_435">e</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_436">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_242">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_437" style="word-spacing: 0.1238em"
              >h of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_204">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_434" style="word-spacing: 0.1243em"
              >errante of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_204">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_242">aples &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 27.8075em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0428em"
              >has occurred, additional land units may remain in Atella and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5832em; top: 28.7575em; z-index: 3063"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_438">L</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">’</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >Aquila (21.7). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 29.9577em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.001em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.004em"
              >the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: 0.0015em"
              >ttomans </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ei</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0057em"
              >e </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_201" style="word-spacing: 0.0014em"
              >tranto </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >Mandatory Event is played, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 30.9077em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >additional land units may remain in Otranto (20.2). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.3772em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_36" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >18.3 Discard Unused Resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.1942em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_144">Attrition &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.957em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.061em"
              >Discard any resources still remaining in a player’s Warehouse
              (that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.907em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >they were not able to spend during the Action Phase).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.4404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0217em"
              >Land units move according to the procedure listed below. All land
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.3904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0209em"
              >units moving between the same two spaces are moved as a stack.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.3404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0648em"
              >Check for an open path of any length of adjacent land spaces or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.2904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: 0.0526em"
              >Sea Zones from the stack’s current location to its destination.
              To &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.2404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0838em"
              >avoid losing units to attrition, all spaces on the path (except
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.1904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >space where the path begins) must be: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.6438em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_28" style="word-spacing: -0.0009em"
              >18.4 Loaned Naval Unit Markers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.2237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.121em"
              >Remove all </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.12em"
              >Loaned </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1172em"
              >markers from naval units. These fleets will &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.1737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >return to a port controlled by their owning power in the
              following &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.1237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >18.7 step, not to a port controlled by the power to which they
              have &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.0737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >been on loan. If a Nao or naval squadron has been captured by
              rivals, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.0237em; z-index: 1259"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0031em"
              >it remains in the possession of the capturing power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 39.3905em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Friendly-controlled &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 40.5907em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Free</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0052em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >of Unrest &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.9571em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Note that unlike the determination of LOC (12.1), enemy units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.9071em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0218em"
              >are ignored at this time. In addition, paths can be traced over
              any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.8571em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.045em"
              >number of Sea Zones without a friendly naval unit being present
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.8071em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0304em"
              >in the Sea Zone. Because alliances are in effect until the end of
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.7571em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0097em"
              >18.9 step of the Winter Phase, land units may trace a path
              through &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.7071em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0561em"
              >spaces controlled by allied powers. If no such path exists, the
              stack &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.6571em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1101em"
              >suffers attrition, losing half of its units (round up). The
              owning &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.6071em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >player chooses which units are lost to attrition. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.7605em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_201" style="word-spacing: -0.003em"
              >18.5 Return of Land Units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.3404em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_300" style="word-spacing: 0.0498em"
              >Next land units return to fortified spaces (though units in
              Plague &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.2904em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >spaces and militia may be eliminated first). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.5775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_123" style="word-spacing: -0.0058em"
              >Check for Death from Plague &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 47.8237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">•</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.5023em; top: 47.8237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >Count the number of land and naval units (but not &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.4983em; top: 48.7737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_263" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >leaders) you have in each space with a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_263">Plague &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.4983em; top: 49.7237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0664em"
              >marker. Roll that many dice. For each roll of “1”, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.4983em; top: 50.6737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >eliminate one unit of your choice from that space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.8942em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_90" style="word-spacing: 0.0005em"
              >Land Unit Return Home Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.1404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0191em"
              >Each power performs the following steps to check the status of
              all &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.0904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0441em"
              >of its land units. This procedure may be performed simultaneously
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.0404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >for all powers. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4165em; top: 51.8739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Then</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0809em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0759em"
              >roll one die for each leader in that space. If you roll a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0831em; top: 52.8239em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >“1”, the leader becomes seriously ill and retreats to quarantine.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0831em; top: 53.7739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0239em"
              >Place the leader on the turn track, to return two turns beyond
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0831em; top: 54.7239em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >the current turn (as specified in 8.1). If, due to the effect of
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0831em; top: 55.6739em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0132em"
              >Mandatory event, the leader affected by Plague dies and is
              re</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0132em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0831em; top: 56.6239em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0463em"
              >placed by another, the new leader replacing him is not affected
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0831em; top: 57.5739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >by Plague and enters the game normally at that time. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.4068em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_439" style="word-spacing: 0.1237em"
              >1. Check Stacking Violations: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >Review all land units that are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.3568em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0148em"
              >stacked in fortified spaces controlled by their power (other than
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.3068em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0359em"
              >home key). For each such fortified space that contains more than
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.2568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0439em"
              >four units, the power must return the excess units to a
              controlled &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.2068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >home key (minor power units could also optionally return to a
              minor &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.1568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >power home key). Artillery and cavalry units are always counted
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 60.1068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1099em"
              >against this limit of four units. Other land units in these
              spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4165em; top: 58.774em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.2321em"
              >• Now</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >remove the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Plague </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >markers from the board. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_36" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">37 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0099em"
              >also have the option of returning to a home key (or minor key for
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0381em"
              >minor power units) if desired, even if not overstacked. The stack
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0129em"
              >takes attrition (see above) if its path must cross or end on a
              space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >in unrest or not under friendly control. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0562em"
              >4. Frenc</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_183">h</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_101">A</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0661em"
              >nd Principality of Catalonia Units: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >French units may &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >return to a Catalan controlled fortified space in the
              Principality of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0441em"
              >Catalonia, but French units returning to Barcelona may not exceed
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >one valid formation. Catalan units may not return to a French
              home &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >space except in a formation with th</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_441">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_193">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_442" style="word-spacing: -0.057em"
              >njou leader. Catalan units may &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >return to the followin</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_443">g</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_69">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >ragon home spaces if they possess a French &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.0435em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0567em"
              >control marker and are fortified: Gerona, Palamós, or Tarragona.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.9935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0172em"
              >Catalan units may return to spaces with French control markers in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.9435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0422em"
              >Roussillon. Catalan and French units can winter in home,
              strategic &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.8935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0062em"
              >spaces controlled by the other in either Catalonia or Aragon.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.5599em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.036em"
              >2. Return Units: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0352em"
              >Now review all land units in unfortified spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.5099em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0714em"
              >and in fortified spaces not controlled by their major power.
              (Re</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0714em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.4599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0252em"
              >member that one unit may remain in each strategic space.) These
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.4099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >units must either: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 12.61em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Return</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0649em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0599em"
              >to a home key (or minor power key for minor power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 13.56em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >units), or &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.2599em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_179" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >5. Portugues</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_383">e</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_213">A</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_179" style="word-spacing: -0.0674em"
              >nd Beltranejos Units: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_179" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Portuguese units may return &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.2099em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >to a fortified home space of the Beltranejos faction. In the case
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.1599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0561em"
              >Beltranejos home keys, Portuguese units may not exceed one valid
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.1099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0808em"
              >formation. Beltranejos units may never return to any space con-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.0599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0461em"
              >trolled by Portugal. Portuguese units can winter in strategic
              spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.0099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0998em"
              >controlled by the Beltranejos. Once the Peace of Alcaçovas has
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.9599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0571em"
              >been signed, Portuguese units may no longer return to
              Beltranejos- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.9099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >controlled spaces, as they are no longer allies. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 14.7602em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: 0.2538em"
              >• Return</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0691em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0629em"
              >to the nearest fortified space controlled by the power (but
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 15.7102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0149em"
              >not if that would put more than four land units in that space).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 16.6602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0669em"
              >The nearest space is always computed using a direct path to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 17.6102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >the destination without regard to which power controls any of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 18.5602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >the intervening spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.9266em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0461em"
              >Players may split a stack at this time, choosing to move some
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.8766em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.022em"
              >to the nearest fortified space and returning the rest to a home
              key &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.8266em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0378em"
              >(or minor power key). If more than one fortified space is </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_21">nearest &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 22.7766em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1119em"
              >(i.e., they are equidistant from the stack´s current location),
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 23.7266em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0272em"
              >player may move units to each of these spaces, as long as the
              limit &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 24.6766em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0371em"
              >of four land units is observed. Any stack moving during this
              phase &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 25.6266em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0129em"
              >takes attrition (see above) if its path must cross or end on a
              space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 26.5766em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >in unrest or not under friendly control. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.2763em; z-index: 3621"
          >
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.016em"
              >6. Otranto, </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_252">L</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13">’</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0357em"
              >Aquila, and Atella: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0171em"
              >These 3 spaces in the southern &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.2263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0119em"
              >end of the Italian peninsula are each marked with a small colored
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.1763em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0178em"
              >square to remind players of their Winter Phase capabilities. If
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.1263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.094em"
              >Mandatory Event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: 0.0805em"
              >ttomans </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_236">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: 0.092em"
              >ake </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_201" style="word-spacing: 0.0984em"
              >tranto </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0938em"
              >has been played, a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.0763em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0978em"
              >North African formation whose size is determined by the Com-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.0263em; z-index: 3879"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0032em"
              >mand </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0149em"
              >lue of a single leader present in that space may winter in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.9763em; z-index: 3957"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.012em"
              >Otranto. If the Mandatory Event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">e</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0209em"
              >h </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0206em"
              >f </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0105em"
              >errante </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0206em"
              >f </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">aples &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.9263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0139em"
              >has been played, a French formation whose size is determined by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.8763em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1049em"
              >a single leader present in that space may winter in L´Aquila. If
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.8263em; z-index: 4103"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0613em"
              >the Mandatory Event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">e</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >h </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0706em"
              >f </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0605em"
              >errante </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0706em"
              >f </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.3818em"
              >aples </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0617em"
              >has been &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.7763em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0129em"
              >played, a Spanish formation whose size is determined by a single
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.7263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.053em"
              >leader present in that space may winter in Atella. If the
              appropriate &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.6763em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0289em"
              >event has occurred but no leader is present in such a space, up
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.6263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >4 appropriate land units may winter there. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 27.943em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0572em"
              >3. Return Army Leaders: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >If a space containing an army leader &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 28.893em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0238em"
              >is vacated during this procedure, that army leader must either
              ac- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 29.843em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0899em"
              >company one of the land units leaving the space throughout the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 30.793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.119em"
              >entire winter move or return to a controlled home key. Leaders
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 31.743em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0046em"
              >never suffer attrition. Moreover, if they are alone they can
              always &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 32.693em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0169em"
              >return to a controlled home key regardless of whether or not they
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 33.643em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >are able to trace an LOC. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.9306em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_52" style="word-spacing: -0.0006em"
              >ere are six exceptions to the rules in this procedure:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.3434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.1128em"
              >1. Enemy-Controlled Key: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.1126em"
              >If a power’s home key is currently &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.2935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.059em"
              >controlled by an enemy power, none of its land units may be re-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0183em"
              >turned to that key. If a power does not control any home keys,
              all &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.1934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0169em"
              >units that would normally have been required to return to a home
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.1434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >key are eliminated &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.3636em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_11" style="word-spacing: -0.0024em"
              >18.6 Replacements and Morisco Uprising &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.9434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0221em"
              >Each major power (including the Principality of Catalonia and the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.8934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0519em"
              >Beltranejos) adds one regular to their choice of home key that is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.8434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0429em"
              >controlled and not in unrest. Remember that the regular received
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.7934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0282em"
              >by the North African Alliance can be placed in any Fez or Berbers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.7434em; z-index: 4602"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_140" style="word-spacing: 0.009em"
              >home key that is in play. </span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13">Exceptions: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.5099em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_56" style="word-spacing: -0.0623em"
              >2. Spanish Units: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >The Spanish player controls two powers</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_444">,</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_67">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171">ragon &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.4599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0636em"
              >and Castile. The units of each power must return to their own
              home &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.4099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0024em"
              >spaces. However, there are three exceptions: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 42.9436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >Nasrid Kingdom can choose to receive a cavalry in place
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5832em; top: 43.8936em; z-index: 4676"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_44" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >of the regular. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4997em; top: 44.61em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.165em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >Castilian units may return t</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_444">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_67">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >ragonese home spaces in Sicily &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 45.0938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.0918em"
              >• Any Major Power controlling Tunis, as long as the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131">lgiers &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 46.0438em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_130">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_25" style="word-spacing: -0.0625em"
              >egency </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >event has not been played, receives the Djerba corsair
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 46.9938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >if it had been sunk during the previous turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 45.56em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >or Sardinia as if they were Castilian home spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4997em; top: 46.7602em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.1093em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_205" style="word-spacing: -0.0615em"
              >Units of both powers returning as part of a formation with Fer-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 47.7102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >dinand or the Great Captain may winter in the other power’s
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 48.6602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >home space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 48.1939em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0451em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0193em"
              >North African Alliance also receives a corsair in Algiers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 49.1439em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0448em"
              >if he controls this space, the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0349em"
              >lgiers </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0345em"
              >egency </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0352em"
              >event has been &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 50.0939em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >played, and an unbuilt corsair is available. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4997em; top: 49.8604em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.2207em"
              >c) </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0808em"
              >Units of either power may winter in a fortified or strategic
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 50.8104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >space controlled by the Spanish player that is not a home space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.4996em; top: 51.7604em; z-index: 2227"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.0099em"
              >of either power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 51.2941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_344" style="word-spacing: 0.1353em"
              >• Any major power that has surrendered (22.1)—other than
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 52.2441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0469em"
              >the Beltranejos, the Principality of Catalonia, and the Nasrid
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 53.1941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.014em"
              >Kingdom—will receive one militia (instead of one regular) in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 54.1441em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0419em"
              >a controlled fortified or strategic space of their choice that is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 55.0941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >valid for winter stacking purposes. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7492em; top: 53.1268em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1044em"
              >3. Muslim Units: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1109em"
              >The Muslim player controls three nations, of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7492em; top: 54.0768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0289em"
              >which two of them (Berbers and Sultanate of Fez) are one power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7492em; top: 55.0268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >(North African Alliance) that share a force pool of units
              although &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7492em; top: 55.9768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0513em"
              >their spaces on the map are of a different color. North African
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7492em; top: 56.9268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.118em"
              >may return to any North African-controlled space. Nasrid units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7492em; top: 57.8768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_104" style="word-spacing: 0.118em"
              >must always return to a Nasrid-controlled space. North African
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7492em; top: 58.8268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0359em"
              >units in a formation with a Nasrid leader may return to a Nasrid-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7492em; top: 59.7768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >controlled space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.4605em; z-index: 5252"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0261em"
              >If any Morisco regular unit or </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.026em"
              >Morisco Uprising </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_62" style="word-spacing: -0.0144em"
              >marker is in play, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.4105em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >the Muslim player executes the Effects of Morisco Uprising
              (20.1). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_37" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">38 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.233em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_36" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >18.7 Naos and Naval Units Return &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.7333em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0023em"
              >Naos Return &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.233em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_357" style="word-spacing: -0.0019em"
              >18.8 Resource Return and Foreign Trade &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.7333em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_140" style="word-spacing: -0.001em"
              >Return of Naval Resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.442em; top: 6.9795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_446" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Determine whether the naval resources placed in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.9795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0839em"
              >Naos on the Exploration Map are returned to either one of their
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.9295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0867em"
              >power’s settlements or the Built Naos box—or they can risk re-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.8795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >maining at sea. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.4246em; top: 7.9295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: -0.0598em"
              >settlements arrive at their owner’s Warehouse by roll-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.4246em; top: 8.8795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0521em"
              >ing on the Resource Return Table. Each player makes &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.4246em; top: 9.8295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.08em"
              >one roll for each Ocean Zone where he has at least &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.4246em; top: 10.7795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.071em"
              >one naval resource in a settlement. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_321">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.077em"
              >u must select &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2494em; top: 11.7295em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1239em"
              >the appropriate column according to whether or not the fleet is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2494em; top: 12.6795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0499em"
              >subject to Plunder (see Plunder of Naval Resources below). Add
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2494em; top: 13.6295em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the following modifiers to that roll (all cumulative):
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 10.0797em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_321">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">u</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.075em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0649em"
              >can return a Nao to one of your own settlements if it is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 11.0297em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0052em"
              >closest to the Nao’s current Ocean Zone and there is no Navi-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 11.9797em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0198em"
              >gation arrow between the two zones. A settlement can hold a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 12.9297em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >maximum of one Nao. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 14.1299em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_321">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">u</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.076em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0659em"
              >can voluntarily return a Nao with or without a resource
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 15.0799em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0919em"
              >directly to the Built Naos Box. Roll a Navigation check for
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 16.0299em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0389em"
              >that Nao, with a +2 modifier to the die roll. Place the Nao in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 16.9799em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >the Built Naos Box if it has no resource. If it has at least one
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 17.9299em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0088em"
              >resource, the resource goes to the player’s warehouse and the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 18.8799em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_66" style="word-spacing: 0.0012em"
              >Nao is placed on the Turn Track. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.916em; top: 14.8297em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• +2</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >if you have a naval escort squadron in that Ocean Zone
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.916em; top: 16.0299em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2418em"
              >• +1</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >if you are benefiting from th</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_447">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_37">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0805em"
              >aritime </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_152">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0629em"
              >echnology </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30">event &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.916em; top: 17.23em; z-index: 2981"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• +1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.04em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0473em"
              >if Ocean Zone 5, you are Portugal, and </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0449em"
              >sco Da Gama has &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 18.18em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >arrived in India &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.916em; top: 19.3802em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• +1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.046em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0511em"
              >if Ocean Zone 7, you are Spain, and Christopher Columbus
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5825em; top: 20.3302em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_52" style="word-spacing: 0.0033em"
              >discovered the New World &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 20.08em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.022em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >a Nao chooses to stay in its current Ocean Zone, it must im-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 21.03em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.025em"
              >mediately pass a Navigation Check. This check is done with a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 21.98em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0201em"
              >+1 modifier if the Nao belongs to a group of at least two Naos
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 22.93em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0541em"
              >of the same power trying to stay in that Ocean Zone. Each Nao
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 23.88em; z-index: 893"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.042em"
              >must roll separately. </span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0541em"
              >Exception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.05em"
              >On the turn that the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">verseas &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 24.83em; z-index: 950"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">V</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191">o</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_192">y</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0855em"
              >ges </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0792em"
              >event is played, </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: 0.0904em"
              >sco da Gama’s and Christopher &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 25.78em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1067em"
              >Columbus’ Naos do not perform Navigation Checks if they
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 26.73em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >decide to stay in their Ocean Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 31.0512em; top: 21.7091em">
            <span class="stl_448 stl_17 stl_52" style="word-spacing: 0.0003em"
              >RESOURCE RETURN TABLE &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.068em; top: 23.074em">
            <span class="stl_288 stl_17 stl_80">Roll &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.0704em; top: 24.024em">
            <span class="stl_288 stl_17 stl_131">2D6 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.8705em; top: 23.074em">
            <span class="stl_288 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Return free</span
            ><span class="stl_288 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 1.1872em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_288 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Return Subject &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.0043em; top: 24.024em">
            <span class="stl_288 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >of Plunder</span
            ><span class="stl_288 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 2.2828em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_288 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >to Plunder &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 29.6394em; top: 25.169em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >All Eliminated</span
            ><span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 1.178em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >All Eliminated &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 40.7821em; top: 23.549em">
            <span class="stl_288 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Caravan Blocked &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.2248em; top: 25.2329em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">2-4 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 41.8807em; top: 25.2396em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Eliminated &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 30.4398em; top: 26.4552em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >1 Arrives &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 29.9204em; top: 27.4052em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >1 Eliminated &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 30.2425em; top: 28.3552em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >1 Remains &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 35.5613em; top: 26.4552em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >1 Plundered &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 35.7629em; top: 27.4052em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >1 Remains &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 35.961em; top: 28.3552em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >1 Arrives &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.2245em; top: 27.3985em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">5-6 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 42.3785em; top: 27.4052em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_80">Remains &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.0167em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0022em"
              >Naval Units Return &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.2629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0839em"
              >Naval units on the main map must be placed in the nearest port
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.2129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0143em"
              >controlled by their major power. Squadrons of a controlled minor
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.1629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.029em"
              >power have the option to go to the nearest home port of that
              minor &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.1129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >power instead as long as it is also under control of their major
              power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.0629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_186" style="word-spacing: 0.0305em"
              >ally. If more than one port is the same distance away, the owning
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.0129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0419em"
              >player selects any of these equidistant ports (splitting a stack
              be- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.9629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >tween several ports if desired). Naval units returning home at
              this &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.9129em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.075em"
              >time cannot be intercepted, do not fight naval combat if moving
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.8629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >through enemy units, never suffer any attrition, and may return
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.8129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.003em"
              >a port that was under siege at the start of the phase. Naval
              leaders &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.7629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.056em"
              >in a Sea Zone must return to a port with one of the units that
              started &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.7129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0159em"
              >this phase in the same Sea Zone. Remember that you cannot pass
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.6629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0464em"
              >from the Alboran Sea to the Gulf of Cadiz (or vice versa) unless
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.6129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0849em"
              >you control one of the three spaces in the Strait of Gibraltar,
              an &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.5629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0121em"
              >ally controls one of them, or one of those powers has allowed you
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.5129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0719em"
              >to pass through. If there is no valid port for a naval squadron
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.4628em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >return to, it is eliminated. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 30.4398em; top: 29.5707em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >1 Arrives &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 30.2417em; top: 30.5207em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >1 Remains &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 29.9197em; top: 31.4707em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >1 Eliminated &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 35.5598em; top: 29.5707em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >1 Plundered &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 35.9588em; top: 30.5207em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >1 Arrives &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_449" style="left: 35.7608em; top: 31.4707em">
            <span class="stl_450 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >1 Remains &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.2242em; top: 30.5144em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">7-8 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.0142em; top: 30.5207em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Plundered &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 41.4458em; top: 32.6859em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >Eliminated or &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 40.7594em; top: 33.6359em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >Remains (Muslim &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 41.0737em; top: 34.5859em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0024em"
              >player’s choice) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.2377em; top: 33.6296em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0102em"
              >≥ 9 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.136em; top: 33.6359em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0548em"
              >All Arrive &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.6563em; top: 33.6359em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0548em"
              >All Arrive &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.9818em">
            <span class="stl_54 stl_17 stl_13">Results: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.0483em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.7624em"
              >Eliminated Resource</span
            ><span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_52" style="word-spacing: -0.0585em"
              >lost to owner. Place it on the turn track to return &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.3337em; top: 37.9483em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >to the game on the next turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2507em; top: 39.0148em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_13">Arrives &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.3337em; top: 39.0148em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0033em"
              >Add resource to owner’s Warehouse. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.3337em; top: 40.0813em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Resource remains in current settlement. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2507em; top: 40.0813em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_80">Remains &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2507em; top: 41.1478em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 1.0948em"
              >Plundered Add</span
            ><span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >a randomly chosen resource from those in the Ocean &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.3345em; top: 42.0478em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_33" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >Zone to plundering player’s Warehouse. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.628em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0149em"
              >On results of 5-6 or 7-8 for naval resources, apply the results
              one &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.578em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0251em"
              >at a time. If fewer than three naval resources are present in a
              zone, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >apply the results in the order listed above (from top to bottom).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.8293em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >A naval squadron acting as an escort on the Exploration Map must
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.7793em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >choose between: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2642em; top: 46.8944em">
            <span class="stl_208 stl_17 stl_451" style="word-spacing: 0.0618em"
              >EXAMPLE: </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: 0.135em"
              >There are two naval resources in an Ocean Zone &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2508em; top: 47.8444em; z-index: 3923"
          >
            <span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.113em"
              >subject to plunde</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_194">r</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.104em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_99">A</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1127em"
              >fter modif</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0999em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.1148em"
              >ication, a 5 roll is obtained. One &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2508em; top: 48.7944em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_33" style="word-spacing: 0.0067em"
              >resource is plundered and the other remains in its settlement.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4997em; top: 47.9794em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.165em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Staying in its Ocean Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4997em; top: 49.1796em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.1093em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >Attempting to return to a controlled home port on the main
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 50.1296em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: 0.0923em"
              >map. To return the squadron performs a Navigation Check
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 51.0796em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >with a +3 modifier and applies these results: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2508em; top: 50.1608em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0789em"
              >The random choice of a resource for plunder is always resolved
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2508em; top: 51.1108em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0451em"
              >first. Then the player determines the status of the other
              returning &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2508em; top: 52.0608em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >resources. If that player controls a fortress in the Ocean Zone
              being &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2508em; top: 53.0108em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0559em"
              >resolved they may freely choose which resources arrive, remain,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2508em; top: 53.9608em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0339em"
              >or are eliminated among those present in the zone. If they do not
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2508em; top: 54.9108em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.114em"
              >possess a fortress, apply each result to a random resource from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2508em; top: 55.8608em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >those present in the zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.0829em; top: 52.2798em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0646em"
              >No effect: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0221em"
              >The naval squadron arrives at its destination. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.0829em; top: 53.4799em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_253" style="word-spacing: 0.128em"
              >Damaged: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_452" style="word-spacing: 0.1274em"
              >Transfer is blocked; unit remains in the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.0829em; top: 54.4299em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Ocean Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.0829em; top: 55.6301em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >Sunken: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Destroys the naval squadron. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7492em; top: 56.9965em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_453" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >Remember that in the Naval Escort segment of the spring
              deployment &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7492em; top: 57.9465em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >(10.0) you can move one squadron without a Navigation Check.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
