          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9996em; top: 57.8023em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_324" style="word-spacing: -0.0382em"
              >France. If a player’s force pool does not contain any units of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9996em; top: 58.7523em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_225" style="word-spacing: 0.062em"
              >the appropriate type, the resource is lost without awarding
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9996em; top: 59.7023em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >the unit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7491em; top: 53.7585em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.0083em"
              >FRANCE NORTH SEA: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >France then checks the success of their &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7491em; top: 54.7085em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >commerce in the North Sea with the Hanseatic cities. France can
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7491em; top: 55.6585em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >benefit from French investment in commercial improvements, once
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7491em; top: 56.6085em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_379" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >the Treaty of Etaples is signed. France receives a +1 die roll
              modifier &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7491em; top: 57.5585em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >for each trade improvement marker (maximum +4) you have in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7491em; top: 58.5085em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_185" style="word-spacing: -0.0594em"
              >North Sea Trade box, as shown in the table below. Roll two dice
              and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7491em; top: 59.4585em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the resources received are immediately added to your warehouse:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_39" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">40 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0278em"
              >This same procedure for revealing resources applies to any naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >or caravan resource drawn in any other phase of the game, except
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >in these cases: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0277em"
              >the resolution roll from +0 to +4. The minimum CP required to at-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0032em"
              >tempt a resolution roll is 1 CP (+0 modifier), and the maximum is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0138em"
              >5 CP (+4 modifier). It is possible to invest CP in different
              actions &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0191em"
              >to increase an already established dowry to its maximum allowed.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >Several weddings may be arranged in the same turn, and each can
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: -0.0514em"
              >be advanced to the full 5 CP of dowry. The male son (the heir,
              John &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.0435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0232em"
              >Prince of Asturias) automatically receives the full +4 dowry when
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.9935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.002em"
              >just a single CP is spent on his marriage. Place the child and
              their &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.9435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_66" style="word-spacing: 0.0116em"
              >suitor in the appropriate Dowry Box on the Royal Wedding Table
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.8935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >according to the number of CPs invested. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 7.4436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Resource</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0209em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0261em"
              >awards a card draw: Draw a new card from the deck &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 8.3936em; z-index: 264"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_62">immediately. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 9.5938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Resource</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0521em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0409em"
              >awards CP: These CP may be spent by the owning &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 10.5438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0969em"
              >player at any time during the turn, including in the impulse
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 11.4938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >being resolved (assuming the impulse has not already been
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 12.4438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">extended). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.1802em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0.0003em"
              >18.9 Major Power Alliance and Piracy Markers &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.7601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.036em"
              >Remove all </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0357em"
              >Allied </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0359em"
              >markers between Major Powers from the Dip- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.7101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0264em"
              >lomatic Status Display. All alliances declared for this turn
              during &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.6601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >the Diplomacy Phase are over; all alliances with minor powers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.6101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >remain in effect. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.9765em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0699em"
              >Remove all piracy markers from the map in both ocean and Sea
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.9265em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Zones. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.6636em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_11" style="word-spacing: -0.0025em"
              >18.10 Diplomacy Reset &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.176em; top: 23.3482em">
            <span class="stl_226 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: 0.001em"
              >2 CP Promote Marriage action between Isabella and Afonso on Turn
              3 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.2434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >All influence markers in a “Resolved this turn” box on the
              Diplo</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.1934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0392em"
              >matic Influence on Minors Table are reset to their default
              values. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.1434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0231em"
              >Default values are shown by the colored filled in boxes that
              match &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.0934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: -0.0175em"
              >the colors of each power. If no colored box exists for a power,
              this &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.0434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0013em"
              >power’s marker is placed in the “0” box. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.9319em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_181" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >19.1 Resolving Weddings &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.64em; top: 26.5118em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_468" style="word-spacing: 0.1295em"
              >To resolve a wedding roll two dice, add the die roll &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.6447em; top: 27.4618em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: -0.034em"
              >modifier from the dowry, and consult the table below. If
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.6447em; top: 28.4118em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0032em"
              >successful, Spain scores 1 VP by adding a wedding VP &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.6447em; top: 29.3618em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0528em"
              >marker to their Player Card and the suitor is placed in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.4099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: -0.0579em"
              >Any –</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_469">1</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0582em"
              >dmin Rating markers on Player Cards are removed at this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.3599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >time. All rulers revert to their full Admin Rating (at least
              until the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.3099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >next Headline Event is resolved). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 30.3118em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: -0.0053em"
              >the Married To box below the appropriate child. Also add a Span-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 31.2618em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0549em"
              >ish control marker to the appropriate box at the top of the Royal
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 32.2118em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: 0.0677em"
              >Wedding Table to mark the Dynastic Alliance with Portugal, the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 33.1618em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >Holy Roman Empire, or England (if one is not already present). If
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 34.1118em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >the marriage is postponed, the dowry remains and may be increased
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 35.0618em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >on the next turn if desired (always up to a maximum of 4), unless
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 36.0118em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >one of the two royals dies (in which case the dowry is lost).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.1789em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_470" style="word-spacing: -0.011em"
              >19. Royal Weddings &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0618em"
              >Starting on Turn 3, in this sixth phase of the turn the Spanish
              player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.6268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0545em"
              >resolves all the weddings he has arranged during the Action
              Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.5768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Ferdinand and Isabella were active in establishing alliances
              through &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.5268em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0441em"
              >the marriages of their five children—a policy that would lead to
              an &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.4768em; z-index: 1393"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >extensive empire in the hands of their grandson Charles </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_393">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_393">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 27.7206em; top: 37.5063em">
            <span class="stl_471 stl_17 stl_13">RO</span
            ><span class="stl_471 stl_17 stl_83">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_471 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_471 stl_17 stl_102">L &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 27.1392em; top: 38.4563em">
            <span class="stl_471 stl_17 stl_131">WEDDING &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 27.7762em; top: 39.4063em">
            <span class="stl_471 stl_17 stl_459">TABLE &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5548em; top: 40.6088em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >Roll 2D6 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.5001em; top: 41.824em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">2-8 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 32.8075em; top: 39.4063em">
            <span class="stl_472 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0013em"
              >Add modifier (+0 to +4) from Dowry &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 37.9811em; top: 40.6088em">
            <span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13">Result &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.8432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0601em"
              >Each child of the Catholic Monarchs is represented by a portrait
              on &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.7932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0119em"
              >a Spanish-colored marker and each suitor by a portrait on a beige
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.7432em; z-index: 1515"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_44" style="word-spacing: 0.0108em"
              >color marker. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 35.8143em; top: 41.824em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >Marriage postponed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 28.5135em; top: 43.0392em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0102em"
              >≥ 9 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 31.6786em; top: 43.0392em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0093em"
              >Marriage celebrated successfully; 1VP gained &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 44.3257em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0241em"
              >HISTORICAL NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0089em"
              >The Isabella depicted here is the first- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 45.2757em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_104" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >born daughter of the Catholic Monarchs, not Queen Isabella
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 46.2257em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">herself). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.369em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_274" style="word-spacing: 0.0055em"
              >Alcaçovas Peace Wedding bonus &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.649em; top: 45.6152em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0951em"
              >If the Peace of Alcaçovas is signed between Portugal &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.645em; top: 46.5652em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.105em"
              >and Castile, the marriage of Isabella of Asturias with
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.645em; top: 47.5152em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >Afonso of Portugal is immediately arranged and auto- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.645em; top: 48.4652em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >matically successful, as long as both are still alive</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_473">.</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_292">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_213">w</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158">ard &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 49.4152em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0032em"
              >the 1 VP immediately at no CP cost; this is the only marriage
              that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 50.3652em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101" style="word-spacing: 0.002em"
              >can be celebrated outside the Royal Wedding Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.9351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_268" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >As they arrive during the Card Draw Phase (8.1), each child or
              suitor &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 48.8851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_11" style="word-spacing: 0.0418em"
              >is placed in their box on the Royal Wedding Table; note that it
              is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 49.8351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0541em"
              >indicated in the upper left corner of this portrait whether or
              not this &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 50.7851em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.003em"
              >royal might die. Place Manuel I in the box under Isabella if she
              is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.7351em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >alive (even if married); otherwise add him to the box beneath
              Maria. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.1015em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0287em"
              >During the Action Phase the Spanish player can spend CP on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.0515em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_267" style="word-spacing: -0.0598em"
              >Promote Marriage action to try to marry off Ferdinand and
              Isabella’s &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.0015em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0194em"
              >children. Each child must be married to the highest priority
              suitor, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.9515em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_111" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >indicated by their proximity on this chart to the corresponding
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.9015em">
