          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5973em; top: 5.164em">
            <span class="stl_208 stl_17 stl_482" style="word-spacing: -0.1011em"
              >CONTROL MARKERS IN NASRID HOME SPACES - EX- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5973em; top: 6.114em">
            <span class="stl_208 stl_17 stl_483" style="word-spacing: -0.1263em"
              >AMPLE: </span
            ><span
              class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_162"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Portugal has allied with Spain and begun a campaign &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5838em; top: 7.064em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0533em"
              >to try and drive the Nasrid Kingdom from the Iberian peninsula.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5838em; top: 8.014em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0148em"
              >For the purposes of this example, we will show control marker
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5838em; top: 8.964em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: -0.0454em"
              >changes only – no military units are shown (to improve the clar-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5838em; top: 9.914em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >ity of the example). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5838em; top: 11.2804em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.085em"
              >At the start of the campaign the region northeast of Granada
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5838em; top: 12.2304em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >looks as follows: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.9615em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.0597em"
              >In the Winter Phase, the Baza control marker is switched to a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.9115em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >normal Spanish one: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 29.1393em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0146em"
              >In the initial impulses, Portugal captures Loja, and Spain cap-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 30.0893em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_484" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >tures Baza and Albox. Special Spanish control markers are placed
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 31.0393em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >on those spaces which now looks like this: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.8202em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_68" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >Now in the next turn, the Nasrids are reinforced and recapture
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.7702em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.046em"
              >both Loja and Baza.</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.352em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: 0.0516em"
              >The Portuguese marker is removed from &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.7202em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.0317em"
              >Loja: this space has regained its Nasrid home space properties.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.6702em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: -0.0307em"
              >But when Baza is recaptured, a Nasrid control marker is placed
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.6202em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_271" style="word-spacing: -0.0606em"
              >there instead. Although the Nasrid controls that space, he may
              not &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.5702em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_11" style="word-spacing: -0.0193em"
              >recruit new units there since it has lost its home space
              property. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 47.948em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_485" style="word-spacing: 0.1267em"
              >Later that turn, Albox is recaptured and the special marker
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 48.898em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_90">removed: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_42" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">43 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_333" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >marker (or one from any other power) was present before
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >capture, add a normal Spanish control marker instead.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_50" style="word-spacing: -0.0106em"
              >Reconquista Victory Points &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0124em"
              >The Muslim and Spanish players earn VP for the Spanish Recon-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >quista as follows: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9168em; top: 6.4936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0352em"
              >Nasrids Control Space: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.038em"
              >If the Nasrid gains control of a space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 7.4436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.011em"
              >with a special Spanish control marker (or gains one from any
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 8.3936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0428em"
              >other power), remove the other power’s control marker from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 9.3436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.067em"
              >the space. If the Nasrid gains control of such a space with a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 10.2936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0249em"
              >normal Spanish control marker, add a Nasrid control marker;
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 11.2436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.005em"
              >if the Nasrid gains control of a space from a power other than
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 12.1936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Spain, no new control marker is placed. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 7.6739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">•</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.4527em; top: 7.6737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_253" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >As long as the Granada space is under Muslim &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.478em; top: 8.6237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.024em"
              >player control (even after the Surrender of the Nas- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.478em; top: 9.5737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.047em"
              >rid Kingdom), place the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0411em"
              >1 VP Granada </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0468em"
              >marker on &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.478em; top: 10.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0019em"
              >the Muslim player’s card. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.416em; top: 11.7239em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">•</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.4823em; top: 11.7237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: 0.0713em"
              >In the Victory Determination Phase of Turns 5, 6, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.4783em; top: 12.6737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.0091em"
              >and 7, check to see if the Nasrid Kingdom has sur- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.4783em; top: 13.6237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1048em"
              >rendered. If this objective has not been achieved, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.4783em; top: 14.5737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0579em"
              >the Spanish player subtracts 1 VP from his accumu- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0837em; top: 15.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0722em"
              >lated VP total by placing a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >–1 VP </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >marker for </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >Nasrid Resistance &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0837em; top: 16.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >on his Player Card. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9168em; top: 13.3938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0682em"
              >Other Power Controls Space: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >If a power besides Spain or the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 14.3438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >Nasrid gains control of such a space, add one of their control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 15.2938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >markers as usual. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9168em; top: 16.494em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: 0.0211em"
              >Winter Phase: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.027em"
              >All Nasrid home spaces with special Spanish &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 17.444em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >control markers are switched to normal Spanish control markers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 18.394em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >(to show the Nasrid home property has been lost). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4171em; top: 17.6739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">•</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.468em; top: 17.6737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.003em"
              >When the Nasrid Kingdom surrenders, the Spanish &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.4783em; top: 18.6237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0952em"
              >player receives 1 VP for </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.107em"
              >End of the Reconquista</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.107em"
              >. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.4783em; top: 19.5737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_270" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >Place the corresponding marker on the Spanish &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.4783em; top: 20.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Player Card. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9168em; top: 19.5941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_344" style="word-spacing: 0.128em"
              >Morisco Uprising: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_487" style="word-spacing: 0.1246em"
              >During the Winter Phase, spaces with &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 20.5441em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.053em"
              >Morisco Uprising </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0529em"
              >markers or Morisco regulars under Nasrid &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 21.4941em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >control may regain their home status. See Winter Phase Effects
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 22.4441em; z-index: 3190"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_27" style="word-spacing: 0.0085em"
              >from Moriscos below. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4162em; top: 21.7239em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• When</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0239em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.019em"
              >the Nasrid Kingdom surrenders, the Muslim player re- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0828em; top: 22.6739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0614em"
              >ceives VPs based on the home spaces of Castile and/or Aragon
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0828em; top: 23.6239em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >he currently controls (22.1). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9168em; top: 23.6443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >Nasrid Kingdom Surrender: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.006em"
              >All Nasrid home spaces which &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 24.5943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >are neither marked with a Morisco Uprising marker, nor have
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 25.5443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_104" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >a Morisco regular present are marked with normal Spanish
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 26.4943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0597em"
              >control markers. The special Spanish control markers are no
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 27.4443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.036em"
              >longer used. Furthermore, from this moment on these Nasrid
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 28.3943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >non-key home spaces are considered Castilian home spaces.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.9108em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_27" style="word-spacing: -0.0014em"
              >Control Markers in Nasrid Home Spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.16em; top: 26.2061em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >As the Reconquista progresses, Nasrid non-key home &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.2051em; top: 27.1561em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0689em"
              >spaces can lose their home property for the Nasrid &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.2051em; top: 28.1061em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0592em"
              >player. This only happens if the Spanish player gains
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.2051em; top: 29.0561em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0099em"
              >control of the space, and therefore there is a special
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.2051em; top: 30.0061em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1159em"
              >Spanish control marker used only in Nasrid home &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 30.9561em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: 0.0644em"
              >territory. To show this transition, control marker usage is
              altered &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 31.9061em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >on these spaces. Nasrid non-key home spaces should always be in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 32.8561em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1006em"
              >one of these control states, which will affect their property as
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 33.8061em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >home space: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.6806em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.006em"
              >Morisco Uprising &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8519em; top: 30.9268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.065em"
              >The </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_186">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.0634em"
              >orisco </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_186">U</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_172"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0633em"
              >prising </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >event causes a special revolt &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8646em; top: 31.8768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >that results in the placement of two Morisco regular &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8646em; top: 32.8268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_488" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >units in Spanish-controlled Nasrid home spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8646em; top: 33.7768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.043em"
              >(spaces printed on the map in the Nasrid color). The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8646em; top: 34.7268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0411em"
              >Morisco Uprising rules below apply to any Morisco &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 35.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >regular units on the map that have been placed by event card
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2499em; top: 36.6268em; z-index: 3791"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">(</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0058em"
              >orisco </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">U</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0063em"
              >prising </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.006em"
              >or </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0056em"
              >ity </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_489">ta</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0037em"
              >e </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131">ebels</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: -0.0025em"
              >) or because of the Sur- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 37.5768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >render of the Nasrid Kingdom (22.1). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.417em; top: 35.0063em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0241em"
              >No Control Marker: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >This space is under Nasrid control and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 35.9563em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >still serves as a Nasrid home space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.417em; top: 37.1565em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_490" style="word-spacing: -0.0025em"
              >Special Spanish Control Marker: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >Control of this space has &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 38.1065em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >been gained by Spain from the Nasrid during thi</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_491">s</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_37">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >ction Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 39.0565em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_225" style="word-spacing: 0.071em"
              >The space will lose its home property for the Nasrid unless
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 40.0065em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >control is taken from Spain before the end of the current Ac-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 40.9565em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_225" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >tion Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 38.9432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0552em"
              >Morisco regular and militia units are limited to the number of
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 39.8932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >provided in the force pool. If the Nasrid power has not
              surrendered, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 40.8432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0191em"
              >the Morisco regular units on the map are considered Nasrid for
              all &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 41.7932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.052em"
              >purposes, including having the ability to restore the home
              property &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 42.7432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >to Nasrid spaces that had lost it. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.417em; top: 42.1566em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0216em"
              >Normal Spanish Control Marker: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.024em"
              >Control of this space was &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 43.1066em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0409em"
              >gained by Spain in a previous turn and this space has lost its
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0836em; top: 44.0566em; z-index: 1625"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: 0.0081em"
              >Nasrid home property. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 44.1096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1091em"
              >Follow the steps below to resolve the event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.1092em"
              >orisco </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">U</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131">prising &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 45.0596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >when that card is played or if the surrender of the Nasrid
              Kingdom &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 46.0096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >has triggered a Morisco uprising: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.417em; top: 45.2568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0202em"
              >Nasrid Control Marker: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0171em"
              >This space has lost its Nasrid home &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 46.2068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.029em"
              >property (and therefore had a normal Spanish control marker
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 47.1568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >when the Nasrid controlled it) but has been recaptured by the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 48.1068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1051em"
              >Nasrids. The explicit placement of a control marker on this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 49.0568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.021em"
              >space shows that while under Nasrid control, it does not serve
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 50.0068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >as a Nasrid home space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9997em; top: 47.2098em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.165em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >Draw a caravan resource from the pool, putting back resources
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.9995em; top: 48.1598em; z-index: 4335"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >as necessary until you have drawn one that awards C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_492">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_492">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9997em; top: 49.3599em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.1093em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Place (or move from another space) two Morisco regular units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9995em; top: 50.3099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0629em"
              >of value 1 (there are only two such units in the force pool)
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9995em; top: 51.2599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >in one or two unoccupied Nasrid home spaces controlled by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9995em; top: 52.2099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0672em"
              >Spain (spaces printed on the map in the Nasrid color). The
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9995em; top: 53.1599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Nasrid power gains control of each of these spaces by placing
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9995em; top: 54.1099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0201em"
              >a Nasrid control marker (remember that if either of them is a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9995em; top: 55.0599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.028em"
              >key, it will directly obtain its status as a home space, as these
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9995em; top: 56.0099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >spaces never lose it). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.417em; top: 51.207em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0726em"
              >Control Marker From Power Other Than Spain: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0633em"
              >This other &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 52.157em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >major power has gained control of the space. If recaptured by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 53.107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >the Nasrid, this control marker is removed and the space returns
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0836em; top: 54.057em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >to the “No Control Marker” state. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.3433em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_50" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >Control Marker State Changes &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.5895em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >The following events cause updates to the control marker on a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 57.5395em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Nasrid non-key home space: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 57.2101em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_470" style="word-spacing: -0.0623em"
              >c) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0623em"
              >Place (or move from another space) up to two </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_188" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >Morisco Uprising &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 58.1601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >markers (there are only two of these markers) on unoccupied
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 59.1101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >non-key Nasrid spaces (spaces printed on the map in the Nasrid
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 60.0601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1156em"
              >color) controlled by Spain. The Nasrid power gains control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 58.7396em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_123" style="word-spacing: -0.0641em"
              >Spanish Control Space: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >If Spain gains control of such a space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 59.6896em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.038em"
              >during the Action Phase, add a special Spanish control marker
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 60.6396em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >if no control marker was present. However if a Nasrid control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_43" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">44 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 5.164em">
            <span class="stl_494 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Morisco Uprising </span
            ><span
              class="stl_208 stl_17 stl_422"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0482em"
              >- EXAMPLE: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.1776em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.0249em"
              >The Muslim now has 2 Morisco regulars and 2 uprising mark-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.1276em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0818em"
              >ers to place. Morisco regulars can be placed in any Spanish-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.0776em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: -0.0603em"
              >controlled space that was originally a Nasrid home space. When
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.0276em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.1158em"
              >placed the Nasrid gains immediate control of the space (and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.9776em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.0138em"
              >remember keys are especially useful since they immediately be-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.9276em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0069em"
              >come friendly home spaces once again). One regular</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2428em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0094em"
              >is placed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.8776em; z-index: 2472"
          >
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0601em"
              >in Gibralta</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_194">r</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.05em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0601em"
              >nd the other in Setenil. The one in Gibraltar gains &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.8276em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_27" style="word-spacing: 0.0046em"
              >1VP and a square control marker is placed there. As a key, this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.7776em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_267" style="word-spacing: -0.0577em"
              >space could never lose its home space property, so the Nasrid can
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.7276em; z-index: 2655"
          >
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.041em"
              >once again construct units in Gibralta</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_194">r</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.051em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_102">T</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.0461em"
              >he regular in Setenil &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.6776em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: 0.0235em"
              >grants control of the space but does not restore its home space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.6276em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0032em"
              >abilities, so a hexagonal Nasrid control marker is placed here.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 18.6612em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0126em"
              >In the Action Phase the situation in the Kingdom of Granada is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 19.6112em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >as shown on the map. The French player in his impulse plays the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 20.5612em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >event </span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_13">M</span
            ><span class="stl_495 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.0357em"
              >orisco </span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_102">U</span
            ><span class="stl_495 stl_17 stl_173">prisin</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0454em"
              >g </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.0397em"
              >to help his Muslim ally. The Spanish &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.5833em; top: 21.5112em; z-index: 1826"
          >
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_80">playe</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_496">r</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.053em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_99">k</span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >nowing that he can recruit militias in Alhama (thanks to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 22.4612em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_167" style="word-spacing: -0.0604em"
              >the event played earlier), had previously kept only a few
              garrison &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 23.4112em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: -0.0583em"
              >forces in Malaga and Alhama, while recruiting an army with the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 24.3612em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0209em"
              >Grand Captain in Seville. Now the play of this event can make
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 25.3112em">
            <span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_80">thin</span
            ><span class="stl_495 stl_17 stl_13">g</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0701em"
              >s dif f </span
            ><span class="stl_495 stl_17 stl_115">i</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >cult ri</span
            ><span class="stl_495 stl_17 stl_13">g</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >ht in these spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 26.5114em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_497" style="word-spacing: 0.1193em"
              >To </span
            ><span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_277">b</span
            ><span
              class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_214"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >egin executing the </span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_277">M</span
            ><span
              class="stl_495 stl_17 stl_302"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0613em"
              >orisco </span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_302">U</span
            ><span class="stl_495 stl_17 stl_498">prisin</span
            ><span class="stl_306 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0766em"
              >g </span
            ><span
              class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_499"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0538em"
              >event, a naval resource &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.5833em; top: 27.4614em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >that awards 3 CP is drawn by the Muslim. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.057em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0035em"
              >Finally, the Nasrid places the uprising markers: in Zahara and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.007em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0562em"
              >Sohail. He gains control of these spaces (but not the home space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.957em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_126" style="word-spacing: 0.065em"
              >property); Nasrid control markers are placed in those spaces.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.907em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >Zahara being a strategic space awards 1VP to the Nasrid. These
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.857em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0463em"
              >spaces with Morisco Uprising markers act as Unrest against all
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.807em">
            <span class="stl_209 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >players other than the Muslim. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 42.3434em; z-index: 128"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.1008em"
              >of each of these spaces by placing a Nasrid control marker.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 43.2935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0682em"
              >Spaces with a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.069em"
              >Morisco Uprising </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0688em"
              >marker act as if they are in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 44.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0367em"
              >Unrest for all powers except the Nasrid. These markers can be
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 45.1934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0401em"
              >removed by the Spanish player (only) using the usual rules for
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 46.1434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >removing unrest. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 42.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >If the Nasrid power has surrendered, use of Morisco units is
              further &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 43.2935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >limited as follows: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 44.4936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.2316em"
              >• Each</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0052em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.01em"
              >turn, the Muslim player may only use CPs from a single
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 45.4436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0039em"
              >resource (never a card) to recruit Morisco militias, recruit the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 46.3936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >Nasrid corsair, move Morisco units, and/or use such units to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 47.3436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: 0.0036em"
              >control spaces, assault, initiate piracy, etc. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7502em; top: 47.5099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >The following restrictions apply to Morisco units at all times:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 48.71em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Moriscos</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0048em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >regulars can never be built by spending CPs. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 48.5438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0963em"
              >• Once the Muslim player has used a resource to act with the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 49.4938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.021em"
              >Morisco, place the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0118em"
              >Morisco Activated </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.021em"
              >marker on the space of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 50.4438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0159em"
              >the Muslim Player Card as a reminder that these units cannot
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 51.3938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >be activated again this turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 49.9102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: 0.1344em"
              >• Moriscos units (both regulars and militia) can only move,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 50.8602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.066em"
              >control spaces, and assault into original Nasrid home spaces
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 51.8102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0129em"
              >(spaces printed on the map in the Nasrid color), regardless of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 52.7602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >who controls them. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 52.5939em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.2339em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.059em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Morisco militia or the Nasrid corsair are recruited, they must
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 53.544em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.044em"
              >be added to a Nasrid-controlled home key or a Nasrid non-key
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 54.4939em; z-index: 1334"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: 0.0055em"
              >space with no control marker. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 53.9604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_335" style="word-spacing: 0.2579em"
              >• In</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.071em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_399" style="word-spacing: -0.0613em"
              >winter, Moriscos units remain in place and never return home,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 54.9104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0481em"
              >except if they are part of a besieging formation. In such a case,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 55.8604em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >they are moved to the nearest fortified space they control (or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 56.8104em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >non-fortified if they do not control any). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 55.6941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.2358em"
              >• Boabdil</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0599em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >can command Morisco regulars and recruited Morisco &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 56.6441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0572em"
              >militias but never in the same formation as Nort</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_500">h</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0572em"
              >frican units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 57.5941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0909em"
              >(although they can share formation with Nasrid units exiled
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 58.5441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >with Boabdil during the surrender of the Nasrid Kingdom).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 59.7443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Assaults</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0292em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >by Morisco units can be made during this impulse on &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 60.6943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >spaces that were not under siege at the start of the impulse.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_44" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">45 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_126" style="word-spacing: -0.005em"
              >Winter Phase Eﬀects from Moriscos: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0082em"
              >Ottoman Support &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0625em"
              >If, in the Winter Phase, a Morisco regular unit is present in a
              Nasrid &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0412em"
              >non-key home space marked with a Nasrid control marker, the fol-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.4237em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >lowing two effects are applied: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0539em"
              >The North African power may receive Ottoman regulars as rein-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0499em"
              >forcements from the events </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: 0.0545em"
              >ttomans </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ei</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0587em"
              >e </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_228">tranto</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: -0.0047em"
              >, A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131">lgiers &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.4237em; z-index: 2359"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_61">R</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_172"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0595em"
              >egency </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0612em"
              >and </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_186">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_39">ttoman</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_172">-V</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_172"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0799em"
              >enetian </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_502">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_128">ar</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.076em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >They have the same color &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.3737em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >as the Nort</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_295">h</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_37">A</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >frican units but a different silhouette to identify them.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.3237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >If these units are eliminated, they cannot be recruited again. If
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.2737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0628em"
              >Ottomans take Otranto, a North African formation whose size is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.2237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >determined by a single leader may winter there. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 8.6239em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: 0.2377em"
              >• That</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0599em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >space automatically recovers its Nasrid home space status
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 9.5739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >(remove the Nasrid control marker from the space). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 10.774em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.2321em"
              >• Add</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0349em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0401em"
              >two Morisco Militia units to this space (if available in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 11.724em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >force pool). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.5108em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0062em"
              >e Algiers Regency &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.0904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.0186em"
              >If, in the Winter Phase, any </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.017em"
              >Morisco Uprising </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0167em"
              >markers remain on &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.0405em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >the map, roll one die for each such space: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.757em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0472em"
              >The Algiers space comes into play with the other Berber spaces at
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.707em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_503" style="word-spacing: -0.0478em"
              >the beginning of Turn 4. It does so as a special independent
              space, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.657em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0171em"
              >hence its gray color on its bottom half. No power can control
              this &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0644em"
              >space while it is independent. When the mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_468">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_504">lgiers &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.557em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_203">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_505" style="word-spacing: 0.1235em"
              >egency </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_137" style="word-spacing: 0.1111em"
              >is played, Algiers becomes a Berber home space. At &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.507em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0004em"
              >this time: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 15.2406em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.2322em"
              >• On</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0582em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.053em"
              >a roll of 4, 5, or 6, remove the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.053em"
              >Morisco Uprising </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">marker &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 16.1906em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >and the Nasrid control marker; the space is once again a Nasrid
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 17.1406em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0092em"
              >home space. Add one Morisco Militia there. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 18.3408em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.039em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0339em"
              >the roll is 1, 2, or 3, the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.034em"
              >Morisco Uprising </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0338em"
              >marker remains &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 19.2908em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in that space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 19.7072em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Displace</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0221em"
              >any non-North African units from Algiers. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 20.9074em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.2321em"
              >• Add</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0139em"
              >four Ottoman regulars to Algiers. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.6572em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0602em"
              >Finally, if the Nasrid kingdom has surrendered but there are
              Moris- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.6072em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0499em"
              >cos (regulars or militias) on the map, the Muslim player draws a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.5572em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >caravan resource from the pool, putting back resources as
              necessary &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.5072em; z-index: 885"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >until they have drawn one that awards C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 22.1075em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1299em"
              >• Add the Barbarossa naval leader to Algiers, remove Kemal
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 23.0575em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: 0.0037em"
              >Reis from play, and add three corsairs to this space.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 24.2577em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: 0.2437em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0639em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.0673em"
              >Muslim player gains 2 V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_475">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_21">f</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_21">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_92">r</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_42">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70">lgiers</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_506">.</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_42">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.0629em"
              >dd a square control &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 25.2077em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_188" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >marker from the Nort</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_507">h</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_508">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >frican key section of the Muslim Player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 26.1577em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0139em"
              >Card to the Algiers space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.7942em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_11" style="word-spacing: -0.0023em"
              >Surrender of the Nasrid Kingdom of Granada &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.0404em; z-index: 966"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0039em"
              >See 22.1 for details of this major power’s surrender.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.5241em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >Now complete </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0301em"
              >lgiers </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0315em"
              >egency </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0263em"
              >event. This mandatory event is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.4741em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0004em"
              >required to occur by the winter of Turn 5. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.7772em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_67" style="word-spacing: -0.0016em"
              >20.2 North African Alliance (Sultanate of Fez and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01 stl_75"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.9772em; z-index: 1033"
          >
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0173em"
              >Berber Sultanate of Tlemcen) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.7608em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_201" style="word-spacing: -0.018em"
              >Ceuta, Strait Control &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.4775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.023em"
              >e North African Alliance. </span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_391">T</span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_56" style="word-spacing: -0.0018em"
              >wo Brotherly Kingdoms. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.007em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0649em"
              >This important control point guarding the Strait of Gibraltar is
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.957em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0312em"
              >Portuguese home space. The Sultanate of Fez begins the game at
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.907em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.017em"
              >war with Portugal, but not the Nasrid Kingdom. Whenever Ceuta
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.857em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_242" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >is controlled by one of the Muslim powers, the Muslim player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.807em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >gains these benefits: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.7237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0176em"
              >The North African power is the combination of two historical sul-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.6737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0259em"
              >tanates: the Sultanate of Fez and the Berber Sultanate of
              Tlemcen. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.6237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0292em"
              >The Sultanate of Fez participates immediately on Turn 1 while the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.5737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0391em"
              >Berber Sultanate of Tlemcen enters the game at the beginning of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0708em"
              >Turn 4. At the start of Turn 4 the Berber Home card is added to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >those available to the Muslim player and Berber home spaces and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.4237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0534em"
              >units (out of play until that time) are added to the game. These
              new &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.3737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >spaces, units and Home cards simply augment the existing North
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.3237em; z-index: 1559"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0026em"
              >African power and are not considered to be an additional power.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 36.0072em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0161em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >Muslim receives a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_179" style="word-spacing: 0.029em"
              >+1 Card </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0127em"
              >marker (placed in the ruler’s &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 36.9572em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >box on his Player Card). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 38.1574em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.2438em"
              >• Muslims</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_182" style="word-spacing: -0.0598em"
              >Naos gain a +1 die roll modifier on the Terra Incognita
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 39.1074em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0124em"
              >exploration chart for zones 1, 2, 3, A and B. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 40.3075em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.2321em"
              >• Add</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0381em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >a fifth Muslim settlement marker into their force pool if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 41.2575em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >you have not already done so. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.6901em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Follow the following procedure at the start of Turn 4:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 41.8903em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Place</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0147em"
              >one North African regular in Tlemcen. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 43.0904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Place</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >one militia in Oran and one militia in Bejaía. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.6239em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_509" style="word-spacing: 0.1274em"
              >Ceuta’s benefits are not cumulative with those of Gibraltar but
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.5739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >are a second chance to obtain them if the capture of Gibraltar
              was &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.5239em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0101em"
              >unsuccessful before the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0097em"
              >uley </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">H</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">ac</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_173">é</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >n </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ei</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0094em"
              >es </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">Z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315" style="word-spacing: 0.0099em"
              >ahara </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0101em"
              >event was &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.4739em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0231em"
              >played. Unlike when Gibraltar triggers these benefits, the first
              two &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.4239em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0018em"
              >abilities listed in this section only apply while Ceuta is
              controlled &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.3739em; z-index: 4044"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >by the Muslim player. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 44.2906em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Place</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0601em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0489em"
              >in the North African force pool a 2-value infantry unit
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 45.2406em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >and a naval squadron. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 46.4408em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0301em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0177em"
              >Muslim player gains 3 VPs: 1 VP for Constantine plus 2
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 47.3908em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.019em"
              >VP for control of Tlemcen. Add a square control marker from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 48.3408em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0629em"
              >the Nort</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_206">h</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >frican key section of the Muslim Player Card to the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 49.2908em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0069em"
              >Tlemcen space (see 22.3 and “North African Keys” below).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.6608em; z-index: 4052"
          >
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.049em"
              >Sahara </span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_134">T</span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_13">r</span
            ><span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >ade Caravans &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.907em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0171em"
              >The Muslims controlled the trade routes that brought spices,
              gold, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.857em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.025em"
              >and ivory for the European market to the North African ports. At
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.807em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0391em"
              >the beginning of each turn the Muslim player places one randomly
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.757em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0231em"
              >chosen caravan resource in the caravan trade route box directed
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.707em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0098em"
              >Marrakesh and another in the box directed to Fez. If this is Turn
              4 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.657em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0129em"
              >or later also add one to the box directed to Tlemcen. In the
              Winter &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.0533em"
              >Phase, these resources may reach the Muslim player’s hand (18.7).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 50.6572em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_218" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >Starting on Turn 4, Nort</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_510">h</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_69">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >frican units may be built in a home space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.6072em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0217em"
              >of either of the two North African sultanates. On the map you
              will &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.5572em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >notice that each kingdom has a slightly different shade of color
              for &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.5072em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0058em"
              >its home spaces; this difference is to identify the spaces that
              enter &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.4572em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >with the arrival of the Berber Sultanate. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_45" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">46 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0421em"
              >If at any point during the game, Portugal controls </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.042em"
              >all </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.042em"
              >of these ports &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2942em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: -0.0637em"
              >for the first time, he directly earns 3 VPs for Portuguese
              Supremacy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.2442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.0555em"
              >of the Atlantic Coast of Africa. However, these 3 VPs are lost if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.1942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1009em"
              >Portugal and the North African Alliance sign peace at any time
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.1442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0134em"
              >after the achievement of those 3 VPs, even if they were not at
              war &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.0942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >when they were achieved. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_274" style="word-spacing: -0.0063em"
              >Tunis, Anfa, and Rome: Target Cities of the Muslim &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0398em"
              >If the mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0249em"
              >lgiers </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0245em"
              >egency </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0252em"
              >has been played and the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0508em"
              >Muslim controls the independent city of Tunis, that city grants 1
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.4237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0138em"
              >additional VP to the Muslim. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.7901em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0153em"
              >The port city of Anfa, the most important port on the African At-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.7401em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0048em"
              >lantic coast, grants 1VP if controlled by the Muslim.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.3814em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_11" style="word-spacing: -0.0025em"
              >Foreign Support for the Beltranejos Cause &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.1065em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >Both Muslim powers are perpetually at war with the minor power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.0565em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.055em"
              >the Papacy. If the Muslim player gains control of Rome for the
              first &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.0065em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >time, award a </span
            ><span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0623em"
              >5 VP </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.063em"
              >marker to the Muslim. If such a conquest of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.9565em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0261em"
              >Rome occurs, all Christian major powers enter a state of
              perpetual &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.9065em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >war against both Muslim powers (see Papacy in 21.7 for details).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.6276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >See 20.4 for details on Supporting the Cause of Beltranejos.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.3644em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_201" style="word-spacing: -0.0029em"
              >20.4 Beltranejos &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.9442em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0608em"
              >Beltranejo Units And Home Card: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0718em"
              >Beltranejos units are under &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.8942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0313em"
              >the control of the Portuguese player. Beltranejos units and
              Portu- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.8442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0938em"
              >guese units are always allied as long as the Peace of Alcaçovas
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.7942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0913em"
              >has not been signed. The Portuguese player also gets the use of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.7442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1068em"
              >the Beltranejos Home card as long as this limited Major Power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.6942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >has not surrendered. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.1942em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0022em"
              >Bejaía and Oran in the Cisneros Regency &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.4404em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0544em"
              >With the arrival of Cardinal Cisneros, the fortified spaces of
              Bejaía &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.3904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >and Oran became controlled by the Spanish. If the Muslim player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.3404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0082em"
              >gains military control of either of these two spaces after this
              time, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.2904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0044em"
              >they gain 1 VP for each space for as long as it is controlled.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.9814em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_308" style="word-spacing: 0.0057em"
              >Peace of Alcaçovas &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.5775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0077em"
              >North African´s Keys &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.2276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >This peace treaty puts an end to the confrontation between
              Portugal &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.1776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >and Castile for the succession of the Castilian crown, although
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.1276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0969em"
              >several Beltranejos nobles will refuse to surrender and continue
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.0776em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.022em"
              >the fight. This Peace can be activated in the game when the
              P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">eace &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.0276em; z-index: 3310"
          >
            <span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191" style="word-spacing: -0.0314em"
              >of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315">lcaço</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_317">v</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0349em"
              >s </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0248em"
              >event card is played or by a diplomatic agreement &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.9776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.028em"
              >between Portugal and Castile in the Diplomacy Phase of Turn 3 or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.9276em; z-index: 3429"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_275" style="word-spacing: -0.0424em"
              >later. The </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0763em"
              >eace of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_315">lcaço</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_317">v</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >s </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0481em"
              >is the only way Spain and Portugal &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.8776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0209em"
              >can end the war they are in at the start of the game. If later in
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.8276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.007em"
              >game they are in a new war with each other, peace deals are made
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.7776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >between these powers as normal. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.8237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0046em"
              >If two or more North African home keys are not controlled by the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.7737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0392em"
              >Muslim in the card draw phase, subtract 1 from the Muslim ruler’s
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.7237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Charisma, placing a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_411" style="word-spacing: -0.0444em"
              >–1 Card </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >marker on his Player Card that he will &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.6737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >keep until he regains control again. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.0401em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0561em"
              >Each North African home key gives the Muslim player 2 VP for its
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.9901em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0154em"
              >control, as indicated on his Player Card. North African control
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.9401em; z-index: 1252"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_33" style="word-spacing: -0.0593em"
              >all of these keys is necessary to be eligible for an automatic
              victory. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.6772em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_60" style="word-spacing: 0.0014em"
              >20.3 Portugal &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.144em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0521em"
              >IMMEDIATE EFFECTS: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >The signing of the Peace of Alcaçovas &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.094em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >has the following immediate effects: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.1775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0131em"
              >School of Sagres, Henry the Navigator &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.149em; top: 33.507em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0424em"
              >Play of this event grants Portugal 1 VP and allows them
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.145em; top: 34.457em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.1004em"
              >to circumvent some of the normal Turn 1 and Turn 2 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.145em; top: 35.407em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >limitations on the Exploration Map: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 34.2941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Portugal</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0011em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0042em"
              >and the Beltranejos are no longer allies (though they
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 35.2441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0602em"
              >are still both controlled by the Portuguese player, who may play
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 36.1941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0679em"
              >“Combat” and “Response” cards on behalf of either power).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 37.1441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Immediately displace (12.5) all Portuguese units in Beltranejos-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 38.0941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >controlled spaces and vice versa. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_464" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 36.607em">
            <span class="stl_512 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2509em"
