            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0417em"
              >astile </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0452em"
              >plit </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0429em"
              >(required in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.3934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_66" style="word-spacing: -0.0619em"
              >the Winter of Turn 5). Note that Nasrid home spaces are
              considered &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >Castilian home spaces for the purposes of this rule if the
              Nasrids &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >have surrendered. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 44.4105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Units</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0758em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0739em"
              >in Ferdinand’s stack may be displaced (12.5). Flip the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 45.3605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0274em"
              >Fernando counter to its red reverse side only (Crown of Ara-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 46.3105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1149em"
              >gon). If the stack is not in a Castilian home space, start by
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 47.2605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >displacing all Castilian units to the nearest controlled
              Castilian &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 48.2105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0638em"
              >home space. Then, if the remaining stack is in a Castilian home
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 49.1605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >space—or in a non-Castilian home space but the Spanish player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 50.1105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0101em"
              >voluntarily chooses to displace the remaining units—displace
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 51.0605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0092em"
              >them to a controlled Aragonese home space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 52.1775em; z-index: 2153"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_528" style="word-spacing: 0.2748em"
              >• Now,</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0274em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.006em"
              >displace all Castilian units in an Aragonese home space
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 53.1275em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0871em"
              >to the nearest Castilian home space. Then do the same with
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 54.0775em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0929em"
              >Aragonese units in Castilian home spaces. Units in the four
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 55.0275em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >spaces on Sicily (Palermo, Etna, Syracuse, and Messina) ignore
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 55.9775em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >the displacements in this bullet. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_48" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">49 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_36" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >La Mesta &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.233em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_158" style="word-spacing: 0.0077em"
              >20.7 France &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.1147em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >The Catholic Monarchs granted important privileges to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.7333em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_216" style="word-spacing: 0.0033em"
              >Consolidating the Power of the Monarch &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.125em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0612em"
              >this organization of sheep owners, since the sale of wool
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.125em; top: 7.4237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_110" style="word-spacing: 0.1227em"
              >to Europe brought great resources to the crown. The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.125em; top: 8.3737em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >Mesta </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0453em"
              >marker is placed as detailed in 8.2, and grants the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 7.3618em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0496em"
              >HISTORICAL NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >The fifteenth century was a weak time &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 8.3118em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.042em"
              >for the French monarchy, having numerous troops tied up in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.7083em; top: 9.2618em; z-index: 2481"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130">Hundre</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_469">d</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_530">Y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_167">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_339" style="word-spacing: -0.058em"
              >ars War with England. Late in that time, however, the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 10.2118em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0151em"
              >kings were able to strengthen their position by absorbing noble
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 11.1618em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0537em"
              >titles and locking up the loyalty of the main noble houses. Thus,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 12.1118em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0429em"
              >the French rulers have lower Charismas but the French player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 13.0618em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >is able to gain back those cards through ensuring the loyalty of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 14.0118em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the nobles and controlling the Roussillon region. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 9.3237em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >following benefits: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 10.5239em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_470" style="word-spacing: 0.2536em"
              >• Each</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0682em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_277" style="word-spacing: -0.0616em"
              >turn in the Winter Phase, the Spanish player will roll on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 11.4739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_210" style="word-spacing: -0.0438em"
              >Mesta Trade Table (18.8) to see if resources are received, using
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 12.4239em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_167" style="word-spacing: -0.0283em"
              >the modifiers described there. If a Foreign War with Brittany is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 13.3739em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: 0.0323em"
              >active in the Winter Phase, the Spanish player will roll on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 14.3239em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_354" style="word-spacing: 0.0013em"
              >Mesta Trade Table one additional time for this war (20.9).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 15.524em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• During</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.082em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.0726em"
              >the Action Phase, if at the end of a Spanish player’s
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 16.474em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1219em"
              >impulse, Castile is supporting with at least two militias the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 17.424em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_66" style="word-spacing: 0.0196em"
              >Foreign War of Brittany, he can gain an additional roll on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 18.374em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_126" style="word-spacing: 0.0761em"
              >Mesta Trade Table with the modifiers applicable at that mo</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_126" style="word-spacing: 0.0761em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 19.3241em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0646em"
              >ment. This bonus roll can only happen once per turn and is done
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 20.2741em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0769em"
              >by substituting the opportunity to extend the impulse with a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 21.2241em; z-index: 881"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0708em"
              >resource. The mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_62">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_62" style="word-spacing: -0.0627em"
              >rade </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_21">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_65">i</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_531">v</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_39">a</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_453"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0402em"
              >lry with </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_62">E</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_21">ngland &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 22.1741em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.0017em"
              >also guarantees the Spanish a roll on the Mesta Trade Table.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.7212em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0749em"
              >The six great noble houses of France (Anjou, Alençon, Orleans,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.6712em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0901em"
              >Bourbon, Armagnac and Foix-Navarre) can each provide a card
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.6212em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0243em"
              >to the French player if sufficiently loyal to the French ruler.
              Each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.5712em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0251em"
              >noble house has a row on the map with a track of up to six
              squares &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.5212em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >filled with values ranging from 0 to 5. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 32.9946em; top: 20.8879em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1203em"
              >The French player may spend 1 CP on the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.0041em; top: 21.8379em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0609em"
              >Consolidate Power </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0608em"
              >action to gain a level of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.0041em; top: 22.7879em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.019em"
              >loyalty with one of these houses; the number &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 33.0041em; top: 23.7379em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_294" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >within each box represents the maximum &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 24.6879em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0409em"
              >number that the French player can roll on a single die during the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 25.6379em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Card Draw Phase in order to gain a card from that house.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.9105em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_36" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >20.6 Aragon &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.4108em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >One Crown for Several Kingdoms &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.657em; z-index: 1034"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >The kings of the Crown o</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_58">f</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_84">A</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0628em"
              >ragon had under their command diffe</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_532">r</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_532">- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0078em"
              >ent kingdoms with their own institutions and particularities.
              Each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.557em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >kingdom may provide a card to the Crown o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_444">f</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_67">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >ragon (and therefore &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.507em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0259em"
              >to the hand of the Spanish player) but receipt of that card is
              vari- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.457em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.061em"
              >able since the courts of each kingdom were not always sensitive
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.407em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: 0.0068em"
              >to the King’s requests. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2639em; top: 27.0043em">
            <span class="stl_340 stl_17 stl_422" style="word-spacing: -0.0662em"
              >EXAMPLE: </span
            ><span class="stl_342 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: 0.0045em"
              >If a noble house is at a loyalty of 4 it awards a card
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 27.9543em">
            <span class="stl_342 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: 0.006em"
              >with a result of 1-4. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 29.3207em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0617em"
              >The French player earns 1 VP the first time he reaches loyalty
              level &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 30.2707em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >5 in each row of this table. Loyalty levels can be lowered by
              events, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 31.2207em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0653em"
              >although this never causes the loss of the V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_183">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_470">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >ward mentioned above &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 32.1707em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >if France was already at level 5. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.7734em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0452em"
              >The Spanish player always receives the Aragonese Home card and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.7234em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0117em"
              >one card for the Kingdom of Aragon itself (two cards on Turn 1).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.6734em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >Receipt of additional cards is dependent on three factors:
              whether &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.6234em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0749em"
              >or not this is an odd- or even-numbered turn, control of specific
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.5734em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >spaces, and successfully making a roll on one die, as follows:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 33.5371em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_533" style="word-spacing: 0.1269em"
              >The House of Foix Navarre measures its loyalty differently. If
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 34.4871em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.052em"
              >France gains political control of the Pamplona space through as-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 35.4371em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0139em"
              >sault, the house is considered a level 3 for the purposes of
              rolling &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 36.3871em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_65" style="word-spacing: -0.0594em"
              >for cards. If France allies with Navarra by diplomacy,
              Foix-Navarre &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 37.3371em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >is considered to have level 5 for the purposes of that die roll.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 11.2935em; top: 38.0682em">
            <span class="stl_461 stl_17 stl_411">Turns &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 15.0268em; top: 38.0682em">
            <span class="stl_461 stl_17 stl_13">Required &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 19.4175em; top: 38.0682em">
            <span class="stl_461 stl_17 stl_13">Required &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 20.1981em; top: 39.0182em">
            <span class="stl_461 stl_17 stl_80">Roll &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 38.7035em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.007em"
              >For a house to be eligible to grant a card, France must control
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 39.6535em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0351em"
              >most significant space related to that family (</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0991em"
              >Exception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0349em"
              >The most &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 40.6035em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0619em"
              >significant space for the house o</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_323">f</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_101">A</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >lencon is beyond the game map: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2496em; top: 41.5535em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0627em"
              >that house always grants a roll for card). The associated spaces
              are: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 6.0755em; top: 39.0182em">
            <span class="stl_461 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 1.2078em"
              >KINGDOM Received &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 15.2479em; top: 39.0182em">
            <span class="stl_461 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >Space </span
            ><span class="stl_455 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >† &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.3184em; top: 40.2338em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Aragon </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >* &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.4546em; top: 41.4426em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_83">V</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">a</span
            ><span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_80">lencia &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.24em; top: 42.6578em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Catalonia &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.3596em; top: 43.873em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_126">Mallorca &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.4395em; top: 45.0883em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Sardinia &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.9707em; top: 46.3035em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_80">Sicily &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7184em; top: 40.2338em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">All &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7191em; top: 41.449em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">All &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.6854em; top: 40.2338em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">none &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 19.2756em; top: 40.2338em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">automatic &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 15.0845em; top: 41.449em; z-index: 1701"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">a</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">lencia &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 14.8407em; top: 42.6642em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Barcelona &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.018em; top: 43.8794em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Mallorca &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.1716em; top: 45.0946em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Cagliari &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.1289em; top: 46.3098em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Palermo &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 14.8399em; top: 47.525em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Perpignan &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 20.3206em; top: 41.449em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">4-6 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 20.3206em; top: 42.6642em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">3-6 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 20.6539em; top: 43.8794em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">6</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.7191em; top: 42.6642em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">All &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.579em; top: 43.049em">
            <span class="stl_456 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >Noble House &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.9266em; top: 44.2579em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Armagnac &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 31.3683em; top: 45.4731em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_80">Orleans &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 36.5561em; top: 43.049em">
            <span class="stl_456 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Required Space </span
            ><span class="stl_534 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >† &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 38.5812em; top: 44.2642em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Auch &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.5426em; top: 43.8794em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131">Odd &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.5426em; top: 45.0946em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131">Odd &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.408em; top: 46.3098em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Even &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 11.4088em; top: 47.525em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Even &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 20.3198em; top: 45.0946em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">5-6 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 20.3198em; top: 46.3098em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">4-6 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 20.6539em; top: 47.525em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">6</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 38.202em; top: 45.4794em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Orleans &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 38.2218em; top: 46.6946em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Poitiers &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 38.6255em; top: 47.9098em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_409">Lyon &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 31.6581em; top: 46.6883em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_131">Anjou &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 6.1268em; top: 47.5187em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Roussillon &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 31.214em; top: 47.9035em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Borboun &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 48.9227em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_18">*</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 49.9892em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_18">†</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.7498em; top: 48.9227em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Aragon always grants two cards on Turn 1. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.4215em; top: 49.1187em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_87">Foix-Navarre &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 31.3256em; top: 50.3339em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13">Alencon &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 37.8489em; top: 49.1251em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Pamplona &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 38.7823em; top: 50.3403em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">N/A &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.7498em; top: 49.9892em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0092em"
              >As a reminder, these spaces are indicated on the map with a
              shield &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.7498em; top: 50.8892em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0137em"
              >of the crown of Aragon. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.7379em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_18">†</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.2498em; top: 51.7379em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0092em"
              >As a reminder, these spaces are indicated on the map with a
              shield &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.2498em; top: 52.6379em">
            <span class="stl_29 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >of each noble house. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.2227em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_14" style="word-spacing: -0.0026em"
              >Dynastic Rights on Naples and Roussillon &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.4689em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >Aragon wins special VPs for maintaining political control of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.4189em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Kingdom of Naples and/or the County of Roussillon. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.0508em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.04em"
              >Finally, if in the Card Draw Phase France controls the Perpignan
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.0008em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0559em"
              >space in Roussillon, France may receive an extra card. If France
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.9508em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0281em"
              >has fewer than three houses at level 5 loyalty, receipt of the
              card is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.9008em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0321em"
              >automatic. If three or more houses are loyal (which diminishes
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.8508em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >importance of Roussillon), the French player rolls a die and
              receives &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.8008em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0642em"
              >an extra card on a roll of 1 or 2. The house of Foix-Navarre is
              never &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.7508em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0351em"
              >considered for the purposes of counting loyal houses for receipt
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 60.7008em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >this card from Perpignan. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.7022em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_351" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >After the mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_535">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_536">e</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_537">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_350">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_538" style="word-spacing: 0.1238em"
              >h of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_535">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_539" style="word-spacing: 0.1243em"
              >errante of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_535">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_350" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >aples </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_539">is &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.6522em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0311em"
              >played, whenever Spain controls the Naples space and at least two
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 57.6022em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >of these three strategic spaces: Gaeta, Cerignola, and
              Garigliano, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 58.5522em; z-index: 2236"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >Spain gains 1 V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 59.8355em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0595em"
              >Additionally, whenever Spain controls both spaces in Roussillon
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 60.7855em; z-index: 2328"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0027em"
              >(Perpignan and Ceret) they gain 1 bonus V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_49" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">50 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_52" style="word-spacing: 0.044em"
              >4. Reinforce Foreign Wars: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_14" style="word-spacing: 0.0441em"
              >If a Foreign War event is active for &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >France, reinforce the defenders by adding five independent
              regulars &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_126" style="word-spacing: 0.0791em"
              >to France’s rival. If the leader </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0739em"
              >Maximilian </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0739em"
              >is not already present &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0011em"
              >besieging Milan or Metz, add his leader unit to the active
              Foreign &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_49" style="word-spacing: -0.0056em"
              >War. If both Foreign Wars are active for France, place </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80">Maximilian &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.0935em; z-index: 3272"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0096em"
              >in the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_192">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >ar against </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_102">urgund</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_317">y</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_317">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_14" style="word-spacing: -0.0026em"
              >Dynastic Rights on Naples and Roussillon &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >France wins special VPs for maintaining political control of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Kingdom of Naples and/or the County of Roussillon. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.8401em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_351" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >After the mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_535">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_536">e</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_537">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_350">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_538" style="word-spacing: 0.1238em"
              >h of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_535">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_539" style="word-spacing: 0.1243em"
              >errante of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_535">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_350" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >aples </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_539">is &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.7901em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >played, whenever France controls the Naples space and at least
              two &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.7401em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >of these three strategic spaces: Gaeta, Cerignola, and
              Garigliano, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.6901em; z-index: 390"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >France gains 1 V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.6293em; top: 10.4601em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >5. Event Played Marker: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_201" style="word-spacing: 0.1319em"
              >Finally, play of this event &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.6253em; top: 11.4101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0551em"
              >raises the cost for France to enact the Treaty of Senlis
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.6253em; top: 12.3601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: -0.0079em"
              >(1493) as described in the “France Turns Toward Italy”
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 29.6253em; top: 13.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_14" style="word-spacing: 0.0665em"
              >section below. Place the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0588em"
              >Maximilian Played </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0588em"
              >marker in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2505em; top: 14.2601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >the Treaty of Senlis box on the French power card. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.0565em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0045em"
              >Additionally, whenever France controls both spaces in Roussillon
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.0065em; z-index: 483"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0027em"
              >(Perpignan and Ceret) they gain 1 bonus V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.2942em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_293" style="word-spacing: -0.0046em"
              >Rivalry with Maximilian of Austria &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.5472em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_275" style="word-spacing: 0.0004em"
              >France’s Trade in the North Sea and the Mediterranean Sea
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 15.9226em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0774em"
              >HISTORICAL NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0881em"
              >Maximilian of Austria, Holy Roman &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 16.8726em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_62" style="word-spacing: -0.0583em"
              >Empire and ruler of Burgundy (after marrying Mary, daughter of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.2083em; top: 17.8226em; z-index: 660"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.0067em"
              >Charles the Bold) was a sworn enemy of the French monarchy,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 18.7726em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >vying for control of northern and eastern France. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.7934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0389em"
              >During the Winter Phase, France rolls on both the French Mediter-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.7434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >ranean and North Sea trade tables. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.1099em; z-index: 3660"
          >
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_277" style="word-spacing: -0.0681em"
              >Mediterranean: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_277" style="word-spacing: -0.0664em"
              >Control of the keys of </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_541">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_314">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >nice, Genoa, and Florence &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.0599em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >provide modifiers to the Mediterranean die roll (18.7).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.4487em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0589em"
              >The mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">E</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.058em"
              >mperor </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.03em"
              >aximilian of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0596em"
              >ustria </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">triggers &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.3987em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0586em"
              >challenges for France to represent this rivalry. Execute the
              event &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.3487em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0169em"
              >in the order set forth below and undertaking all five steps as
              each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.2987em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >one is applicable. Once one of the first three steps applies to
              either &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.2487em; z-index: 974"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Milan or Met</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0102em"
              >z </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0041em"
              >ignore the other steps for that specific city. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 21.4263em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_36" style="word-spacing: -0.0626em"
              >North Sea: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0602em"
              >Trade enhancement markers earned by France each add &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 22.3763em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >a +1 modifier to this die roll. France earns one such marker
              every &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.3263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_379" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >time they undertake their Improve North Sea Trade action at the
              cost &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.2763em; z-index: 3900"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >of 2 C</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_542">P</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.074em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_100">T</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.064em"
              >his action can be used four times per game. The modifiers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.2263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0191em"
              >are never applied until after the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_164" style="word-spacing: -0.0039em"
              >Treaty of Etaples </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0192em"
              >has been signed. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.6151em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.067em"
              >1. Relief For Besieged Milan or Metz: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >If one or both of the spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.5651em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >of Milan and Metz are besieged by France when this event is
              played, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.5151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Maximilian (leader 2-8) arrives with a relief force of eight
              indepen- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.4651em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_271" style="word-spacing: -0.0583em"
              >dent units in each besieged city (if Maximilian was in a Foreign
              War, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.4151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >remove him from that war). If both are besieged, the player
              playing &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.3651em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0112em"
              >the event decides the order of execution. A relief force field
              battle &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.3151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0022em"
              >immediately take places where the units inside those cities join
              in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.2651em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_172" style="word-spacing: -0.0588em"
              >the attack with Maximilian’s eight reinforcements. If
              Maximilian’s &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 33.2151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0488em"
              >relief units are forced to retreat, they are eliminated. If there
              is a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.1651em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >tie in the number of hits, retreat up to four independent units
              into &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.1151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >the city (the rest are removed from the map). However, if they
              win &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.0651em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0949em"
              >and break the siege, all surviving units of the liberated city
              and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.0151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0634em"
              >Maximilian’s relief force remain in the city space as a defensive
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.9651em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >army for future attacks. In either case, remove Maximilian from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.9151em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0062em"
              >the map after the combat, he is immediately available for the
              next &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.8651em; z-index: 1872"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0601em"
              >use on the other besieged city or for the reconquer use listed
              below. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.5139em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_543" style="word-spacing: -0.011em"
              >France Turns Towards Italy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 27.7601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_544" style="word-spacing: 0.128em"
              >France may, without restriction, declare war on the Papacy or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.7101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0412em"
              >Naples. However, for France to declare war on Genoa, Florence or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.6601em; z-index: 4136"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_542">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >nice in the declarations of war phase, it must have all three of
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.6101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >following treaties signed (place the corresponding marker on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.5601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >French Player´s Card when signing each one). In addition, once
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.5101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0286em"
              >three International Treaties are signed, the French player gets a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0286em"
              >2 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.4601em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0112em"
              >VP </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.011em"
              >marker (use a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0156em"
              >2 VP Consolidate Power </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: -0.0121em"
              >marker) for Turning to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 34.4101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0102em"
              >Italy that is retained as long as these three conditions are
              fulfilled: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9997em; top: 35.7765em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.165em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Controls Milan space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9997em; top: 36.9767em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.1093em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Controls at least one of the Nice or Modena spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.9997em; top: 38.1769em; z-index: 4571"
          >
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.2207em"
              >c) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0646em"
              >Controls at least one of the Florence, </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_542">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >nice or Genoa spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.3547em; top: 39.3768em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: 0.0061em"
              >Treaty of Etaples 1492 (with England): </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0014em"
              >This treaty &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 30.365em; top: 40.3268em; z-index: 4667"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0201em"
              >is signed when the mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">re</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >y of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">E</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_197">ta</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_197">- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.365em; top: 41.2768em">
            <span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0851em"
              >ples </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0853em"
              >(required in the winter of Turn 3) is played. It &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.365em; top: 42.2268em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >provides these benefits: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.2315em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1177em"
              >2. Reconquer Milan or Metz: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >If at least one of these cities is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.1815em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0032em"
              >controlled by France, Maximilian sends an attack formation com-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.1315em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >posed of eight independent units and the leader Maximilian to one
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.0815em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0249em"
              >and only one of them (chosen by the player executing the event).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.0315em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0191em"
              >The combat is now resolved by one round of field battle or
              assault &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.9815em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0241em"
              >(make an immediate assault if there are four or fewer French
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.9315em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0789em"
              >and they take refuge inside) without the need to wait for an im-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.8815em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0265em"
              >pulse. This one round of attack by Maximilian’s units is repeated
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 48.8315em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >at the beginning of each new impulse of the player who played the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 49.7815em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Maximilian event until either Maximilian or the defender no
              longer &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 50.7315em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >have units in this space (even if the player chooses to Pass
              during &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.6815em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0298em"
              >the impulse). If Maximilian’s formation suffers a retreat result
              in a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.6315em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0068em"
              >field battle or no longer maintains enough units for siege,
              remove &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.5815em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >his entire formation from the map. If the city besieged by
              Maximil- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 54.5315em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: -0.0055em"
              >ian’s formation is controlled by Maximilian’s units, he leaves as
              a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.4815em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0319em"
              >garrison all the independent units still surviving and removes
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.4315em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >leader Maximilian. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9996em; top: 43.4269em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.165em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >France moves the units in the Garrison Box against England
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9995em; top: 44.3769em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.064em"
              >(which previously could not move) to Paris. The squadron and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9995em; top: 45.327em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0259em"
              >naval leader Casenove are then placed in a controlled home
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9995em; top: 46.2769em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >port of their choice bordering any Sea Zone. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9996em; top: 47.4771em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.1093em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0959em"
              >Die roll modifiers from North Sea trade improvements are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.9995em; top: 48.4271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >now applied. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.3547em; top: 49.6268em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_172" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >Treaty of Senlis 1493 (with Maximilian): </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.056em"
              >There is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.365em; top: 50.5768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_545" style="word-spacing: 0.1287em"
              >no card that represents this treaty, but France may &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.365em; top: 51.5268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1209em"
              >unilaterally sign it by extending the impulse in the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.365em; top: 52.4768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >Action Phase or announcing it in the Diplomacy Phase &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 53.4268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0156em"
              >of a turn. Signing the treaty is only possible on Turn 3 or later
              and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 54.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.1157em"
              >only if France is not in a Foreign War with either Burgundy or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 55.3268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_60" style="word-spacing: 0.0355em"
              >Brittany. If the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">E</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.023em"
              >mperor </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0045em"
              >aximilian of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0246em"
              >ustria </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0238em"
              >event has been &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 56.2768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0469em"
              >played at least once (indicated by the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0468em"
              >Maximilian Played </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">marker &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 57.2268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0571em"
              >in the Treaty of Senlis box), announcing this treaty has a cost
              of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 58.1768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.08em"
              >either discarding a random resource, or choosing a specific card
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2499em; top: 59.1268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0121em"
              >and discarding it. If the French player does not have the
              resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2499em; top: 60.0768em; z-index: 5584"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0035em"
              >or card to make this payment, he cannot sign the treaty.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 57.7979em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0637em"
              >3. Reinforce Milan or Metz: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >If Milan and/or Metz are not besieged, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 58.7479em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: -0.036em"
              >are still independent, and have fewer units than initial starting
              gar- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 59.6979em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0441em"
              >rison, add independent regulars to this space until they regain
              their &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 60.6479em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >initial unit deployment level. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_50" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">51 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1019em"
              >On the turn that this treaty is signed, the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">E</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.102em"
              >mperor </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80">aximilian &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191" style="word-spacing: -0.0604em"
              >of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0034em"
              >ustria </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.004em"
              >event may not be executed: such an event would only &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0099em"
              >be used for CP if played by any player. From now on Maximilian
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0221em"
              >will no longer intervene over the city of Metz. If Maximilian is
              on &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0159em"
              >map besieging Milan or Metz, he is removed from the map along
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.0935em; z-index: 343">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_14" style="word-spacing: 0.0073em"
              >with his besieging army. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_210" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >Paris and French Keys &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >The Paris space represents the off-map part of France and its
              con</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 6.4737em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0237em"
              >trol is exclusive to the French player, unconquerable by the
              other &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 7.4237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >powers (so France can never surrender and can always build
              units). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 8.3737em; z-index: 2621"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0589em"
              >Otherwise, it has the same characteristics as a French home key,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 9.3237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >but can never receive either </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >Plague </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >or </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_205" style="word-spacing: 0.0147em"
              >Unrest </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">markers. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.8629em; top: 10.4601em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_283" style="word-spacing: -0.0665em"
              >Treaty of Barcelona 1493 (with Catholic Monarchs): &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.8851em; top: 11.4101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.0517em"
              >This Treaty cannot be signed if it is Turn 1 or if the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 7.8851em; top: 12.3601em; z-index: 439"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_304">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_364">e</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_547">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_182">t</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_164"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >h of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_304">F</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_308"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0627em"
              >errante of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_304">N</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_182"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >aples </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >has been played. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 7.8851em; top: 13.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >It can be signed in any of these three ways: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 10.6901em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0676em"
              >Each French home key gives the French player 2 VP for its
              control, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 11.6401em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >as indicated on his Player Card. French control of all of them is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 12.5901em; z-index: 2817"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0036em"
              >necessary to be eligible for an automatic victory. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 13.8775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_11" style="word-spacing: -0.0025em"
              >Foreign Support for the Beltranejos Cause &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4999em; top: 14.5103em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_135" style="word-spacing: 0.12em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_266" style="word-spacing: 0.0794em"
              >It may be signed by extending the impulse in the Action
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4998em; top: 15.4603em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_135" style="word-spacing: 0.042em"
              >Phase or announcing it in the Diplomacy Phase of a turn.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4998em; top: 16.4103em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_135" style="word-spacing: 0.044em"
              >In these cases, France must cede control of all the spaces
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4998em; top: 17.3603em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_135" style="word-spacing: 0.0551em"
              >under French control in Roussillon to Aragon, displacing
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4998em; top: 18.3103em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_266" style="word-spacing: 0.0673em"
              >(12.5) any non-Spanish units there. This act immediately
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4998em; top: 19.2603em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_266" style="word-spacing: 0.0589em"
              >puts the Spanish player and the French player at peace if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4998em; top: 20.2103em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_548" style="word-spacing: 0.0064em"
              >they are currently at war. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.1237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >See 20.4 for details on French support of the Beltranejos.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.4108em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_56" style="word-spacing: -0.0018em"
              >Letter of Marque &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 18.0393em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_549" style="word-spacing: 0.0922em"
              >HISTORICAL NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_276" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >The privateer French Guillaume de &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 18.9893em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0449em"
              >Casenove Coulon became an admiral of the French navy with
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 19.9393em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0119em"
              >the approval of Louis XI. His legend was based on famous ac</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0119em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 20.8893em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0559em"
              >tions in support of Portugal, including sending relief to Ceuta
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 21.8393em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >and the plundering of Genoese, Flemish, and Spanish merchants.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4999em; top: 21.4105em; z-index: 841"
          >
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.1093em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.004em"
              >If any player plays the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">re</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0011em"
              >y of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >arcelona </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">event. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4999em; top: 22.6106em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.2207em"
              >c) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0578em"
              >During the French player’s Spring Deployment, the French
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4998em; top: 23.5606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0689em"
              >player can give the Spanish player either two cards chosen
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4998em; top: 24.5106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >by the French player from his hand, or one of his resources
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4998em; top: 25.4606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >chosen at random and one card the French player choses from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4998em; top: 26.4106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >his hand. In this case the current war state is left unaltered
              but &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4998em; top: 27.3606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0016em"
              >the Treaty is considered signed. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 23.5654em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >The French naval leader Casenove has a piracy factor of one (P1)
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 24.5154em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0131em"
              >and his presence in a fleet of French naval squadrons allows
              those &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 25.4654em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0142em"
              >units to carry out piracy actions as if they were Corsairs (i.e.,
              they &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 26.4154em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.012em"
              >can be carried out against powers with which they are not at
              war). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.1522em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_68" style="word-spacing: -0.0013em"
              >20.8 Principality of Catalonia. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.6525em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_293" style="word-spacing: -0.0046em"
              >Dynasty of Anjou and the Generalitat &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 31.2809em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0576em"
              >HISTORICAL NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.033em"
              >Catalonia under the power of the Gen- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 32.2309em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >eralitat starts the game in a civil war against the King o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_200">f</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162">ragon. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 33.1809em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1009em"
              >At the start of the game, the war has already reached its last
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 34.1309em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0338em"
              >phase, where—with the support of France—the Anjou Dynasty
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 35.0809em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >is established as a monarchy of the Principality of Catalonia to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.7083em; top: 36.0309em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >help maintain the struggle. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7494em; top: 28.727em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0761em"
              >If this Treaty was signed by either (a) or (b), the following now
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7494em; top: 29.677em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">applies: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.416em; top: 30.8772em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.2439em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.064em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_184" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Spain or France still controls some of the other power’s home
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0826em; top: 31.8272em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >spaces it returns them to their opponent. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.416em; top: 33.0274em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1361em"
              >• Calculate the number of fortifications, strategic spaces, and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0826em; top: 33.9774em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >keys of the opponent that each player returns. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.416em; top: 35.1775em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0691em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0642em"
              >difference between these totals is awarded as Barcelona
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0826em; top: 36.1275em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0047em"
              >VP markers to the player who returns more spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7629em; top: 37.3277em">
            <span class="stl_340 stl_17 stl_550" style="word-spacing: 0.0568em"
              >EXAMPLE: </span
            ><span class="stl_342 stl_17 stl_551" style="word-spacing: 0.1336em"
              >France returns Vitoria while Spain returns both &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7486em; top: 38.2777em; z-index: 1573"
          >
            <span class="stl_342 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Bayona and Auch; Spain is awarded one Barcelona VP marke</span
            ><span class="stl_342 stl_17 stl_194">r</span
            ><span class="stl_342 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.8904em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_277" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >Catalan Unit</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_552">s</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_302">A</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_277" style="word-spacing: -0.065em"
              >nd Home Card: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Catalan units are under the control &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.8404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0513em"
              >of the French player. Catalan and French units are always allied.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.7904em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0471em"
              >The French player also gains use of the Catalan Home card as long
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.7404em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >as this limited major power has not surrendered. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7486em; top: 39.6441em; z-index: 1609"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0078em"
              >If this Treaty was signed, remove the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">re</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >y of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0049em"
              >arcelona </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">card &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7486em; top: 40.5941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0371em"
              >from the game. If a player has it in his hand, he must discard it
              and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7486em; top: 41.5441em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >draw a new card from the deck. Also remove the card if the event
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7486em; top: 42.4941em; z-index: 1734"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">e</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0012em"
              >h of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0007em"
              >errante of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >aples </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >has been played. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.1068em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_553" style="word-spacing: 0.1262em"
              >Restrictions On French Leaders: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_135" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >Until the surrender of the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.0568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0178em"
              >Principality of Catalonia, no French leader other than Anjou may
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.0068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >enter Catalan home spaces. French formations without a leader may
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.9568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0398em"
              >always enter such spaces. Anjou may command both French and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.9068em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0688em"
              >Catalan units (the leader counter has both colors as a reminder),
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.8568em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >even in the same formation. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.7806em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0033em"
              >e Monarch of France, Lord of Italy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.0268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0258em"
              >France receives VP for controlling these spaces in the Victory
              De- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.9768em; z-index: 1903"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0647em"
              >termination Phase: Naples, Rome, Ravenna, Milan, Genoa, </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_428">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_228">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79">nice, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.9268em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0637em"
              >Florence, and Otranto. When France has at least five of these
              spaces &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.8768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >controlled, it gains one of these awards as follows: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.2232em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_275" style="word-spacing: -0.0581em"
              >Space Control: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >Despite being allied, French units may gain control &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.1732em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0531em"
              >of unfortified spaces with Catalan control markers, exchanging
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.1232em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0861em"
              >existing Catalan control marker for a French one. This action is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.0732em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0064em"
              >performed with the usual 1 CP actions listed in 12.2; the
              presence &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.0232em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >of Catalan units nearby never prevents it. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 49.077em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Control</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0026em"
              >of 5 out of 8: gain 1 VP &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 50.2771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Control</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0026em"
              >of 6 out of 8: gain 2 VP &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 51.4773em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Control</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0073em"
              >all 8: gain 3 VP (first time only; afterwards 2 VP) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 52.8437em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_227" style="word-spacing: 0.1233em"
              >These VPs are in addition to those granted by control of those
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 53.7937em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">spaces. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.3896em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.1169em"
              >Barcelona: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.1146em"
              >If in the Victory Determination phase, Barcelona is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.3396em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0889em"
              >under the control of the Spanish player, the Catalan faction sur-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.2896em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0263em"
              >renders to the King of Aragon and ceases to exist in the game.
              See &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.2396em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0475em"
              >22.1 for steps to follow for the Catalan surrender. If on the
              other &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.1896em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >hand Barcelona is controlled by the Principality of Catalonia
              during &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.1396em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0687em"
              >this phase, the French player receives one bonus VP for
              controlling &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.0896em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >this key at the end of the turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 55.0806em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Metz and Milan &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 56.3268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >Control of the ecclesiastical city of Metz grants the French
              player &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 57.2768em; z-index: 2244"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0535em"
              >1 bonus V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.035em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >aximilian may aid this city until the Treaty of Senlis
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 58.2268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >is signed. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 59.5932em; z-index: 2343"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0481em"
              >Control of Milan grants the French player 1 bonus V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.036em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">aximilian &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 60.5432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >may aid this city at any time. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_51" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">52 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.011em"
              >Split Home Spaces: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >Many spaces near Barcelona are split Home &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >spaces with two colors (gold for Catalan and red fo</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_295">r</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_37">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0801em"
              >ragon). When &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0182em"
              >Catalan controls them, no marker needs to be placed on the space.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >When Spain controls them, a Spanish control marker is placed on
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0211em"
              >that space. If a mixed formation of Catalan and French units
              gains &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >controls of a space, place a French or Catalan control marker as
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.0435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0359em"
              >desired by the French player. A formation containing only Catalan
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.9935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >units gaining control must place a Catalan control marker; one
              with &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.9435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0249em"
              >only French units must place a French one. Once the Principality
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.8935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0389em"
              >of Catalonia has surrendered, it does not return to play and
              these &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.8435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0169em"
              >split Home spaces are considered Aragonese home spaces for the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.7935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >rest of the game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 4.3425em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >If all independent units are not eliminated, the major power at
              war &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 5.2925em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.0424em"
              >will have to pay for another Fight Foreign War action in a future
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 6.2425em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >impulse. The French or Portuguese player receive one less card if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 7.1925em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0243em"
              >they are fighting a Foreign War during the Card Draw Phase (use
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 8.1425em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0102em"
              >a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_411" style="word-spacing: 0.0186em"
              >–1 Card </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >marker as a reminder). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 9.5089em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0401em"
              >Major powers can construct new land units directly onto a Foreign
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 10.4589em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0362em"
              >War card they are fighting. They may also add leaders to the war
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 11.4089em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.0862em"
              >at any time by removing them from the map. However, a major
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 12.3589em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0119em"
              >power may never exceed the indicated limit of units on a Foreign
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 13.3089em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0083em"
              >War card. Major power units on a Foreign War card cannot return
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 14.2589em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0122em"
              >home (even in the Winter Phase) until they have eliminated all of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 15.2089em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_11" style="word-spacing: -0.0582em"
              >the independent units in the Foreign War. Militia fighting a
              Foreign &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 16.1589em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_33" style="word-spacing: 0.0847em"
              >War are not subject to die rolls for desertion in winter. If at
              any &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 17.1089em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0628em"
              >time the number of units of the major power participating in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 18.0589em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0262em"
              >war falls below the minimum number indicated, the first units
              that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 19.0089em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.0543em"
              >player recruits must go to a Foreign War until the minimum unit
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 19.9589em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >count is restored. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.1599em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.0011em"
              >Surrender of the Principality of Catalonia: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >See 22.1 for details &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.1099em; z-index: 773"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_172" style="word-spacing: 0.0062em"
              >of this major power’s surrender. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.8469em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_527" style="word-spacing: 0.0103em"
              >20.9 Foreign War Cards &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 8.3326em; top: 20.4268em; z-index: 832"
          >
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_56" style="word-spacing: -0.0582em"
              >The three event cards: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_228">T</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_228"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0625em"
              >ribal </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_61">I</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_61">nsurrection</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.07em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_502">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_128">ar &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 8.3453em; top: 21.3768em; z-index: 867"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.1082em"
              >gainst </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_102">urgund</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_555">y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0988em"
              >, and </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_192">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.108em"
              >ar in </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_425">rittan</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_556">y</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.118em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">ad &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2504em; top: 21.3253em; z-index: 3788"
          >
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_11" style="word-spacing: 0.0292em"
              >War of Brittany, Castile Intervention: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0165em"
              >If the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_192">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.025em"
              >ar in </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_425">rittan</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_317">y</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_317">, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 22.2753em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_557">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_558" style="word-spacing: 0.1061em"
              >ad </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_559">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_558" style="word-spacing: 0.1236em"
              >ar </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_487" style="word-spacing: 0.128em"
              >Foreign War is active, Castile can build up to two &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 23.2253em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0089em"
              >Castilian militia per impulse directly onto this card to support
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 24.1753em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0393em"
              >Bretons. The number of Castilian militia on the card after such a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 25.1253em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0401em"
              >build action may never exceed the number of independent Bretons
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 26.0753em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0639em"
              >on the card. Whenever both Castilian militia and Bretons are
              present &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 27.0253em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >on the card and the French player inflicts losses on them, remove
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 27.9753em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >first a Breton independent and then a militia to keep the numbers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 28.9253em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >as balanced as possible. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 8.3453em; top: 22.3268em; z-index: 871"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_192">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_265" style="word-spacing: 0.1076em"
              >ar </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.106em"
              >force Portugal or France to divert land units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.3453em; top: 23.2768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_137" style="word-spacing: 0.1239em"
              >and/or army leaders off-map to resolve a foreign &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 8.3453em; top: 24.2268em; z-index: 969"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.1159em"
              >conflict. Spain, </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_560">V</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_485">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >nice, and Muslims can also be &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7504em; top: 25.1768em; z-index: 1040"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >affected in a similar fashion by th</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_561">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_213">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_277">ttoman</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_218">-V</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_218"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0809em"
              >enetian </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_562">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_563">ar</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0812em"
              >. When &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 26.1268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0431em"
              >these events are played, place the Event card on the map. Place
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 27.0768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0531em"
              >specified number of independent units to represent the opponent
              in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 28.0268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: -0.0431em"
              >question on the Foreign War card. In the case of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0445em"
              >ribal </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">I</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">nsurrec</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 28.9768em">
            <span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">tion</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0362em"
              >, place native insurgent units; for combat purposes these units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 29.9268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0301em"
              >are considered to be Militia, and remember to place a minimum of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 30.8768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >four such tribal units, even if Portugal has fewer than four
              settle- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 31.8268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0538em"
              >ments. The French or Portuguese player then selects the number of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 32.7768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >units designated on the card from any location on the map (except
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 33.7268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1em"
              >a space under siege, the Garrison space against England, or an-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 34.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0559em"
              >other Foreign War) and moves those units onto the card. Units may
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 35.6268em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0998em"
              >be chosen from multiple stacks in different spaces. If you don’t
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 36.5768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0367em"
              >have enough available units in play, the first units to be
              recruited &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 37.5268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0449em"
              >must be added to the Foreign War card to meet these requirements.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7504em; top: 38.4768em; z-index: 1795"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">(</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0739em"
              >Exception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.074em"
              >In the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">O</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_228">ttoman</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_131">-V</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0561em"
              >enetian </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_192">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">ar</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0738em"
              >, units are added to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 39.4268em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >this conflict directly from the various powers force pools of
              unbuilt &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 40.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">units). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 30.2918em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.044em"
              >If at the end of a Spanish impulse Castile is supporting the
              Foreign &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 31.2418em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0123em"
              >War in Brittany with at least two militias, Spain may take an
              extra &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 32.1918em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0276em"
              >roll on the Mesta Table using the modifiers applicable at that
              time. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 33.1418em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0251em"
              >This extra roll may only be taken once per turn and if taken it
              sub- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 34.0918em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0119em"
              >stitutes for the opportunity to extend the impulse with a
              resource. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 35.0417em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: 0.0639em"
              >If a Foreign War with Brittany is active in the Winter Phase, the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 35.9917em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0015em"
              >Spanish player also receives an extra roll on the Mesta Table.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 37.3582em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_99">O</span
            ><span class="stl_564 stl_17 stl_61">ttoman</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131">-V</span
            ><span
              class="stl_564 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0679em"
              >enetian </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_565">W</span
            ><span class="stl_564 stl_17 stl_80">ar</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_172" style="word-spacing: -0.0477em"
              >This special Foreign War is fought ex- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 38.3082em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0641em"
              >clusively between Christian and Muslim naval units. The naval
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 39.2582em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0519em"
              >that participate are added to the game when this event is played;
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 40.2082em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0139em"
              >surviving units from the winning side (along with additional land
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 41.1582em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >units) are awarded to the winning power(s). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 41.7432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0629em"
              >Army leaders may be selected from any location from the board
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 42.6932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >(even under siege) and also placed on the card (if you select
              multiple &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 43.6432em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0679em"
              >leaders only the one with the highest Battle Rating has an effect
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 44.5932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >on the outcome). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 42.5246em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Follow these steps when the event is played: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 45.9596em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_201" style="word-spacing: -0.059em"
              >To resolve the conflict, the French or Portuguese player must
              spend &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 46.9096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >1 CP on the Fight Foreign War action for each resolution attempt.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 47.8596em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0579em"
              >A field battle then occurs between </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.038em"
              >all </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >units of the major power and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 48.8096em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.02em"
              >all </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0182em"
              >independent units on the card. The battle is resolved as a field
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 49.7596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0131em"
              >battle on the map, except that there is no defender to receive
              extra &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 50.7096em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0301em"
              >dice and there is no retreat. If all independent units are
              eliminated, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 51.6596em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_33" style="word-spacing: 0.0057em"
              >the Foreign War is over. The use of combat or response cards that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 52.6096em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >affect a field battle is allowed. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.9167em; top: 47.4318em; z-index: 4915"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Place</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0439em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0514em"
              >the five naval units (Christian units are one </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0492em"
              >netian and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 48.3818em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >one Spanish; Muslim units are three Ottoman) reserved for this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 49.3318em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.041em"
              >war on the event card. (They have crossed swords in the upper
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 50.2818em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >right as shown in the illustration.) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 51.482em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Place</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0091em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0039em"
              >the Great Captain with the Christian naval units even if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 52.4319em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >he is currently captured or besieged or off the map. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 53.6321em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">•</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 31.7183em; top: 53.6318em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0331em"
              >Place Kemal Reis (with a Battle Rating of 1) with &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 31.7183em; top: 54.5818em; z-index: 5238"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_566" style="word-spacing: -0.0581em"
              >the Ottoman naval units. If Kemal Reis was in play, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 31.7183em; top: 55.5318em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >remove the counter with the Battle Rating of 2 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 31.7183em; top: 56.4818em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: 0.0078em"
              >from the map; it will return at the end of the For- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 57.4318em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: 0.1321em"
              >eign War. If Kemal Reis had already been replaced by Bar-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 58.3818em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.1229em"
              >barossa, he returns exclusively to participate in this Foreign
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5835em; top: 59.3318em; z-index: 5421"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_567">War. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 53.976em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_152" style="word-spacing: -0.0587em"
              >When a Foreign War is over, all remaining units of the major
              power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 54.926em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0522em"
              >on the card are placed back in Paris (if this is the French
              player), or &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 55.876em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0339em"
              >in a home key (if this is the Portuguese player). Portuguese
              units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 56.826em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0429em"
              >may not return if they do not have a home key; in this case keep
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 57.776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: -0.0606em"
              >the units on the Foreign War card until they regain control of
              such a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 58.726em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.036em"
              >space. If the French or Portuguese defeat the enemy in the
              Foreign &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7504em; top: 59.676em; z-index: 2836"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_499" style="word-spacing: -0.0545em"
              >War that power receives one War Winner V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_568">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.07em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_213">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >lace the proper bonus &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7504em; top: 60.626em; z-index: 2890"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0005em"
              >VP marker on the Player Card as a reminder. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_52" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">53 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4167em; top: 4.3434em; z-index: 67"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_203" style="word-spacing: 0.1635em"
              >• If </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_570">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_571">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_137" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >nice is allied to the Muslim player when the event is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 5.2934em; z-index: 129"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1014em"
              >played, deactivate </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1099em"
              >nice—it will not be able to ally to the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.032em"
              >Muslim player while this war is active. The Portuguese player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 7.1935em; z-index: 225"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0509em"
              >controls the </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0599em"
              >netian naval squadron in the war in this case, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 8.1435em; z-index: 269"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0092em"
              >or if </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >nice was neutral when the war started. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Kemal</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0191em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0138em"
              >Reis is removed from the game if he has already been &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >replaced by Barbarossa. If not, he returns with the victorious
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >fleet (if the war was a Muslim victory) or in a controlled home
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >port (if his side lost). In both cases replace him with his
              counter &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >with a Battle Rating of 2. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 9.3436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.2321em"
              >• Now</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0339em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0289em"
              >the player who played the event decides whether or not
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 10.2936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.017em"
              >to undertake a free Fight Foreign War action to start resolving
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 11.2436em; z-index: 411"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_218" style="word-spacing: 0.0181em"
              >this war. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 9.3436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: 0.2537em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0689em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Great Captain returns to a controlle</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_507">d</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_508">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >ragonese or Castilian &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 10.2936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >home space that is not under siege. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 11.4938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.047em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0579em"
              >the Christians won the war, award 1 VP to Spain and 1 VP to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5833em; top: 12.4438em; z-index: 2848"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0306em"
              >the power controlling the </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.026em"
              >netian squadron at the conclusion &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 13.3938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0029em"
              >of the war. The Muslim gains 2 VP if their side wins.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 12.61em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: 0.0023em"
              >When resolving this Foreign War: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 13.8102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• All</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0528em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0581em"
              >naval units on each side roll 2 dice against their opponents,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 14.7602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: 0.0776em"
              >regardless of which player undertook the Fight Foreign War
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 15.7102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">action. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 14.6771em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >Special naval units and specific regulars that entered the game
              due &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2501em; top: 15.6271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >to this war cannot be built once they are eliminated.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 16.9104em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Kemal</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Reis always contributes one die to the Muslim side. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 18.1105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0011em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0042em"
              >Great Captain contributes two dice if either (a) this is the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 19.0605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >initial free action at the start of the war and the event was
              played &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 20.0105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0336em"
              >by a Christian player; or (b) this Fight Foreign War action was
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 20.9605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >taken by a Christian player who spent 2 C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_572">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_182">o</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >n the action instead &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 21.9105em; z-index: 827"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.048em"
              >of the usual 1 C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.038em"
              >. </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">I</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >f such cases do not occur, the Great Captain &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 22.8605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >contributes one die. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.4956em">
            <span class="stl_198 stl_08 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.01em"
              >21. Minors and Independents &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 24.0607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >side initiating the action always rolls one extra die.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 25.4271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_235" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >The combat follows the usual rules for naval combat (with an
              enemy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 26.3771em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.009em"
              >squadron being sunk for every two full hits, ignore odd hits)
              with &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 27.3271em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >the following exceptions: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 28.5273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Neither</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >side retreats after combat. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 28.7501em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0591em"
              >The major powers can recruit minor powers during play to serve as
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 29.7001em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0648em"
              >important partners. The minor powers share a common set of rules,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 30.6501em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0447em"
              >as presented below. All these minor powers have two states:
              active &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 31.6001em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0698em"
              >and inactive. Minor powers may start in either of these states as
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 32.5501em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0636em"
              >specified by the scenario setup. The Papacy is a special type of
              minor &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 33.5001em; z-index: 3385"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0025em"
              >power that possesses additional attributes detailed in 21.7
              below. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 29.7275em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: 0.2498em"
              >• Christian</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0661em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >casualties are selected by the player spending the CPs.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 30.9276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Leaders</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0047em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >may never be eliminated by the combat. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 32.1278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Naval</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0831em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0778em"
              >units eliminated in this combat are removed from the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 33.0778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.001em"
              >game rather than entering a power’s force pool. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 34.4442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >The war continues until units of only one side (Muslim or
              Christian) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 35.3942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0251em"
              >remain. Players who control a naval squadron on this Foreign War
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7501em; top: 36.3442em; z-index: 1414"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0932em"
              >card (including the </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0944em"
              >netian one) may spend 1 CP on the Fight &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7501em; top: 37.2942em; z-index: 1485"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_126" style="word-spacing: 0.0639em"
              >Foreign War action during their impulse. (If </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0638em"
              >nice allies with a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 38.2442em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >different power during the course of the war, the new major power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.7501em; top: 39.1942em; z-index: 1592"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.093em"
              >ally may take such an action on behalf of the </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0769em"
              >netians). There &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 40.1442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >is no –1 Card penalty on any power while the war is still active.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.2369em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_275" style="word-spacing: 0.0054em"
              >21.1 Inactive Minor Powers. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.8168em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >In the inactive states, minor power forces behave as follows:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 38.0169em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• They</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >do not move from their current space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 39.2171em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• They</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >do not intercept or avoid battle. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 40.4173em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.057em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >there are four or fewer land units in a space, they will always
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 41.3673em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >withdraw into the fortifications and try to withstand a siege if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 42.3173em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >their space is entered. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7501em; top: 41.5106em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Apply these effects when the war ends: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 42.7108em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0359em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0411em"
              >winning player(s) moves the surviving naval units to con-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 43.6608em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0313em"
              >trolled home ports, one port per winning power. If the Muslim
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 44.6108em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.021em"
              >side won, move the units to a single Berber home space or the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 45.5608em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0365em"
              >Otranto space, if controlled. Winning Spanish units are placed
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 46.5108em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0517em"
              >in any Spanish-controlled port in Italy or Sicily. A surviving
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0833em; top: 47.4608em; z-index: 1982"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0537em"
              >netian unit returns to the city of </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0571em"
              >nice. The surviving Otto- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 48.4108em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >man naval squadrons can return as naval squadrons or corsairs,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0833em; top: 49.3608em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >as the Muslim player prefers. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 43.5174em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.026em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0312em"
              >there are five or more land units, they will hold their ground
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 44.4675em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0629em"
              >and fight a field battle. If they lose that battle, do not
              retreat &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 45.4175em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0469em"
              >their units from the space as usual. Instead, they retain up to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 46.3674em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0551em"
              >four units which withdraw into the fortifications; all other land
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 47.3174em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >units in excess of four are eliminated. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 48.5176em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Inactive</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0349em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0401em"
              >naval units remain in their port and defend if that port
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 49.4676em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0004em"
              >is attacked. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4167em; top: 50.561em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18">•</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 18.9376em; top: 50.5601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_225" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >The winning side &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 18.9439em; top: 51.5101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.1247em"
              >now receives one &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.2036em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >21.2 Activation &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 18.9439em; top: 52.4601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_573" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >regular for each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.7834em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0799em"
              >Changing a power from inactive to active is called “activation”.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.7334em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0399em"
              >Each minor power can only be activated by three different major
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.6834em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0753em"
              >powers, as shown by the entries in the Activate lines at the bot-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.6334em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: -0.0212em"
              >tom of the Diplomatic Influence Table. Note that in the case of
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.5835em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0479em"
              >Muslim, some minors can be activated exclusively by one of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.5334em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >two powers of that player; the activation in the Spanish case is
              joint &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.4834em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127">fo</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_323">r</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_101">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >ragon and Castile for their common foreign policy; for French
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.4334em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0501em"
              >and Portuguese players only their main power can activate minors.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 18.9439em; top: 53.4101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_574" style="word-spacing: 0.1339em"
              >surviving naval &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 18.9439em; top: 54.3601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_575" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >unit. Place each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0834em; top: 55.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >regular in the same space as a returning naval unit of the same
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0834em; top: 56.2601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_576" style="word-spacing: 0.1252em"
              >power. The Muslim player receives Ottoman regulars; the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0834em; top: 57.2101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >Spanish player receives a specific Aragonese regular with the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0834em; top: 58.1601em; z-index: 2333"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_344" style="word-spacing: 0.1195em"
              >returning Spanish unit and </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_321">V</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_577">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_157" style="word-spacing: 0.1239em"
              >nice also receives a specific &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0834em; top: 59.1101em; z-index: 2372"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0218em"
              >regular if the </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >netian squadron returned. (They have crossed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0834em; top: 60.0601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >swords in the lower right as shown in the illustration.)
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_53" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">54 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Minor powers can be activated in the following ways: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.055em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0498em"
              >the minor power has regulars units in his counter mix, the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0213em"
              >controlling major power may use the Raise Regular Troop ac-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >tion to build a regular unit of this minor power in one of this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >minor power´s home spaces (assuming an unbuilt regular exists
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >in the counter mix). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 5.5436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.2322em"
              >• An</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0058em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0111em"
              >event has caused the diplomatic status of the minor power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 6.4936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >to be evaluated (which is resolved by the procedure in 21.6)
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 7.4436em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0969em"
              >or that allows direct alignment (place the influence markers
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 8.3936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0292em"
              >on that minor in resolved this turn in this case). The winning
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 9.3436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0267em"
              >power gets to activate this minor as their new ally if they are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 10.2936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0011em"
              >listed as an “Activate” power at the bottom of the Diplomatic
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 11.2436em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_90" style="word-spacing: -0.0072em"
              >Influence Table. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 9.2605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.042em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0471em"
              >the minor power has naval squadrons in his counter mix, the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 10.2105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.079em"
              >controlling major power may use the Build Naval Squadron
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 11.1605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0139em"
              >action to build a naval unit of this minor power in one of this
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 12.1105em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >minor power´s home ports (assuming an unbuilt unit exists in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 13.0605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the counter mix). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 12.4438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0248em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0699em"
              >major power declared war on this minor power and a dif-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 13.3938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: 0.0012em"
              >ferent major power intervened according to Step 4 of the War
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 14.3438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Declaration Procedure (9.4). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 14.7969em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_52" style="word-spacing: -0.0006em"
              >21.4 Deactivation &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.6306em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_167" style="word-spacing: 0.0036em"
              >Activation Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 16.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0261em"
              >Changing a power from active to inactive is called
              “deactivation.” &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.6601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Minor powers may be deactivated in either of these ways:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.8768em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1224em"
              >1. Place </span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1197em"
              >Allied </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1208em"
              >Marker: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_227" style="word-spacing: 0.123em"
              >Add an </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_545" style="word-spacing: 0.1207em"
              >Allied </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >marker to the box that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.8268em; z-index: 693"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0026em"
              >cross-references these powers on the Diplomatic Status Display.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 18.8602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_37" style="word-spacing: 0.2422em"
              >• An</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0438em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0442em"
              >event has caused that Minor Power to be deactivated, or the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 19.8102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_168" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >diplomatic status of the minor power to be evaluated and a power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 20.7602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_44" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >that is not the minor power’s former ally won that evaluation.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.1932em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: -0.0355em"
              >2. Declarations of War: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.032em"
              >A power currently at war with this minor &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.1432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0521em"
              >power has the choice to immediately declare war (at no cost in
              CP) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.0932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0281em"
              >on the major power that is activating the minor power. That power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.0432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0581em"
              >may only declare war if none of the “restrictions at all times”
              listed &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.9932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_126" style="word-spacing: -0.0479em"
              >in Section 9.4 apply. If the power chooses to declare war, add an </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_108">At &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.9432em; z-index: 1024"
          >
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_579">W</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_268">a</span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0712em"
              >r </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_580" style="word-spacing: -0.0592em"
              >marker to the appropriate box on the Diplomatic Status Display.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.8932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >If the power declines to declare war, any units of that power oc-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.8432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
