              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 56.4773em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Military</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0111em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >units of the minor power have one additional charac- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 57.4273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0647em"
              >teristic during the Winter Phase. These units may also return to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 58.3773em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >a home key of that minor power just as if it were an additional
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 59.3273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0148em"
              >key. The units of their major power ally do not enjoy this op-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
