              >Rome space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 35.8435em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0833em"
              >2. Roll Dice: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0838em"
              >If rolls are required, each competing major power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 36.7935em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >rolls a single die and computes a final total by adding their
              influ</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 37.7435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0288em"
              >ence points (if any) with the target minor power to the roll of
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 38.6935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >die roll. If this roll is for the arrival of a new pope, players
              should &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 39.6435em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >also add their affinity points (if any). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.733em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_66" style="word-spacing: -0.0029em"
              >21.6 Resolving Diplomatic Status &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.3129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: -0.0149em"
              >A minor power’s diplomatic status is evaluated based on either an
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.2629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0939em"
              >Event card play or a declaration of war (9.4). Diplomatic status
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.2129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0299em"
              >may only be evaluated once per turn, except for the fall of Rome
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.1629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.094em"
              >to Muslim control and the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: 0.0931em"
              >oman </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0946em"
              >uria </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0938em"
              >event, after which the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.1129em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0199em"
              >Papacy’s influence marker levels are placed in their starting
              boxes &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.0629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >instead of </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0614em"
              >Resolved this turn</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_271" style="word-spacing: -0.0597em"
              >. For each Minor Power, ignore a second &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.0129em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0698em"
              >such event if it occurs while all of this Minor Power’s influence
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.9629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >markers are in the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: 0.0067em"
              >Resolved this Turn box</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_50" style="word-spacing: 0.0067em"
              >. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.0099em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0049em"
              >3. Determine Winner: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >The power with the highest total in step 2 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.9599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >is the winner (provided that no automatic winner has been
              declared &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.9099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >in step 1b). In the case of a tie, the winner is the power listed
              high- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.8599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0355em"
              >est in the list of Activate powers at the bottom of the
              Diplomatic &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.8099em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_90" style="word-spacing: -0.0072em"
              >Influence Table. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.25em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_37" style="word-spacing: 0.0005em"
              >Diplomatic Status Procedure &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.1764em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0076em"
              >4. Activate: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0144em"
              >If the winner is listed as an Activate power and does
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.1263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0182em"
              >not currently have this power as an ally, then deactivate the
              power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.0763em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0418em"
              >from its current ally (if any) and then activate it as an ally of
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.0264em; z-index: 1866"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >winning power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.4962em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >1. Determine Competing Powers: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4997em; top: 47.6964em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.165em"
              >a) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0188em"
              >If Diplomatic Status is evaluated as a result of a declaration
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 48.6464em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.113em"
              >of war on a minor power (9.4); by playing the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_131">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_611">ultanate &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 49.5964em">
            <span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191" style="word-spacing: 0.0176em"
              >of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0292em"
              >z </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.019em"
              >Home card event; or by the Papal Diplomatic Status &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 50.5464em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0857em"
              >resolution (21.7), all players listed as either an Activate or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 51.4964em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0431em"
              >Deactivate power compete and do so regardless of their level
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 52.4464em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0014em"
              >of influence over the minor target. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.3928em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0106em"
              >5. Deactivate: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: -0.0077em"
              >If the winning is listed as a Deactivate power, then &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.3428em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >deactivate the power from its current ally (if any). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.7092em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0583em"
              >6. Reset Influence: </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.0776em"
              >All influence markers in this minor power’s &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.6592em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0554em"
              >column of the Diplomatic Influence Table are placed in the
              “Re</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0554em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.6092em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >solved this turn” box (except if the resolution was for the
              Papacy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.5592em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >due to the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_61">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >oman </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_61">C</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_172"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0724em"
              >uria </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0653em"
              >event, see 21.7). They will be reset to their &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.5092em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0803em"
              >default positions during the Winter Phase at the end of the turn.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.4592em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">(</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Exception: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >See Enemy of Islam below). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4997em; top: 53.6465em">
            <span class="stl_120 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.1093em"
              >b) </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0132em"
              >If Diplomatic Status is evaluated as a result of the play of an
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 54.5965em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0091em"
              >event and the objective is not the Papacy, the player playing
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 55.5465em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0678em"
              >the event only competes against the players listed as either
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 56.4965em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.035em"
              >an Activate or Deactivate power who are at the same level of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 57.4465em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_140" style="word-spacing: -0.059em"
              >influence (or higher) with this minor. If this player’s influence
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 58.3965em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0029em"
              >marker on that minor is at a higher level than all others, that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.4996em; top: 59.3465em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >player automatically wins this procedure (skip to Step 4).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_55" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">56 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 4.3441em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.1108em"
              >Control of the Papacy: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1078em"
              >When a Christian Player is allied with &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 5.2941em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >the Papacy: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.233em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.0019em"
              >21.7 Minors with Speciﬁc Rules &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.7333em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_130" style="word-spacing: 0.004em"
              >e Papacy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 6.6605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.2321em"
              >• Add</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0499em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0551em"
              >the card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_83">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_252">p</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0441em"
              >l </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0545em"
              >ull </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_265" style="word-spacing: -0.0537em"
              >to the allied player’s hand during the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 7.6105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Card Draw Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.9795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: -0.048em"
              >The Papacy is a special Minor Power that has additional
              character- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.9295em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >istics beyond those of the other Minor Powers. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 8.8107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Papal</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0409em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0461em"
              >land units may not leave Papal home spaces. If forced to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 9.7607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >retreat to a non-home space they are eliminated. (</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_80">Exception: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 10.7107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0015em"
              >See Cesare Borgia section below). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.2959em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0935em"
              >Succession for the Papacy: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0979em"
              >Every time a new Pope ascends to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.2459em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >the throne of Rome: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 11.4461em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.2416em"
              >• Immediately</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: -0.0655em"
              >deactivate The Papacy from their current ally; this &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 12.3961em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >deactivation may cause Papal units to be displaced. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 11.9109em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0521em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0469em"
              >Papacy naval squadron is controlled by the allied Major
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 12.8609em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Power just like any minor power naval unit. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 13.5963em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Remove</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0691em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.064em"
              >control markers from all Christian powers from the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 14.5463em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0411em"
              >Papal home spaces (even if they were at war with the Papacy).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 15.4963em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Displace any Christian units in the Papal home spaces.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 14.061em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >If the Papacy is an inactive Minor Power: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 15.2612em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.2337em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0589em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >Muslim player draws a card from the deck during the Card
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 16.2112em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Draw Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 16.6964em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• After</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.007em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0019em"
              >displacement, check to see if there are five regulars and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 17.6464em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.007em"
              >one naval squadron in Papal home spaces. If not, add units to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 18.5964em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0939em"
              >those spaces until those minimums are restored, placing the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 19.5464em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >units added to a space still under Papal control in this priority
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 20.4964em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0093em"
              >order: Rome, then Ravenna, and finally Ancona. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 17.4114em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0617em"
              >Declaration of War: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: 0.0647em"
              >Rome is the Pope’s city and the heart of &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 18.3614em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_330" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Christendom, so Christian declarations of war against the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 19.3114em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >Papacy come with special considerations: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 20.5115em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0682em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0231em"
              >Christian Power who is not currently allied with the Papacy
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 21.4615em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.023em"
              >can declare war during the Action Phase by paying the cost of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 22.4115em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >one random card draw from their hand (the card is placed in the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 23.3615em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0906em"
              >discard pile). </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_53">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162">d</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >eclaration of war of this sort does not trigger a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 24.3115em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >Diplomatic Status check for the Papacy; its diplomatic status is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 25.2615em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >never changed by receiving a declaration of war from a major
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5831em; top: 26.2115em; z-index: 3318"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_67" style="word-spacing: 0.0084em"
              >Christian power. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.8629em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0455em"
              >Activation of the Papacy: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.041em"
              >The Pope may change during the game &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.8129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0031em"
              >through Mandatory Event cards, either during the Headline Event
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.7629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0082em"
              >Segment, the Action Phase or in the Winter Phase when resolving
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.7129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1159em"
              >a Mandatory Required Event. Each time a new Pope enters the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.6629em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >game, or when the appropriate option of the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: 0.0261em"
              >oman </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0276em"
              >uria </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">event &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.6129em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0242em"
              >is played, perform a Diplomatic Status check for the Papacy. Each
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.5629em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >player rolls one die and adds the following modifiers to the
              result: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 27.4117em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.2419em"
              >• A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0652em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0301em"
              >Christian Power at war with the Papacy (including the case
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 28.3617em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_338" style="word-spacing: 0.126em"
              >of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_338">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_243" style="word-spacing: 0.1246em"
              >esare </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_338">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_243">orgia</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_338" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >, C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_338">ondottiere</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_243" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >, see below) will remain &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 29.3117em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.108em"
              >at war until the arrival of a new Pope, who will return the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 30.2617em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >Papacy to an inactive state (and cause any Christian units in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 31.2117em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_225" style="word-spacing: 0.074em"
              >Papal home spaces to be displaced, see “Succession for the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 32.1617em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_146" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >Papacy” above). If the Christian power at war with the Papacy
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 33.1117em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >controlled Ravenna or Rome and was forced to return either
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 34.0617em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.0339em"
              >of these spaces, he receives a </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_485" style="word-spacing: 0.0338em"
              >1 VP </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.0339em"
              >marker for each (use the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 35.0117em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: 0.041em"
              >1 Papal VP </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_377" style="word-spacing: 0.0395em"
              >markers with the image of Cesare Borgia). This &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 35.9617em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >award can only be received by each player a maximum of once
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 36.9117em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >per game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 28.763em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0331em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >value of their influence marker in the Papacy column on
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 29.713em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_28" style="word-spacing: 0.0002em"
              >the Diplomacy Table. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 30.9132em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0169em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_99">A</span
            ><span class="stl_613 stl_17 stl_13">ffi</span
            ><span class="stl_94 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0221em"
              >nity </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: -0.0185em"
              >value on the new Pope’s card (this does not apply &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 31.8632em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0768em"
              >if the Diplomatic Status check is triggered as a result of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 32.8132em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0009em"
              >oman </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0006em"
              >uria </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">event). &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.1796em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >The player with the highest total wins the status check.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.546em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0912em"
              >If the check is triggered as a result of the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187" style="word-spacing: 0.0901em"
              >oman </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0926em"
              >uria </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">Event, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.496em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >reset all Papal influence markers to their initial positions
              after the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.446em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0239em"
              >Diplomatic Status check, instead of placing them in the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80">Resolved &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.396em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_213" style="word-spacing: 0.0182em"
              >this Turn </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">box. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 38.1119em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.105em"
              >• Declaring war on the Major Power that controls the Papacy
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 39.0619em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >does not imply declaring war on the Papacy; its allied or war
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5831em; top: 40.0119em; z-index: 3966"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0054em"
              >status with Christian powers is always tracked independently.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 39.9784em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: -0.081em"
              >NOTE: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.067em"
              >The </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_21">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_39" style="word-spacing: -0.0629em"
              >oman </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_21">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_49" style="word-spacing: -0.0684em"
              >uria </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >event has a second option that allows &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 40.9284em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0868em"
              >any player to deactivate the Papacy immediately and without
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 41.8784em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >further benefit; so no rolls are made in this case, nor does the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 42.8284em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0469em"
              >Muslim player move influence markers, nor does he receive a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 43.7784em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0189em"
              >card at this time, although he will do so in the next deal, if
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.2083em; top: 44.7284em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >Papacy is still independent. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.3783em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0334em"
              >Conquest of Rome: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.034em"
              >If a Christian power at war with the Papacy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 42.3283em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0119em"
              >gains controls of Rome, the Papal alliance passes to the
              Christian &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 43.2783em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1089em"
              >power now controlling Rome. Follow the steps for “Succession
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 44.2283em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0399em"
              >for the Papacy” listed above, allying the Papacy to this
              Christian &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 45.1783em; z-index: 4190"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_49">conqueror. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.4212em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >The winner of the Diplomatic Status check (even the Muslim player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.3712em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1199em"
              >if they were successful in keeping the Papacy deactivated, or a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 48.3212em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >Christian player allied with a Muslim power) gains these
              benefits: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 46.5447em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0619em"
              >Muslim Alliance: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0899em"
              >If a Christian power that controls the Papacy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.4947em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0919em"
              >allies with a Muslim Power during the Diplomacy Phase, it im-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.4447em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_293" style="word-spacing: -0.0024em"
              >mediately loses control of the Papacy. Deactivate the Papacy. The
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.3947em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0079em"
              >Muslim player immediately draws a card from the deck. This loss
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.3447em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >of control does not occur if a Christian power already allied to
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.2947em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0129em"
              >Muslim player controls the Papacy militarily during the Headline
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.2447em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0137em"
              >Event Phase or Action Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 49.5214em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.108em"
              >• If the change of Pope happened during the Action Phase or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 50.4714em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0399em"
              >Headline Event Segment, the winning player draws one card
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 51.4214em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >from the deck. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 52.6215em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.028em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.031em"
              >you are a Christian player allied with a Muslim power, keep
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 53.5715em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the Papacy inactive. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.6111em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_100" style="word-spacing: 0.0622em"
              >Threat to Rome: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.0601em"
              >If the Papacy is inactive, Cesare Borgia is not &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.5611em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.1221em"
              >on the map, and any space in Italy, Sardinia, Corsica, or Sicily
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.5111em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0449em"
              >is occupied by Muslim land units or controlled by the Muslim, a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.4611em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0439em"
              >Christian player may spend CPs to recruit, move, or assault with
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.4111em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0311em"
              >Papal land units (within Papal home spaces), even though they are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.3611em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_199" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >not a Papal ally. If Rome is controlled by the Muslim player,
              Papal &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.3111em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >units are considered to be able to trace LOC to any fortified
              space &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 60.2611em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0533em"
              >controlled by a Christian player. Likewise, if Rome is controlled
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 54.7717em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_513" style="word-spacing: 0.248em"
              >• Move</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0658em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
