              >markers in the Papacy &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 25.9607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_336" style="word-spacing: -0.0605em"
              >column on the Diplomacy Status Table with all major powers as
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 26.9107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0225em"
              >a reminder. They can also attack inactive minor powers (other
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 27.8607em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0378em"
              >than Navarre)—no Diplomatic Status check is performed for
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 28.8107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >any of these minor powers entering a new war state. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 24.7606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• All</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0652em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0599em"
              >Christian major powers will be in a state of war with all
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 25.7106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
