              >during the diplomacy status check. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 32.161em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: 0.2378em"
              >• Papal</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0599em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >units can control spaces using their own control markers.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 33.111em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0361em"
              >In the case of fortified port spaces, they do not need to comply
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 34.061em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >with the naval requirements for assaulting. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 35.0111em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0741em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.069em"
              >Muslim player draws one extra card at the start of each
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 35.9611em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">turn. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 35.2612em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_112" style="word-spacing: 0.1347em"
              >• In Winter of Turn 4 (exclusively) the Papal units return to
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 36.2112em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0528em"
              >fortified spaces (Rome) as if they were another major power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 37.1612em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0759em"
              >and a Papal regular is received as a reinforcement in Rome.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 38.1112em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0324em"
              >On Turn 5 (exclusively), they may make spring deployments
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 39.0612em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >from Rome. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.3275em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_616">C</span
            ><span class="stl_564 stl_17 stl_617" style="word-spacing: 0.1246em"
              >esare </span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_176">B</span
            ><span class="stl_564 stl_17 stl_176">orgia</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_616" style="word-spacing: 0.1253em"
              >, C</span
            ><span class="stl_564 stl_17 stl_618">ondottiere</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.178em"
              >: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_617" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >The event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_176">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_617" style="word-spacing: 0.1246em"
              >esare </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_176">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_617">orgia</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_617">, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 38.2775em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1176em"
              >ondottiere </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1178em"
              >brings an extra leader onto the map, who acts as &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 39.2275em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0403em"
              >a leader for the power playing the event. These two rules always
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 40.1775em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0031em"
              >apply to Borgia: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 40.4276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0277em"
              >When Alexander VI dies or the Muslim player loses control of the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4174em; top: 41.3776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.074em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0698em"
              >Borgia is controlled by the same power that is allied with
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.084em; top: 42.3276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.028em"
              >the Papacy, Papal units in his formation may move (or retreat)
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.084em; top: 43.2776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_158" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >outside Papal home spaces and may gain control of those spaces
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.084em; top: 44.2276em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: -0.0545em"
              >(putting them under control of the Papacy’s major power ally).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 41.3776em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Papacy by play of the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_187"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0009em"
              >oman </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0006em"
              >uria </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >event, apply these effects: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 42.5778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0421em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0309em"
              >Muslim player gains 1 VP for every key space, strategic
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 43.5278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >space or fortress with a Papal control marker in Italy (including
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 44.4778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >Nice but excluding Papal home spaces), Corsica, Sardinia, or
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5832em; top: 45.4278em; z-index: 4377"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_619">Sicily. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4174em; top: 45.4278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_66" style="word-spacing: 0.239em"
              >• Borgia</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0067em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >is removed from the map during the Card Draw Phase &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.084em; top: 46.3778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0398em"
              >if any Pope other than Alexander VI is in power in Rome. If
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.084em; top: 47.3278em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_185" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >Alexander VI is the current Pope, Borgia remains in play during
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.084em; top: 48.2778em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >this phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9166em; top: 46.628em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1345em"
              >• Displace all Papal units that are not in Papal home spaces.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 47.578em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.031em"
              >Then remove Papal control markers from all spaces, returning
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 48.528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0228em"
              >control of each space to its home Power. If an inactive minor
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 49.478em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0009em"
              >power regains a space in this fashion it restores any units that
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5832em; top: 50.428em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >started the game in that space back onto the map. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 49.6442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.056em"
              >However, there are two conditions (both related to Pop</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_620">e</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">lexander &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 50.5942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.001em"
              >VI) where even more special rules apply to Borgia: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.7139em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_67">Navarre &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 51.9606em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_115" style="word-spacing: 0.0387em"
              >Alexander VI Becomes Pope; Borgia Already On Map: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.005em"
              >If Al- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 52.9106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0237em"
              >exander VI comes into play while the leader Borgia is on the map,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 53.8606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0352em"
              >and the Papacy after its Diplomatic Status check is now
              controlled &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 54.8106em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0437em"
              >by a different Christian player than the one who controls Borgia,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 55.7606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: 0.0678em"
              >displace Borgia and Papal units in his formation to Rome. He is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 56.7106em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: 0.0608em"
              >now controlled by the Christian player allied with the Papacy. If
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 57.6606em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.047em"
              >the Diplomacy check was won by the Muslim player, there is no
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7508em; top: 58.6106em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_11" style="word-spacing: 0.0076em"
              >effect on Borgia’s status. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.9601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0654em"
              >Diplomatic influence on Navarre costs 1 CP for the first three
              levels &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.9101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0093em"
              >and 2 CP for the remaining three. The entry of Pope Julius II
              (T5) &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.8601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >helps the alignment of Navarre to the Spanish player if the event
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.8101em; z-index: 4816"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_104">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_526" style="word-spacing: 0.1244em"
              >lash of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_104">I</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_375" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >nterests in </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_307">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_621">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_555">v</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_86">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_86" style="word-spacing: 0.124em"
              >rre </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1138em"
              >is played. As specified in 9.4, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.7601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0381em"
              >you may not declare war on Navarre unless the level of diplomatic
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.7101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0151em"
              >influence over an inactive Navarre by some other opposing player
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.6601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >is at least two levels higher than your own. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_57" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">58 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.9167em; top: 4.3434em; z-index: 2418"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_104" style="word-spacing: 0.1176em"
              >◊ From this point on, while </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_623">L</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_104">’</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1239em"
              >Aquila is controlled by France &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0659em"
              >and Atella by Spain, each may winter a full formation of its
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0161em"
              >units in these spaces (up to the size allowed by a single leader
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 7.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0371em"
              >present). Consider these two spaces as if they were home keys
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 8.1435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0089em"
              >only for purposes of eligibility for the return of units allowed
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 9.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0142em"
              >in the Winter Phase. These spaces have a small symbol on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 10.0435em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >map to remind you of this. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.2775em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_42" style="word-spacing: 0.0024em"
              >Naples and the Event </span
            ><span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_36">D</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_624" style="word-spacing: 0.1232em"
              >eath of </span
            ><span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_36">f</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_25" style="word-spacing: 0.09em"
              >erraNte of </span
            ><span class="stl_248 stl_08 stl_36">N</span
            ><span class="stl_249 stl_08 stl_442">aPles &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.5237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >Naples is considered a Minor Power like any other until the man-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.4737em; z-index: 188">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0779em"
              >datory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">e</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191" style="word-spacing: 0.0758em"
              >h of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0763em"
              >errante of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0778em"
              >aples </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0778em"
              >is played, required &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.4237em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0212em"
              >in the winter of Turn 4. Until that time, all strategic spaces of
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.3737em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0555em"
              >Minor Power are considered simple unfortified (circular) spaces.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.3237em; z-index: 377">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0028em"
              >Therefore, only its capital Naples grants 1 V</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.6901em; z-index: 402"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1139em"
              >When the mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">e</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191" style="word-spacing: 0.1118em"
              >h of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.1123em"
              >errante of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.1138em"
              >aples </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">oc- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.6401em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0071em"
              >curs, the kingdom of Naples ceases to exist as a Minor Power and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.5901em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0839em"
              >its spaces become Independent (hence the gray color also on its
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.5401em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">spaces): &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9167em; top: 11.2436em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: 0.1017em"
              >◊ The</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0639em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >spaces of Gaeta, Cerignola, and Garigliano in the Kingdom
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 12.1936em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >of Naples—which were previously treated as simple unfortified
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 13.1436em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >(circular) spaces—are considered strategic spaces for the rest
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5833em; top: 14.0936em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >of the game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 14.7403em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0114em"
              >◊ Remove major power influence markers from the Naples col</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0114em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 15.6903em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >umn of the diplomacy track. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 26.25em; top: 15.6636em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0023em"
              >21.8 Independent Spaces and Canarian Guanches &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 16.8905em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1141em"
              >◊ Remove any major power control markers (including Papal
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 17.8405em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_121" style="word-spacing: -0.0122em"
              >control markers, see Cesare Borgia, Condottiere, above) from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 18.7905em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1099em"
              >the spaces of the Kingdom of Naples on the map except in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 19.7405em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0419em"
              >Naples and Otranto whose spaces retain their current control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 20.6905em; z-index: 816"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_218">marker. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 17.2434em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0464em"
              >Entering Independent Spaces: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0459em"
              >Gray independent spaces do not &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 18.1935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0069em"
              >belong to any major or minor power and are therefore not subject
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 19.1435em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0132em"
              >to diplomatic influence or declarations of war. Units belonging
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 20.0935em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >any power may enter independent spaces at any time. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.8769em; top: 21.4601em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_136" style="word-spacing: 0.0193em"
              >Independent Unit Placement: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: 0.0201em"
              >Independent units &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.865em; top: 22.4101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: -0.0141em"
              >in these spaces may not move; they simply defend &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.865em; top: 23.3601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: -0.0531em"
              >against any power that may be attacking them (just &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 21.8906em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0231em"
              >◊ Displace any non-Naples units in any spaces of the Kingdom
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 22.8406em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >of Naples other than the Naples and Otranto spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 24.0408em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0789em"
              >◊ Remove all units belonging to the Kingdom of Naples from
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 24.9908em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.865em; top: 24.3101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_625" style="word-spacing: -0.0598em"
              >like an inactive minor power, Section 21.1). If they &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 30.865em; top: 25.2601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: -0.0611em"
              >are in an unfortified space, these units never retreat
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 26.2101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >from their space, so if they are not eliminated in the field
              battle, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 27.1601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: -0.0221em"
              >the attacker must retreat (an exception to the usual retreat
              rules). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 28.1101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_551" style="word-spacing: -0.0514em"
              >Guanches units are subject to special rules listed below.
              Indepen- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 29.0601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: -0.043em"
              >dent naval units never move from the port space they occupy and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 30.0101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: -0.0303em"
              >contribute to protecting their space against assault. The
              indepen- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 30.9601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_626" style="word-spacing: 0.0139em"
              >dent corsair of Djerba (based in Tunis) has its own special rules
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 31.9101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_136" style="word-spacing: 0.0001em"
              >(see below). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 26.191em; z-index: 980"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0292em"
              >◊ Remove the T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">re</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_191" style="word-spacing: 0.0079em"
              >y of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0091em"
              >arcelona </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.009em"
              >card from the game deck &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 27.141em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0121em"
              >if it was not already removed. If any player had it in his hand,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 28.091em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >they draw another from the deck to replace it. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.4574em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0593em"
              >Follow one of the cases in the steps below, based on the state of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 30.4074em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Naples before the event: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 31.7738em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0044em"
              >Case One: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0051em"
              >If a major power controls the Naples space at the time
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 32.7238em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_89" style="word-spacing: 0.0034em"
              >of Ferdinand’s death, apply these effects: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 33.2765em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.1108em"
              >Independent Unit Combat: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1099em"
              >Independent units are always con- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 34.2265em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: -0.0352em"
              >sidered as regulars for combat purposes. Tribal units in the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">T</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">ribal &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 35.1765em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_268">I</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_268"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >nsurrection </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0601em"
              >event are considered militias, however, Guanches are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 36.1265em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0318em"
              >considered militias unless they are in a formation with the
              leader &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 37.0765em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1089em"
              >Bencomo. Independent regulars cannot be built by players with
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 38.0265em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0382em"
              >the Recruit Regular action, although certain events may bring new
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2504em; top: 38.9765em; z-index: 4053"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_61" style="word-spacing: 0.0059em"
              >independent units into play. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 33.924em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: 0.0957em"
              >◊ The</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0609em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >Major Power controlling Naples automatically goes to war
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 34.874em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0679em"
              >with Spain and France, receiving two regulars in the Naples
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 35.824em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">space. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 37.0241em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0475em"
              >◊ If Naples was controlled by the North Africans or the
              Portu</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0475em"
              >- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 37.9741em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.072em"
              >guese and they do not want to go to war with these powers,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 38.9241em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >move all their units from Naples and remove the control marker
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 39.8741em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >from the Naples space and immediately jump to Case </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_69">Three</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_69">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 40.3429em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0872em"
              >Independent Space Control: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0909em"
              >When a Major Power controls an &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 41.2929em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1209em"
              >independent space, that space is no longer independent. Such a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 42.2429em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.057em"
              >space will be controlled by one Major Power or another for the
              rest &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 43.1929em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0199em"
              >of the game, unless it becomes independent again due to the play
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2504em; top: 44.1429em; z-index: 4285"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >of the Event card </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0274em"
              >ity </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_489">ta</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0367em"
              >e </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131">ebels</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.027em"
              >. (</span
            ><span class="stl_119 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >Exceptions: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0268em"
              >Spaces in the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 45.0929em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0459em"
              >Canaries may be recaptured by the Guanches and Milan or Metz
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2504em; top: 46.0429em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >recovered by Maximilian). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 41.2405em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_353" style="word-spacing: 0.0374em"
              >Case Two: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0209em"
              >If the Papacy controls the Naples space at the time of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 42.1905em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_128" style="word-spacing: 0.0942em"
              >Ferdinand’s death (because the Muslim controls the Papacy, see
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 43.1405em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0236em"
              >esare </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80">orgia</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.024em"
              >, C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0236em"
              >ondottiere </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0239em"
              >above), add two Papal regulars to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 44.0905em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the Naples space. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 45.2907em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_133" style="word-spacing: -0.0084em"
              >Case Three: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0041em"
              >If neither a major power nor the Papacy controls the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 46.2407em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.1245em"
              >Naples city space at the time of Ferdinand’s death; apply these
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 47.1907em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80">effects: &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 47.3306em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_61">Ragusa &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 48.3909em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0339em"
              >◊ Place two Independent units in the capital Naples and—if no
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 49.3409em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >power controls Otranto—two more Independents in this space.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 48.5768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0379em"
              >Ragusa is an independent space that starts the game with a naval
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 49.5268em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0537em"
              >squadron in place there. This naval unit makes it difficult to
              assault &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 50.4768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0649em"
              >the city and prevents direct naval transport into the space
              unless &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 51.4268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84" style="word-spacing: 0.0905em"
              >eliminated. When a Major Power attacks Ragusa’s naval unit in
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 52.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.011em"
              >port, the Ragusans roll 2 dice for defense in port instead of 1
              (the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 53.3268em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_88" style="word-spacing: 0.0812em"
              >city’s natural harbor favors the defense). Ragusa starts with
              five &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 54.2768em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_170" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >independent regulars so it fights a field battle whenever it is
              attacked &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 55.2268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >as described in 21.1. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 50.7073em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0486em"
              >Additional Effects: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.076em"
              >After resolving the above cases, these addi- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 51.6573em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >tional effects apply: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 52.8575em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0279em"
              >◊ Spain and France divide the spaces of the Minor as indicated
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 53.8075em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_39" style="word-spacing: -0.0616em"
              >on the event card: Spain gains control of Seminara, Taranto and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 5.0832em; top: 54.7575em; z-index: 2166"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0569em"
              >Atella. France gains control of </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_438">L</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">’</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0569em"
              >Aquila, Gaeta and Pescara. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 55.7075em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0241em"
              >All other spaces remain Independent with no control markers.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 56.5932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >If a Major Power controls Ragusa, it will receive an additional </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_228" style="word-spacing: -0.0633em"
              >1 VP &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 57.5432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0383em"
              >marker on its Player Card as long as it maintains its control.
              The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 58.4932em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.06em"
              >power controlling Ragusa will have the option to receive
              resources &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.25em; top: 59.4432em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_433" style="word-spacing: -0.063em"
              >in the Winter Phase. If Ragusa becomes independent again as a
              result &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 56.9076em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0067em"
              >◊ France and Spain enter a state of war (if not already at war).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 58.1078em; z-index: 2329"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0176em"
              >◊ France places two regulars in each of the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_438">L</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">’</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.009em"
              >Aquila and Gaeta &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 59.0578em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">spaces. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 60.258em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0033em"
              >◊ Spain places four Aragonese regulars in Atella. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 22.0134em; top: 62.1188em">
            <span class="stl_71 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: -0.0043em"
              >© 2023 GMT Games, LLC &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_58" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 46.4333em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">59 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_73 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.3108em; top: 2.1235em">
            <span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_74 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.3434em; z-index: 78">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0345em"
              >of the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span
              class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131"
              style="word-spacing: -0.0336em"
              >ity </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_489">ta</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0243em"
              >e </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: -0.034em"
              >ebels </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0341em"
              >event, place five independent regulars in &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Ragusa instead of one regular as instructed by the event.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 4.3434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1249em"
              >Playing one of these cards as an event allows construction and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 5.2934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >movement of Guanche units. During that impulse, the Guanche units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 6.2434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0465em"
              >are controlled by the player that played one of these events.
              This is &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 7.1934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0255em"
              >the only way players may use CPs on behalf of the Guanches. The
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.2503em; top: 8.1434em; z-index: 2641"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >cost to build a Guanche unit is 1 C</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_194">P</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >, </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_99">t</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >he same as Militias. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.5806em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_170" style="word-spacing: 0.0057em"
              >Tunis and the Pirates of Djerba &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.8268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0164em"
              >Throughout the Middle Ages and early 16th century the island of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.7768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0868em"
              >Djerba near Tunis was a more or less independent pirate haven.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 9.7268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: 0.0696em"
              >Control of the independent space of Tunis grants the controlling
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 10.6768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.012em"
              >power an independent corsair naval unit from Djerba to use as its
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 11.6268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0818em"
              >own naval unit (including its corsair characteristic) as long as
              it &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 12.5768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0519em"
              >maintains control of that space. At the start of each turn,
              receive &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 13.5268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_108" style="word-spacing: 0.0891em"
              >this corsair as a free reinforcement in Tunis if it has been
              sunk. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 14.4768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1154em"
              >The moment the mandatory event </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_307">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_375" style="word-spacing: 0.1251em"
              >lgiers </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_104">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_375" style="word-spacing: 0.1255em"
              >egency </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_105" style="word-spacing: 0.1247em"
              >is played, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 15.4268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0191em"
              >immediately remove this corsair unit from the game. The possible
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 16.3768em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0242em"
              >piracy VPs obtained by this corsair count against the 6 piracy
              VPs &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.3268em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >that each player can obtain with Naos or naval squadrons.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 9.5099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Guanches units operate under the following special rules:
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9169em; top: 10.71em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• They</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >may never leave the Canary Island map section. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9169em; top: 11.9102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• They</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0269em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >may never control spaces. Instead, they remove control
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 12.8602em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0561em"
              >markers from other Powers in Canary Islands spaces at no cost
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 13.8102em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >when entering an unoccupied space controlled by another power
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 14.7602em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >(even fortified spaces). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9169em; top: 15.9604em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: 0.0018em"
              >they enter an unfortified space with units of another power,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 16.9104em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0432em"
              >a field battle occurs. If the Guanches win that battle, remove
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 17.8604em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >any control marker that is present. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.6139em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0062em"
              >Sforza Lord of Milan &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9169em; top: 19.0605em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.057em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0519em"
              >they enter a fortified space defended by enemy units, they
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 20.0105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_107" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >may assault it directly without having set up a siege in an
              earlier &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 20.9605em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >impulse. Follow the normal rules for assault though Guanche
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 21.9105em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_79" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >units never need to establish a LOC before initiating an assault.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.8601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0579em"
              >The Sforza family was the dominant family in the Italian city of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.8101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0477em"
              >Milan and they actively participated in the wars of this period.
              The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 21.7601em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0329em"
              >city of Milan starts with eight independent regulars, so it
              fights a &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.7101em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0458em"
              >field battle whenever it is attacked as described in 21.1. If
              Milan &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.6601em; z-index: 1068"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0529em"
              >becomes independent again as a result of the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.0534em"
              >ity </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_489">ta</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0627em"
              >e </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131">ebels &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.6101em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1179em"
              >event, place eight independent regulars in Milan instead of one
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.5601em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >regular as instructed by the event. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9169em; top: 23.1107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_374" style="word-spacing: 0.1358em"
              >• Although treated as militia for combat purposes, Guanche
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 24.0607em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_173" style="word-spacing: 0.0927em"
              >units are never affected by cards targeting militia and never
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 25.0107em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: -0.0009em"
              >are eliminated during the Winter Phase. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9169em; top: 26.2109em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: 0.2399em"
              >• Unless</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_35" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >there is only one unit in the starting space, the minimum
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 27.1609em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0068em"
              >formation of the Guanches is two units and their leader (if on
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 28.1109em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0669em"
              >the map) can never move alone or be abandoned in a space.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 29.0609em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0709em"
              >If a Guanche stack with a leader is split in two, its leader is
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 30.0109em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0451em"
              >always added to the formation with the higher number of units
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5835em; top: 30.9609em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >(the player chooses in case of a tie). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.8472em">
            <span class="stl_10 stl_08 stl_171" style="word-spacing: -0.012em"
              >Guanches, the Native Canarians &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.3769em; top: 28.0934em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0106em"
              >Canary Island Map Section: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.011em"
              >Next to the Explora- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.365em; top: 29.0434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0078em"
              >tion Map there is a map of the Canary Islands. This &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.365em; top: 29.9934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0968em"
              >auxiliary map is considered to be a section of the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.365em; top: 30.9434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0057em"
              >main map for all gameplay purposes. The seven is- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 8.365em; top: 31.8934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_263" style="word-spacing: 0.1248em"
              >lands of this archipelago are connected to each &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 32.3273em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: -0.0609em"
              >Conquest Of Canary Islands</span
            ><span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_239">:</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_572">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">p</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0612em"
              >layer is considered to have con- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 33.2773em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0601em"
              >quered one of the Canary Islands when he controls all of its
              spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 34.2273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_87" style="word-spacing: 0.0755em"
              >The player who controls Gran Canaria, or Tenerife is awarded a
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 35.1773em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0419em"
              >specific marker of 1 VP (so up to two </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: -0.0292em"
              >1 VP </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0475em"
              >markers in total). Also, &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 36.1273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0062em"
              >a player who controls all spaces in the Canaries is awarded an
              ad- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 37.0773em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.031em"
              >ditional </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0313em"
              >1 VP </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.034em"
              >marker. If a player controls all five Canary Islands,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 38.0273em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0446em"
              >his units may move from Ocean Zone 1 to Zone A (and vice versa)
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.2503em; top: 38.9773em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >without having to make Navigation Checks. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 32.8434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0529em"
              >other by land connection lines. Movement between these islands
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 33.7934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0039em"
              >can be completed without naval transport (although it is also
              pos- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 34.7434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >sible to move between spaces with ports following naval transport
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 35.6934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0271em"
              >rules). Note that the Canary Islands is considered to be adjacent
              to &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 36.6434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0592em"
              >the Cape Bojador Sea Zone. Units located in spaces of this map
              are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 37.5934em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0038em"
              >not obliged to return home in the Winter Phase; militia units
              from &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 38.5434em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >major powers are not subject to disbanding if in the Canary
              Islands. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 39.9099em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0455em"
              >Castile Only: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0538em"
              >The Spanish player can never move Aragonese land &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 40.8599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0272em"
              >units or the leader Ferdinand to the Canary Islands spaces, as
              their &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 41.8099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0192em"
              >conquest was a purely Castilian undertaking. All other powers are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 42.7599em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_106" style="word-spacing: -0.0622em"
              >not limited in this respect, except the Powers of Beltranejos and
              the &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 43.7099em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >Principality of Catalonia, which cannot enter there. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 45.0763em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0203em"
              >Activating Guanche Units: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0021em"
              >Although the Guanches are indepen- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 46.0263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_70" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >dent units, they follow special rules that allow them to recruit,
              move &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 46.9763em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >and attack/assault units belonging to major powers that occupying
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 47.9263em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0524em"
              >a space in the Canary Islands. There are four cards in the game
              that &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7504em; top: 48.8763em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >affect the Guanche people: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.417em; top: 50.0764em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_628" style="word-spacing: 0.2812em"
              >• #111</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0297em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">encomo</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102" style="word-spacing: 0.0003em"
              >, G</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >uanche </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">L</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131">eader &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.417em; top: 51.2766em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• #19</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">I</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >sland </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">eople</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">’</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0099em"
              >s </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">P</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">ride &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.417em; top: 52.4768em; z-index: 2355"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• #103</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">G</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">re</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.01em"
              >t </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80">rowsiness &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.417em; top: 53.6769em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• #104</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">G</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0003em"
              >uanche </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >ebellion on </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">L</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0104em"
              >a </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">G</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">omera &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div id="page_59" class="stl_ stl_02">
      <div class="stl_03"></div>
      <div class="stl_view">
        <div class="stl_05 stl_06">
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.7667em; top: 1.9227em">
            <span class="stl_16 stl_17 stl_18">60 &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 15.311em; top: 2.1277em">
            <span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_20">T</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_18">a</span
            ><span class="stl_19 stl_17 stl_21" style="word-spacing: 0.0021em"
              >nto Monta: The Rise of Ferdinand &amp; Isabella ~ 1470-1516
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 42.001em; top: 2.1269em">
            <span class="stl_22 stl_17 stl_23" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 4.3438em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.035em"
              >Nasrid units are treated as if they were North African units for
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 5.2938em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >all purposes until eliminated (see also Morisco Uprising).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 4.055em">
            <span class="stl_77 stl_08 stl_504" style="word-spacing: -0.0648em"
              >22. Victory &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 6.494em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• If</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.044em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0545em"
              >Malaga or Almería were controlled by the Nasrid at the time
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 7.444em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: 0.064em"
              >of the surrender, place up to two Morisco regulars there and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 8.394em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.1089em"
              >apply steps (a), (b) and (c) of the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.1092em"
              >orisco </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">U</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: 0.1087em"
              >prising </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">event &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 9.344em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.068em"
              >(20.1). At least one of the Morisco regular units must be placed
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 10.294em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >in the key still controlled by the Nasrids. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 6.5528em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0228em"
              >The seventh and final phase of the turn is the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_30" style="word-spacing: 0.0389em"
              >Victory Determina- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 7.5028em">
            <span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0521em"
              >tion Phase</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0521em"
              >. In this phase you check if any player has won the game
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 8.4528em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0018em"
              >or you continue playing for another turn. The steps to follow
              are: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 9.653em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: 0.2537em"
              >• Check</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0691em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0632em"
              >if Catalonia, Beltranejos or Nasrids have surrendered and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 10.603em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0448em"
              >resolve their surrenders (22.1). </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_83">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_102">w</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.045em"
              >ard VP markers for Catalan &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 11.553em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0121em"
              >ownership of Barcelona, Reconquista, or Nasrid Resistance if
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 5.0832em; top: 12.503em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80">applicable. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 11.4942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0291em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0149em"
              >Muslim player gains 1 VP (use </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0238em"
              >1 VP </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0056em"
              >markers for the Al- &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 12.4442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0431em"
              >hambra) for every three Castilian or Aragonese home spaces
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 13.3942em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0839em"
              >controlled (consider Zahara and Gibraltar as worth 2 spaces
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 14.3442em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >each for the purpose of this rule). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 13.7032em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Check</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.007em"
              >to see if France earns any VP for </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: 0.008em"
              >Lord of Italy</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: 0.008em"
              >. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 4.4166em; top: 14.9034em; z-index: 495"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Check</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_140" style="word-spacing: 0.0091em"
              >if there is a winner. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 15.5443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_446" style="word-spacing: 0.134em"
              >• The Spanish player takes control of all Nasrid-controlled
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 16.4943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_338" style="word-spacing: 0.118em"
              >spaces in Castile, Aragon, or the Nasrid Kingdom, except
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 17.4443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0351em"
              >those already marked with </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_225" style="word-spacing: -0.035em"
              >Morisco Uprising </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_217" style="word-spacing: -0.0352em"
              >markers or with &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 18.3943em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_242" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >Morisco regulars present. Place regular Spanish control mark-
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 19.3443em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_225" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >ers on all such spaces. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 16.1035em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Advance</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0em"
              >the </span
            ><span class="stl_82 stl_17 stl_283" style="word-spacing: 0.0369em"
              >Turn </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >marker to start a new turn. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 17.4699em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0577em"
              >There are two ways to win the game: Automatic Victory (22.2) and
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 18.4199em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_130" style="word-spacing: -0.0511em"
              >Victory Poin</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_40">t</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_84">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_109" style="word-spacing: -0.0753em"
              >ccumulation (22.3). Always remember that VPs are &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 19.3699em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0038em"
              >indicated either by the occupation of keys and strategic spaces
              on &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 20.3199em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >the map or by a specific marker on your Player Card. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 20.5445em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.11em"
              >• If Genoa was allied to the Nasrid it is deactivated. Remove
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 21.4945em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.04em"
              >the Muslim influence marker with Genoa from the Diplomatic
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 22.4445em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_90" style="word-spacing: -0.0072em"
              >Influence Table. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01 stl_75" style="left: 3.75em; top: 22.0563em">
            <span class="stl_76 stl_08 stl_70" style="word-spacing: 0.0017em"
              >22.1 Surrender of a Major Power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 23.6362em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0259em"
              >Surrender Conditions: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_127" style="word-spacing: -0.0185em"
              >Start the Victory Determination Phase by &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 3.75em; top: 24.5862em; z-index: 873"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: -0.0571em"
              >checking to see if any major powers have surrendered to an enemy.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 25.5362em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0794em"
              >A power is always considered to have surrendered when it does
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 26.4862em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.006em"
              >not control any home keys (France can never surrender because it
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 27.4362em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_178" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >always controls the Paris space). Specific powers may also
              surrender &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 28.3862em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_85" style="word-spacing: 0.0057em"
              >if specific requirements are met, as detailed below. The
              following &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 29.3362em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >powers are eliminated from play if they surrender: &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 23.6447em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Remove</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0001em"
              >all Nasrid leaders from the game except Boabdil. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 24.8448em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_214" style="word-spacing: 0.2558em"
              >• Remove</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0689em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_277" style="word-spacing: -0.062em"
              >all non-Morisco Nasrid units on the map from the game
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5831em; top: 25.7948em; z-index: 3400"
          >
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0621em"
              >except for those units previously moved to a Nort</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_295">h</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_37">A</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_241" style="word-spacing: -0.0462em"
              >frican key. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 26.7448em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0109em"
              >From this moment on, no more Nasrid units can be recruited,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 27.6948em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0631em"
              >(except for the corsair due to the effects of th</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_630">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0634em"
              >orisco </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">U</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">pris</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">- &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 28.6448em">
            <span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_102">ing</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >, 20.1). &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 29.845em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• All</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0038em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0091em"
              >Nasrid-controlled spaces outside the kingdoms of Castile,
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 30.795em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0061em"
              >Aragon or the Nasrid Kingdom go to North African control.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 30.5363em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.2319em"
              >• Nasrid</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.005em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13">Kingdom &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 31.7365em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Principality</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0049em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >of Catalonia &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 4.4166em; top: 32.9367em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• The</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0004em"
              >Beltranejos faction &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 31.9952em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Remove</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0051em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0em"
              >the Nasrid Home card from the game. &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 26.9165em; top: 33.1953em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2318em"
              >• Remove</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0429em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0481em"
              >the following cards from the game (if any of them are
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 34.1453em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_144" style="word-spacing: -0.0612em"
              >in a player’s hand, they discard it and draw one from the deck):
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 35.0953em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_131" style="word-spacing: -0.0469em"
              >#84 N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0463em"
              >asrid </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">R</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">aids</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0739em"
              >, #100 A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.046em"
              >ndalusian </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">N</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0464em"
              >obles </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_131">S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">ei</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: -0.0923em"
              >e </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">lhama</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99">, &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5831em; top: 36.0453em; z-index: 3827"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_213" style="word-spacing: 0.0695em"
              >#112 B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0506em"
              >oabdil </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0509em"
              >aptured by the </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0513em"
              >holic </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">M</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_99">onarchs</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.051em"
              >, #25 &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 36.9953em">
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_227">B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_112">oabdil</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_545" style="word-spacing: 0.1247em"
              >, E</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_545" style="word-spacing: 0.1246em"
              >mir of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_509">G</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_545" style="word-spacing: 0.125em"
              >ranada </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_171" style="word-spacing: 0.1424em"
              >and #110 B</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_631">a</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_545">z</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_631">a</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_509" style="word-spacing: 0.1253em"
              >, G</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_227" style="word-spacing: 0.1252em"
              >uadix and &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 27.5831em; top: 37.9453em; z-index: 3902"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">A</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0004em"
              >lmería </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13">C</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_131">apitul</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_173">. &nbsp;</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 34.3031em">
            <span class="stl_91 stl_17 stl_159" style="word-spacing: -0.0169em"
              >Unit Construction Prohibited: </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: -0.0291em"
              >A power that has surrendered but &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 35.2531em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0629em"
              >not eliminated from play may not use an action to construct any
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 36.2031em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_97" style="word-spacing: 0.0286em"
              >units (land or naval) until they regain control of a home key.
              The &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 37.1531em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0181em"
              >surrendered power remains in play with the units they have on the
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 38.1031em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0119em"
              >board, and any units they may receive from events. If they regain
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 39.0531em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0249em"
              >control of a home key space they may immediately recruit again.
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.0031em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0501em"
              >Note that this prohibition does not include the militia such a
              power &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 3.75em; top: 40.9531em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_162" style="word-spacing: -0.0002em"
              >is eligible to receive during the Winter Phase (18.6).
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div
            class="stl_01"
            style="left: 26.9165em; top: 39.1455em; z-index: 3933"
          >
            <span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.2317em"
              >• Place</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_18" style="word-spacing: 0.0861em"
              >&nbsp;</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_13" style="word-spacing: 0.0811em"
              >the #131 S</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_196" style="word-spacing: 0.1376em"
              >ultans of </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">F</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_173">e</span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_99" style="word-spacing: 0.0626em"
              >z, </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_192">W</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_190">a</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_13">t</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_251" style="word-spacing: 0.1209em"
              >tasid </span
            ><span class="stl_78 stl_17 stl_102">D</span
            ><span class="stl_163 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.081em"
              >ynasty </span
            ><span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0808em"
              >card as &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 40.0955em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: 0.0219em"
              >the Muslim Ruler; this ruler remains in place until the end of
              &nbsp;</span
            >
          </div>
          <div class="stl_01" style="left: 27.5831em; top: 41.0455em">
            <span class="stl_81 stl_17 stl_80" style="word-spacing: -0.0531em"
